P_HTM[1616]="*5. Paṭhamasamajīvīsuttaṃ**Equality (1st)*";
P_HTM[1617]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[1618]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Bhaggas on Crocodile Hill, in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood.*";
P_HTM[1619]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena nakulapituno gahapatissa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the home of the householder Nakula’s father, where he sat on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[1620]="*Atha kho nakulapitā ca gahapati nakulamātā ca gahapatānī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho nakulapitā gahapati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the householder Nakula’s father and the housewife Nakula’s mother went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. Nakula’s father said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[1621]="*“Yato me, bhante, nakulamātā gahapatānī daharasseva daharā ānītā, nābhijānāmi nakulamātaraṃ gahapatāniṃ manasāpi aticaritā, kuto pana kāyena.**“Sir, ever since we were both young, and Nakula’s mother was given to me in marriage, I can’t recall betraying her even in thought, still less in deed.*";
P_HTM[1622]="*Iccheyyāma mayaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passituṃ abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passitun”ti.**We want to see each other in both this life and the next.”*";
P_HTM[1623]="*Nakulamātāpi kho gahapatānī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Nakula’s mother said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[1624]="*“yatohaṃ, bhante, nakulapituno gahapatissa daharasseva daharā ānītā, nābhijānāmi nakulapitaraṃ gahapatiṃ manasāpi aticaritā, kuto pana kāyena.**“Sir, ever since we were both young, and I was given in marriage to Nakula’s father, I can’t recall betraying him even in thought, still less in deed.*";
P_HTM[1625]="*Iccheyyāma mayaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passituṃ abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passitun”ti.**We want to see each other in both this life and the next.”*";
P_HTM[1626]="*“Ākaṅkheyyuñce, gahapatayo, ubho jānipatayo diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passituṃ abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passituṃ ubhova assu samasaddhā samasīlā samacāgā samapaññā, te diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passanti abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passantīti.**“Householders, if wife and husband want to see each other in both this life and the next, they should be equals in faith, ethical conduct, generosity, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[1627]="*Ubho saddhā vadaññū ca,**When both are faithful and kind,*";
P_HTM[1628]="*saññatā dhammajīvino;**disciplined, living properly,*";
P_HTM[1629]="*Te honti jānipatayo,**then wife and husband*";
P_HTM[1630]="*aññamaññaṃ piyaṃvadā.**say nice things to each other.*";
P_HTM[1631]="*Atthāsaṃ pacurā honti,**They get all the things they need,*";
P_HTM[1632]="*phāsukaṃ upajāyati;**so they live at ease.*";
P_HTM[1633]="*Amittā dummanā honti,**Their enemies are downhearted,*";
P_HTM[1634]="*ubhinnaṃ samasīlinaṃ.**when both are equal in ethics.*";
P_HTM[1635]="*Idha dhammaṃ caritvāna,**Having practiced the teaching here,*";
P_HTM[1636]="*samasīlabbatā ubho;**both equal in precepts and observances,*";
P_HTM[1637]="*Nandino devalokasmiṃ,**they delight in the heavenly realm,*";
P_HTM[1638]="*modanti kāmakāmino”ti.**enjoying all the pleasures they desire.”*";
P_HTM[1639]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1640]="*6. Dutiyasamajīvīsuttaṃ**Equality (2nd)*";
P_HTM[1641]="*“Ākaṅkheyyuñce, bhikkhave, ubho jānipatayo diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passituṃ abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passituṃ ubhova assu samasaddhā samasīlā samacāgā samapaññā, te diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passanti abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passantīti.**“Mendicants, if wife and husband want to see each other in both this life and the next, they should be equals in faith, ethical conduct, generosity, and wisdom. …”*";
P_HTM[1642]="*Ubho saddhā vadaññū ca,* **";
P_HTM[1643]="*saññatā dhammajīvino;* **";
P_HTM[1644]="*Te honti jānipatayo,* **";
P_HTM[1645]="*aññamaññaṃ piyaṃvadā.* **";
P_HTM[1646]="*Atthāsaṃ pacurā honti,* **";
P_HTM[1647]="*phāsukaṃ upajāyati;* **";
P_HTM[1648]="*Amittā dummanā honti,* **";
P_HTM[1649]="*ubhinnaṃ samasīlinaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1650]="*Idha dhammaṃ caritvāna,* **";
P_HTM[1651]="*samasīlabbatā ubho;* **";
P_HTM[1652]="*Nandino devalokasmiṃ,* **";
P_HTM[1653]="*modanti kāmakāmino”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1654]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1655]="*7. Suppavāsāsuttaṃ**Suppavāsā*";
P_HTM[1656]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā koliyesu viharati pajjanikaṃ nāma koliyānaṃ nigamo.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Koliyans, where they have a town named Pajjanika.*";
P_HTM[1657]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena suppavāsāya koliyadhītuyā nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the home of Suppavāsā the Koliyan, where he sat on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[1658]="*Atha kho suppavāsā koliyadhītā bhagavantaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi.**Then Suppavāsā served and satisfied the Buddha with her own hands with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[1659]="*Atha kho suppavāsā koliyadhītā bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, she sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[1660]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho suppavāsaṃ koliyadhītaraṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said to her:*";
P_HTM[1661]="*“Bhojanaṃ, suppavāse, dentī ariyasāvikā paṭiggāhakānaṃ cattāri ṭhānāni deti.**“Suppavāsā, when a noble disciple gives food, she gives the recipients four things.*";
P_HTM[1662]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1663]="*Āyuṃ deti, vaṇṇaṃ deti, sukhaṃ deti, balaṃ deti.**Long life, beauty, happiness, and strength.*";
P_HTM[1664]="*Āyuṃ kho pana datvā āyussa bhāginī hoti dibbassa vā mānusassa vā.**Giving long life, she has long life as a god or human.*";
P_HTM[1665]="*Vaṇṇaṃ datvā vaṇṇassa bhāginī hoti dibbassa vā mānusassa vā.**Giving beauty, she has beauty as a god or human.*";
P_HTM[1666]="*Sukhaṃ datvā sukhassa bhāginī hoti dibbassa vā mānusassa vā.**Giving happiness, she has happiness as a god or human.*";
P_HTM[1667]="*Balaṃ datvā balassa bhāginī hoti dibbassa vā mānusassa vā.**Giving strength, she has strength as a god or human.*";
P_HTM[1668]="*Bhojanaṃ, suppavāse, dentī ariyasāvikā paṭiggāhakānaṃ imāni cattāri ṭhānāni detīti.**When a noble disciple gives food, she gives the recipients these four things.*";
P_HTM[1669]="*Susaṅkhataṃ bhojanaṃ yā dadāti,**When she gives well-prepared food,*";
P_HTM[1670]="*Suciṃ paṇītaṃ rasasā upetaṃ;**pure, fine, and full of flavor,*";
P_HTM[1671]="*Sā dakkhiṇā ujjugatesu dinnā,**that offering—given to people of integrity,*";
P_HTM[1672]="*Caraṇūpapannesu mahaggatesu;**who have good conduct, and are big-hearted—*";
P_HTM[1673]="*Puññena puññaṃ saṃsandamānā,**joins merit to merit. It’s very fruitful,*";
P_HTM[1674]="*Mahapphalā lokavidūna vaṇṇitā.**and is praised by those who know the world.*";
P_HTM[1675]="*Etādisaṃ yaññamanussarantā,**Those who recall such sacrifices,*";
P_HTM[1676]="*Ye vedajātā vicaranti loke;**live in the world full of joy.*";
P_HTM[1677]="*Vineyya maccheramalaṃ samūlaṃ,**They’ve driven out the stain of stinginess down to the root,*";
P_HTM[1678]="*Aninditā saggamupenti ṭhānan”ti.**blameless, they go to a heavenly place.”*";
P_HTM[1679]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1680]="*8. Sudattasuttaṃ**Sudatta*";
P_HTM[1681]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[1682]="*“Bhojanaṃ, gahapati, dadamāno ariyasāvako paṭiggāhakānaṃ cattāri ṭhānāni deti.**“Householder, when a noble disciple gives food, they give the recipients four things.*";
P_HTM[1683]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1684]="*Āyuṃ deti, vaṇṇaṃ deti, sukhaṃ deti, balaṃ deti.**Long life, beauty, happiness, and strength.*";
P_HTM[1685]="*Āyuṃ kho pana datvā āyussa bhāgī hoti dibbassa vā mānusassa vā.**Giving long life, they have long life as a god or human. …*";
P_HTM[1686]="*Vaṇṇaṃ datvā … sukhaṃ datvā … balaṃ datvā balassa bhāgī hoti dibbassa vā mānusassa vā.**Giving beauty … happiness … strength …*";
P_HTM[1687]="*Bhojanaṃ, gahapati, dadamāno ariyasāvako paṭiggāhakānaṃ imāni cattāri ṭhānāni detīti.**When a noble disciple gives food, they give the recipients these four things.*";
P_HTM[1688]="*Yo saññatānaṃ paradattabhojinaṃ,**Carefully giving food at the right time,*";
P_HTM[1689]="*Kālena sakkacca dadāti bhojanaṃ;**to those who are disciplined, eating only what others give,*";
P_HTM[1690]="*Cattāri ṭhānāni anuppavecchati,**you provide them with four things:*";
P_HTM[1691]="*Āyuñca vaṇṇañca sukhaṃ balañca.**long life, beauty, happiness, and strength.*";
P_HTM[1692]="*So āyudāyī vaṇṇadāyī,**A person who gives long life, beauty,*";
P_HTM[1693]="*sukhaṃ balaṃ dado naro;**happiness, and strength,*";
P_HTM[1694]="*Dīghāyu yasavā hoti,**has long life and fame*";
P_HTM[1695]="*yattha yatthūpapajjatī”ti.**wherever they’re reborn.”*";
P_HTM[1696]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1697]="*9. Bhojanasuttaṃ**Food*";
P_HTM[1698]="*“Bhojanaṃ, bhikkhave, dadamāno dāyako paṭiggāhakānaṃ cattāri ṭhānāni deti.**“Mendicants, when a noble disciple gives food, they give the recipients four things.*";
P_HTM[1699]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1700]="*Āyuṃ deti, vaṇṇaṃ deti, sukhaṃ deti, balaṃ deti.**Long life, beauty, happiness, and strength. …”*";
P_HTM[1701]="*Āyuṃ kho pana datvā āyussa bhāgī hoti dibbassa vā mānusassa vā.* **";
P_HTM[1702]="*Vaṇṇaṃ datvā … sukhaṃ datvā … balaṃ datvā balassa bhāgī hoti dibbassa vā mānusassa vā.* **";
P_HTM[1703]="*Bhojanaṃ, bhikkhave, dadamāno dāyako paṭiggāhakānaṃ imāni cattāri ṭhānāni detīti.* **";
P_HTM[1704]="*Yo saññatānaṃ paradattabhojinaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[1705]="*Kālena sakkacca dadāti bhojanaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[1706]="*Cattāri ṭhānāni anuppavecchati,* **";
P_HTM[1707]="*Āyuñca vaṇṇañca sukhaṃ balañca.* **";
P_HTM[1708]="*So āyudāyī vaṇṇadāyī,* **";
P_HTM[1709]="*sukhaṃ balaṃ dado naro;* **";
P_HTM[1710]="*Dīghāyu yasavā hoti,* **";
P_HTM[1711]="*yattha yatthūpapajjatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1712]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1713]="*10. Gihisāmīcisuttaṃ**Lay Practice*";
P_HTM[1714]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[1715]="*“Catūhi kho, gahapati, dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako gihisāmīcipaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno hoti yasopaṭilābhiniṃ saggasaṃvattanikaṃ.**“Householder, when a noble disciple does four things they are practicing appropriately for a layperson, which brings fame and leads to heaven.*";
P_HTM[1716]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1717]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paccupaṭṭhito hoti cīvarena, bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paccupaṭṭhito hoti piṇḍapātena, bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paccupaṭṭhito hoti senāsanena, bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paccupaṭṭhito hoti gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena.**It’s when a noble disciple serves the mendicant Saṅgha with robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[1718]="*Imehi kho, gahapati, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako gihisāmīcipaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno hoti yasopaṭilābhiniṃ saggasaṃvattanikanti.**When a noble disciple does these four things they are practicing appropriately for a layperson, which brings fame and leads to heaven.*";
P_HTM[1719]="*Gihisāmīcipaṭipadaṃ,**Those who are astute practice the way*";
P_HTM[1720]="*paṭipajjanti paṇḍitā;**that’s appropriate for laypeople.*";
P_HTM[1721]="*Sammaggate sīlavante,**They provide those who are ethical*";
P_HTM[1722]="*cīvarena upaṭṭhitā.**and on the right path with robes,*";
P_HTM[1723]="*Piṇḍapātasayanena,**alms-food, lodgings,*";
P_HTM[1724]="*Gilānappaccayena ca;**and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[1725]="*Tesaṃ divā ca ratto ca,**Their merit always grows*";
P_HTM[1726]="*Sadā puññaṃ pavaḍḍhati;**by day and by night.*";
P_HTM[1727]="*Saggañca kamatiṭṭhānaṃ,**They pass on to a place in heaven,*";
P_HTM[1728]="*Kammaṃ katvāna bhaddakan”ti.**having done excellent deeds.”*";
P_HTM[1729]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1730]="*Puññābhisandavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[1731]="*Dve puññābhisandā dve ca,* **";
P_HTM[1732]="*saṃvāsā samajīvino;* **";
P_HTM[1733]="*Suppavāsā sudatto ca,* **";
P_HTM[1734]="*bhojanaṃ gihisāmicīti.* **";
P_HTM[1735]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Deeds of Substance*";
P_HTM[1736]="*1. Pattakammasuttaṃ**Deeds of Substance*";
P_HTM[1737]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[1738]="*“Cattārome, gahapati, dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dullabhā lokasmiṃ.**“Householder, these four things that are likable, desirable, and agreeable are hard to get in the world.*";
P_HTM[1739]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1740]="*Bhogā me uppajjantu sahadhammenāti, ayaṃ paṭhamo dhammo iṭṭho kanto manāpo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**The first thing is the wish: ‘May wealth come to me by legitimate means!’*";
P_HTM[1741]="*Bhoge laddhā sahadhammena yaso me āgacchatu saha ñātīhi saha upajjhāyehīti, ayaṃ dutiyo dhammo iṭṭho kanto manāpo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**The second thing, having got wealth by legitimate means, is the wish: ‘May fame come to me, together with my family and teachers.’*";
P_HTM[1742]="*Bhoge laddhā sahadhammena yasaṃ laddhā saha ñātīhi saha upajjhāyehi ciraṃ jīvāmi dīghamāyuṃ pālemīti, ayaṃ tatiyo dhammo iṭṭho kanto manāpo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**The third thing, having got wealth and fame, is the wish: ‘May I live long, keeping alive for a long time!’*";
P_HTM[1743]="*Bhoge laddhā sahadhammena yasaṃ laddhā saha ñātīhi saha upajjhāyehi ciraṃ jīvitvā dīghamāyuṃ pāletvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjāmīti, ayaṃ catuttho dhammo iṭṭho kanto manāpo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**The fourth thing, having got wealth, fame, and long life, is the wish: ‘When my body breaks up, after death, may I be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm!’*";
P_HTM[1744]="*Ime kho, gahapati, cattāro dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dullabhā lokasmiṃ.**These are the four things that are likable, desirable, and agreeable, but hard to get in the world.*";
P_HTM[1745]="*Imesaṃ kho, gahapati, catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ dullabhānaṃ lokasmiṃ cattāro dhammā paṭilābhāya saṃvattanti.**These next four things lead to the getting of those four things.*";
P_HTM[1746]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1747]="*Saddhāsampadā, sīlasampadā, cāgasampadā, paññāsampadā.**Accomplishment in faith, ethics, generosity, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[1748]="*Katamā ca, gahapati, saddhāsampadā?**And what is accomplishment in faith?*";
P_HTM[1749]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:**It’s when a noble disciple has faith in the Realized One’s awakening:*";
P_HTM[1750]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi, satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[1751]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapati, saddhāsampadā.**This is called accomplishment in faith.*";
P_HTM[1752]="*Katamā ca, gahapati, sīlasampadā?**And what is accomplishment in ethics?*";
P_HTM[1753]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti.**It’s when a noble disciple doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or take alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[1754]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapati, sīlasampadā.**This is called accomplishment in ethics.*";
P_HTM[1755]="*Katamā ca, gahapati, cāgasampadā?**And what is accomplishment in generosity?*";
P_HTM[1756]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati muttacāgo payatapāṇi vosaggarato yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato.**It’s when a noble disciple lives at home rid of the stain of stinginess, freely generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to give and to share.*";
P_HTM[1757]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapati, cāgasampadā.**This is called accomplishment in generosity.*";
P_HTM[1758]="*Katamā ca, gahapati, paññāsampadā?**And what is accomplishment in wisdom?*";
P_HTM[1759]="*Abhijjhāvisamalobhābhibhūtena, gahapati, cetasā viharanto akiccaṃ karoti, kiccaṃ aparādheti.**When your heart is mastered by covetousness and immoral greed, you do what you shouldn’t, and fail to do what you should.*";
P_HTM[1760]="*Akiccaṃ karonto kiccaṃ aparādhento yasā ca sukhā ca dhaṃsati.**Your fame and happiness are crushed.*";
P_HTM[1761]="*Byāpādābhibhūtena, gahapati, cetasā viharanto akiccaṃ karoti, kiccaṃ aparādheti.**When your heart is mastered by ill will …*";
P_HTM[1762]="*Akiccaṃ karonto kiccaṃ aparādhento yasā ca sukhā ca dhaṃsati.* **";
P_HTM[1763]="*Thinamiddhābhibhūtena, gahapati, cetasā viharanto akiccaṃ karoti kiccaṃ aparādheti.**dullness and drowsiness …*";
P_HTM[1764]="*Akiccaṃ karonto kiccaṃ aparādhento yasā ca sukhā ca dhaṃsati.* **";
P_HTM[1765]="*Uddhaccakukkuccābhibhūtena, gahapati, cetasā viharanto akiccaṃ karoti, kiccaṃ aparādheti.**restlessness and remorse …*";
P_HTM[1766]="*Akiccaṃ karonto kiccaṃ aparādhento yasā ca sukhā ca dhaṃsati.* **";
P_HTM[1767]="*Vicikicchābhibhūtena, gahapati, cetasā viharanto akiccaṃ karoti, kiccaṃ aparādheti.**doubt, you do what you shouldn’t, and fail to do what you should.*";
P_HTM[1768]="*Akiccaṃ karonto kiccaṃ aparādhento yasā ca sukhā ca dhaṃsati.**Your fame and happiness are crushed.*";
P_HTM[1769]="*Sa kho so, gahapati, ariyasāvako abhijjhāvisamalobho cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā abhijjhāvisamalobhaṃ cittassa upakkilesaṃ pajahati.**Knowing that ‘covetousness and immoral greed are corruptions of the mind’, that noble disciple gives them up.*";
P_HTM[1770]="*Byāpādo cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā byāpādaṃ cittassa upakkilesaṃ pajahati.**Knowing that ‘ill will …’ …*";
P_HTM[1771]="*Thinamiddhaṃ cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā thinamiddhaṃ cittassa upakkilesaṃ pajahati.**‘dullness and drowsiness …’ …*";
P_HTM[1772]="*Uddhaccakukkuccaṃ cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā uddhaccakukkuccaṃ cittassa upakkilesaṃ pajahati.**‘restlessness and remorse …’ …*";
P_HTM[1773]="*Vicikicchā cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā vicikicchaṃ cittassa upakkilesaṃ pajahati.**‘doubt is a corruption of the mind’, that noble disciple gives it up.*";
P_HTM[1774]="*Yato ca kho, gahapati, ariyasāvakassa abhijjhāvisamalobho cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā abhijjhāvisamalobho cittassa upakkileso pahīno hoti.**When a noble disciple has given up these things,*";
P_HTM[1775]="*Byāpādo cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā byāpādo cittassa upakkileso pahīno hoti.* **";
P_HTM[1776]="*Thinamiddhaṃ cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā thinamiddhaṃ cittassa upakkileso pahīno hoti.* **";
P_HTM[1777]="*Uddhaccakukkuccaṃ cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā uddhaccakukkuccaṃ cittassa upakkileso pahīno hoti.* **";
P_HTM[1778]="*Vicikicchā cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā vicikicchā cittassa upakkileso pahīno hoti.* **";
P_HTM[1779]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapati, ariyasāvako mahāpañño puthupañño āpātadaso paññāsampanno.**they’re called ‘a noble disciple of great wisdom, of widespread wisdom, who sees what matters, and is accomplished in wisdom’.*";
P_HTM[1780]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapati, paññāsampadā.**This is called accomplishment in wisdom.*";
P_HTM[1781]="*Imesaṃ kho, gahapati, catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ dullabhānaṃ lokasmiṃ ime cattāro dhammā paṭilābhāya saṃvattanti.**These are the four things that lead to the getting of the four things that are likable, desirable, and agreeable, but hard to get in the world.*";
P_HTM[1782]="*Sa kho so, gahapati, ariyasāvako uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi cattāri pattakammāni kattā hoti.**There are four deeds of substance that a noble disciple does with the legitimate wealth he has earned by his efforts and initiative, built up with his own hands, gathered by the sweat of the brow.*";
P_HTM[1783]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1784]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti sammā sukhaṃ pariharati.**To start with, with his legitimate wealth he makes himself happy and pleased, keeping himself properly happy.*";
P_HTM[1785]="*Mātāpitaro sukheti pīṇeti sammā sukhaṃ pariharati.**He makes his mother and father happy …*";
P_HTM[1786]="*Puttadāradāsakammakaraporise sukheti pīṇeti sammā sukhaṃ pariharati.**He makes his children, partners, bondservants, workers, and staff happy …*";
P_HTM[1787]="*Mittāmacce sukheti pīṇeti sammā sukhaṃ pariharati.**He makes his friends and colleagues happy …*";
P_HTM[1788]="*Idamassa paṭhamaṃ ṭhānagataṃ hoti pattagataṃ āyatanaso paribhuttaṃ.**This is his first solid and substantive investment, used in the appropriate sphere.*";
P_HTM[1789]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, ariyasāvako uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi yā tā honti āpadā aggito vā udakato vā rājato vā corato vā appiyato vā dāyādato, tathārūpāsu āpadāsu pariyodhāya saṃvattati.**Furthermore, with his legitimate wealth he defends himself against threats from such things as fire, flood, rulers, bandits, or unloved heirs.*";
P_HTM[1790]="*Sotthiṃ attānaṃ karoti.**He keeps himself safe.*";
P_HTM[1791]="*Idamassa dutiyaṃ ṭhānagataṃ hoti pattagataṃ āyatanaso paribhuttaṃ.**This is his second solid and substantive investment, used in the appropriate sphere.*";
P_HTM[1792]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, ariyasāvako uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi pañcabaliṃ kattā hoti—**Furthermore, with his legitimate wealth he makes five spirit-offerings:*";
P_HTM[1793]="*ñātibaliṃ, atithibaliṃ, pubbapetabaliṃ, rājabaliṃ, devatābaliṃ.**to relatives, guests, ancestors, king, and deities.*";
P_HTM[1794]="*Idamassa tatiyaṃ ṭhānagataṃ hoti pattagataṃ āyatanaso paribhuttaṃ.**This is his third solid and substantive investment, used in the appropriate sphere.*";
P_HTM[1795]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, ariyasāvako uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā madappamādā paṭiviratā khantisoracce niviṭṭhā ekamattānaṃ damenti, ekamattānaṃ samenti, ekamattānaṃ parinibbāpenti, tathārūpesu samaṇabrāhmaṇesu uddhaggikaṃ dakkhiṇaṃ patiṭṭhāpeti sovaggikaṃ sukhavipākaṃ saggasaṃvattanikaṃ.**Furthermore, with his legitimate wealth he establishes an uplifting religious donation for ascetics and brahmins—those who avoid intoxication and negligence, are settled in patience and gentleness, and who tame, calm, and extinguish themselves—that’s conducive to heaven, ripens in happiness, and leads to heaven.*";
P_HTM[1796]="*Idamassa catutthaṃ ṭhānagataṃ hoti pattagataṃ āyatanaso paribhuttaṃ.**This is his fourth solid and substantive investment, used in the appropriate sphere.*";
P_HTM[1797]="*Sa kho so, gahapati, ariyasāvako uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi imāni cattāri pattakammāni kattā hoti.**These are the four deeds of substance that a noble disciple does with the legitimate wealth he has earned by his efforts and initiative, built up with his own hands, gathered by the sweat of the brow.*";
P_HTM[1798]="*Yassa kassaci, gahapati, aññatra imehi catūhi pattakammehi bhogā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ime vuccanti, gahapati, bhogā aṭṭhānagatā apattagatā anāyatanaso paribhuttā.**Whatever wealth is spent on something other than these four deeds of substance is said to be not a solid or substantive investment, and not used in the appropriate sphere.*";
P_HTM[1799]="*Yassa kassaci, gahapati, imehi catūhi pattakammehi bhogā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ime vuccanti, gahapati, bhogā ṭhānagatā pattagatā āyatanaso paribhuttāti.**But whatever wealth is spent on these four deeds of substance is said to be a solid and substantive investment, used in the appropriate sphere.*";
P_HTM[1800]="*Bhuttā bhogā bhatā bhaccā,**‘I’ve enjoyed my wealth, supporting those who depend on me;*";
P_HTM[1801]="*Vitiṇṇā āpadāsu me;**I’ve overcome losses;*";
P_HTM[1802]="*Uddhaggā dakkhiṇā dinnā,**I’ve given uplifting religious donations;*";
P_HTM[1803]="*Atho pañcabalī katā;**and made the five spirit-offerings.*";
P_HTM[1804]="*Upaṭṭhitā sīlavanto,**I have looked after the ethical and*";
P_HTM[1805]="*Saññatā brahmacārayo.**disciplined spiritual practitioners.*";
P_HTM[1806]="*Yadatthaṃ bhogaṃ iccheyya,**I’ve achieved the purpose*";
P_HTM[1807]="*paṇḍito gharamāvasaṃ;**for which an astute lay person*";
P_HTM[1808]="*So me attho anuppatto,**wishes to gain wealth.*";
P_HTM[1809]="*kataṃ ananutāpiyaṃ.**I don’t regret what I’ve done.’*";
P_HTM[1810]="*Etaṃ anussaraṃ macco,**A mortal person who recollects this*";
P_HTM[1811]="*ariyadhamme ṭhito naro;**stands firm in the teaching of the noble ones.*";
P_HTM[1812]="*Idheva naṃ pasaṃsanti,**They’re praised in this life,*";
P_HTM[1813]="*pecca sagge pamodatī”ti.**and they depart to rejoice in heaven.”*";
P_HTM[1814]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1815]="*2. Ānaṇyasuttaṃ**Debtlessness*";
P_HTM[1816]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[1817]="*“Cattārimāni, gahapati, sukhāni adhigamanīyāni gihinā kāmabhoginā kālena kālaṃ samayena samayaṃ upādāya.**“Householder, these four kinds of happiness can be earned by a layperson who enjoys sensual pleasures, depending on time and occasion.*";
P_HTM[1818]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1819]="*Atthisukhaṃ, bhogasukhaṃ, ānaṇyasukhaṃ, anavajjasukhaṃ.**The happiness of ownership, using wealth, debtlessness, and blamelessness.*";
P_HTM[1820]="*Katamañca, gahapati, atthisukhaṃ?**And what is the happiness of ownership?*";
P_HTM[1821]="*Idha, gahapati, kulaputtassa bhogā honti uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatā bāhābalaparicitā sedāvakkhittā dhammikā dhammaladdhā.**It’s when a gentleman owns legitimate wealth that he has earned by his own efforts and initiative, built up with his own hands, gathered by the sweat of the brow.*";
P_HTM[1822]="*So ‘bhogā me atthi uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatā bāhābalaparicitā sedāvakkhittā dhammikā dhammaladdhā’ti adhigacchati sukhaṃ, adhigacchati somanassaṃ.**When he reflects on this, he’s filled with pleasure and happiness.*";
P_HTM[1823]="*Idaṃ vuccati, gahapati, atthisukhaṃ.**This is called ‘the happiness of ownership’.*";
P_HTM[1824]="*Katamañca, gahapati, bhogasukhaṃ?**And what is the happiness of using wealth?*";
P_HTM[1825]="*Idha, gahapati, kulaputto uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi paribhuñjati puññāni ca karoti.**It’s when a gentleman uses his legitimate wealth, and makes merit with it.*";
P_HTM[1826]="*So ‘uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi paribhuñjāmi puññāni ca karomī’ti adhigacchati sukhaṃ, adhigacchati somanassaṃ.**When he reflects on this, he’s filled with pleasure and happiness.*";
P_HTM[1827]="*Idaṃ vuccati, gahapati, bhogasukhaṃ.**This is called ‘the happiness of using wealth’.*";
P_HTM[1828]="*Katamañca, gahapati, ānaṇyasukhaṃ?**And what is the happiness of debtlessness?*";
P_HTM[1829]="*Idha, gahapati, kulaputto na kassaci kiñci dhāreti appaṃ vā bahuṃ vā.**It’s when a gentleman owes no debt, large or small, to anyone.*";
P_HTM[1830]="*So ‘na kassaci kiñci dhāremi appaṃ vā bahuṃ vā’ti adhigacchati sukhaṃ, adhigacchati somanassaṃ.**When he reflects on this, he’s filled with pleasure and happiness.*";
P_HTM[1831]="*Idaṃ vuccati, gahapati, ānaṇyasukhaṃ.**This is called ‘the happiness of debtlessness’.*";
P_HTM[1832]="*Katamañca, gahapati, anavajjasukhaṃ?**And what is the happiness of blamelessness?*";
P_HTM[1833]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako anavajjena kāyakammena samannāgato hoti, anavajjena vacīkammena samannāgato hoti, anavajjena manokammena samannāgato hoti.**It’s when a noble disciple has blameless conduct by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[1834]="*So ‘anavajjenamhi kāyakammena samannāgato, anavajjena vacīkammena samannāgato, anavajjena manokammena samannāgato’ti adhigacchati sukhaṃ, adhigacchati somanassaṃ.**When he reflects on this, he’s filled with pleasure and happiness.*";
P_HTM[1835]="*Idaṃ vuccati, gahapati, anavajjasukhaṃ.**This is called ‘the happiness of blamelessness’.*";
P_HTM[1836]="*Imāni kho, gahapati, cattāri sukhāni adhigamanīyāni gihinā kāmabhoginā kālena kālaṃ samayena samayaṃ upādāyāti.**These four kinds of happiness can be earned by a layperson who enjoys sensual pleasures, depending on time and occasion.*";
P_HTM[1837]="*Ānaṇyasukhaṃ ñatvāna,**Knowing the happiness of debtlessness,*";
P_HTM[1838]="*Atho atthisukhaṃ paraṃ;**and the extra happiness of possession,*";
P_HTM[1839]="*Bhuñjaṃ bhogasukhaṃ macco,**a mortal enjoying the happiness of using wealth,*";
P_HTM[1840]="*Tato paññā vipassati.**then sees clearly with wisdom.*";
P_HTM[1841]="*Vipassamāno jānāti,**Seeing clearly, a clever person knows*";
P_HTM[1842]="*ubho bhoge sumedhaso;**both kinds of happiness:*";
P_HTM[1843]="*Anavajjasukhassetaṃ,**the other kind is not worth a sixteenth part*";
P_HTM[1844]="*kalaṃ nāgghati soḷasin”ti.**of the happiness of blamelessness.”*";
P_HTM[1845]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1846]="*3. Brahmasuttaṃ**Living with Brahmā*";
P_HTM[1847]="*“Sabrahmakāni, bhikkhave, tāni kulāni yesaṃ puttānaṃ mātāpitaro ajjhāgāre pūjitā honti.**“Mendicants, a family where the children honor their parents in their home is said to live with Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[1848]="*Sapubbācariyakāni, bhikkhave, tāni kulāni, yesaṃ puttānaṃ mātāpitaro ajjhāgāre pūjitā honti.**A family where the children honor their parents in their home is said to live with the first teachers.*";
P_HTM[1849]="*Sapubbadevatāni, bhikkhave, tāni kulāni yesaṃ puttānaṃ mātāpitaro ajjhāgāre pūjitā honti.**A family where the children honor their parents in their home is said to live with the old deities.*";
P_HTM[1850]="*Sāhuneyyakāni, bhikkhave, tāni kulāni yesaṃ puttānaṃ mātāpitaro ajjhāgāre pūjitā honti.**A family where the children honor their parents in their home is said to live with those worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods.*";
P_HTM[1851]="*Brahmāti, bhikkhave, mātāpitūnaṃ etaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Brahmā’ is a term for your parents.*";
P_HTM[1852]="*Pubbācariyāti, bhikkhave, mātāpitūnaṃ etaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘First teachers’ is a term for your parents.*";
P_HTM[1853]="*Pubbadevatāti, bhikkhave, mātāpitūnaṃ etaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Old deities’ is a term for your parents.*";
P_HTM[1854]="*Āhuneyyāti, bhikkhave, mātāpitūnaṃ etaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Worthy of an offering dedicated to the gods’ is a term for your parents.*";
P_HTM[1855]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1856]="*Bahukārā, bhikkhave, mātāpitaro, puttānaṃ āpādakā posakā imassa lokassa dassetāroti.**Parents are very helpful to their children, they raise them, nurture them, and show them the world.*";
P_HTM[1857]="*Brahmāti mātāpitaro,**Parents are said to be ‘Brahmā’*";
P_HTM[1858]="*pubbācariyāti vuccare;**and ‘first teachers’.*";
P_HTM[1859]="*Āhuneyyā ca puttānaṃ,**They’re worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods from their children,*";
P_HTM[1860]="*pajāya anukampakā.**for they love their offspring.*";
P_HTM[1861]="*Tasmā hi ne namasseyya,**Therefore an astute person*";
P_HTM[1862]="*sakkareyya ca paṇḍito;**would revere them and honor them*";
P_HTM[1863]="*Annena atha pānena,**with food and drink,*";
P_HTM[1864]="*vatthena sayanena ca;**clothes and bedding,*";
P_HTM[1865]="*Ucchādanena nhāpanena,**by anointing and bathing,*";
P_HTM[1866]="*pādānaṃ dhovanena ca.**and by washing their feet.*";
P_HTM[1867]="*Tāya naṃ pāricariyāya,**Because they look after*";
P_HTM[1868]="*mātāpitūsu paṇḍitā;**their parents like this,*";
P_HTM[1869]="*Idheva naṃ pasaṃsanti,**they’re praised in this life by the astute,*";
P_HTM[1870]="*pecca sagge pamodatī”ti.**and they depart to rejoice in heaven.”*";
P_HTM[1871]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1872]="*4. Nirayasuttaṃ**Hell*";
P_HTM[1873]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[1874]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1875]="*Pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti—**They kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, and lie.*";
P_HTM[1876]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ nirayeti.**Someone with these four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[1877]="*Pāṇātipāto adinnādānaṃ,**Killing, stealing,*";
P_HTM[1878]="*Musāvādo ca vuccati;**telling lies,*";
P_HTM[1879]="*Paradāragamanañcāpi,**and visiting others’ wives:*";
P_HTM[1880]="*Nappasaṃsanti paṇḍitā”ti.**astute people don’t praise these things.”*";
P_HTM[1881]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1882]="*5. Rūpasuttaṃ**Appearance*";
P_HTM[1883]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[1884]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1885]="*Rūpappamāṇo rūpappasanno, ghosappamāṇo ghosappasanno, lūkhappamāṇo lūkhappasanno, dhammappamāṇo dhammappasanno—**There are those whose estimation of and confidence in others is based on appearance, on eloquence, on mortification, and on principle.*";
P_HTM[1886]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasminti.**These are the four people found in the world.*";
P_HTM[1887]="*Ye ca rūpe pamāṇiṃsu,**Those who judge on appearance,*";
P_HTM[1888]="*ye ca ghosena anvagū;**and those swayed by a voice,*";
P_HTM[1889]="*Chandarāgavasūpetā,**are full of desire and greed;*";
P_HTM[1890]="*nābhijānanti te janā.**those people just don’t understand.*";
P_HTM[1891]="*Ajjhattañca na jānāti,**Not knowing what’s inside,*";
P_HTM[1892]="*bahiddhā ca na passati;**nor seeing what’s outside,*";
P_HTM[1893]="*Samantāvaraṇo bālo,**the fool shut in on every side,*";
P_HTM[1894]="*sa ve ghosena vuyhati.**gets carried away by a voice.*";
P_HTM[1895]="*Ajjhattañca na jānāti,**Not knowing what’s inside,*";
P_HTM[1896]="*bahiddhā ca vipassati;**but seeing what’s outside,*";
P_HTM[1897]="*Bahiddhā phaladassāvī,**seeing the fruit outside,*";
P_HTM[1898]="*sopi ghosena vuyhati.**they’re also carried away by a voice.*";
P_HTM[1899]="*Ajjhattañca pajānāti,**Understanding what’s inside,*";
P_HTM[1900]="*bahiddhā ca vipassati;**and seeing what’s outside,*";
P_HTM[1901]="*Vinīvaraṇadassāvī,**seeing without hindrances,*";
P_HTM[1902]="*na so ghosena vuyhatī”ti.**they don’t get carried away by a voice.”*";
P_HTM[1903]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1904]="*6. Sarāgasuttaṃ**Greedy*";
P_HTM[1905]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[1906]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1907]="*Sarāgo, sadoso, samoho, samāno—**The greedy, the hateful, the delusional, and the conceited.*";
P_HTM[1908]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasminti.**These are the four people found in the world.*";
P_HTM[1909]="*Sārattā rajanīyesu,**Full of desire for desirable things,*";
P_HTM[1910]="*Piyarūpābhinandino;**enjoying things that seem pleasant,*";
P_HTM[1911]="*Mohena āvutā sattā,**beings shrouded by ignorance,*";
P_HTM[1912]="*Baddhā vaḍḍhenti bandhanaṃ.**only tighten their bonds.*";
P_HTM[1913]="*Rāgajaṃ dosajañcāpi,**Born of greed, born of hate,*";
P_HTM[1914]="*mohajaṃ cāpaviddasū;**born of delusion: the ignorant*";
P_HTM[1915]="*Karontākusalaṃ kammaṃ,**make bad karma*";
P_HTM[1916]="*savighātaṃ dukhudrayaṃ.**that afflicts and produces pain.*";
P_HTM[1917]="*Avijjānivutā posā,**If you act out of these qualities, that’s what you become.*";
P_HTM[1918]="*andhabhūtā acakkhukā;**But men hindered by ignorance,*";
P_HTM[1919]="*Yathā dhammā tathā santā,**are blind, with no eyes to see,*";
P_HTM[1920]="*na tassevanti maññare”ti.**and they never imagine that this could be so.”*";
P_HTM[1921]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1922]="*7. Ahirājasuttaṃ**The Snake King*";
P_HTM[1923]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[1924]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ aññataro bhikkhu ahinā daṭṭho kālaṅkato hoti.**Now, at that time a monk in Sāvatthī passed away due to a snake bite.*";
P_HTM[1925]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[1926]="*“idha, bhante, sāvatthiyaṃ aññataro bhikkhu ahinā daṭṭho kālaṅkato”ti.**“Sir, a monk in Sāvatthī has passed away due to a snake bite.”*";
P_HTM[1927]="*“Na hi nūna so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāri ahirājakulāni mettena cittena phari.**“Mendicants, that monk mustn’t have spread a mind of love to the four royal snake families.*";
P_HTM[1928]="*Sace hi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāri ahirājakulāni mettena cittena phareyya, na hi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ahinā daṭṭho kālaṃ kareyya.**If he had, he wouldn’t have died due to a snake bite.*";
P_HTM[1929]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1930]="*Virūpakkhaṃ ahirājakulaṃ, erāpathaṃ ahirājakulaṃ, chabyāputtaṃ ahirājakulaṃ, kaṇhāgotamakaṃ ahirājakulaṃ.**The royal snake families of Virūpakkha, Erāpatha, Chabyāputta, and Kaṇhāgotamaka. …*";
P_HTM[1931]="*Na hi nūna so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imāni cattāri ahirājakulāni mettena cittena phari.* **";
P_HTM[1932]="*Sace hi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imāni cattāri ahirājakulāni mettena cittena phareyya, na hi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ahinā daṭṭho kālaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1933]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, imāni cattāri ahirājakulāni mettena cittena pharituṃ attaguttiyā attarakkhāya attaparittāyāti.**Mendicants, I urge you to spread a mind of love to the four royal snake families, for your own safety, security, and protection.*";
P_HTM[1934]="*Virūpakkhehi me mettaṃ,**I love the Virūpakkhas,*";
P_HTM[1935]="*Mettaṃ erāpathehi me;**the Erāpathas I love,*";
P_HTM[1936]="*Chabyāputtehi me mettaṃ,**I love the Chabyāputtas,*";
P_HTM[1937]="*Mettaṃ kaṇhāgotamakehi ca.**the Kaṇhāgotamakas I love.*";
P_HTM[1938]="*Apādakehi me mettaṃ,**I love the footless creatures,*";
P_HTM[1939]="*mettaṃ dvipādakehi me;**the two-footed I love,*";
P_HTM[1940]="*Catuppadehi me mettaṃ,**I love the four-footed,*";
P_HTM[1941]="*mettaṃ bahuppadehi me.**the many-footed I love.*";
P_HTM[1942]="*Mā maṃ apādako hiṃsi,**May the footless not harm me!*";
P_HTM[1943]="*mā maṃ hiṃsi dvipādako;**May I not be harmed by the two-footed!*";
P_HTM[1944]="*Mā maṃ catuppado hiṃsi,**May the four-footed not harm me!*";
P_HTM[1945]="*mā maṃ hiṃsi bahuppado.**May I not be harmed by the many-footed!*";
P_HTM[1946]="*Sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā,**All sentient beings, all living things,*";
P_HTM[1947]="*sabbe bhūtā ca kevalā;**all creatures, every one:*";
P_HTM[1948]="*Sabbe bhadrāni passantu,**may they see only nice things,*";
P_HTM[1949]="*mā kañci pāpamāgamā.**may bad not come to anyone.*";
P_HTM[1950]="*Appamāṇo buddho,**The Buddha is immeasurable,*";
P_HTM[1951]="*Appamāṇo dhammo;**the teaching is immeasurable,*";
P_HTM[1952]="*Appamāṇo saṃgho,**the Saṅgha is immeasurable.*";
P_HTM[1953]="*Pamāṇavantāni sarīsapāni.**But limited are crawling things,*";
P_HTM[1954]="*Ahivicchikā satapadī,**snakes and scorpions, centipedes,*";
P_HTM[1955]="*Uṇṇanābhī sarabū mūsikā;**spiders and lizards and mice.*";
P_HTM[1956]="*Katā me rakkhā katā me parittā,**I’ve made this safeguard, I’ve made this protection:*";
P_HTM[1957]="*Paṭikkamantu bhūtāni;**go away, creatures!*";
P_HTM[1958]="*Sohaṃ namo bhagavato,**And so I revere the Blessed One,*";
P_HTM[1959]="*Namo sattannaṃ sammāsambuddhānan”ti.**I revere the seven perfectly awakened Buddhas.”*";
P_HTM[1960]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1961]="*8. Devadattasuttaṃ**Devadatta*";
P_HTM[1962]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate acirapakkante devadatte.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain, not long after Devadatta had left.*";
P_HTM[1963]="*Tatra kho bhagavā devadattaṃ ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha spoke to the mendicants about Devadatta:*";
P_HTM[1964]="*“attavadhāya, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity came to Devadatta for his own ruin and downfall.*";
P_HTM[1965]="*Parābhavāya, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.* **";
P_HTM[1966]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kadalī attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;**It’s like a banana tree,*";
P_HTM[1967]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.* **";
P_HTM[1968]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, veḷu attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;**or a bamboo,*";
P_HTM[1969]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.* **";
P_HTM[1970]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, naḷo attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;**or a reed, all of which bear fruit to their own ruin and downfall …*";
P_HTM[1971]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.* **";
P_HTM[1972]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, assatarī attavadhāya gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti, parābhavāya gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti;**It’s like a mule, which becomes pregnant to its own ruin and downfall.*";
P_HTM[1973]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādīti.**In the same way, possessions, honor, and popularity came to Devadatta for his own ruin and downfall.*";
P_HTM[1974]="*Phalaṃ ve kadaliṃ hanti,**The banana tree is destroyed by its own fruit,*";
P_HTM[1975]="*phalaṃ veḷuṃ phalaṃ naḷaṃ;**as are the bamboo and the reed.*";
P_HTM[1976]="*Sakkāro kāpurisaṃ hanti,**Honor destroys a sinner,*";
P_HTM[1977]="*gabbho assatariṃ yathā”ti.**as pregnancy destroys a mule.”*";
P_HTM[1978]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1979]="*9. Padhānasuttaṃ**Effort*";
P_HTM[1980]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, padhānāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four efforts.*";
P_HTM[1981]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1982]="*Saṃvarappadhānaṃ, pahānappadhānaṃ, bhāvanāppadhānaṃ, anurakkhaṇāppadhānaṃ.**The efforts to restrain, to give up, to develop, and to preserve.*";
P_HTM[1983]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, saṃvarappadhānaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the effort to restrain?*";
P_HTM[1984]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ anuppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati.**It’s when you generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise.*";
P_HTM[1985]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, saṃvarappadhānaṃ.**This is called the effort to restrain.*";
P_HTM[1986]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, pahānappadhānaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the effort to give up?*";
P_HTM[1987]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati.**It’s when you generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that bad, unskillful qualities are given up.*";
P_HTM[1988]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, pahānappadhānaṃ.**This is called the effort to give up.*";
P_HTM[1989]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, bhāvanāppadhānaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the effort to develop?*";
P_HTM[1990]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ uppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati.**It’s when you generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that skillful qualities arise.*";
P_HTM[1991]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhāvanāppadhānaṃ.**This is called the effort to develop.*";
P_HTM[1992]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, anurakkhaṇāppadhānaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the effort to preserve?*";
P_HTM[1993]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati.**It’s when you generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are fulfilled by development.*";
P_HTM[1994]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anurakkhaṇāppadhānaṃ.**This is called the effort to preserve.*";
P_HTM[1995]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri padhānānīti.**These are the four efforts.*";
P_HTM[1996]="*Saṃvaro ca pahānañca,**Restraint and giving up,*";
P_HTM[1997]="*bhāvanā anurakkhaṇā;**development and preservation:*";
P_HTM[1998]="*Ete padhānā cattāro,**these are the four efforts*";
P_HTM[1999]="*desitādiccabandhunā;**taught by the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[2000]="*Yo hi bhikkhu idhātāpī,**Any mendicant who keenly applies these*";
P_HTM[2001]="*khayaṃ dukkhassa pāpuṇe”ti.**may attain the ending of suffering.”*";
P_HTM[2002]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2003]="*10. Adhammikasuttaṃ**Unprincipled*";
P_HTM[2004]="*“Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye rājāno adhammikā honti, rājāyuttāpi tasmiṃ samaye adhammikā honti.**“At a time when kings are unprincipled, royal officials become unprincipled.*";
P_HTM[2005]="*Rājāyuttesu adhammikesu brāhmaṇagahapatikāpi tasmiṃ samaye adhammikā honti.**When royal officials are unprincipled, brahmins and householders become unprincipled.*";
P_HTM[2006]="*Brāhmaṇagahapatikesu adhammikesu negamajānapadāpi tasmiṃ samaye adhammikā honti.**When brahmins and householders are unprincipled, the people of town and country become unprincipled.*";
P_HTM[2007]="*Negamajānapadesu adhammikesu visamaṃ candimasūriyā parivattanti.**When the people of town and country are unprincipled, the courses of the moon and sun become erratic.*";
P_HTM[2008]="*Visamaṃ candimasūriyesu parivattantesu visamaṃ nakkhattāni tārakarūpāni parivattanti.**… the courses of the stars and constellations …*";
P_HTM[2009]="*Visamaṃ nakkhattesu tārakarūpesu parivattantesu visamaṃ rattindivā parivattanti.**the days and nights …*";
P_HTM[2010]="*Visamaṃ rattindivesu parivattantesu visamaṃ māsaddhamāsā parivattanti.**the months and fortnights …*";
P_HTM[2011]="*Visamaṃ māsaddhamāsesu parivattantesu visamaṃ utusaṃvaccharā parivattanti.**the seasons and years become erratic.*";
P_HTM[2012]="*Visamaṃ utusaṃvaccharesu parivattantesu visamaṃ vātā vāyanti visamā apañjasā.**… the blowing of the winds becomes erratic and chaotic.*";
P_HTM[2013]="*Visamaṃ vātesu vāyantesu visamesu apañjasesu devatā parikupitā bhavanti.**… the deities are angered.*";
P_HTM[2014]="*Devatāsu parikupitāsu devo na sammā dhāraṃ anuppavecchati.**… the heavens don’t provide enough rain.*";
P_HTM[2015]="*Deve na sammā dhāraṃ anuppavecchante visamapākāni sassāni bhavanti.**… the crops ripen erratically.*";
P_HTM[2016]="*Visamapākāni, bhikkhave, sassāni manussā paribhuñjantā appāyukā honti dubbaṇṇā ca bavhābādhā ca.**When people eat crops that have ripened erratically, they become short-lived, ugly, weak, and sickly.*";
P_HTM[2017]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye rājāno dhammikā honti, rājāyuttāpi tasmiṃ samaye dhammikā honti.**At a time when kings are principled, royal officials become principled.*";
P_HTM[2018]="*Rājāyuttesu dhammikesu brāhmaṇagahapatikāpi tasmiṃ samaye dhammikā honti.**… brahmins and householders …*";
P_HTM[2019]="*Brāhmaṇagahapatikesu dhammikesu negamajānapadāpi tasmiṃ samaye dhammikā honti.**people of town and country become principled.*";
P_HTM[2020]="*Negamajānapadesu dhammikesu samaṃ candimasūriyā parivattanti.**When the people of town and country are principled, the courses of the sun and moon become regular.*";
P_HTM[2021]="*Samaṃ candimasūriyesu parivattantesu samaṃ nakkhattāni tārakarūpāni parivattanti.**… the stars and constellations …*";
P_HTM[2022]="*Samaṃ nakkhattesu tārakarūpesu parivattantesu samaṃ rattindivā parivattanti.**the days and nights …*";
P_HTM[2023]="*Samaṃ rattindivesu parivattantesu samaṃ māsaddhamāsā parivattanti.**the months and fortnights …*";
P_HTM[2024]="*Samaṃ māsaddhamāsesu parivattantesu samaṃ utusaṃvaccharā parivattanti.**the seasons and years become regular.*";
P_HTM[2025]="*Samaṃ utusaṃvaccharesu parivattantesu samaṃ vātā vāyanti samā pañjasā.**… the blowing of the winds becomes regular and orderly.*";
P_HTM[2026]="*Samaṃ vātesu vāyantesu samesu pañjasesu devatā aparikupitā bhavanti.**… the deities are not angered …*";
P_HTM[2027]="*Devatāsu aparikupitāsu devo sammā dhāraṃ anuppavecchati.**… the heavens provide plenty of rain.*";
P_HTM[2028]="*Deve sammā dhāraṃ anuppavecchante samapākāni sassāni bhavanti.**When the heavens provide plenty of rain, the crops ripen well.*";
P_HTM[2029]="*Samapākāni, bhikkhave, sassāni manussā paribhuñjantā dīghāyukā ca honti vaṇṇavanto ca balavanto ca appābādhā cāti.**When people eat crops that have ripened well, they become long-lived, beautiful, strong, and healthy.*";
P_HTM[2030]="*Gunnañce taramānānaṃ,**When cattle ford a river,*";
P_HTM[2031]="*jimhaṃ gacchati puṅgavo;**if the bull goes off course,*";
P_HTM[2032]="*Sabbā tā jimhaṃ gacchanti,**they all go off course,*";
P_HTM[2033]="*nette jimhaṃ gate sati.**because their leader is off course.*";
P_HTM[2034]="*Evamevaṃ manussesu,**So it is for humans:*";
P_HTM[2035]="*yo hoti seṭṭhasammato;**when the one agreed on as chief*";
P_HTM[2036]="*So ce adhammaṃ carati,**behaves badly,*";
P_HTM[2037]="*pageva itarā pajā;**what do you expect the rest to do?*";
P_HTM[2038]="*Sabbaṃ raṭṭhaṃ dukkhaṃ seti,**The whole country sleeps badly,*";
P_HTM[2039]="*rājā ce hoti adhammiko.**when the king is unprincipled.*";
P_HTM[2040]="*Gunnañce taramānānaṃ,**When cattle ford a river,*";
P_HTM[2041]="*ujuṃ gacchati puṅgavo;**if the bull goes straight,*";
P_HTM[2042]="*Sabbā tā ujuṃ gacchanti,**they all go straight,*";
P_HTM[2043]="*nette ujuṃ gate sati.**because their leader is straight.*";
P_HTM[2044]="*Evamevaṃ manussesu,**So it is for humans:*";
P_HTM[2045]="*yo hoti seṭṭhasammato;**when the one agreed on as chief*";
P_HTM[2046]="*So sace dhammaṃ carati,**does the right thing,*";
P_HTM[2047]="*pageva itarā pajā;**what do you expect the rest to do?*";
P_HTM[2048]="*Sabbaṃ raṭṭhaṃ sukhaṃ seti,**The whole country sleeps happily,*";
P_HTM[2049]="*rājā ce hoti dhammiko”ti.**when the king is just.”*";
P_HTM[2050]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2051]="*Pattakammavaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[2052]="*Pattakammaṃ ānaṇyako,* **";
P_HTM[2053]="*Sabrahmanirayā rūpena pañcamaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2054]="*Sarāgaahirājā devadatto,* **";
P_HTM[2055]="*Padhānaṃ adhammikena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[2056]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Guaranteed*";
P_HTM[2057]="*1. Padhānasuttaṃ**Effort*";
P_HTM[2058]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu apaṇṇakappaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno hoti, yoni cassa āraddhā hoti āsavānaṃ khayāya.**“Mendicants, when a mendicant has four things their practice is guaranteed, and they have laid the groundwork for ending the defilements.*";
P_HTM[2059]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2060]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, bahussuto hoti, āraddhavīriyo hoti, paññavā hoti.**It’s when a mendicant is ethical, learned, energetic, and wise.*";
P_HTM[2061]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu apaṇṇakappaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno hoti, yoni cassa āraddhā hoti āsavānaṃ khayāyā”ti.**When a mendicant has these four things their practice is guaranteed, and they have laid the groundwork for ending the defilements.”*";
P_HTM[2062]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2063]="*2. Sammādiṭṭhisuttaṃ**Right View*";
P_HTM[2064]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu apaṇṇakappaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno hoti, yoni cassa āraddhā hoti āsavānaṃ khayāya.**“Mendicants, when a mendicant has four things their practice is guaranteed, and they have laid the groundwork for ending the defilements.*";
P_HTM[2065]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2066]="*Nekkhammavitakkena, abyāpādavitakkena, avihiṃsāvitakkena, sammādiṭṭhiyā—**Thoughts of renunciation, good will, and harmlessness; and right view.*";
P_HTM[2067]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu apaṇṇakappaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno hoti, yoni cassa āraddhā hoti āsavānaṃ khayāyā”ti.**When a mendicant has these four things their practice is guaranteed, and they have laid the groundwork for ending the defilements.”*";
P_HTM[2068]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2069]="*3. Sappurisasuttaṃ**A Good Person*";
P_HTM[2070]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato asappuriso veditabbo.**“Mendicants, a bad person can be known by four qualities.*";
P_HTM[2071]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2072]="*Idha, bhikkhave, asappuriso yo hoti parassa avaṇṇo taṃ apuṭṭhopi pātu karoti, ko pana vādo puṭṭhassa.**To start with, a bad person speaks ill of another even when not asked, let alone when asked.*";
P_HTM[2073]="*Puṭṭho kho pana pañhābhinīto ahāpetvā alambitvā paripūraṃ vitthārena parassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**But when led on by questions they speak ill of another in full detail, not leaving anything out.*";
P_HTM[2074]="*Veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.**That’s how to know that this is a bad person.*";
P_HTM[2075]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso yo hoti parassa vaṇṇo taṃ puṭṭhopi na pātu karoti, ko pana vādo apuṭṭhassa.**Furthermore, a bad person doesn’t speak well of another even when asked, let alone when not asked.*";
P_HTM[2076]="*Puṭṭho kho pana pañhābhinīto hāpetvā lambitvā aparipūraṃ avitthārena parassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**But when led on by questions they speak well of another without giving the full details, leaving many things out.*";
P_HTM[2077]="*Veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.**That’s how to know that this is a bad person.*";
P_HTM[2078]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso yo hoti attano avaṇṇo taṃ puṭṭhopi na pātu karoti, ko pana vādo apuṭṭhassa.**Furthermore, a bad person doesn’t speak ill of themselves even when asked, let alone when not asked.*";
P_HTM[2079]="*Puṭṭho kho pana pañhābhinīto hāpetvā lambitvā aparipūraṃ avitthārena attano avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**But when led on by questions they speak ill of themselves without giving the full details, leaving many things out.*";
P_HTM[2080]="*Veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.**That’s how to know that this is a bad person.*";
P_HTM[2081]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso yo hoti attano vaṇṇo taṃ apuṭṭhopi pātu karoti, ko pana vādo puṭṭhassa.**Furthermore, a bad person speaks well of themselves even when not asked, let alone when asked.*";
P_HTM[2082]="*Puṭṭho kho pana pañhābhinīto ahāpetvā alambitvā paripūraṃ vitthārena attano vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**But when led on by questions they speak well of themselves in full detail, not leaving anything out.*";
P_HTM[2083]="*Veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.**That’s how to know that this is a bad person.*";
P_HTM[2084]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato asappuriso veditabbo.**A bad person can be known by these four qualities.*";
P_HTM[2085]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato sappuriso veditabbo.**A good person can be known by four qualities.*";
P_HTM[2086]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2087]="*Idha, bhikkhave, sappuriso yo hoti parassa avaṇṇo taṃ puṭṭhopi na pātu karoti, ko pana vādo apuṭṭhassa.**To start with, a good person doesn’t speak ill of another even when asked, let alone when not asked.*";
P_HTM[2088]="*Puṭṭho kho pana pañhābhinīto hāpetvā lambitvā aparipūraṃ avitthārena parassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**But when led on by questions they speak ill of another without giving the full details, leaving many things out.*";
P_HTM[2089]="*Veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, sappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.**That’s how to know that this is a good person.*";
P_HTM[2090]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sappuriso yo hoti parassa vaṇṇo taṃ apuṭṭhopi pātu karoti, ko pana vādo puṭṭhassa.**Furthermore, a good person speaks well of another even when not asked, let alone when asked.*";
P_HTM[2091]="*Puṭṭho kho pana pañhābhinīto ahāpetvā alambitvā paripūraṃ vitthārena parassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**But when led on by questions they speak well of another in full detail, not leaving anything out.*";
P_HTM[2092]="*Veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, sappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.**That’s how to know that this is a good person.*";
P_HTM[2093]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sappuriso yo hoti attano avaṇṇo taṃ apuṭṭhopi pātu karoti, ko pana vādo puṭṭhassa.**Furthermore, a good person speaks ill of themselves even when not asked, let alone when asked.*";
P_HTM[2094]="*Puṭṭho kho pana pañhābhinīto ahāpetvā alambitvā paripūraṃ vitthārena attano avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**But when led on by questions they speak ill of themselves in full detail, not leaving anything out.*";
P_HTM[2095]="*Veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, sappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.**That’s how to know that this is a good person.*";
P_HTM[2096]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sappuriso yo hoti attano vaṇṇo taṃ puṭṭhopi na pātu karoti, ko pana vādo apuṭṭhassa.**Furthermore, a good person doesn’t speak well of themselves even when asked, let alone when not asked.*";
P_HTM[2097]="*Puṭṭho kho pana pañhābhinīto hāpetvā lambitvā aparipūraṃ avitthārena attano vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**But when led on by questions they speak well of themselves without giving the full details, leaving many things out.*";
P_HTM[2098]="*Veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, sappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.**That’s how to know that this is a good person.*";
P_HTM[2099]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato sappuriso veditabbo.**A good person can be known by these four qualities.*";
P_HTM[2100]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, vadhukā yaññadeva rattiṃ vā divaṃ vā ānītā hoti, tāvadevassā tibbaṃ hirottappaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sassuyāpi sasurepi sāmikepi antamaso dāsakammakaraporisesu.**It’s like a bride on the day or night she’s first brought to her husband’s home. Right away she sets up a keen sense of conscience and prudence for her mother and father in law, her husband, and even the bondservants, workers, and staff.*";
P_HTM[2101]="*Sā aparena samayena saṃvāsamanvāya vissāsamanvāya sassumpi sasurampi sāmikampi evamāha:**But after some time, because of living together and familiarity, she’ll even say to her mother and father in law, or to her husband:*";
P_HTM[2102]="*‘apetha, kiṃ pana tumhe jānāthā’ti.**‘Go away! What would you know?’*";
P_HTM[2103]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhikkhu yaññadeva rattiṃ vā divaṃ vā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, tāvadevassa tibbaṃ hirottappaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti bhikkhūsu bhikkhunīsu upāsakesu upāsikāsu antamaso ārāmikasamaṇuddesesu.**In the same way, on the day or night a mendicant first goes forth from the lay life to homelessness, right away they set up a keen sense of conscience and prudence for the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen, and even the monastery workers and novices.*";
P_HTM[2104]="*So aparena samayena saṃvāsamanvāya vissāsamanvāya ācariyampi upajjhāyampi evamāha:**But after some time, because of living together and familiarity, they’ll even say to their teacher or mentor:*";
P_HTM[2105]="*‘apetha, kiṃ pana tumhe jānāthā’ti.**‘Go away! What would you know?’*";
P_HTM[2106]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[2107]="*‘adhunāgatavadhukāsamena cetasā viharissāmā’ti.**‘We will live with hearts like that of a newly wedded bride.’*";
P_HTM[2108]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[2109]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2110]="*4. Paṭhamaaggasuttaṃ**Best (1st)*";
P_HTM[2111]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, aggāni.**“Mendicants, these four things are the best.*";
P_HTM[2112]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2113]="*Sīlaggaṃ, samādhiggaṃ, paññāggaṃ, vimuttaggaṃ—**The best ethics, immersion, wisdom, and freedom.*";
P_HTM[2114]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri aggānī”ti.**These are the four things that are the best.”*";
P_HTM[2115]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2116]="*5. Dutiyaaggasuttaṃ**Best (2nd)*";
P_HTM[2117]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, aggāni.**“Mendicants, these four things are the best.*";
P_HTM[2118]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2119]="*Rūpaggaṃ, vedanāggaṃ, saññāggaṃ, bhavaggaṃ—**The best form, feeling, perception, and state of existence.*";
P_HTM[2120]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri aggānī”ti.**These are the four things that are the best.”*";
P_HTM[2121]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2122]="*6. Kusinārasuttaṃ**At Kusinārā*";
P_HTM[2123]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kusinārāyaṃ viharati upavattane mallānaṃ sālavane antarena yamakasālānaṃ parinibbānasamaye.**At one time the Buddha was staying between a pair of sal trees in the sal forest of the Mallas at Upavattana near Kusinārā at the time of his final extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[2124]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[2125]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[2126]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2127]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[2128]="*“Siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, ekabhikkhussapi kaṅkhā vā vimati vā buddhe vā dhamme vā saṃghe vā magge vā paṭipadāya vā, pucchatha, bhikkhave, mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha:**“Perhaps even a single mendicant has doubt or uncertainty regarding the Buddha, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the path, or the practice. So ask, mendicants! Don’t regret it later, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2129]="*‘sammukhībhūto no satthā ahosi, nāsakkhimha bhagavantaṃ sammukhā paṭipucchitun’”ti.**‘We were in the Teacher’s presence and we weren’t able to ask the Buddha a question.’”*";
P_HTM[2130]="*Evaṃ vutte, te bhikkhū tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**When this was said, the mendicants kept silent.*";
P_HTM[2131]="*Dutiyampi kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**For a second time the Buddha addressed the mendicants: …*";
P_HTM[2132]="*“siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, ekabhikkhussapi kaṅkhā vā vimati vā buddhe vā dhamme vā saṅghe vā magge vā paṭipadāya vā, pucchatha, bhikkhave, mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha:* **";
P_HTM[2133]="*‘sammukhībhūto no satthā ahosi, nāsakkhimha bhagavantaṃ sammukhā paṭipucchitun’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2134]="*Dutiyampi kho te bhikkhū tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**For a second time, the mendicants kept silent.*";
P_HTM[2135]="*Tatiyampi kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**For a third time the Buddha addressed the mendicants: …*";
P_HTM[2136]="*“siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, ekabhikkhussapi kaṅkhā vā vimati vā buddhe vā dhamme vā saṅghe vā magge vā paṭipadāya vā, pucchatha, bhikkhave, mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha:* **";
P_HTM[2137]="*‘sammukhībhūto no satthā ahosi, nāsakkhimha bhagavantaṃ sammukhā paṭipucchitun’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2138]="*Tatiyampi kho te bhikkhū tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**For a third time, the mendicants kept silent.*";
P_HTM[2139]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[2140]="*“siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, satthugāravenapi na puccheyyātha, sahāyakopi, bhikkhave, sahāyakassa ārocetū”ti.**“Mendicants, perhaps you don’t ask out of respect for the Teacher. So let a friend tell a friend.”*";
P_HTM[2141]="*Evaṃ vutte, te bhikkhū tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**When this was said, the mendicants kept silent.*";
P_HTM[2142]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[2143]="*“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante.**“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[2144]="*Evaṃ pasanno ahaṃ, bhante. Natthi imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṅghe ekabhikkhussapi kaṅkhā vā vimati vā buddhe vā dhamme vā saṅghe vā magge vā paṭipadāya vā”ti.**I am quite confident that there’s not even a single mendicant in this Saṅgha who has doubt or uncertainty regarding the Buddha, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the path, or the practice.”*";
P_HTM[2145]="*“Pasādā kho tvaṃ, ānanda, vadesi. Ñāṇameva hettha, ānanda, tathāgatassa: ‘natthi imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṅghe ekabhikkhussapi kaṅkhā vā vimati vā buddhe vā dhamme vā saṅghe vā magge vā paṭipadāya vā’.**“Ānanda, you speak from faith. But the Realized One knows that there’s not even a single mendicant in this Saṅgha who has doubt or uncertainty regarding the Buddha, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the path, or the practice.*";
P_HTM[2146]="*Imesañhi, ānanda, pañcannaṃ bhikkhusatānaṃ yo pacchimako bhikkhu so sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo”ti.**Even the last of these five hundred mendicants is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[2147]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2148]="*7. Acinteyyasuttaṃ**Unthinkable*";
P_HTM[2149]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, acinteyyāni, na cintetabbāni; yāni cintento ummādassa vighātassa bhāgī assa.**“Mendicants, these four things are unthinkable. They should not be thought about, and anyone who tries to think about them will go mad or get frustrated.*";
P_HTM[2150]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2151]="*Buddhānaṃ, bhikkhave, buddhavisayo acinteyyo, na cintetabbo;**The scope of the Buddhas …*";
P_HTM[2152]="*yaṃ cintento ummādassa vighātassa bhāgī assa.* **";
P_HTM[2153]="*Jhāyissa, bhikkhave, jhānavisayo acinteyyo, na cintetabbo;**The scope of one in absorption …*";
P_HTM[2154]="*yaṃ cintento ummādassa vighātassa bhāgī assa.* **";
P_HTM[2155]="*Kammavipāko, bhikkhave, acinteyyo, na cintetabbo;**The results of deeds …*";
P_HTM[2156]="*yaṃ cintento ummādassa vighātassa bhāgī assa.* **";
P_HTM[2157]="*Lokacintā, bhikkhave, acinteyyā, na cintetabbā;**Speculation about the world …*";
P_HTM[2158]="*yaṃ cintento ummādassa vighātassa bhāgī assa.* **";
P_HTM[2159]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri acinteyyāni, na cintetabbāni; yāni cintento ummādassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**These are the four unthinkable things. They should not be thought about, and anyone who tries to think about them will go mad or get frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[2160]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2161]="*8. Dakkhiṇasuttaṃ**A Religious Donation*";
P_HTM[2162]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā visuddhiyo.**“Mendicants, there are these four ways of purifying a religious donation.*";
P_HTM[2163]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2164]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā dāyakato visujjhati, no paṭiggāhakato;**There’s a religious donation that’s purified by the giver, not the recipient.*";
P_HTM[2165]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā paṭiggāhakato visujjhati, no dāyakato;**There’s a religious donation that’s purified by the recipient, not the giver.*";
P_HTM[2166]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā neva dāyakato visujjhati, no paṭiggāhakato;**There’s a religious donation that’s purified by neither the giver nor the recipient.*";
P_HTM[2167]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā dāyakato ceva visujjhati paṭiggāhakato ca.**There’s a religious donation that’s purified by both the giver and the recipient.*";
P_HTM[2168]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā dāyakato visujjhati, no paṭiggāhakato?**And how is a religious donation purified by the giver, not the recipient?*";
P_HTM[2169]="*Idha, bhikkhave, dāyako hoti sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo; paṭiggāhakā honti dussīlā pāpadhammā.**It’s when the giver is ethical, of good character, but the recipient is unethical, of bad character.*";
P_HTM[2170]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā dāyakato visujjhati, no paṭiggāhakato.* **";
P_HTM[2171]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā paṭiggāhakato visujjhati, no dāyakato?**And how is a religious donation purified by the recipient, not the giver?*";
P_HTM[2172]="*Idha, bhikkhave, dāyako hoti dussīlo pāpadhammo; paṭiggāhakā honti sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā.**It’s when the giver is unethical, of bad character, but the recipient is ethical, of good character.*";
P_HTM[2173]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā paṭiggāhakato visujjhati, no dāyakato.* **";
P_HTM[2174]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā neva dāyakato visujjhati, no paṭiggāhakato?**And how is a religious donation purified by neither the giver nor the recipient?*";
P_HTM[2175]="*Idha, bhikkhave, dāyako hoti dussīlo pāpadhammo; paṭiggāhakāpi honti dussīlā pāpadhammā.**It’s when both the giver and the recipient are unethical, of bad character.*";
P_HTM[2176]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā neva dāyakato visujjhati, no paṭiggāhakato.* **";
P_HTM[2177]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā dāyakato ceva visujjhati paṭiggāhakato ca?**And how is a religious donation purified by both the giver and the recipient?*";
P_HTM[2178]="*Idha, bhikkhave, dāyako hoti sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo; paṭiggāhakāpi honti sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā.**It’s when both the giver and the recipient are ethical, of good character.*";
P_HTM[2179]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā dāyakato ceva visujjhati paṭiggāhakato ca.* **";
P_HTM[2180]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso dakkhiṇā visuddhiyo”ti.**These are the four ways of purifying a religious donation.”*";
P_HTM[2181]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2182]="*9. Vaṇijjasuttaṃ**Business*";
P_HTM[2183]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Sāriputta went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2184]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena midhekaccassa tādisāva vaṇijjā payuttā chedagāminī hoti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why for different people the same kind of business undertaking might fail,*";
P_HTM[2185]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena midhekaccassa tādisāva vaṇijjā payuttā na yathādhippāyā hoti?**while another doesn’t meet expectations,*";
P_HTM[2186]="*Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena midhekaccassa tādisāva vaṇijjā payuttā yathādhippāyā hoti?**another meets expectations,*";
P_HTM[2187]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena midhekaccassa tādisāva vaṇijjā payuttā parādhippāyā hotī”ti?**and another exceeds expectations?”*";
P_HTM[2188]="*“Idha, sāriputta, ekacco samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā upasaṅkamitvā pavāreti: ‘vadatu, bhante, paccayenā’ti. So yena pavāreti taṃ na deti.**“Sāriputta, take a case where someone goes to an ascetic or brahmin and invites them to ask for what they need. But they fail to give what’s requested.*";
P_HTM[2189]="*So ce tato cuto itthattaṃ āgacchati, so yaññadeva vaṇijjaṃ payojeti, sāssa hoti chedagāminī.**When they’ve passed away from that life, if they’re reborn in this state of existence, whatever business they undertake fails.*";
P_HTM[2190]="*Idha pana, sāriputta, ekacco samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā upasaṅkamitvā pavāreti: ‘vadatu, bhante, paccayenā’ti. So yena pavāreti taṃ na yathādhippāyaṃ deti.**Take a case where someone goes to an ascetic or brahmin and invites them to ask for what they need. They give what’s requested, but don’t meet expectations.*";
P_HTM[2191]="*So ce tato cuto itthattaṃ āgacchati, so yaññadeva vaṇijjaṃ payojeti, sāssa na hoti yathādhippāyā.**When they’ve passed away from that life, if they’re reborn in this state of existence, whatever business they undertake doesn’t meet expectations.*";
P_HTM[2192]="*Idha pana, sāriputta, ekacco samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā upasaṅkamitvā pavāreti: ‘vadatu, bhante, paccayenā’ti. So yena pavāreti taṃ yathādhippāyaṃ deti.**Take a case where someone goes to an ascetic or brahmin and invites them to ask for what they need. They give what’s requested, meeting expectations.*";
P_HTM[2193]="*So ce tato cuto itthattaṃ āgacchati, so yaññadeva vaṇijjaṃ payojeti, sāssa hoti yathādhippāyā.**When they’ve passed away from that life, if they’re reborn in this state of existence, whatever business they undertake meets expectations.*";
P_HTM[2194]="*Idha, sāriputta, ekacco samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā upasaṅkamitvā pavāreti: ‘vadatu, bhante, paccayenā’ti. So yena pavāreti taṃ parādhippāyaṃ deti.**Take a case where someone goes to an ascetic or brahmin and invites them to ask for what they need. They give what’s requested, exceeding expectations.*";
P_HTM[2195]="*So ce tato cuto itthattaṃ āgacchati, so yaññadeva vaṇijjaṃ payojeti, sāssa hoti parādhippāyā.**When they’ve passed away from that life, if they’re reborn in this state of existence, whatever business they undertake exceeds expectations.*";
P_HTM[2196]="*Ayaṃ kho, sāriputta, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekaccassa tādisāva vaṇijjā payuttā chedagāminī hoti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why for different people the same kind of business enterprise might fail,*";
P_HTM[2197]="*Ayaṃ pana, sāriputta, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekaccassa tādisāva vaṇijjā payuttā na yathādhippāyā hoti.**while another doesn’t meet expectations,*";
P_HTM[2198]="*Ayaṃ kho pana, sāriputta, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekaccassa tādisāva vaṇijjā payuttā yathādhippāyā hoti.**another meets expectations,*";
P_HTM[2199]="*Ayaṃ pana, sāriputta, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekaccassa tādisāva vaṇijjā payuttā parādhippāyā hotī”ti.**and another exceeds expectations.”*";
P_HTM[2200]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2201]="*10. Kambojasuttaṃ**Persia*";
P_HTM[2202]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2203]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2204]="*“Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena mātugāmo neva sabhāyaṃ nisīdati, na kammantaṃ payojeti, na kambojaṃ gacchatī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why females don’t attend council meetings, work for a living, or travel to Persia?”*";
P_HTM[2205]="*“Kodhano, ānanda, mātugāmo;**“Ānanda, females are irritable,*";
P_HTM[2206]="*issukī, ānanda, mātugāmo;**jealous,*";
P_HTM[2207]="*maccharī, ānanda, mātugāmo;**stingy,*";
P_HTM[2208]="*duppañño, ānanda, mātugāmo—**and unintelligent.*";
P_HTM[2209]="*ayaṃ kho, ānanda, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena mātugāmo neva sabhāyaṃ nisīdati, na kammantaṃ payojeti, na kambojaṃ gacchatī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why females don’t attend council meetings, work for a living, or travel to Persia.”*";
P_HTM[2210]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2211]="*Apaṇṇakavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[2212]="*Padhānaṃ diṭṭhisappurisa,* **";
P_HTM[2213]="*Vadhukā dve ca honti aggāni;* **";
P_HTM[2214]="*Kusināraacinteyyā,* **";
P_HTM[2215]="*Dakkhiṇā ca vaṇijjā kambojanti.* **";
P_HTM[2216]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Confirmed*";
P_HTM[2217]="*1. Pāṇātipātasuttaṃ**Killing Living Creatures*";
P_HTM[2218]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2219]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2220]="*Pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti—**They kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, and lie.*";
P_HTM[2221]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2222]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[2223]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2224]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti—**They don’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, or lie.*";
P_HTM[2225]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these four qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[2226]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2227]="*2. Musāvādasuttaṃ**Lying*";
P_HTM[2228]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2229]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2230]="*Musāvādī hoti, pisuṇavāco hoti, pharusavāco hoti, samphappalāpī hoti—**They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical.*";
P_HTM[2231]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2232]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[2233]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2234]="*Musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti—**They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical.*";
P_HTM[2235]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these four qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[2236]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2237]="*3. Avaṇṇārahasuttaṃ**Where Criticism Takes You*";
P_HTM[2238]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2239]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2240]="*Ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**Without examining or scrutinizing, they praise those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[2241]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**and they criticize those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[2242]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā appasādanīye ṭhāne pasādaṃ upadaṃseti, ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā pasādanīye ṭhāne appasādaṃ upadaṃseti—**They arouse faith in things that are dubious, and they don’t arouse faith in things that are inspiring.*";
P_HTM[2243]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2244]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[2245]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2246]="*Anuvicca pariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**After examining and scrutinizing, they criticize those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[2247]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**and they praise those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[2248]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā appasādanīye ṭhāne appasādaṃ upadaṃseti**They don’t arouse faith in things that are dubious,*";
P_HTM[2249]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā pasādanīye ṭhāne pasādaṃ upadaṃseti—**and they do arouse faith in things that are inspiring.*";
P_HTM[2250]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these four qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[2251]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2252]="*4. Kodhagarusuttaṃ**Valuing Anger*";
P_HTM[2253]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2254]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2255]="*Kodhagaru hoti na saddhammagaru, makkhagaru hoti na saddhammagaru, lābhagaru hoti na saddhammagaru, sakkāragaru hoti na saddhammagaru—**They value anger, or denigration, or material possessions, or honor rather than the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[2256]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2257]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[2258]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2259]="*Saddhammagaru hoti na kodhagaru, saddhammagaru hoti na makkhagaru, saddhammagaru hoti na lābhagaru, saddhammagaru hoti na sakkāragaru—**They value the true teaching rather than anger, or denigration, or material possessions, or honor.*";
P_HTM[2260]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these four qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[2261]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2262]="*5. Tamotamasuttaṃ**From Darkness to Darkness*";
P_HTM[2263]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2264]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2265]="*Tamo tamaparāyaṇo, tamo jotiparāyaṇo, joti tamaparāyaṇo, joti jotiparāyaṇo.**~The dark bound for darkness, ~the dark bound for light, ~the light bound for darkness, and ~the light bound for light.*";
P_HTM[2266]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo tamo hoti tamaparāyaṇo?**And how is a person dark and bound for darkness?*";
P_HTM[2267]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo nīce kule paccājāto hoti—caṇḍālakule vā venakule vā nesādakule vā rathakārakule vā pukkusakule vā dalidde appannapānabhojane kasiravuttike, yattha kasirena ghāsacchādo labbhati.**It’s when someone is reborn in a low family—a family of outcastes, bamboo-workers, hunters, chariot-makers, or waste-collectors—poor, with little to eat or drink, where life is tough, and food and shelter are hard to find.*";
P_HTM[2268]="*So ca hoti dubbaṇṇo duddasiko okoṭimako bavhābādho kāṇo vā kuṇī vā khañjo vā pakkhahato vā, na lābhī annassa pānassa vatthassa yānassa mālāgandhavilepanassa seyyāvasathapadīpeyyassa.**And they’re ugly, unsightly, deformed, chronically ill—one-eyed, crippled, lame, or half-paralyzed. They don’t get to have food, drink, clothes, and vehicles; garlands, fragrance, and makeup; or bed, house, and lighting.*";
P_HTM[2269]="*So kāyena duccaritaṃ carati, vācāya duccaritaṃ carati, manasā duccaritaṃ carati.**And they do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[2270]="*So kāyena duccaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya duccaritaṃ caritvā, manasā duccaritaṃ caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[2271]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo tamo hoti tamaparāyaṇo.**That’s how a person is dark and bound for darkness.*";
P_HTM[2272]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo tamo hoti jotiparāyaṇo?**And how is a person dark and bound for light?*";
P_HTM[2273]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo nīce kule paccājāto hoti—caṇḍālakule vā venakule vā nesādakule vā rathakārakule vā pukkusakule vā dalidde appannapānabhojane kasiravuttike, yattha kasirena ghāsacchādo labbhati;**It’s when some person is reborn in a low family …*";
P_HTM[2274]="*so ca hoti dubbaṇṇo duddasiko okoṭimako bavhābādho kāṇo vā kuṇī vā khañjo vā pakkhahato vā na lābhī annassa pānassa vatthassa yānassa mālāgandhavilepanassa seyyāvasathapadīpeyyassa.* **";
P_HTM[2275]="*So kāyena sucaritaṃ carati, vācāya sucaritaṃ carati, manasā sucaritaṃ carati.**But they do good things by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[2276]="*So kāyena sucaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya sucaritaṃ caritvā, manasā sucaritaṃ caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[2277]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo tamo hoti jotiparāyaṇo.**That’s how a person is dark and bound for light.*";
P_HTM[2278]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo joti hoti tamaparāyaṇo?**And how is a person light and bound for darkness?*";
P_HTM[2279]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ucce kule paccājāto hoti—khattiyamahāsālakule vā brāhmaṇamahāsālakule vā gahapatimahāsālakule vā aḍḍhe mahaddhane mahābhoge pahūtajātarūparajate pahūtavittūpakaraṇe pahūtadhanadhaññe;**It’s when some person is reborn in an eminent family—a well-to-do family of aristocrats, brahmins, or householders—rich, affluent, and wealthy, with lots of gold and silver, lots of property and assets, and lots of money and grain.*";
P_HTM[2280]="*so ca hoti abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato, lābhī annassa pānassa vatthassa yānassa mālāgandhavilepanassa seyyāvasathapadīpeyyassa.**And they’re attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty. They get to have food, drink, clothes, and vehicles; garlands, fragrance, and makeup; and bed, house, and lighting.*";
P_HTM[2281]="*So kāyena duccaritaṃ carati, vācāya duccaritaṃ carati, manasā duccaritaṃ carati.**But they do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[2282]="*So kāyena duccaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya duccaritaṃ caritvā, manasā duccaritaṃ caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[2283]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo joti hoti tamaparāyaṇo.**That’s how a person is light and bound for darkness.*";
P_HTM[2284]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo joti hoti jotiparāyaṇo?**And how is a person light and bound for light?*";
P_HTM[2285]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ucce kule paccājāto hoti—khattiyamahāsālakule vā brāhmaṇamahāsālakule vā gahapatimahāsālakule vā aḍḍhe mahaddhane mahābhoge pahūtajātarūparajate pahūtavittūpakaraṇe pahūtadhanadhaññe;**It’s when some person is reborn in an eminent family …*";
P_HTM[2286]="*so ca hoti abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato, lābhī annassa pānassa vatthassa yānassa mālāgandhavilepanassa seyyāvasathapadīpeyyassa.* **";
P_HTM[2287]="*So kāyena sucaritaṃ carati, vācāya sucaritaṃ carati, manasā sucaritaṃ carati.**And they do good things by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[2288]="*So kāyena sucaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya sucaritaṃ caritvā, manasā sucaritaṃ caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[2289]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo joti hoti jotiparāyaṇo.**That’s how a person is light and bound for light.*";
P_HTM[2290]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2291]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2292]="*6. Oṇatoṇatasuttaṃ**Sunk Low*";
P_HTM[2293]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“These four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2294]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2295]="*Oṇatoṇato, oṇatuṇṇato, uṇṇatoṇato, uṇṇatuṇṇato.**~One sunk low who sinks lower, ~one sunk low who rises high, ~one risen high who sinks low, and ~one risen high who rises higher.*";
P_HTM[2296]="*… Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**… These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2297]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2298]="*7. Puttasuttaṃ**The Son*";
P_HTM[2299]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2300]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2301]="*Samaṇamacalo, samaṇapuṇḍarīko, samaṇapadumo, samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo.**The confirmed ascetic, the white lotus ascetic, the pink lotus ascetic, and the exquisite ascetic of ascetics.*";
P_HTM[2302]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇamacalo hoti?**And how is a person a confirmed ascetic?*";
P_HTM[2303]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sekho hoti pāṭipado;**It’s when a mendicant is a practicing trainee,*";
P_HTM[2304]="*anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ patthayamāno viharati.**who lives aspiring to the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[2305]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa jeṭṭho putto ābhiseko anabhisitto macalappatto;**It’s like the eldest son of an anointed king. He has not yet been anointed, but is eligible, and has been confirmed in the succession.*";
P_HTM[2306]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sekho hoti pāṭipado, anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ patthayamāno viharati.**In the same way, a mendicant is a practicing trainee, who lives aspiring to the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[2307]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇamacalo hoti.**That’s how a person is a confirmed ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2308]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapuṇḍarīko hoti?**And how is a person a white lotus ascetic?*";
P_HTM[2309]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati, no ca kho aṭṭha vimokkhe kāyena phusitvā viharati.**It’s when a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. But they don’t have direct meditative experience of the eight liberations.*";
P_HTM[2310]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapuṇḍarīko hoti.**That’s how a person is a white lotus ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2311]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapadumo hoti?**And how is a person a pink lotus ascetic?*";
P_HTM[2312]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati, aṭṭha ca vimokkhe kāyena phusitvā viharati.**It’s when a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. … And they have direct meditative experience of the eight liberations.*";
P_HTM[2313]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapadumo hoti.**That’s how a person is a pink lotus ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2314]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo hoti?**And how is a person an exquisite ascetic of ascetics?*";
P_HTM[2315]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yācitova bahulaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjati, appaṃ ayācito; yācitova bahulaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ paribhuñjati, appaṃ ayācito; yācitova bahulaṃ senāsanaṃ paribhuñjati, appaṃ ayācito; yācitova bahulaṃ gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ paribhuñjati, appaṃ ayācito.**It’s when a mendicant usually uses only what they’ve been invited to accept—robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick—rarely using them without invitation.*";
P_HTM[2316]="*Yehi kho pana sabrahmacārīhi saddhiṃ viharati, tyassa manāpeneva bahulaṃ kāyakammena samudācaranti, appaṃ amanāpena; manāpeneva bahulaṃ vacīkammena samudācaranti, appaṃ amanāpena; manāpeneva bahulaṃ manokammena samudācaranti, appaṃ amanāpena;**When living with other spiritual practitioners, they usually treat them agreeably by way of body, speech, and mind, and rarely disagreeably.*";
P_HTM[2317]="*manāpaṃyeva bahulaṃ upahāraṃ upaharanti, appaṃ amanāpaṃ.**And they usually present them with agreeable things, rarely with disagreeable ones.*";
P_HTM[2318]="*Yāni kho pana tāni vedayitāni pittasamuṭṭhānāni vā semhasamuṭṭhānāni vā vātasamuṭṭhānāni vā sannipātikāni vā utupariṇāmajāni vā visamaparihārajāni vā opakkamikāni vā kammavipākajāni vā, tāni panassa na bahudeva uppajjanti. Appābādho hoti.**They’re healthy, so the various unpleasant feelings—stemming from disorders of bile, phlegm, wind, or their conjunction; or caused by change in weather, by not taking care of yourself, by overexertion, or as the result of past deeds—usually don’t come up.*";
P_HTM[2319]="*Catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī,**They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[2320]="*āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**And they realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. …*";
P_HTM[2321]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo hoti.**That’s how a person is an exquisite ascetic of ascetics.*";
P_HTM[2322]="*Yañhi taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya samaṇesu samaṇasukhumāloti, mameva taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya samaṇesu samaṇasukhumāloti.**And if anyone should be rightly called an exquisite ascetic of ascetics, it’s me.*";
P_HTM[2323]="*Ahañhi, bhikkhave, yācitova bahulaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjāmi, appaṃ ayācito; yācitova bahulaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ paribhuñjāmi, appaṃ ayācito; yācitova bahulaṃ senāsanaṃ paribhuñjāmi, appaṃ ayācito; yācitova bahulaṃ gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ paribhuñjāmi, appaṃ ayācito.**For I usually use only what I’ve been invited to accept …*";
P_HTM[2324]="*Yehi kho pana bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ viharāmi te me manāpeneva bahulaṃ kāyakammena samudācaranti, appaṃ amanāpena; manāpeneva bahulaṃ vacīkammena samudācaranti, appaṃ amanāpena; manāpeneva bahulaṃ manokammena samudācaranti, appaṃ amanāpena; manāpaṃyeva bahulaṃ upahāraṃ upaharanti, appaṃ amanāpaṃ.**When living with other spiritual practitioners, I usually treat them agreeably …*";
P_HTM[2325]="*Yāni kho pana tāni vedayitāni pittasamuṭṭhānāni vā semhasamuṭṭhānāni vā vātasamuṭṭhānāni vā sannipātikāni vā utupariṇāmajāni vā visamaparihārajāni vā opakkamikāni vā kammavipākajāni vā, tāni me na bahudeva uppajjanti. Appābādhohamasmi.**I’m healthy …*";
P_HTM[2326]="*Catunnaṃ kho panasmi jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī akicchalābhī akasiralābhī,**I get the four absorptions when I want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[2327]="*āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmi.**And I’ve realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. …*";
P_HTM[2328]="*Yañhi taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya samaṇesu samaṇasukhumāloti, mameva taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya samaṇesu samaṇasukhumāloti.**So if anyone should be rightly called an exquisite ascetic of ascetics, it’s me.*";
P_HTM[2329]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2330]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2331]="*8. Saṃyojanasuttaṃ**Fetters*";
P_HTM[2332]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2333]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2334]="*Samaṇamacalo, samaṇapuṇḍarīko, samaṇapadumo, samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo.**The confirmed ascetic, the white lotus ascetic, the pink lotus ascetic, and the exquisite ascetic of ascetics.*";
P_HTM[2335]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇamacalo hoti?**And how is a person a confirmed ascetic?*";
P_HTM[2336]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo.**It’s when a mendicant—with the ending of three fetters—is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[2337]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇamacalo hoti.**That’s how a person is a confirmed ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2338]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapuṇḍarīko hoti?**And how is a person a white lotus ascetic?*";
P_HTM[2339]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā, rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmī hoti, sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karoti.**It’s when a mendicant—with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion—is a once-returner. They come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering.*";
P_HTM[2340]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapuṇḍarīko hoti.**That’s how a person is a white lotus ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2341]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapadumo hoti?**And how is a person a pink lotus ascetic?*";
P_HTM[2342]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko hoti tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā.**It’s when a mendicant—with the ending of the five lower fetters—is reborn spontaneously. They’re extinguished there, and are not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[2343]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapadumo hoti.**That’s how a person is a pink lotus ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2344]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo hoti?**And how is a person an exquisite ascetic of ascetics?*";
P_HTM[2345]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[2346]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo hoti.**That’s how a person is an exquisite ascetic of ascetics.*";
P_HTM[2347]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2348]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2349]="*9. Sammādiṭṭhisuttaṃ**Right View*";
P_HTM[2350]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2351]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2352]="*Samaṇamacalo, samaṇapuṇḍarīko, samaṇapadumo, samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo.**The confirmed ascetic, the white lotus ascetic, the pink lotus ascetic, and the exquisite ascetic of ascetics.*";
P_HTM[2353]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇamacalo hoti?**And how is a person a confirmed ascetic?*";
P_HTM[2354]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, sammāsaṅkappo hoti, sammāvāco hoti, sammākammanto hoti, sammāājīvo hoti, sammāvāyāmo hoti, sammāsati hoti, sammāsamādhi hoti.**It’s when a mendicant has right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[2355]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇamacalo hoti.**That’s how a person is a confirmed ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2356]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapuṇḍarīko hoti?**And how is a person a white lotus ascetic?*";
P_HTM[2357]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, sammāsaṅkappo hoti, sammāvāco hoti, sammākammanto hoti, sammāājīvo hoti, sammāvāyāmo hoti, sammāsati hoti, sammāsamādhi hoti, sammāñāṇī hoti, sammāvimutti hoti, no ca kho aṭṭha vimokkhe kāyena phusitvā viharati.**It’s when they have right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom. But they don’t have direct meditative experience of the eight liberations.*";
P_HTM[2358]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapuṇḍarīko hoti.**That’s how a person is a white lotus ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2359]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapadumo hoti?**And how is a person a pink lotus ascetic?*";
P_HTM[2360]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiko hoti … pe … sammāvimutti hoti, aṭṭha ca vimokkhe kāyena phusitvā viharati.**It’s when they have right view … and right freedom. And they do have direct meditative experience of the eight liberations.*";
P_HTM[2361]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapadumo hoti.**That’s how a person is a pink lotus ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2362]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo hoti?**And how is a person an exquisite ascetic of ascetics?*";
P_HTM[2363]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yācitova bahulaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjati, appaṃ ayācito … pe … yañhi taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya samaṇesu samaṇasukhumāloti, mameva taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya samaṇesu samaṇasukhumāloti.**It’s when a mendicant usually uses only what they’ve been invited to accept … And if anyone should be rightly called an exquisite ascetic of ascetics, it’s me.*";
P_HTM[2364]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2365]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2366]="*10. Khandhasuttaṃ**Aggregates*";
P_HTM[2367]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2368]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2369]="*Samaṇamacalo, samaṇapuṇḍarīko, samaṇapadumo, samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo.**The confirmed ascetic, the white lotus ascetic, the pink lotus ascetic, and the exquisite ascetic of ascetics.*";
P_HTM[2370]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇamacalo hoti?**And how is a person a confirmed ascetic?*";
P_HTM[2371]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sekho hoti appattamānaso, anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ patthayamāno viharati.**It’s when a mendicant is a trainee who hasn’t achieved their heart’s desire, but lives aspiring to the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[2372]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇamacalo hoti.**That’s how a person is a confirmed ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2373]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapuṇḍarīko hoti?**And how is a person a white lotus ascetic?*";
P_HTM[2374]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu udayabbayānupassī viharati:**It’s when a mendicant meditates observing rise and fall in the five grasping aggregates.*";
P_HTM[2375]="*‘iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo;**‘Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form.*";
P_HTM[2376]="*iti vedanā … pe …**Such is feeling …*";
P_HTM[2377]="*iti saññā … pe …**Such is perception …*";
P_HTM[2378]="*iti saṅkhārā … pe …**Such are choices …*";
P_HTM[2379]="*iti viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti;**Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the ending of consciousness.’*";
P_HTM[2380]="*no ca kho aṭṭha vimokkhe kāyena phusitvā viharati.**But they don’t have direct meditative experience of the eight liberations.*";
P_HTM[2381]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapuṇḍarīko hoti.**That’s how a person is a white lotus ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2382]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapadumo hoti?**And how is a person a pink lotus ascetic?*";
P_HTM[2383]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu udayabbayānupassī viharati:**It’s when a mendicant meditates observing rise and fall in the five grasping aggregates.*";
P_HTM[2384]="*‘iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo;**‘Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form.*";
P_HTM[2385]="*iti vedanā … pe …**Such is feeling …*";
P_HTM[2386]="*iti saññā … pe …**Such is perception …*";
P_HTM[2387]="*iti saṅkhārā … pe …**Such are choices …*";
P_HTM[2388]="*iti viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti;**Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the ending of consciousness.’*";
P_HTM[2389]="*aṭṭha ca vimokkhe kāyena phusitvā viharati.**And they have direct meditative experience of the eight liberations.*";
P_HTM[2390]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapadumo hoti.**That’s how a person is a pink lotus ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2391]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo hoti?**And how is a person an exquisite ascetic of ascetics?*";
P_HTM[2392]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yācitova bahulaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjati, appaṃ ayācito … pe … mameva taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya samaṇesu samaṇasukhumāloti.**It’s when a mendicant usually uses only what they’ve been invited to accept … And if anyone should be rightly called an exquisite ascetic of ascetics, it’s me.*";
P_HTM[2393]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2394]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2395]="*Macalavaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[2396]="*Pāṇātipāto ca musā,* **";
P_HTM[2397]="*avaṇṇakodhatamoṇatā;* **";
P_HTM[2398]="*Putto saṃyojanañceva,* **";
P_HTM[2399]="*diṭṭhi khandhena te dasāti.* **";
P_HTM[2400]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Demons*";
P_HTM[2401]="*1. Asurasuttaṃ**Demons*";
P_HTM[2402]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2403]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2404]="*Asuro asuraparivāro, asuro devaparivāro, devo asuraparivāro, devo devaparivāro.**~A demon surrounded by demons, ~a demon surrounded by gods, ~a god surrounded by demons, and ~a god surrounded by gods.*";
P_HTM[2405]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo asuro hoti asuraparivāro?**And how is a person a demon surrounded by demons?*";
P_HTM[2406]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dussīlo hoti pāpadhammo, parisāpissa hoti dussīlā pāpadhammā.**It’s when a person is unethical, of bad character, and their followers are the same.*";
P_HTM[2407]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo asuro hoti asuraparivāro.**That’s how a person is a demon surrounded by demons.*";
P_HTM[2408]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo asuro hoti devaparivāro?**And how is a person a demon surrounded by gods?*";
P_HTM[2409]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dussīlo hoti pāpadhammo, parisā ca khvassa hoti sīlavatī kalyāṇadhammā.**It’s when a person is unethical, of bad character, but their followers are ethical, of good character.*";
P_HTM[2410]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo asuro hoti devaparivāro.**That’s how a person is a demon surrounded by gods.*";
P_HTM[2411]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo devo hoti asuraparivāro?**And how is a person a god surrounded by demons?*";
P_HTM[2412]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sīlavā hoti kalyāṇadhammo, parisā ca khvassa hoti dussīlā pāpadhammā.**It’s when a person is ethical, of good character, but their followers are unethical, of bad character.*";
P_HTM[2413]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo devo hoti asuraparivāro.**That’s how a person is a god surrounded by demons.*";
P_HTM[2414]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo devo hoti devaparivāro?**And how is a person a god surrounded by gods?*";
P_HTM[2415]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sīlavā hoti kalyāṇadhammo, parisāpissa hoti sīlavatī kalyāṇadhammā.**It’s when a person is ethical, of good character, and their followers are the same.*";
P_HTM[2416]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo devo hoti, devaparivāro.**That’s how a person is a god surrounded by gods.*";
P_HTM[2417]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2418]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2419]="*2. Paṭhamasamādhisuttaṃ**Immersion (1st)*";
P_HTM[2420]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2421]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2422]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, na lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**One person has internal serenity of heart, but not the higher wisdom of discernment of principles.*";
P_HTM[2423]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī hoti adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, na lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa.**One person has the higher wisdom of discernment of principles, but not internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2424]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na ceva lābhī hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa na ca lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**One person has neither internal serenity of heart, nor the higher wisdom of discernment of principles.*";
P_HTM[2425]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**One person has both internal serenity of heart, and the higher wisdom of discernment of principles.*";
P_HTM[2426]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2427]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2428]="*3. Dutiyasamādhisuttaṃ**Immersion (2nd)*";
P_HTM[2429]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2430]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2431]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, na lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**One person has internal serenity of heart, but not the higher wisdom of discernment of principles.*";
P_HTM[2432]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī hoti adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, na lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa.**One person has the higher wisdom of discernment of principles, but not internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2433]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na ceva lābhī hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa na ca lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**One person has neither internal serenity of heart, nor the higher wisdom of discernment of principles.*";
P_HTM[2434]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**One person has both internal serenity of heart, and the higher wisdom of discernment of principles.*";
P_HTM[2435]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa na lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena ajjhattaṃ cetosamathe patiṭṭhāya adhipaññādhammavipassanāya yogo karaṇīyo.**As for the person who has serenity but not discernment: grounded on serenity, they should practice meditation to get discernment.*";
P_HTM[2436]="*So aparena samayena lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**After some time they have both serenity and discernment.*";
P_HTM[2437]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya na lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena adhipaññādhammavipassanāya patiṭṭhāya ajjhattaṃ cetosamathe yogo karaṇīyo.**As for the person who has discernment but not serenity: grounded on discernment, they should practice meditation to get serenity.*";
P_HTM[2438]="*So aparena samayena lābhī ceva hoti adhipaññādhammavipassanāya lābhī ca ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa.**After some time they have both discernment and serenity.*";
P_HTM[2439]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo na ceva lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa na ca lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena tesaṃyeva kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭilābhāya adhimatto chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca karaṇīyaṃ.**As for the person who has neither serenity nor discernment: in order to get those skillful qualities, they should apply outstanding enthusiasm, effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, mindfulness, and situational awareness.*";
P_HTM[2440]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ādittacelo vā ādittasīso vā tasseva celassa vā sīsassa vā nibbāpanāya adhimattaṃ chandañca vāyāmañca ussāhañca ussoḷhiñca appaṭivāniñca satiñca sampajaññañca kareyya;**Suppose your clothes or head were on fire. In order to extinguish it, you’d apply intense enthusiasm, effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, mindfulness, and situational awareness.*";
P_HTM[2441]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tena puggalena tesaṃyeva kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭilābhāya adhimatto chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca karaṇīyaṃ.**In the same way, in order to get those skillful qualities, that person should apply outstanding enthusiasm …*";
P_HTM[2442]="*So aparena samayena lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**After some time they have both serenity and discernment.*";
P_HTM[2443]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena tesuyeva kusalesu dhammesu patiṭṭhāya uttari āsavānaṃ khayāya yogo karaṇīyo.**As for the person who has both serenity and discernment: grounded on those skillful qualities, they should practice meditation further to end the defilements.*";
P_HTM[2444]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2445]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2446]="*4. Tatiyasamādhisuttaṃ**Immersion (3rd)*";
P_HTM[2447]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2448]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2449]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, na lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**One person has internal serenity of heart, but not the higher wisdom of discernment of principles.*";
P_HTM[2450]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī hoti adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, na lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa.**One person has the higher wisdom of discernment of principles, but not internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2451]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na ceva lābhī hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa na ca lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**One person has neither internal serenity of heart, nor the higher wisdom of discernment of principles.*";
P_HTM[2452]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**One person has both internal serenity of heart, and the higher wisdom of discernment of principles.*";
P_HTM[2453]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa na lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:**As for the person who has serenity but not discernment: they should approach someone who has discernment and ask:*";
P_HTM[2454]="*‘kathaṃ nu kho, āvuso, saṅkhārā daṭṭhabbā?**‘Reverend, how should conditions be seen?*";
P_HTM[2455]="*Kathaṃ saṅkhārā sammasitabbā?**How should they be comprehended?*";
P_HTM[2456]="*Kathaṃ saṅkhārā vipassitabbā’ti?**How should they be discerned?’*";
P_HTM[2457]="*Tassa so yathādiṭṭhaṃ yathāviditaṃ byākaroti:**That person would answer from their own experience:*";
P_HTM[2458]="*‘evaṃ kho, āvuso, saṅkhārā daṭṭhabbā, evaṃ saṅkhārā sammasitabbā, evaṃ saṅkhārā vipassitabbā’ti.**‘This is how conditions should be seen, comprehended, and discerned.’*";
P_HTM[2459]="*So aparena samayena lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**After some time they have both serenity and discernment.*";
P_HTM[2460]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya na lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:**As for the person who has discernment but not serenity: they should approach someone who has serenity and ask:*";
P_HTM[2461]="*‘kathaṃ nu kho, āvuso, cittaṃ saṇṭhapetabbaṃ?**‘Reverend, how should the mind be stilled?*";
P_HTM[2462]="*Kathaṃ cittaṃ sannisādetabbaṃ?**How should it be settled?*";
P_HTM[2463]="*Kathaṃ cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ?**How should it be unified?*";
P_HTM[2464]="*Kathaṃ cittaṃ samādahātabban’ti?**How should it be immersed in samādhi?’*";
P_HTM[2465]="*Tassa so yathādiṭṭhaṃ yathāviditaṃ byākaroti:**That person would answer from their own experience:*";
P_HTM[2466]="*‘evaṃ kho, āvuso, cittaṃ saṇṭhapetabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ sannisādetabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ samādahātabban’ti.**‘Reverend, this is how the mind should be stilled, settled, unified, and immersed in samādhi.’*";
P_HTM[2467]="*So aparena samaye lābhī ceva hoti adhipaññādhammavipassanāya lābhī ca ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa.**After some time they have both discernment and serenity.*";
P_HTM[2468]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo na ceva lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa na ca lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī ceva ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo:**As for the person who has neither serenity nor discernment: they should approach someone who has serenity and discernment and ask:*";
P_HTM[2469]="*‘kathaṃ nu kho, āvuso, cittaṃ saṇṭhapetabbaṃ?**‘Reverend, how should the mind be stilled?*";
P_HTM[2470]="*Kathaṃ cittaṃ sannisādetabbaṃ?**How should it be settled?*";
P_HTM[2471]="*Kathaṃ cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ?**How should it be unified?*";
P_HTM[2472]="*Kathaṃ cittaṃ samādahātabbaṃ?**How should it be immersed in samādhi?’*";
P_HTM[2473]="*Kathaṃ saṅkhārā daṭṭhabbā?**How should conditions be seen?*";
P_HTM[2474]="*Kathaṃ saṅkhārā sammasitabbā?**How should they be comprehended?*";
P_HTM[2475]="*Kathaṃ saṅkhārā vipassitabbā’ti?**How should they be discerned?’*";
P_HTM[2476]="*Tassa so yathādiṭṭhaṃ yathāviditaṃ byākaroti:**That person would answer as they’ve seen and known:*";
P_HTM[2477]="*‘evaṃ kho, āvuso, cittaṃ saṇṭhapetabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ sannisādetabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ samādahātabbaṃ, evaṃ saṅkhārā daṭṭhabbā, evaṃ saṅkhārā sammasitabbā, evaṃ saṅkhārā vipassitabbā’ti.**‘Reverend, this is how the mind should be stilled, settled, unified, and immersed in samādhi. And this is how conditions should be seen, comprehended, and discerned.’*";
P_HTM[2478]="*So aparena samayena lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya.**After some time they have both serenity and discernment.*";
P_HTM[2479]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena tesu ceva kusalesu dhammesu patiṭṭhāya uttari āsavānaṃ khayāya yogo karaṇīyo.**As for the person who has both serenity and discernment: grounded on those skillful qualities, they should practice meditation further to end the defilements.*";
P_HTM[2480]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2481]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2482]="*5. Chavālātasuttaṃ**A Firebrand*";
P_HTM[2483]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2484]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2485]="*Nevattahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, parahitāya paṭipanno no attahitāya, attahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, attahitāya ceva paṭipanno parahitāya ca.**~One who practices to benefit neither themselves nor others; ~one who practices to benefit others, but not themselves; ~one who practices to benefit themselves, but not others; and ~one who practices to benefit both themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[2486]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, chavālātaṃ ubhato padittaṃ, majjhe gūthagataṃ, neva gāme kaṭṭhatthaṃ pharati na araññe ();**Suppose there was a firebrand for lighting a funeral pyre, burning at both ends, and smeared with dung in the middle. It couldn’t be used as timber either in the village or the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[2487]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi yvāyaṃ puggalo nevattahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya.**The person who practices to benefit neither themselves nor others is like this, I say.*";
P_HTM[2488]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo parahitāya paṭipanno no attahitāya, ayaṃ imesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro ca.**The person who practices to benefit others, but not themselves, is better than that.*";
P_HTM[2489]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo attahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, ayaṃ imesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro ca.**The person who practices to benefit themselves, but not others, is better than both of those.*";
P_HTM[2490]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo attahitāya ceva paṭipanno parahitāya ca, ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ puggalānaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca pāmokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.**But the person who practices to benefit both themselves and others is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the four.*";
P_HTM[2491]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ, khīramhā dadhi, dadhimhā navanītaṃ, navanītamhā sappi, sappimhā sappimaṇḍo, sappimaṇḍo tattha aggamakkhāyati;**From a cow comes milk, from milk comes curds, from curds come butter, from butter comes ghee, and from ghee comes cream of ghee. And the cream of ghee is said to be the best of these.*";
P_HTM[2492]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo attahitāya ceva paṭipanno parahitāya ca, ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ puggalānaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca pāmokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.**In the same way, the person who practices to benefit both themselves and others is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the four.*";
P_HTM[2493]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2494]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2495]="*6. Rāgavinayasuttaṃ**Removing Greed*";
P_HTM[2496]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2497]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2498]="*Attahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, parahitāya paṭipanno no attahitāya, nevattahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, attahitāya ceva paṭipanno parahitāya ca.**~One who practices to benefit themselves, but not others; ~one who practices to benefit others, but not themselves; ~one who practices to benefit neither themselves nor others; and ~one who practices to benefit both themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[2499]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya paṭipanno hoti no parahitāya?**And how does a person practice to benefit themselves, but not others?*";
P_HTM[2500]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo attanā rāgavinayāya paṭipanno hoti, no paraṃ rāgavinayāya samādapeti;**It’s when a person practices to remove their own greed, hate, and delusion, but doesn’t encourage others to do the same.*";
P_HTM[2501]="*attanā dosavinayāya paṭipanno hoti, no paraṃ dosavinayāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[2502]="*attanā mohavinayāya paṭipanno hoti, no paraṃ mohavinayāya samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[2503]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya.**That’s how a person practices to benefit themselves, but not others.*";
P_HTM[2504]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo parahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no attahitāya?**And how does a person practice to benefit others, but not themselves?*";
P_HTM[2505]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo attanā na rāgavinayāya paṭipanno hoti, paraṃ rāgavinayāya samādapeti;**It’s when a person doesn’t practice to remove their own greed, hate, and delusion, but encourages others to remove theirs.*";
P_HTM[2506]="*attanā na dosavinayāya paṭipanno hoti, paraṃ dosavinayāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[2507]="*attanā na mohavinayāya paṭipanno hoti, paraṃ mohavinayāya samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[2508]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo parahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no attahitāya.**That’s how a person practices to benefit others, but not themselves.*";
P_HTM[2509]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo nevattahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya?**And how does a person practice to benefit neither themselves nor others?*";
P_HTM[2510]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo attanā na rāgavinayāya paṭipanno hoti, no paraṃ rāgavinayāya samādapeti;**It’s when a person doesn’t practice to remove their own greed, hate, and delusion, nor do they encourage others to remove theirs.*";
P_HTM[2511]="*attanā na dosavinayāya paṭipanno hoti, no paraṃ dosavinayāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[2512]="*attanā na mohavinayāya paṭipanno hoti, no paraṃ mohavinayāya samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[2513]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo nevattahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya.**That’s how a person practices to benefit neither themselves nor others.*";
P_HTM[2514]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya ceva paṭipanno hoti parahitāya ca?**And how does a person practice to benefit both themselves and others?*";
P_HTM[2515]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo attanā ca rāgavinayāya paṭipanno hoti, parañca rāgavinayāya samādapeti;**It’s when a person practices to remove their own greed, hate, and delusion, and encourages others to remove theirs.*";
P_HTM[2516]="*attanā ca dosavinayāya paṭipanno hoti, parañca dosavinayāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[2517]="*attanā ca mohavinayāya paṭipanno hoti, parañca mohavinayāya samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[2518]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya ceva paṭipanno hoti parahitāya ca.**That’s how a person practices to benefit both themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[2519]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2520]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2521]="*7. Khippanisantisuttaṃ**Quick*";
P_HTM[2522]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2523]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2524]="*Attahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, parahitāya paṭipanno no attahitāya, nevattahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, attahitāya ceva paṭipanno parahitāya ca.**~One who practices to benefit themselves, but not others; ~one who practices to benefit others, but not themselves; ~one who practices to benefit neither themselves nor others; and ~one who practices to benefit both themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[2525]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya?**And how does a person practice to benefit themselves, but not others?*";
P_HTM[2526]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo khippanisantī ca hoti kusalesu dhammesu, sutānañca dhammānaṃ dhārakajātiko hoti, dhātānañca dhammānaṃ atthūpaparikkhī hoti atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya, dhammānudhammappaṭipanno hoti;**It’s when a person is quick-witted when it comes to skillful teachings. They readily memorize the teachings they’ve heard. They examine the meaning of teachings they’ve memorized. Understanding the meaning and the teaching, they practice accordingly.*";
P_HTM[2527]="*no ca kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā, no ca sandassako hoti samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**But they’re not a good speaker. Their voice isn’t polished, clear, articulate, and doesn’t express the meaning. They don’t educate, encourage, fire up, and inspire their spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[2528]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya.**That’s how a person practices to benefit themselves, but not others.*";
P_HTM[2529]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo parahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no attahitāya?**And how does a person practice to benefit others, but not themselves?*";
P_HTM[2530]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na heva kho khippanisantī hoti kusalesu dhammesu, no ca sutānaṃ dhammānaṃ dhārakajātiko hoti, no ca dhātānaṃ dhammānaṃ atthūpaparikkhī hoti, no ca atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammappaṭipanno hoti;**It’s when a person is not quick-witted when it comes to skillful teachings. …*";
P_HTM[2531]="*kalyāṇavāco ca hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā, sandassako ca hoti samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**But they’re a good speaker. …*";
P_HTM[2532]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo parahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no attahitāya.**That’s how a person practices to benefit others, but not themselves.*";
P_HTM[2533]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo nevattahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya?**And how does a person practice to benefit neither themselves nor others?*";
P_HTM[2534]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na heva kho khippanisantī hoti kusalesu dhammesu, no ca sutānaṃ dhammānaṃ dhārakajātiko hoti, no ca dhātānaṃ dhammānaṃ atthūpaparikkhī hoti, no ca atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammappaṭipanno hoti;**It’s when a person is not quick-witted when it comes to skillful teachings. …*";
P_HTM[2535]="*no ca kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā, no ca sandassako hoti samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**Nor are they a good speaker. …*";
P_HTM[2536]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo nevattahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya.**That’s how a person practices to benefit neither themselves nor others.*";
P_HTM[2537]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya ceva paṭipanno hoti parahitāya ca?**And how does a person practice to benefit both themselves and others?*";
P_HTM[2538]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo khippanisantī ca hoti kusalesu dhammesu, sutānañca dhammānaṃ dhārakajātiko hoti, dhātānañca dhammānaṃ atthūpaparikkhī hoti atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya, dhammānudhammappaṭipanno hoti;**It’s when a person is quick-witted when it comes to skillful teachings. …*";
P_HTM[2539]="*kalyāṇavāco ca hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā, sandassako ca hoti samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**And they’re a good speaker. …*";
P_HTM[2540]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya ceva paṭipanno hoti parahitāya ca.**That’s how a person practices to benefit both themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[2541]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2542]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2543]="*8. Attahitasuttaṃ**To Benefit Oneself*";
P_HTM[2544]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2545]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2546]="*Attahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, parahitāya paṭipanno no attahitāya, nevattahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, attahitāya ceva paṭipanno parahitāya ca.**~One who practices to benefit themselves, but not others; ~one who practices to benefit others, but not themselves; ~one who practices to benefit neither themselves nor others; and ~one who practices to benefit both themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[2547]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2548]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2549]="*9. Sikkhāpadasuttaṃ**Training Rules*";
P_HTM[2550]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2551]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2552]="*Attahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, parahitāya paṭipanno no attahitāya, nevattahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, attahitāya ceva paṭipanno parahitāya ca.**~One who practices to benefit themselves, but not others; ~one who practices to benefit others, but not themselves; ~one who practices to benefit neither themselves nor others; and ~one who practices to benefit both themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[2553]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya?**And how does a person practice to benefit themselves, but not others?*";
P_HTM[2554]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo attanā pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, no paraṃ pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;**It’s when a person doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. But they don’t encourage others to do the same.*";
P_HTM[2555]="*attanā adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, no paraṃ adinnādānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[2556]="*attanā kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, no paraṃ kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[2557]="*attanā musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, no paraṃ musāvādā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[2558]="*attanā surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti, no paraṃ surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[2559]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya.**That’s how a person practices to benefit themselves, but not others.*";
P_HTM[2560]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo parahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no attahitāya?**And how does a person practice to benefit others, but not themselves?*";
P_HTM[2561]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo attanā pāṇātipātā appaṭivirato hoti, paraṃ pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;**It’s when a person kills living creatures, steals, commits sexual misconduct, lies, and uses alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. But they encourage others to not do these things.*";
P_HTM[2562]="*attanā adinnādānā appaṭivirato hoti, paraṃ adinnādānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[2563]="*attanā kāmesumicchācārā appaṭivirato hoti, paraṃ kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[2564]="*attanā musāvādā appaṭivirato hoti, paraṃ musāvādā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[2565]="*attanā surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā appaṭivirato hoti, paraṃ surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[2566]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo parahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no attahitāya.**That’s how a person practices to benefit others, but not themselves.*";
P_HTM[2567]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo nevattahitāya paṭipanno hoti no parahitāya?**And how does a person practice to benefit neither themselves nor others?*";
P_HTM[2568]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo attanā pāṇātipātā appaṭivirato hoti, no paraṃ pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti … pe … attanā surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā appaṭivirato hoti, no paraṃ surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti.**It’s when a person kills, etc. … and doesn’t encourage others to not do these things.*";
P_HTM[2569]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo nevattahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya.**That’s how a person practices to benefit neither themselves nor others.*";
P_HTM[2570]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya ceva paṭipanno hoti parahitāya ca?**And how does a person practice to benefit both themselves and others?*";
P_HTM[2571]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo attanā ca pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, parañca pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti … pe … attanā ca surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti, parañca surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti.**It’s when a person doesn’t kill, etc. … and encourages others to do the same.*";
P_HTM[2572]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya ceva paṭipanno hoti parahitāya ca.**That’s how a person practices to benefit both themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[2573]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2574]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2575]="*10. Potaliyasuttaṃ**With Potaliya the Wanderer*";
P_HTM[2576]="*Atha kho potaliyo paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the wanderer Potaliya went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[2577]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho potaliyaṃ paribbājakaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side, and the Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[2578]="*“Cattārome, potaliya, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Potaliya, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2579]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2580]="*Idha, potaliya, ekacco puggalo avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena, no ca kho vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena.**One person criticizes those deserving of criticism at the right time, truthfully and substantively. But they don’t praise those deserving of praise at the right time, truthfully and substantively.*";
P_HTM[2581]="*Idha pana, potaliya, ekacco puggalo vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena, no ca kho avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena.**Another person praises those deserving of praise … But they don’t criticize those deserving of criticism …*";
P_HTM[2582]="*Idha pana, potaliya, ekacco puggalo neva avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena, no ca vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena.**Another person doesn’t praise those deserving of praise … Nor do they criticize those deserving of criticism …*";
P_HTM[2583]="*Idha pana, potaliya, ekacco puggalo avaṇṇārahassa ca avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena, vaṇṇārahassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena.**Another person criticizes those deserving of criticism at the right time, truthfully and substantively. And they praise those deserving of praise at the right time, truthfully and substantively.*";
P_HTM[2584]="*Ime kho, potaliya, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**These are the four people found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2585]="*Imesaṃ kho, potaliya, catunnaṃ puggalānaṃ katamo te puggalo khamati abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Of these four people, who do you believe to be the finest?”*";
P_HTM[2586]="*“Cattārome, bho gotama, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2587]="*Katame cattāro?* **";
P_HTM[2588]="*Idha, bho gotama, ekacco puggalo avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena, no ca kho vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena.* **";
P_HTM[2589]="*Idha pana, bho gotama, ekacco puggalo vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena, no ca kho avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena.* **";
P_HTM[2590]="*Idha pana, bho gotama, ekacco puggalo neva avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena, no ca vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena.* **";
P_HTM[2591]="*Idha pana, bho gotama, ekacco puggalo avaṇṇārahassa ca avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena, vaṇṇārahassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena.* **";
P_HTM[2592]="*Ime kho, bho gotama, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2593]="*Imesaṃ, bho gotama, catunnaṃ puggalānaṃ yvāyaṃ puggalo neva avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena, no ca vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena;**“Master Gotama, of these four people, it is the person who neither praises those deserving of praise at the right time, truthfully and substantively; nor criticizes those deserving of criticism at the right time, truthfully and substantively.*";
P_HTM[2594]="*ayaṃ me puggalo khamati imesaṃ catunnaṃ puggalānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro ca.**That is the person I believe to be the finest.*";
P_HTM[2595]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2596]="*Abhikkantā hesā, bho gotama, yadidaṃ upekkhā”ti.**Because, Master Gotama, equanimity is the best.”*";
P_HTM[2597]="*“Cattārome, potaliya, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2598]="*Katame cattāro … pe … ime kho, potaliya, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2599]="*Imesaṃ kho, potaliya, catunnaṃ puggalānaṃ yvāyaṃ puggalo avaṇṇārahassa ca avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena, vaṇṇārahassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena;**“Potaliya, of these four people, it is the person who criticizes those deserving of criticism at the right time, truthfully and substantively; and praises those deserving of praise at the right time, truthfully and substantively.*";
P_HTM[2600]="*ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ puggalānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro ca.**That is the person I consider to be the finest.*";
P_HTM[2601]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2602]="*Abhikkantā hesā, potaliya, yadidaṃ tattha tattha kālaññutā”ti.**Because, Potaliya, understanding of time and context is the best.”*";
P_HTM[2603]="*“Cattārome, bho gotama, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2604]="*Katame cattāro … pe … ime kho, bho gotama, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2605]="*Imesaṃ, bho gotama, catunnaṃ puggalānaṃ yvāyaṃ puggalo avaṇṇārahassa ca avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena, vaṇṇārahassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena;**“Master Gotama, of these four people, it is the person who criticizes those deserving of criticism at the right time, truthfully and substantively; and praises those deserving of praise at the right time, truthfully and substantively.*";
P_HTM[2606]="*ayaṃ me puggalo khamati imesaṃ catunnaṃ puggalānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro ca.**That is the person I believe to be the finest.*";
P_HTM[2607]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2608]="*Abhikkantā hesā, bho gotama, yadidaṃ tattha tattha kālaññutā.**Because, Master Gotama, understanding of time and context is the best.*";
P_HTM[2609]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama.**Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[2610]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[2611]="*Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[2612]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[2613]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2614]="*Asuravaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[2615]="*Asuro tayo samādhī,* **";
P_HTM[2616]="*chavālātena pañcamaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2617]="*Rāgo nisanti attahitaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2618]="*sikkhā potaliyena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[2619]="*Dutiyo paṇṇāsako samatto.* **";
P_HTM[2620]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Clouds*";
P_HTM[2621]="*1. Paṭhamavalāhakasuttaṃ**Clouds (1st)*";
P_HTM[2622]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2623]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[2624]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[2625]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[2626]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2627]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[2628]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, valāhakā.**“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of clouds.*";
P_HTM[2629]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2630]="*Gajjitā no vassitā, vassitā no gajjitā, neva gajjitā no vassitā, gajjitā ca vassitā ca.**~One thunders but doesn’t rain, ~one rains but doesn’t thunder, ~one neither thunders nor rains, and ~one both rains and thunders.*";
P_HTM[2631]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro valāhakā.**These are the four kinds of clouds.*";
P_HTM[2632]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro valāhakūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**In the same way, these four people similar to clouds are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2633]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2634]="*Gajjitā no vassitā, vassitā no gajjitā, neva gajjitā no vassitā, gajjitā ca vassitā ca.**~One thunders but doesn’t rain, ~one rains but doesn’t thunder, ~one neither thunders nor rains, and ~one both rains and thunders.*";
P_HTM[2635]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo gajjitā hoti no vassitā?**And how does a person thunder but not rain?*";
P_HTM[2636]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo bhāsitā hoti, no kattā.**It’s when a person is a talker, not a doer.*";
P_HTM[2637]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo gajjitā hoti, no vassitā.**That’s how a person thunders but doesn’t rain.*";
P_HTM[2638]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, valāhako gajjitā, no vassitā;**That person is like a cloud that thunders but doesn’t rain, I say.*";
P_HTM[2639]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2640]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo vassitā hoti, no gajjitā?**And how does a person rain but not thunder?*";
P_HTM[2641]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo kattā hoti, no bhāsitā.**It’s when a person is a doer, not a talker. …*";
P_HTM[2642]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo vassitā hoti, no gajjitā.* **";
P_HTM[2643]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, valāhako vassitā, no gajjitā;* **";
P_HTM[2644]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2645]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo neva gajjitā hoti, no vassitā?**And how does a person neither thunder nor rain?*";
P_HTM[2646]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo neva bhāsitā hoti, no kattā.**It’s when a person is neither a talker nor a doer. …*";
P_HTM[2647]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo neva gajjitā hoti, no vassitā.* **";
P_HTM[2648]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, valāhako neva gajjitā, no vassitā;* **";
P_HTM[2649]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2650]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo gajjitā ca hoti vassitā ca?**And how does a person both thunder and rain?*";
P_HTM[2651]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo bhāsitā ca hoti kattā ca.**It’s when a person is both a talker and a doer. …*";
P_HTM[2652]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo gajjitā ca hoti vassitā ca.* **";
P_HTM[2653]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, valāhako gajjitā ca vassitā ca;* **";
P_HTM[2654]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2655]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro valāhakūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These four people similar to clouds are found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2656]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2657]="*2. Dutiyavalāhakasuttaṃ**Clouds (2nd)*";
P_HTM[2658]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, valāhakā.**“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of clouds.*";
P_HTM[2659]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2660]="*Gajjitā no vassitā, vassitā no gajjitā, neva gajjitā no vassitā gajjitā ca vassitā ca.**~One thunders but doesn’t rain, ~one rains but doesn’t thunder, ~one neither thunders nor rains, and ~one both rains and thunders.*";
P_HTM[2661]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro valāhakā.**These are the four kinds of clouds.*";
P_HTM[2662]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro valāhakūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**In the same way, these four people similar to clouds are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2663]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2664]="*Gajjitā no vassitā, vassitā no gajjitā, neva gajjitā no vassitā, gajjitā ca vassitā ca.**~One thunders but doesn’t rain, ~one rains but doesn’t thunder, ~one neither thunders nor rains, and ~one both rains and thunders.*";
P_HTM[2665]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo gajjitā hoti, no vassitā?**And how does a person thunder but not rain?*";
P_HTM[2666]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—**It’s when a person memorizes the teaching—*";
P_HTM[2667]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.**statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications.*";
P_HTM[2668]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**But they don’t truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[2669]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo gajjitā hoti, no vassitā.**That’s how a person thunders but doesn’t rain.*";
P_HTM[2670]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, valāhako gajjitā, no vassitā;**That person is like a cloud that thunders but doesn’t rain, I say.*";
P_HTM[2671]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2672]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo vassitā hoti, no gajjitā?**And how does a person rain but not thunder?*";
P_HTM[2673]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dhammaṃ na pariyāpuṇāti—**It’s when a person doesn’t memorize the teaching …*";
P_HTM[2674]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2675]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**But they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2676]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo vassitā hoti, no gajjitā.* **";
P_HTM[2677]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, valāhako vassitā, no gajjitā;* **";
P_HTM[2678]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2679]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo neva gajjitā hoti, no vassitā?**And how does a person neither thunder nor rain?*";
P_HTM[2680]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo neva dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—**It’s when a person doesn’t memorize the teaching …*";
P_HTM[2681]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2682]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**Nor do they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2683]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo neva gajjitā hoti, no vassitā.* **";
P_HTM[2684]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, valāhako neva gajjitā, no vassitā;* **";
P_HTM[2685]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2686]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo gajjitā ca hoti vassitā ca?**And how does a person both thunder and rain?*";
P_HTM[2687]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—**It’s when a person memorizes the teaching …*";
P_HTM[2688]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2689]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**And they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2690]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo gajjitā ca hoti vassitā ca.* **";
P_HTM[2691]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, valāhako gajjitā ca vassitā ca;* **";
P_HTM[2692]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2693]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro valāhakūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These four people similar to clouds are found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2694]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2695]="*3. Kumbhasuttaṃ**Pots*";
P_HTM[2696]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, kumbhā.**“Mendicants, there are these four pots.*";
P_HTM[2697]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2698]="*Tuccho pihito, pūro vivaṭo, tuccho vivaṭo, pūro pihito—**~Covered but hollow, ~uncovered but full, ~uncovered and hollow, and ~covered and full.*";
P_HTM[2699]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro kumbhā.**These are the four pots.*";
P_HTM[2700]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro kumbhūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**In the same way, these four people similar to pots are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2701]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2702]="*Tuccho pihito, pūro vivaṭo, tuccho vivaṭo, pūro pihito.**~Covered but hollow, ~uncovered but full, ~uncovered and hollow, and ~covered and full.*";
P_HTM[2703]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo tuccho hoti pihito?**And how is a person covered but hollow?*";
P_HTM[2704]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ.**It’s when a person is impressive when going out and coming back, when looking ahead and aside, when bending and extending the limbs, and when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes.*";
P_HTM[2705]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**But they don’t truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[2706]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo tuccho hoti pihito.**That’s how a person is covered but hollow.*";
P_HTM[2707]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, kumbho tuccho pihito;**That person is like a pot that’s covered but hollow, I say.*";
P_HTM[2708]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2709]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo pūro hoti vivaṭo?**And how is a person uncovered but full?*";
P_HTM[2710]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa na pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ.**It’s when a person is not impressive …*";
P_HTM[2711]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**But they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2712]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo pūro hoti vivaṭo.* **";
P_HTM[2713]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, kumbho pūro vivaṭo;* **";
P_HTM[2714]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2715]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo tuccho hoti vivaṭo?**And how is a person uncovered and hollow?*";
P_HTM[2716]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa na pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ.**It’s when a person is not impressive …*";
P_HTM[2717]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**Nor do they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2718]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo tuccho hoti vivaṭo.* **";
P_HTM[2719]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, kumbho tuccho vivaṭo;* **";
P_HTM[2720]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2721]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo pūro hoti pihito?**And how is a person covered and full?*";
P_HTM[2722]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ.**It’s when a person is impressive …*";
P_HTM[2723]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**And they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2724]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo pūro hoti pihito.* **";
P_HTM[2725]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, kumbho pūro pihito;* **";
P_HTM[2726]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2727]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro kumbhūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These four people similar to pots are found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2728]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2729]="*4. Udakarahadasuttaṃ**Lakes*";
P_HTM[2730]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, udakarahadā.**“Mendicants, there are these four lakes.*";
P_HTM[2731]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2732]="*Uttāno gambhīrobhāso, gambhīro uttānobhāso, uttāno uttānobhāso, gambhīro gambhīrobhāso—**~One is shallow but appears deep, ~one is deep but appears shallow, ~one is shallow and appears shallow, and ~one is deep and appears deep.*";
P_HTM[2733]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro udakarahadā.**These are the four lakes.*";
P_HTM[2734]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro udakarahadūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**In the same way, these four people similar to lakes are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2735]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2736]="*Uttāno gambhīrobhāso, gambhīro uttānobhāso, uttāno uttānobhāso, gambhīro gambhīrobhāso.**~One is shallow but appears deep, ~one is deep but appears shallow, ~one is shallow and appears shallow, and ~one is deep and appears deep.*";
P_HTM[2737]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo uttāno hoti gambhīrobhāso?**And how is a person shallow but appears deep?*";
P_HTM[2738]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ.**It’s when a person is impressive when going out and coming back, when looking ahead and aside, when bending and extending the limbs, and when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes.*";
P_HTM[2739]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**But they don’t really understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[2740]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo uttāno hoti gambhīrobhāso.**That’s how a person is shallow but appears deep.*";
P_HTM[2741]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, udakarahado uttāno gambhīrobhāso;**That person is like a lake that’s shallow but appears deep, I say.*";
P_HTM[2742]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2743]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo gambhīro hoti uttānobhāso?**And how is a person deep but appears shallow?*";
P_HTM[2744]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa na pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ.**It’s when a person is not impressive …*";
P_HTM[2745]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**But they really understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2746]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo gambhīro hoti uttānobhāso.* **";
P_HTM[2747]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, udakarahado gambhīro uttānobhāso;* **";
P_HTM[2748]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2749]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo uttāno hoti uttānobhāso?**And how is a person shallow and appears shallow?*";
P_HTM[2750]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa na pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ.**It’s when a person is not impressive …*";
P_HTM[2751]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**Nor do they really understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2752]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo uttāno hoti uttānobhāso.* **";
P_HTM[2753]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, udakarahado uttāno uttānobhāso;* **";
P_HTM[2754]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2755]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo gambhīro hoti gambhīrobhāso?**And how is a person deep and appears deep?*";
P_HTM[2756]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ.**It’s when a person is impressive …*";
P_HTM[2757]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**And they really understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2758]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo gambhīro hoti gambhīrobhāso.* **";
P_HTM[2759]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, udakarahado gambhīro gambhīrobhāso;* **";
P_HTM[2760]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2761]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro udakarahadūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These four people similar to lakes are found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2762]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2763]="*5. Ambasuttaṃ**Mangoes*";
P_HTM[2764]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, ambāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four mangoes.*";
P_HTM[2765]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2766]="*Āmaṃ pakkavaṇṇi, pakkaṃ āmavaṇṇi, āmaṃ āmavaṇṇi, pakkaṃ pakkavaṇṇi—**~One is unripe but seems ripe, ~one is ripe but seems unripe, ~one is unripe and seems unripe, and ~one is ripe and seems ripe.*";
P_HTM[2767]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri ambāni.**These are the four mangoes.*";
P_HTM[2768]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro ambūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**In the same way, these four people similar to mangoes are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2769]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2770]="*Āmo pakkavaṇṇī, pakko āmavaṇṇī, āmo āmavaṇṇī, pakko pakkavaṇṇī.**~One is unripe but seems ripe, ~one is ripe but seems unripe, ~one is unripe and seems unripe, and ~one is ripe and seems ripe.*";
P_HTM[2771]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo āmo hoti pakkavaṇṇī?**And how is a person unripe but seems ripe?*";
P_HTM[2772]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ.**It’s when a person is impressive when going out and coming back, when looking ahead and aside, when bending and extending the limbs, and when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes.*";
P_HTM[2773]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**But they don’t really understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[2774]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo āmo hoti pakkavaṇṇī.**That’s how a person is unripe but seems ripe.*";
P_HTM[2775]="*Seyyathāpi taṃ, bhikkhave, ambaṃ āmaṃ pakkavaṇṇi;**That person is like a mango that’s unripe but seems ripe, I say.*";
P_HTM[2776]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2777]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo pakko hoti āmavaṇṇī?**And how is a person ripe but seems unripe?*";
P_HTM[2778]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa na pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ.**It’s when a person is not impressive …*";
P_HTM[2779]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**But they really understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2780]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo pakko hoti āmavaṇṇī.* **";
P_HTM[2781]="*Seyyathāpi taṃ, bhikkhave, ambaṃ pakkaṃ āmavaṇṇi;* **";
P_HTM[2782]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2783]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo āmo hoti āmavaṇṇī?**And how is a person unripe and seems unripe?*";
P_HTM[2784]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa na pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ.**It’s when a person is not impressive …*";
P_HTM[2785]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**Nor do they really understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2786]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo āmo hoti āmavaṇṇī.* **";
P_HTM[2787]="*Seyyathāpi taṃ, bhikkhave, ambaṃ āmaṃ āmavaṇṇi;* **";
P_HTM[2788]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2789]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo pakko hoti pakkavaṇṇī?**And how is a person ripe and seems ripe?*";
P_HTM[2790]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ.**It’s when a person is impressive …*";
P_HTM[2791]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**And they really understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2792]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo pakko hoti pakkavaṇṇī.* **";
P_HTM[2793]="*Seyyathāpi taṃ, bhikkhave, ambaṃ pakkaṃ pakkavaṇṇi;* **";
P_HTM[2794]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2795]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro ambūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These four people similar to mangoes are found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2796]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2797]="*6. Dutiyaambasuttaṃ**Mice*";
P_HTM[2798]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, mūsikā.**“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of mice.*";
P_HTM[2799]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2800]="*Gādhaṃ kattā no vasitā, vasitā no gādhaṃ kattā, neva gādhaṃ kattā no vasitā, gādhaṃ kattā ca vasitā ca—**~One makes a hole but doesn’t live in it, ~one lives in a hole but doesn’t make it, ~one neither makes a hole nor lives in it, and ~one both makes a hole and lives in it.*";
P_HTM[2801]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso mūsikā.**These are the four kinds of mice.*";
P_HTM[2802]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro mūsikūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**In the same way, these four people similar to mice are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2803]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2804]="*Gādhaṃ kattā no vasitā, vasitā no gādhaṃ kattā, neva gādhaṃ kattā no vasitā, gādhaṃ kattā ca vasitā ca.**~One makes a hole but doesn’t live in it, ~one lives in a hole but doesn’t make it, ~one neither makes a hole nor lives in it, and ~one both makes a hole and lives in it.*";
P_HTM[2805]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo gādhaṃ kattā hoti no vasitā?**And how does a person make a hole but not live in it?*";
P_HTM[2806]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—**It’s when a person memorizes the teaching—*";
P_HTM[2807]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.**statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications.*";
P_HTM[2808]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**But they don’t really understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[2809]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo gādhaṃ kattā hoti, no vasitā.**That’s how a person makes a hole but doesn’t live in it.*";
P_HTM[2810]="*Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, mūsikā gādhaṃ kattā, no vasitā;**That person is like a mouse that makes a hole but doesn’t live in it, I say.*";
P_HTM[2811]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2812]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo vasitā hoti, no gādhaṃ kattā?**And how does a person live in a hole but not make it?*";
P_HTM[2813]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dhammaṃ na pariyāpuṇāti—**It’s when a person doesn’t memorize the teaching …*";
P_HTM[2814]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2815]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**But they really understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2816]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo vasitā hoti, no gādhaṃ kattā.* **";
P_HTM[2817]="*Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, mūsikā vasitā hoti, no gādhaṃ kattā;* **";
P_HTM[2818]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ, puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2819]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo neva gādhaṃ kattā hoti no vasitā?**And how does a person neither make a hole nor live in it?*";
P_HTM[2820]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dhammaṃ na pariyāpuṇāti—**It’s when a person doesn’t memorize the teaching …*";
P_HTM[2821]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2822]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**Nor do they really understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2823]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo neva gādhaṃ kattā hoti, no vasitā.* **";
P_HTM[2824]="*Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, mūsikā neva gādhaṃ kattā hoti, no vasitā;* **";
P_HTM[2825]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2826]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo gādhaṃ kattā ca hoti vasitā ca?**And how does a person both make a hole and live in it?*";
P_HTM[2827]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—**It’s when a person memorizes the teaching …*";
P_HTM[2828]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2829]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**And they really understand: ‘This is suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[2830]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo gādhaṃ kattā ca hoti vasitā ca.* **";
P_HTM[2831]="*Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, mūsikā gādhaṃ kattā ca hoti vasitā ca;* **";
P_HTM[2832]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2833]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro mūsikūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These four people similar to mice are found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2834]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2835]="*7. Mūsikasuttaṃ**Oxen*";
P_HTM[2836]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, balībaddā.**“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of oxen.*";
P_HTM[2837]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2838]="*Sagavacaṇḍo no paragavacaṇḍo, paragavacaṇḍo no sagavacaṇḍo, sagavacaṇḍo ca paragavacaṇḍo ca, neva sagavacaṇḍo no paragavacaṇḍo—**~One hostile to its own herd, not others; ~one hostile to other herds, not its own; ~one hostile to both its own herd and others; and ~one hostile to neither its own herd nor others.*";
P_HTM[2839]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro balībaddā.**These are the four kinds of oxen.*";
P_HTM[2840]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro balībaddūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**In the same way, these four people similar to oxen are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2841]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2842]="*Sagavacaṇḍo no paragavacaṇḍo, paragavacaṇḍo no sagavacaṇḍo, sagavacaṇḍo ca paragavacaṇḍo ca, neva sagavacaṇḍo no paragavacaṇḍo.**~One hostile to their own herd, not others; ~one hostile to other herds, not their own; ~one hostile to both their own herd and others; and ~one hostile to neither their own herd nor others.*";
P_HTM[2843]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo sagavacaṇḍo hoti, no paragavacaṇḍo?**And how is a person hostile to their own herd, not others?*";
P_HTM[2844]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sakaparisaṃ ubbejetā hoti, no paraparisaṃ.**It’s when a person intimidates their own followers, not the followers of others.*";
P_HTM[2845]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo sagavacaṇḍo hoti, no paragavacaṇḍo.**That’s how a person is hostile to their own herd, not others.*";
P_HTM[2846]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, balībaddo sagavacaṇḍo, no paragavacaṇḍo;**That person is like an ox that’s hostile to its own herd, not others.*";
P_HTM[2847]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2848]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo paragavacaṇḍo hoti, no sagavacaṇḍo?**And how is a person hostile to other herds, not their own?*";
P_HTM[2849]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo paraparisaṃ ubbejetā hoti, no sakaparisaṃ.**It’s when a person intimidates the followers of others, not their own. …*";
P_HTM[2850]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo paragavacaṇḍo hoti, no sagavacaṇḍo.* **";
P_HTM[2851]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, balībaddo paragavacaṇḍo, no sagavacaṇḍo;* **";
P_HTM[2852]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2853]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo sagavacaṇḍo ca hoti paragavacaṇḍo ca?**And how is a person hostile to both their own herd and others?*";
P_HTM[2854]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sakaparisaṃ ubbejetā hoti paraparisañca.**It’s when a person intimidates their own followers and the followers of others. …*";
P_HTM[2855]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo sagavacaṇḍo ca hoti paragavacaṇḍo ca.* **";
P_HTM[2856]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, balībaddo sagavacaṇḍo ca paragavacaṇḍo ca;* **";
P_HTM[2857]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2858]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo neva sagavacaṇḍo hoti no paragavacaṇḍo?**And how is a person hostile to neither their own herd nor others?*";
P_HTM[2859]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo neva sakaparisaṃ ubbejetā hoti, no paraparisañca.**It’s when a person doesn’t intimidate their own followers or the followers of others.*";
P_HTM[2860]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo neva sagavacaṇḍo hoti, no paragavacaṇḍo.* **";
P_HTM[2861]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, balībaddo neva sagavacaṇḍo, no paragavacaṇḍo;* **";
P_HTM[2862]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2863]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro balībaddūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These four people similar to oxen are found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2864]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2865]="*8. Balībaddasuttaṃ**Trees*";
P_HTM[2866]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, rukkhā.**“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of tree.*";
P_HTM[2867]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2868]="*Pheggu phegguparivāro, pheggu sāraparivāro, sāro phegguparivāro, sāro sāraparivāro—**~One is a softwood surrounded by softwoods, ~one is a softwood surrounded by hardwoods, ~one is a hardwood surrounded by softwoods, and ~one is a hardwood surrounded by hardwoods.*";
P_HTM[2869]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro rukkhā.**These are the four kinds of tree.*";
P_HTM[2870]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro rukkhūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**In the same way, these four people similar to trees are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2871]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2872]="*Pheggu phegguparivāro, pheggu sāraparivāro, sāro phegguparivāro, sāro sāraparivāro.**~One is a softwood surrounded by softwoods, ~one is a softwood surrounded by hardwoods, ~one is a hardwood surrounded by softwoods, and ~one is a hardwood surrounded by hardwoods.*";
P_HTM[2873]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo pheggu hoti phegguparivāro?**And how is a person a softwood surrounded by softwoods?*";
P_HTM[2874]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dussīlo hoti pāpadhammo;**It’s when a person is unethical, of bad character,*";
P_HTM[2875]="*parisāpissa hoti dussīlā pāpadhammā.**and their followers are the same.*";
P_HTM[2876]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo pheggu hoti phegguparivāro.**That’s how a person is a softwood surrounded by softwoods.*";
P_HTM[2877]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, rukkho pheggu phegguparivāro;**That person is like a softwood tree that’s surrounded by softwoods, I say.*";
P_HTM[2878]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2879]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo pheggu hoti sāraparivāro?**And how is a person a softwood surrounded by hardwoods?*";
P_HTM[2880]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dussīlo hoti pāpadhammo;**It’s when a person is unethical, of bad character,*";
P_HTM[2881]="*parisā ca khvassa hoti sīlavatī kalyāṇadhammā.**but their followers are ethical, of good character. …*";
P_HTM[2882]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo pheggu hoti sāraparivāro.* **";
P_HTM[2883]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, rukkho pheggu sāraparivāro;* **";
P_HTM[2884]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2885]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo sāro hoti phegguparivāro?**And how is a person a hardwood surrounded by softwoods?*";
P_HTM[2886]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sīlavā hoti kalyāṇadhammo;**It’s when someone is ethical, of good qualities.*";
P_HTM[2887]="*parisā ca khvassa hoti dussīlā pāpadhammā.**but their followers are unethical, of bad character. …*";
P_HTM[2888]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo sāro hoti phegguparivāro.* **";
P_HTM[2889]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, rukkho sāro phegguparivāro;* **";
P_HTM[2890]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2891]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo sāro hoti sāraparivāro?**And how is a person a hardwood surrounded by hardwoods?*";
P_HTM[2892]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sīlavā hoti kalyāṇadhammo;**It’s when someone is ethical, of good qualities,*";
P_HTM[2893]="*parisāpissa hoti sīlavatī kalyāṇadhammā.**and their followers are the same.*";
P_HTM[2894]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo sāro hoti sāraparivāro.* **";
P_HTM[2895]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, rukkho sāro sāraparivāro;* **";
P_HTM[2896]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2897]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro rukkhūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These four people similar to trees are found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2898]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2899]="*9. Rukkhasuttaṃ**Vipers*";
P_HTM[2900]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, āsīvisā.**“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of viper.*";
P_HTM[2901]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2902]="*Āgataviso na ghoraviso, ghoraviso na āgataviso, āgataviso ca ghoraviso ca, nevāgataviso na ghoraviso—**~One whose venom is fast-acting but not lethal, ~one whose venom is lethal but not fast-acting, ~one whose venom is both fast-acting and lethal, and ~one whose venom is neither fast-acting nor lethal.*";
P_HTM[2903]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro āsīvisā.**These are the four kinds of viper.*";
P_HTM[2904]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro āsīvisūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**In the same way, these four people similar to vipers are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2905]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2906]="*Āgataviso na ghoraviso, ghoraviso na āgataviso, āgataviso ca ghoraviso ca, nevāgataviso na ghoraviso.**~One whose venom is fast-acting but not lethal, ~one whose venom is lethal but not fast-acting, ~one whose venom is both fast-acting and lethal, and ~one whose venom is neither fast-acting nor lethal.*";
P_HTM[2907]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo āgataviso hoti, na ghoraviso?**And how is a person’s venom fast-acting but not lethal?*";
P_HTM[2908]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo abhiṇhaṃ kujjhati.**It’s when a person is often angry,*";
P_HTM[2909]="*So ca khvassa kodho na dīgharattaṃ anuseti.**but their anger doesn’t linger long.*";
P_HTM[2910]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo āgataviso hoti, na ghoraviso.**That’s how a person’s venom is fast-acting but not lethal.*";
P_HTM[2911]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, āsīviso āgataviso, na ghoraviso;**That person is like a viper whose venom is fast-acting but not lethal.*";
P_HTM[2912]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2913]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo ghoraviso hoti, na āgataviso?**And how is a person’s venom lethal but not fast-acting?*";
P_HTM[2914]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na heva kho abhiṇhaṃ kujjhati.**It’s when a person is not often angry,*";
P_HTM[2915]="*So ca khvassa kodho dīgharattaṃ anuseti.**but their anger lingers for a long time.*";
P_HTM[2916]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo ghoraviso hoti, na āgataviso.* **";
P_HTM[2917]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, āsīviso ghoraviso, na āgataviso;* **";
P_HTM[2918]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2919]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo āgataviso ca hoti ghoraviso ca?**And how is a person’s venom both fast-acting and lethal?*";
P_HTM[2920]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo abhiṇhaṃ kujjhati.**It’s when a person is often angry,*";
P_HTM[2921]="*So ca khvassa kodho dīgharattaṃ anuseti.**and their anger lingers for a long time.*";
P_HTM[2922]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo āgataviso ca hoti ghoraviso ca.* **";
P_HTM[2923]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, āsīviso āgataviso ca ghoraviso ca;* **";
P_HTM[2924]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2925]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo nevāgataviso hoti na ghoraviso?**And how is a person’s venom neither fast-acting nor lethal?*";
P_HTM[2926]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na heva kho abhiṇhaṃ kujjhati.**It’s when a person is not often angry,*";
P_HTM[2927]="*So ca khvassa kodho na dīgharattaṃ anuseti.**and their anger doesn’t linger long.*";
P_HTM[2928]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo nevāgataviso hoti, na ghoraviso.* **";
P_HTM[2929]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, āsīviso nevāgataviso na ghoraviso;* **";
P_HTM[2930]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2931]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro āsīvisūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These four people similar to vipers are found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2932]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2933]="*Valāhakavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[2934]="*Dve valāhā kumbha udaka,* **";
P_HTM[2935]="*rahadā dve honti ambāni;* **";
P_HTM[2936]="*Mūsikā balībaddā rukkhā,* **";
P_HTM[2937]="*āsīvisena te dasāti.* **";
P_HTM[2938]="*10. Āsīvisasuttaṃ**With Kesi*";
P_HTM[2939]="*Atha kho kesi assadammasārathi yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho kesiṃ assadammasārathiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Kesi the horse trainer went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[2940]="*“tvaṃ khosi, kesi, paññāto assadammasārathīti.**“Kesi, you’re known as a horse trainer.*";
P_HTM[2941]="*Kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, kesi, assadammaṃ vinesī”ti?**Just how do you guide a horse in training?”*";
P_HTM[2942]="*“Ahaṃ kho, bhante, assadammaṃ saṇhenapi vinemi, pharusenapi vinemi, saṇhapharusenapi vinemī”ti.**“Sir, I guide a horse in training sometimes gently, sometimes harshly, and sometimes both gently and harshly.”*";
P_HTM[2943]="*“Sace te, kesi, assadammo saṇhena vinayaṃ na upeti, pharusena vinayaṃ na upeti, saṇhapharusena vinayaṃ na upeti, kinti naṃ karosī”ti?**“Kesi, what do you do with a horse in training that doesn’t follow these forms of training?”*";
P_HTM[2944]="*“Sace me, bhante, assadammo saṇhena vinayaṃ na upeti, pharusena vinayaṃ na upeti, saṇhapharusena vinayaṃ na upeti;* **";
P_HTM[2945]="*hanāmi naṃ, bhante.**“In that case, sir, I kill it.*";
P_HTM[2946]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2947]="*‘Mā me ācariyakulassa avaṇṇo ahosī’ti.**So that I don’t disgrace my profession.*";
P_HTM[2948]="*Bhagavā pana, bhante, anuttaro purisadammasārathi.**But sir, the Buddha is the supreme guide for those who wish to train.*";
P_HTM[2949]="*Kathaṃ pana, bhante, bhagavā purisadammaṃ vinetī”ti?**Just how do you guide a person in training?”*";
P_HTM[2950]="*“Ahaṃ kho, kesi, purisadammaṃ saṇhenapi vinemi, pharusenapi vinemi, saṇhapharusenapi vinemi.**“Kesi, I guide a person in training sometimes gently, sometimes harshly, and sometimes both gently and harshly.*";
P_HTM[2951]="*Tatridaṃ, kesi, saṇhasmiṃ—**The gentle way is this:*";
P_HTM[2952]="*iti kāyasucaritaṃ iti kāyasucaritassa vipāko, iti vacīsucaritaṃ iti vacīsucaritassa vipāko, iti manosucaritaṃ iti manosucaritassa vipāko, iti devā, iti manussāti.**‘This is good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind. This is the result of good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind. This is life as a god. This is life as a human.’*";
P_HTM[2953]="*Tatridaṃ, kesi, pharusasmiṃ—**The harsh way is this:*";
P_HTM[2954]="*iti kāyaduccaritaṃ iti kāyaduccaritassa vipāko, iti vacīduccaritaṃ iti vacīduccaritassa vipāko, iti manoduccaritaṃ iti manoduccaritassa vipāko, iti nirayo, iti tiracchānayoni, iti pettivisayoti.**‘This is bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind. This is the result of bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind. This is life in hell. This is life as an animal. This is life as a ghost.’*";
P_HTM[2955]="*Tatridaṃ, kesi, saṇhapharusasmiṃ—**The both gentle and harsh way is this:*";
P_HTM[2956]="*iti kāyasucaritaṃ iti kāyasucaritassa vipāko, iti kāyaduccaritaṃ iti kāyaduccaritassa vipāko, iti vacīsucaritaṃ iti vacīsucaritassa vipāko, iti vacīduccaritaṃ iti vacīduccaritassa vipāko, iti manosucaritaṃ iti manosucaritassa vipāko, iti manoduccaritaṃ iti manoduccaritassa vipāko, iti devā, iti manussā, iti nirayo, iti tiracchānayoni, iti pettivisayo”ti.**‘This is good conduct … this is bad conduct …’”*";
P_HTM[2957]="*“Sace te, bhante, purisadammo saṇhena vinayaṃ na upeti, pharusena vinayaṃ na upeti, saṇhapharusena vinayaṃ na upeti, kinti naṃ bhagavā karotī”ti?**“Sir, what do you do with a person in training who doesn’t follow these forms of training?”*";
P_HTM[2958]="*“Sace me, kesi, purisadammo saṇhena vinayaṃ na upeti, pharusena vinayaṃ na upeti, saṇhapharusena vinayaṃ na upeti, hanāmi naṃ, kesī”ti.**“In that case, Kesi, I kill them.”*";
P_HTM[2959]="*“Na kho, bhante, bhagavato pāṇātipāto kappati.**“Sir, it’s not appropriate for the Buddha to kill living creatures.*";
P_HTM[2960]="*Atha ca pana bhagavā evamāha:**And yet you say*";
P_HTM[2961]="*‘hanāmi naṃ, kesī’”ti.**you kill them.”*";
P_HTM[2962]="*“Saccaṃ, kesi.**“It’s true, Kesi,*";
P_HTM[2963]="*Na tathāgatassa pāṇātipāto kappati.**it’s not appropriate for a Realized One to kill living creatures.*";
P_HTM[2964]="*Api ca yo purisadammo saṇhena vinayaṃ na upeti, pharusena vinayaṃ na upeti, saṇhapharusena vinayaṃ na upeti, na taṃ tathāgato vattabbaṃ anusāsitabbaṃ maññati, nāpi viññū sabrahmacārī vattabbaṃ anusāsitabbaṃ maññanti.**But when a person in training doesn’t follow any of these forms of training, the Realized One doesn’t think they’re worth advising or instructing, and neither do their sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[2965]="*Vadho heso, kesi, ariyassa vinaye—**For it is death in the training of the noble one*";
P_HTM[2966]="*yaṃ na tathāgato vattabbaṃ anusāsitabbaṃ maññati, nāpi viññū sabrahmacārī vattabbaṃ anusāsitabbaṃ maññantī”ti.**when the Realized One doesn’t think they’re worth advising or instructing, and neither do their sensible spiritual companions.”*";
P_HTM[2967]="*“So hi nūna, bhante, suhato hoti—**“Well, they’re definitely dead*";
P_HTM[2968]="*yaṃ na tathāgato vattabbaṃ anusāsitabbaṃ maññati, nāpi viññū sabrahmacārī vattabbaṃ anusāsitabbaṃ maññantīti.**when the Realized One doesn’t think they’re worth advising or instructing, and neither do their sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[2969]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe … upāsakaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**Excellent, sir! … From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[2970]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2971]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**With Kesi*";
P_HTM[2972]="*1. Kesisuttaṃ**Speed*";
P_HTM[2973]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**“Mendicants, a fine royal thoroughbred with four factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[2974]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2975]="*Ajjavena, javena, khantiyā, soraccena—**Integrity, speed, patience, and sweetness.*";
P_HTM[2976]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti, rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**A fine royal thoroughbred with these four factors is worthy of a king. …*";
P_HTM[2977]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**In the same way, a mendicant with four factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[2978]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2979]="*Ajjavena, javena, khantiyā, soraccena—**Integrity, speed, patience, and sweetness.*";
P_HTM[2980]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti.**A mendicant with these four factors … is the supreme field of merit for the world.”*";
P_HTM[2981]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2982]="*2. Javasuttaṃ**The Goad*";
P_HTM[2983]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, bhadrā assājānīyā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four fine thoroughbreds are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2984]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2985]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco bhadro assājānīyo patodacchāyaṃ disvā saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati:**One fine thoroughbred is moved to act when it sees the shadow of the goad, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2986]="*‘kiṃ nu kho maṃ ajja assadammasārathi kāraṇaṃ kāressati, kimassāhaṃ paṭikaromī’ti.**‘What task will the horse trainer have me do today? How should I respond?’*";
P_HTM[2987]="*Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro assājānīyo hoti.**Some fine thoroughbreds are like that.*";
P_HTM[2988]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo bhadro assājānīyo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ.**This is the first fine thoroughbred found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2989]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro assājānīyo na heva kho patodacchāyaṃ disvā saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati, api ca kho lomavedhaviddho saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati:**Furthermore, one fine thoroughbred isn’t moved to act when it sees the shadow of the goad, but only when its hairs are struck, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2990]="*‘kiṃ nu kho maṃ ajja assadammasārathi kāraṇaṃ kāressati, kimassāhaṃ paṭikaromī’ti.**‘What task will the horse trainer have me do today? How should I respond?’*";
P_HTM[2991]="*Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro assājānīyo hoti.**Some fine thoroughbreds are like that.*";
P_HTM[2992]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo bhadro assājānīyo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ.**This is the second fine thoroughbred found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2993]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro assājānīyo na heva kho patodacchāyaṃ disvā saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati nāpi lomavedhaviddho saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati, api ca kho cammavedhaviddho saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati:**Furthermore, one fine thoroughbred isn’t moved to act when it sees the shadow of the goad, nor when its hairs are struck, but only when its hide is struck, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2994]="*‘kiṃ nu kho maṃ ajja assadammasārathi kāraṇaṃ kāressati, kimassāhaṃ paṭikaromī’ti.**‘What task will the horse trainer have me do today? How should I respond?’*";
P_HTM[2995]="*Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro assājānīyo hoti.**Some fine thoroughbreds are like that.*";
P_HTM[2996]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo bhadro assājānīyo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ.**This is the third fine thoroughbred found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2997]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro assājānīyo na heva kho patodacchāyaṃ disvā saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati nāpi lomavedhaviddho saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati nāpi cammavedhaviddho saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati, api ca kho aṭṭhivedhaviddho saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati:**Furthermore, one fine thoroughbred isn’t moved to act when it sees the shadow of the goad, nor when its hairs are struck, nor when its hide is struck, but only when its bone is struck, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2998]="*‘kiṃ nu kho maṃ ajja assadammasārathi kāraṇaṃ kāressati, kimassāhaṃ paṭikaromī’ti.**‘What task will the horse trainer have me do today? How should I respond?’*";
P_HTM[2999]="*Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro assājānīyo hoti.**Some fine thoroughbreds are like that.*";
P_HTM[3000]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho bhadro assājānīyo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ.**This is the fourth fine thoroughbred found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3001]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro bhadrā assājānīyā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**These are the four fine thoroughbreds found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3002]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattārome bhadrā purisājānīyā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**In the same way, these four fine thoroughbred people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3003]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3004]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco bhadro purisājānīyo suṇāti:**One fine thoroughbred person hears about*";
P_HTM[3005]="*‘amukasmiṃ nāma gāme vā nigame vā itthī vā puriso vā dukkhito vā kālaṅkato vā’ti.**the suffering or death of a woman or man in such and such village or town.*";
P_HTM[3006]="*So tena saṃvijjati, saṃvegaṃ āpajjati.**They’re moved to act by this,*";
P_HTM[3007]="*Saṃviggo yoniso padahati.**and strive effectively.*";
P_HTM[3008]="*Pahitatto kāyena ceva paramasaccaṃ sacchikaroti, paññāya ca ativijjha passati.**Applying themselves, they directly realize the ultimate truth, and see it with penetrating wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3009]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, bhadro assājānīyo patodacchāyaṃ disvā saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati;**This person is like the fine thoroughbred*";
P_HTM[3010]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ bhadraṃ purisājānīyaṃ vadāmi.**that’s shaken when it sees the shadow of the goad.*";
P_HTM[3011]="*Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro purisājānīyo hoti.**Some fine thoroughbred people are like that.*";
P_HTM[3012]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo bhadro purisājānīyo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ.**This is the first fine thoroughbred person found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3013]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro purisājānīyo na heva kho suṇāti:**Furthermore, one fine thoroughbred person doesn’t hear about*";
P_HTM[3014]="*‘amukasmiṃ nāma gāme vā nigame vā itthī vā puriso vā dukkhito vā kālaṅkato vā’ti, api ca kho sāmaṃ passati itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā dukkhitaṃ vā kālaṅkataṃ vā.**the suffering or death of a woman or man in such and such village or town, but they see it themselves.*";
P_HTM[3015]="*So tena saṃvijjati, saṃvegaṃ āpajjati.**They’re moved to act by this,*";
P_HTM[3016]="*Saṃviggo yoniso padahati.**and strive effectively.*";
P_HTM[3017]="*Pahitatto kāyena ceva paramasaccaṃ sacchikaroti, paññāya ca ativijjha passati.**Applying themselves, they directly realize the ultimate truth, and see it with penetrating wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3018]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, bhadro assājānīyo lomavedhaviddho saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati;**This person is like the fine thoroughbred that’s moved to act*";
P_HTM[3019]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ bhadraṃ purisājānīyaṃ vadāmi.**when its hairs are struck.*";
P_HTM[3020]="*Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro purisājānīyo hoti.**Some fine thoroughbred people are like that.*";
P_HTM[3021]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo bhadro purisājānīyo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ.**This is the second fine thoroughbred person found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3022]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro purisājānīyo na heva kho suṇāti:**Furthermore, one fine thoroughbred person doesn’t hear about*";
P_HTM[3023]="*‘amukasmiṃ nāma gāme vā nigame vā itthī vā puriso vā dukkhito vā kālaṅkato vā’ti, nāpi sāmaṃ passati itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā dukkhitaṃ vā kālaṅkataṃ vā, api ca khvassa ñāti vā sālohito vā dukkhito vā hoti kālaṅkato vā.**the suffering or death of a woman or man in such and such village or town, nor do they see it themselves, but it happens to their own relative or family member.*";
P_HTM[3024]="*So tena saṃvijjati, saṃvegaṃ āpajjati.**They’re moved to act by this,*";
P_HTM[3025]="*Saṃviggo yoniso padahati.**and strive effectively.*";
P_HTM[3026]="*Pahitatto kāyena ceva paramasaccaṃ sacchikaroti, paññāya ca ativijjha passati.**Applying themselves, they directly realize the ultimate truth, and see it with penetrating wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3027]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, bhadro assājānīyo cammavedhaviddho saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati;**This person is like the fine thoroughbred that’s moved to act*";
P_HTM[3028]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ bhadraṃ purisājānīyaṃ vadāmi.**when its skin is struck.*";
P_HTM[3029]="*Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro purisājānīyo hoti.**Some fine thoroughbred people are like that.*";
P_HTM[3030]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo bhadro purisājānīyo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ.**This is the third fine thoroughbred person found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3031]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro purisājānīyo na heva kho suṇāti:**Furthermore, one fine thoroughbred person doesn’t hear about*";
P_HTM[3032]="*‘amukasmiṃ nāma gāme vā nigame vā itthī vā puriso vā dukkhito vā kālaṅkato vā’ti, nāpi sāmaṃ passati itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā dukkhitaṃ vā kālaṅkataṃ vā, nāpissa ñāti vā sālohito vā dukkhito vā hoti kālaṅkato vā, api ca kho sāmaññeva phuṭṭho hoti sārīrikāhi vedanāhi dukkhāhi tibbāhi kharāhi kaṭukāhi asātāhi amanāpāhi pāṇaharāhi.**the suffering or death of a woman or man in such and such village or town, nor do they see it themselves, nor does it happen to their own relative or family member, but they themselves are afflicted with physical pain—sharp, severe, acute, unpleasant, disagreeable, and life-threatening.*";
P_HTM[3033]="*So tena saṃvijjati, saṃvegaṃ āpajjati.**They’re moved to act by this,*";
P_HTM[3034]="*Saṃviggo yoniso padahati.**and strive effectively.*";
P_HTM[3035]="*Pahitatto kāyena ceva paramasaccaṃ sacchikaroti, paññāya ca ativijjha passati.**Applying themselves, they directly realize the ultimate truth, and see it with penetrating wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3036]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, bhadro assājānīyo aṭṭhivedhaviddho saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati;**This person is like the fine thoroughbred that’s moved to act*";
P_HTM[3037]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ bhadraṃ purisājānīyaṃ vadāmi.**when its bone is struck.*";
P_HTM[3038]="*Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhadro purisājānīyo hoti.**Some fine thoroughbred people are like that.*";
P_HTM[3039]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho bhadro purisājānīyo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ.**This is the fourth fine thoroughbred person found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3040]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro bhadrā purisājānīyā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four fine thoroughbred people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3041]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3042]="*3. Patodasuttaṃ**A Royal Elephant*";
P_HTM[3043]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**“Mendicants, a royal bull elephant with four factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[3044]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3045]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo sotā ca hoti, hantā ca, khantā ca, gantā ca.**A royal bull elephant listens, destroys, endures, and goes fast.*";
P_HTM[3046]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo sotā hoti?**And how does a royal bull elephant listen?*";
P_HTM[3047]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo yamenaṃ hatthidammasārathi kāraṇaṃ kāreti—**It’s when a royal bull elephant pays heed, pays attention, engages wholeheartedly, and lends an ear to whatever task the elephant trainer has it do,*";
P_HTM[3048]="*yadi vā katapubbaṃ yadi vā akatapubbaṃ—**whether or not it has done it before.*";
P_HTM[3049]="*taṃ aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasoto suṇāti.* **";
P_HTM[3050]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo sotā hoti.**That’s how a royal bull elephant listens.*";
P_HTM[3051]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo hantā hoti?**And how does a royal bull elephant destroy?*";
P_HTM[3052]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato hatthimpi hanati, hatthāruhampi hanati, assampi hanati, assāruhampi hanati, rathampi hanati, rathikampi hanati, pattikampi hanati.**It’s when a royal bull elephant in battle destroys elephants with their riders, horses with their riders, chariots and charioteers, and foot soldiers.*";
P_HTM[3053]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo hantā hoti.**That’s how a royal bull elephant destroys.*";
P_HTM[3054]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khantā hoti?**And how does a royal bull elephant endure?*";
P_HTM[3055]="*Idha bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato khamo hoti sattippahārānaṃ asippahārānaṃ usuppahārānaṃ bheripaṇavasaṅkhatiṇavaninnādasaddānaṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant in battle endures being struck by spears, swords, arrows, and axes; it endures the thunder of the drums, kettledrums, horns, and cymbals.*";
P_HTM[3056]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khantā hoti.**That’s how a royal bull elephant endures.*";
P_HTM[3057]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo gantā hoti?**And how does a royal bull elephant go fast?*";
P_HTM[3058]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo yamenaṃ hatthidammasārathi disaṃ peseti—**It’s when a royal bull elephant swiftly goes in whatever direction the elephant trainer sends it,*";
P_HTM[3059]="*yadi vā gatapubbaṃ yadi vā agatapubbaṃ—**whether or not it has been there before.*";
P_HTM[3060]="*taṃ khippameva gantā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[3061]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo gantā hoti.**That’s how a royal bull elephant goes fast.*";
P_HTM[3062]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**A royal bull elephant with four factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[3063]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**In the same way, a mendicant with four factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[3064]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3065]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sotā ca hoti, hantā ca, khantā ca, gantā ca.**A mendicant listens, destroys, endures, and goes fast.*";
P_HTM[3066]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sotā hoti?**And how does a mendicant listen?*";
P_HTM[3067]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye desiyamāne aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasoto dhammaṃ suṇāti.**It’s when a mendicant pays heed, pays attention, engages wholeheartedly, and lends an ear when the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One is being taught.*";
P_HTM[3068]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sotā hoti.**That’s how a mendicant listens.*";
P_HTM[3069]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu hantā hoti?**And how does a mendicant destroy?*";
P_HTM[3070]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ nādhivāseti pajahati vinodeti hanati byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti, uppannaṃ byāpādavitakkaṃ … pe … uppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ … pe … uppannuppanne pāpake akusale dhamme nādhivāseti pajahati vinodeti hanati byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti.**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t tolerate a sensual, malicious, or cruel thought. They don’t tolerate any bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen, but give them up, get rid of them, eliminate them, and obliterate them.*";
P_HTM[3071]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu hantā hoti.**That’s how a mendicant destroys.*";
P_HTM[3072]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khantā hoti?**And how does a mendicant endure?*";
P_HTM[3073]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti sītassa uṇhassa jighacchāya pipāsāya, ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ duruttānaṃ durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ adhivāsakajātiko hoti.**It’s when a mendicant endures cold, heat, hunger, and thirst; the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles; rude and unwelcome criticism; and they put up with physical pain—sharp, severe, acute, unpleasant, disagreeable, and life-threatening.*";
P_HTM[3074]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khantā hoti.**That’s how a mendicant endures.*";
P_HTM[3075]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gantā hoti?**And how does a mendicant go fast?*";
P_HTM[3076]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yāyaṃ disā agatapubbā iminā dīghena addhunā yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ, taṃ khippaññeva gantā hoti.**It’s when a mendicant swiftly goes in the direction they’ve never gone before in all this long time; that is, the stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[3077]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gantā hoti.**That’s how a mendicant goes fast.*";
P_HTM[3078]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti.**A mendicant with these four factors … is the supreme field of merit for the world.”*";
P_HTM[3079]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3080]="*4. Nāgasuttaṃ**Things*";
P_HTM[3081]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, ṭhānāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four things.*";
P_HTM[3082]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3083]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, ṭhānaṃ amanāpaṃ kātuṃ;**There is a thing that’s unpleasant to do,*";
P_HTM[3084]="*tañca kayiramānaṃ anatthāya saṃvattati.**and doing it proves harmful.*";
P_HTM[3085]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, ṭhānaṃ amanāpaṃ kātuṃ;**There is a thing that’s unpleasant to do,*";
P_HTM[3086]="*tañca kayiramānaṃ atthāya saṃvattati.**but doing it proves beneficial.*";
P_HTM[3087]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, ṭhānaṃ manāpaṃ kātuṃ;**There is a thing that’s pleasant to do,*";
P_HTM[3088]="*tañca kayiramānaṃ anatthāya saṃvattati.**but doing it proves harmful.*";
P_HTM[3089]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, ṭhānaṃ manāpaṃ kātuṃ;**There is a thing that’s pleasant to do,*";
P_HTM[3090]="*tañca kayiramānaṃ atthāya saṃvattati.**and doing it proves beneficial.*";
P_HTM[3091]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ ṭhānaṃ amanāpaṃ kātuṃ;**Take the thing that’s unpleasant to do,*";
P_HTM[3092]="*tañca kayiramānaṃ anatthāya saṃvattati—**and doing it proves harmful.*";
P_HTM[3093]="*idaṃ, bhikkhave, ṭhānaṃ ubhayeneva na kattabbaṃ maññati.**This is regarded as a thing that shouldn’t be done on both grounds:*";
P_HTM[3094]="*Yampidaṃ ṭhānaṃ amanāpaṃ kātuṃ;**because it’s unpleasant,*";
P_HTM[3095]="*imināpi naṃ na kattabbaṃ maññati.* **";
P_HTM[3096]="*Yampidaṃ ṭhānaṃ kayiramānaṃ anatthāya saṃvattati;**and because doing it proves harmful.*";
P_HTM[3097]="*imināpi naṃ na kattabbaṃ maññati.* **";
P_HTM[3098]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, ṭhānaṃ ubhayeneva na kattabbaṃ maññati.**This is regarded as a thing that shouldn’t be done on both grounds.*";
P_HTM[3099]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ ṭhānaṃ amanāpaṃ kātuṃ;**Next, take the thing that’s unpleasant to do,*";
P_HTM[3100]="*tañca kayiramānaṃ atthāya saṃvattati—**but doing it proves beneficial.*";
P_HTM[3101]="*imasmiṃ, bhikkhave, ṭhāne bālo ca paṇḍito ca veditabbo purisathāme purisavīriye purisaparakkame.**It is here that you can tell who is foolish and who is astute in regard to manly strength, energy, and vigor.*";
P_HTM[3102]="*Na, bhikkhave, bālo iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A fool doesn’t reflect:*";
P_HTM[3103]="*‘kiñcāpi kho idaṃ ṭhānaṃ amanāpaṃ kātuṃ;**‘Despite the fact that this thing is unpleasant to do,*";
P_HTM[3104]="*atha carahidaṃ ṭhānaṃ kayiramānaṃ atthāya saṃvattatī’ti.**doing it still proves beneficial.’*";
P_HTM[3105]="*So taṃ ṭhānaṃ na karoti.**They don’t do that thing,*";
P_HTM[3106]="*Tassa taṃ ṭhānaṃ akayiramānaṃ anatthāya saṃvattati.**so that proves harmful.*";
P_HTM[3107]="*Paṇḍito ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati:**An astute person does reflect:*";
P_HTM[3108]="*‘kiñcāpi kho idaṃ ṭhānaṃ amanāpaṃ kātuṃ;**‘Despite the fact that this thing is unpleasant to do,*";
P_HTM[3109]="*atha carahidaṃ ṭhānaṃ kayiramānaṃ atthāya saṃvattatī’ti.**doing it still proves beneficial.’*";
P_HTM[3110]="*So taṃ ṭhānaṃ karoti.**They do that thing,*";
P_HTM[3111]="*Tassa taṃ ṭhānaṃ kayiramānaṃ atthāya saṃvattati.**so that proves beneficial.*";
P_HTM[3112]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ ṭhānaṃ manāpaṃ kātuṃ;**Next, take the thing that’s pleasant to do,*";
P_HTM[3113]="*tañca kayiramānaṃ anatthāya saṃvattati—**but doing it proves harmful.*";
P_HTM[3114]="*imasmimpi, bhikkhave, ṭhāne bālo ca paṇḍito ca veditabbo purisathāme purisavīriye purisaparakkame.**It is here that you can tell who is foolish and who is astute in regard to manly strength, energy, and vigor.*";
P_HTM[3115]="*Na, bhikkhave, bālo iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A fool doesn’t reflect:*";
P_HTM[3116]="*‘kiñcāpi kho idaṃ ṭhānaṃ manāpaṃ kātuṃ;**‘Despite the fact that this thing is pleasant to do,*";
P_HTM[3117]="*atha carahidaṃ ṭhānaṃ kayiramānaṃ anatthāya saṃvattatī’ti.**doing it still proves harmful.’*";
P_HTM[3118]="*So taṃ ṭhānaṃ karoti.**They do that thing,*";
P_HTM[3119]="*Tassa taṃ ṭhānaṃ kayiramānaṃ anatthāya saṃvattati.**and so that proves harmful.*";
P_HTM[3120]="*Paṇḍito ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati:**An astute person does reflect:*";
P_HTM[3121]="*‘kiñcāpi kho idaṃ ṭhānaṃ manāpaṃ kātuṃ;**‘Despite the fact that this thing is pleasant to do,*";
P_HTM[3122]="*atha carahidaṃ ṭhānaṃ kayiramānaṃ anatthāya saṃvattatī’ti.**doing it still proves harmful.’*";
P_HTM[3123]="*So taṃ ṭhānaṃ na karoti.**They don’t do that thing,*";
P_HTM[3124]="*Tassa taṃ ṭhānaṃ akayiramānaṃ atthāya saṃvattati.**so that proves beneficial.*";
P_HTM[3125]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ ṭhānaṃ manāpaṃ kātuṃ, tañca kayiramānaṃ atthāya saṃvattati—**Next, take the thing that’s pleasant to do, and doing it proves beneficial.*";
P_HTM[3126]="*idaṃ, bhikkhave, ṭhānaṃ ubhayeneva kattabbaṃ maññati.**This is regarded as a thing that should be done on both grounds:*";
P_HTM[3127]="*Yampidaṃ ṭhānaṃ manāpaṃ kātuṃ, imināpi naṃ kattabbaṃ maññati;**because it’s pleasant,*";
P_HTM[3128]="*yampidaṃ ṭhānaṃ kayiramānaṃ atthāya saṃvattati, imināpi naṃ kattabbaṃ maññati.**and because doing it proves beneficial.*";
P_HTM[3129]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, ṭhānaṃ ubhayeneva kattabbaṃ maññati.**This is regarded as a thing that should be done on both grounds.*";
P_HTM[3130]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri ṭhānānī”ti.**These are the four things.”*";
P_HTM[3131]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3132]="*5. Ṭhānasuttaṃ**Diligence*";
P_HTM[3133]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, ṭhānehi appamādo karaṇīyo.**“Mendicants, you should be diligent in four situations.*";
P_HTM[3134]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3135]="*Kāyaduccaritaṃ, bhikkhave, pajahatha, kāyasucaritaṃ bhāvetha;**Give up bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind; and develop good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[3136]="*tattha ca mā pamādattha.**Don’t neglect these things.*";
P_HTM[3137]="*Vacīduccaritaṃ, bhikkhave, pajahatha, vacīsucaritaṃ bhāvetha;* **";
P_HTM[3138]="*tattha ca mā pamādattha.* **";
P_HTM[3139]="*Manoduccaritaṃ, bhikkhave, pajahatha, manosucaritaṃ bhāvetha;* **";
P_HTM[3140]="*tattha ca mā pamādattha.* **";
P_HTM[3141]="*Micchādiṭṭhiṃ, bhikkhave, pajahatha, sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāvetha;**Give up wrong view; and develop right view.*";
P_HTM[3142]="*tattha ca mā pamādattha.**Don’t neglect this.*";
P_HTM[3143]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno kāyaduccaritaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti kāyasucaritaṃ bhāvitaṃ, vacīduccaritaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti vacīsucaritaṃ bhāvitaṃ, manoduccaritaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti manosucaritaṃ bhāvitaṃ, micchādiṭṭhi pahīnā hoti sammādiṭṭhi bhāvitā, so na bhāyati samparāyikassa maraṇassā”ti.**A mendicant who has done these things does not fear death in lives to come.”*";
P_HTM[3144]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3145]="*6. Appamādasuttaṃ**Guarding*";
P_HTM[3146]="*“Catūsu, bhikkhave, ṭhānesu attarūpena appamādo sati cetaso ārakkho karaṇīyo.**“Mendicants, in your own way you should practice diligence, mindfulness, and guarding of the mind in four situations.*";
P_HTM[3147]="*Katamesu catūsu?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3148]="*‘Mā me rajanīyesu dhammesu cittaṃ rajjī’ti attarūpena appamādo sati cetaso ārakkho karaṇīyo;**‘May my mind not be aroused by things that arouse greed.’ In your own way you should practice diligence, mindfulness, and guarding of the mind.*";
P_HTM[3149]="*‘mā me dosanīyesu dhammesu cittaṃ dussī’ti attarūpena appamādo sati cetaso ārakkho karaṇīyo;**‘May my mind not be angered by things that provoke hate.’ …*";
P_HTM[3150]="*‘mā me mohanīyesu dhammesu cittaṃ muyhī’ti attarūpena appamādo sati cetaso ārakkho karaṇīyo;**‘May my mind not be deluded by things that promote delusion.’ …*";
P_HTM[3151]="*‘mā me madanīyesu dhammesu cittaṃ majjī’ti attarūpena appamādo sati cetaso ārakkho karaṇīyo.**‘May my mind not be intoxicated by things that intoxicate.’ …*";
P_HTM[3152]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno rajanīyesu dhammesu cittaṃ na rajjati vītarāgattā, dosanīyesu dhammesu cittaṃ na dussati vītadosattā, mohanīyesu dhammesu cittaṃ na muyhati vītamohattā, madanīyesu dhammesu cittaṃ na majjati vītamadattā, so na chambhati na kampati na vedhati na santāsaṃ āpajjati, na ca pana samaṇavacanahetupi gacchatī”ti.**When a mendicant’s mind is no longer affected by greed, hate, delusion, or intoxication because they’ve got rid of these things, they don’t cower or shake or tremble or get scared, nor are they persuaded by the teachings of other ascetics.”*";
P_HTM[3153]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3154]="*7. Ārakkhasuttaṃ**Inspiring*";
P_HTM[3155]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, saddhassa kulaputtassa dassanīyāni saṃvejanīyāni ṭhānāni.**“Mendicants, a faithful gentleman should go to see these four inspiring places.*";
P_HTM[3156]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3157]="*‘Idha tathāgato jāto’ti, bhikkhave, saddhassa kulaputtassa dassanīyaṃ saṃvejanīyaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**Thinking: ‘Here the Realized One was born!’—that is an inspiring place.*";
P_HTM[3158]="*‘Idha tathāgato anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti, bhikkhave, saddhassa kulaputtassa dassanīyaṃ saṃvejanīyaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**Thinking: ‘Here the Realized One became awakened as a supreme fully awakened Buddha!’—that is an inspiring place.*";
P_HTM[3159]="*‘Idha tathāgato anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavattesī’ti, bhikkhave, saddhassa kulaputtassa dassanīyaṃ saṃvejanīyaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**Thinking: ‘Here the Realized One rolled forth the supreme Wheel of Dhamma!’—that is an inspiring place.*";
P_HTM[3160]="*‘Idha tathāgato anupādisesāya nibbānadhātuyā parinibbuto’ti, bhikkhave, saddhassa kulaputtassa dassanīyaṃ saṃvejanīyaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**Thinking: ‘Here the Realized One became fully extinguished through the natural principle of extinguishment, without anything left over!’—that is an inspiring place.*";
P_HTM[3161]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri saddhassa kulaputtassa dassanīyāni saṃvejanīyāni ṭhānānī”ti.**These are the four inspiring places that a faithful gentleman should go to see.”*";
P_HTM[3162]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3163]="*8. Saṃvejanīyasuttaṃ**Perils (1st)*";
P_HTM[3164]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, bhayāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four perils.*";
P_HTM[3165]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3166]="*Jātibhayaṃ, jarābhayaṃ, byādhibhayaṃ, maraṇabhayaṃ—**The perils of rebirth, old age, sickness, and death.*";
P_HTM[3167]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri bhayānī”ti.**These are the four perils.”*";
P_HTM[3168]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3169]="*9. Paṭhamabhayasuttaṃ**Perils (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3170]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, bhayāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four perils.*";
P_HTM[3171]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3172]="*Aggibhayaṃ, udakabhayaṃ, rājabhayaṃ, corabhayaṃ—**The perils of fire, water, kings, and bandits.*";
P_HTM[3173]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri bhayānī”ti.**These are the four perils.”*";
P_HTM[3174]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3175]="*Kesivaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[3176]="*Kesi javo patodo ca,* **";
P_HTM[3177]="*Nāgo ṭhānena pañcamaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3178]="*Appamādo ca ārakkho,* **";
P_HTM[3179]="*Saṃvejanīyañca dve bhayāti.* **";
P_HTM[3180]="*10. Dutiyabhayasuttaṃ**Guilt*";
P_HTM[3181]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, bhayāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four fears.*";
P_HTM[3182]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3183]="*Attānuvādabhayaṃ, parānuvādabhayaṃ, daṇḍabhayaṃ, duggatibhayaṃ.**The fears of guilt, shame, punishment, and going to a bad place.*";
P_HTM[3184]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, attānuvādabhayaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the fear of guilt?*";
P_HTM[3185]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco iti paṭisañcikkhati:**It’s when someone reflects:*";
P_HTM[3186]="*‘ahañceva kho pana kāyena duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, vācāya duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, manasā duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, kiñca taṃ yaṃ maṃ attā sīlato na upavadeyyā’ti.**‘If I were to do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind, wouldn’t I blame myself for my conduct?’*";
P_HTM[3187]="*So attānuvādabhayassa bhīto kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya kāyasucaritaṃ bhāveti, vacīduccaritaṃ pahāya vacīsucaritaṃ bhāveti, manoduccaritaṃ pahāya manosucaritaṃ bhāveti, suddhaṃ attānaṃ pariharati.**Being afraid of guilt, they give up bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and develop good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, keeping themselves pure.*";
P_HTM[3188]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, attānuvādabhayaṃ.**This is called the fear of guilt.*";
P_HTM[3189]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, parānuvādabhayaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the fear of shame?*";
P_HTM[3190]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco iti paṭisañcikkhati:**It’s when someone reflects:*";
P_HTM[3191]="*‘ahañceva kho pana kāyena duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, vācāya duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, manasā duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, kiñca taṃ yaṃ maṃ pare sīlato na upavadeyyun’ti.**‘If I were to do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind, wouldn’t others blame me for my conduct?’*";
P_HTM[3192]="*So parānuvādabhayassa bhīto kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya kāyasucaritaṃ bhāveti, vacīduccaritaṃ pahāya vacīsucaritaṃ bhāveti, manoduccaritaṃ pahāya manosucaritaṃ bhāveti, suddhaṃ attānaṃ pariharati.**Being afraid of shame, they give up bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and develop good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, keeping themselves pure.*";
P_HTM[3193]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, parānuvādabhayaṃ.**This is called the fear of shame.*";
P_HTM[3194]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, daṇḍabhayaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the fear of punishment?*";
P_HTM[3195]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco passati coraṃ āgucāriṃ, rājāno gahetvā vividhā kammakāraṇā kārente,**It’s when someone sees that the kings have arrested a bandit, a criminal, and subjected them to various punishments—*";
P_HTM[3196]="*kasāhipi tāḷente, vettehipi tāḷente, addhadaṇḍakehipi tāḷente, hatthampi chindante, pādampi chindante, hatthapādampi chindante, kaṇṇampi chindante, nāsampi chindante, kaṇṇanāsampi chindante, bilaṅgathālikampi karonte, saṅkhamuṇḍikampi karonte, rāhumukhampi karonte, jotimālikampi karonte, hatthapajjotikampi karonte, erakavattikampi karonte, cīrakavāsikampi karonte, eṇeyyakampi karonte, balisamaṃsikampi karonte, kahāpaṇakampi karonte, khārāpatacchikampi karonte, palighaparivattikampi karonte, palālapīṭhakampi karonte, tattenapi telena osiñcante, sunakhehipi khādāpente, jīvantampi sūle uttāsente, asināpi sīsaṃ chindante.**whipping, caning, and clubbing; cutting off hands or feet, or both; cutting off ears or nose, or both; the ‘porridge pot’, the ‘shell-shave’, the ‘demon’s mouth’, the ‘garland of fire’, the ‘burning hand’, the ‘grass blades’, the ‘bark dress’, the ‘antelope’, the ‘meat hook’, the ‘coins’, the ‘acid pickle’, the ‘twisting bar’, the ‘straw mat’; being splashed with hot oil, being fed to the dogs, being impaled alive, and being beheaded.*";
P_HTM[3197]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[3198]="*‘yathārūpānaṃ kho pāpakānaṃ kammānaṃ hetu coraṃ āgucāriṃ rājāno gahetvā vividhā kammakāraṇā kārenti, kasāhipi tāḷenti … pe … asināpi sīsaṃ chindanti, ahañceva kho pana evarūpaṃ pāpakammaṃ kareyyaṃ, mampi rājāno gahetvā evarūpā vividhā kammakāraṇā kāreyyuṃ, kasāhipi tāḷeyyuṃ, vettehipi tāḷeyyuṃ, addhadaṇḍakehipi tāḷeyyuṃ, hatthampi chindeyyuṃ, pādampi chindeyyuṃ, hatthapādampi chindeyyuṃ, kaṇṇampi chindeyyuṃ, nāsampi chindeyyuṃ, kaṇṇanāsampi chindeyyuṃ, bilaṅgathālikampi kareyyuṃ, saṅkhamuṇḍikampi kareyyuṃ;**‘If I were to do the same kind of bad deed, the kings would punish me in the same way.’ …*";
P_HTM[3199]="*rāhumukhampi kareyyuṃ, jotimālikampi kareyyuṃ, hatthapajjotikampi kareyyuṃ, erakavattikampi kareyyuṃ, cīrakavāsikampi kareyyuṃ, eṇeyyakampi kareyyuṃ, balisamaṃsikampi kareyyuṃ, kahāpaṇakampi kareyyuṃ, khārāpatacchikampi kareyyuṃ, palighaparivattikampi kareyyuṃ, palālapīṭhakampi kareyyuṃ, tattenapi telena osiñceyyuṃ, sunakhehipi khādāpeyyuṃ, jīvantampi sūle uttāseyyuṃ, asināpi sīsaṃ chindeyyun’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3200]="*So daṇḍabhayassa bhīto na paresaṃ pābhataṃ vilumpanto carati.**Being afraid of punishment, they don’t steal the belongings of others.*";
P_HTM[3201]="*Kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya … pe … suddhaṃ attānaṃ pariharati.**They give up bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and develop good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, keeping themselves pure.*";
P_HTM[3202]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, daṇḍabhayaṃ.**This is called the fear of punishment.*";
P_HTM[3203]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, duggatibhayaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the fear of rebirth in a bad place?*";
P_HTM[3204]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco iti paṭisañcikkhati:**It’s when someone reflects:*";
P_HTM[3205]="*‘kāyaduccaritassa kho pāpako vipāko abhisamparāyaṃ, vacīduccaritassa pāpako vipāko abhisamparāyaṃ, manoduccaritassa pāpako vipāko abhisamparāyaṃ.**‘Bad conduct of body, speech, or mind has a bad result in the next life.*";
P_HTM[3206]="*Ahañceva kho pana kāyena duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, vācāya duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, manasā duccaritaṃ careyyaṃ, kiñca taṃ yāhaṃ na kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyyan’ti.**If I were to do such bad things, when my body breaks up, after death, I’d be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.’*";
P_HTM[3207]="*So duggatibhayassa bhīto kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya kāyasucaritaṃ bhāveti, vacīduccaritaṃ pahāya vacīsucaritaṃ bhāveti, manoduccaritaṃ pahāya manosucaritaṃ bhāveti, suddhaṃ attānaṃ pariharati.**Being afraid of rebirth in a bad place, they give up bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and develop good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, keeping themselves pure.*";
P_HTM[3208]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, duggatibhayaṃ.**This is called the fear of rebirth in a bad place.*";
P_HTM[3209]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri bhayānī”ti.**These are the four fears.”*";
P_HTM[3210]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3211]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Fears*";
P_HTM[3212]="*1. Attānuvādasuttaṃ**The Danger of Waves*";
P_HTM[3213]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, bhayāni udakorohantassa pāṭikaṅkhitabbāni.**“Mendicants, anyone who enters the water should anticipate four dangers.*";
P_HTM[3214]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3215]="*Ūmibhayaṃ, kumbhīlabhayaṃ, āvaṭṭabhayaṃ, susukābhayaṃ—**The dangers of waves, crocodiles, whirlpools, and sharks.*";
P_HTM[3216]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri bhayāni udakorohantassa pāṭikaṅkhitabbāni.**These are the four dangers that anyone who enters the water should anticipate.*";
P_HTM[3217]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāri bhayāni idhekaccassa kulaputtassa imasmiṃ dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitassa pāṭikaṅkhitabbāni.**In the same way, a gentleman who goes forth from the lay life to homelessness in this teaching and training should anticipate four dangers.*";
P_HTM[3218]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3219]="*Ūmibhayaṃ, kumbhīlabhayaṃ, āvaṭṭabhayaṃ, susukābhayaṃ.**The dangers of waves, crocodiles, whirlpools, and sharks.*";
P_HTM[3220]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, ūmibhayaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the danger of waves?*";
P_HTM[3221]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**It’s when a gentleman has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness, thinking:*";
P_HTM[3222]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto;**‘I’m swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I’m swamped by suffering, mired in suffering.*";
P_HTM[3223]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.**Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[3224]="*Tamenaṃ tathā pabbajitaṃ samānaṃ sabrahmacārino ovadanti anusāsanti:**When they’ve gone forth, their spiritual companions advise and instruct them:*";
P_HTM[3225]="*‘evaṃ te abhikkamitabbaṃ, evaṃ te paṭikkamitabbaṃ, evaṃ te āloketabbaṃ, evaṃ te viloketabbaṃ, evaṃ te samiñjitabbaṃ, evaṃ te pasāritabbaṃ, evaṃ te saṅghāṭipattacīvaraṃ dhāretabban’ti.**‘You should go out like this, and come back like that. You should look to the front like this, and to the side like that. You should contract your limbs like this, and extend them like that. This is how you should bear your outer robe, bowl, and robes.’*";
P_HTM[3226]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[3227]="*‘mayaṃ kho pubbe agāriyabhūtā samānā aññe ovadāmapi anusāsāmapi.**‘Formerly, as a lay person, I advised and instructed others.*";
P_HTM[3228]="*Ime panamhākaṃ puttamattā maññe nattamattā maññe ovaditabbaṃ anusāsitabbaṃ maññantī’ti.**And now these mendicants—who you’d think were my children or grandchildren—imagine they can advise and instruct me!’*";
P_HTM[3229]="*So kupito anattamano sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati.**Angry and upset, they reject the training and return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[3230]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ūmibhayassa bhīto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvatto.**This is called a mendicant who rejects the training and returns to a lesser life because they’re afraid of the danger of waves.*";
P_HTM[3231]="*Ūmibhayanti kho, bhikkhave, kodhūpāyāsassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Danger of waves’ is a term for anger and distress.*";
P_HTM[3232]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ūmibhayaṃ.**This is called the danger of waves.*";
P_HTM[3233]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kumbhīlabhayaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the danger of crocodiles?*";
P_HTM[3234]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**It’s when a gentleman has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness …*";
P_HTM[3235]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto;* **";
P_HTM[3236]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3237]="*Tamenaṃ tathā pabbajitaṃ samānaṃ sabrahmacārino ovadanti anusāsanti:**When they’ve gone forth, their spiritual companions advise and instruct them:*";
P_HTM[3238]="*‘idaṃ te khāditabbaṃ, idaṃ te na khāditabbaṃ, idaṃ te bhuñjitabbaṃ, idaṃ te na bhuñjitabbaṃ, idaṃ te sāyitabbaṃ, idaṃ te na sāyitabbaṃ, idaṃ te pātabbaṃ, idaṃ te na pātabbaṃ, kappiyaṃ te khāditabbaṃ, akappiyaṃ te na khāditabbaṃ, kappiyaṃ te bhuñjitabbaṃ, akappiyaṃ te na bhuñjitabbaṃ, kappiyaṃ te sāyitabbaṃ, akappiyaṃ te na sāyitabbaṃ, kappiyaṃ te pātabbaṃ, akappiyaṃ te na pātabbaṃ, kāle te khāditabbaṃ, vikāle te na khāditabbaṃ, kāle te bhuñjitabbaṃ, vikāle te na bhuñjitabbaṃ, kāle te sāyitabbaṃ, vikāle te na sāyitabbaṃ, kāle te pātabbaṃ, vikāle te na pātabban’ti.**‘You may eat, consume, taste, and drink these things, but not those. You may eat what’s allowable, but not what’s unallowable. You may eat at the right time, but not at the wrong time.’*";
P_HTM[3239]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[3240]="*‘mayaṃ kho pubbe agāriyabhūtā samānā yaṃ icchāma taṃ khādāma, yaṃ na icchāma na taṃ khādāma;**‘When I was a lay person, I used to eat, consume, taste, and drink what I wanted, not what I didn’t want.*";
P_HTM[3241]="*yaṃ icchāma taṃ bhuñjāma, yaṃ na icchāma na taṃ bhuñjāma;* **";
P_HTM[3242]="*yaṃ icchāma taṃ sāyāma, yaṃ na icchāma na taṃ sāyāma;* **";
P_HTM[3243]="*yaṃ icchāma taṃ pivāma, yaṃ na icchāma na taṃ pivāma;* **";
P_HTM[3244]="*kappiyampi khādāma akappiyampi khādāma kappiyampi bhuñjāma akappiyampi bhuñjāma kappiyampi sāyāma akappiyampi sāyāma kappiyampi pivāma akappiyampi pivāma, kālepi khādāma vikālepi khādāma kālepi bhuñjāma vikālepi bhuñjāma kālepi sāyāma vikālepi sāyāma kālepi pivāma vikālepi pivāma;**I ate and drank both allowable and unallowable things, at the right time and the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[3245]="*yampi no saddhā gahapatikā divā vikāle paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā denti, tatrapime mukhāvaraṇaṃ maññe karontī’ti.**And these faithful householders give us a variety of delicious foods at the wrong time of day. But these mendicants imagine they can gag our mouths!’*";
P_HTM[3246]="*So kupito anattamano sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati.**Angry and upset, they reject the training and return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[3247]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kumbhīlabhayassa bhīto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvatto.**This is called a mendicant who rejects the training and returns to a lesser life because they’re afraid of the danger of crocodiles.*";
P_HTM[3248]="*Kumbhīlabhayanti kho, bhikkhave, odarikattassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Danger of crocodiles’ is a term for gluttony.*";
P_HTM[3249]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kumbhīlabhayaṃ.**This is called the danger of crocodiles.*";
P_HTM[3250]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, āvaṭṭabhayaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the danger of whirlpools?*";
P_HTM[3251]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**It’s when a gentleman has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness …*";
P_HTM[3252]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi, dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto;* **";
P_HTM[3253]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3254]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati arakkhiteneva kāyena arakkhitāya vācāya arakkhitena cittena anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā asaṃvutehi indriyehi.**When they’ve gone forth, they robe up in the morning and, taking their bowl and robe, enter a village or town for alms without guarding body, speech, and mind, without establishing mindfulness, and without restraining the sense faculties.*";
P_HTM[3255]="*So tattha passati gahapatiṃ vā gahapatiputtaṃ vā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitaṃ samaṅgībhūtaṃ paricārayamānaṃ.**There they see a householder or their child amusing themselves, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[3256]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[3257]="*‘mayaṃ kho pubbe agāriyabhūtā samānā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitā samaṅgībhūtā paricārimhā;**‘Formerly, as a lay person, I amused myself, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[3258]="*saṃvijjanti kho pana me kule bhogā.**And it’s true that my family is wealthy.*";
P_HTM[3259]="*Sakkā bhoge ca bhuñjituṃ puññāni ca kātuṃ.**I can both enjoy my wealth and make merit.*";
P_HTM[3260]="*Yannūnāhaṃ sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattitvā bhoge ca bhuñjeyyaṃ puññāni ca kareyyan’ti.**Why don’t I reject the training and return to a lesser life, so I can enjoy my wealth and make merit?’*";
P_HTM[3261]="*So sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati.**They reject the training and return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[3262]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āvaṭṭabhayassa bhīto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvatto.**This is called a mendicant who rejects the training and returns to a lesser life because they’re afraid of the danger of whirlpools.*";
P_HTM[3263]="*Āvaṭṭabhayanti kho, bhikkhave, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Danger of whirlpools’ is a term for the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[3264]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, āvaṭṭabhayaṃ.**This is called the danger of whirlpools.*";
P_HTM[3265]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, susukābhayaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the danger of sharks?*";
P_HTM[3266]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**It’s when a gentleman has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness …*";
P_HTM[3267]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto;* **";
P_HTM[3268]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3269]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati arakkhiteneva kāyena arakkhitāya vācāya arakkhitena cittena anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā asaṃvutehi indriyehi.**When they’ve gone forth, they robe up in the morning and, taking their bowl and robe, enter a village or town for alms without guarding body, speech, and mind, without establishing mindfulness, and without restraining the sense faculties.*";
P_HTM[3270]="*So tattha passati mātugāmaṃ dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā.**There they see a female scantily clad, with revealing clothes.*";
P_HTM[3271]="*Tassa mātugāmaṃ disvā dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti.**Lust infects their mind,*";
P_HTM[3272]="*So rāgānuddhaṃsitena cittena sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati.**so they reject the training and return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[3273]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu susukābhayassa bhīto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvatto.**This is called a mendicant who rejects the training and returns to a lesser life because they’re afraid of the danger of sharks.*";
P_HTM[3274]="*Susukābhayanti kho, bhikkhave, mātugāmassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Danger of sharks’ is a term for females.*";
P_HTM[3275]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, susukābhayaṃ.**This is called the danger of sharks.*";
P_HTM[3276]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri bhayāni idhekaccassa kulaputtassa imasmiṃ dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitassa pāṭikaṅkhitabbānī”ti.**These are the four dangers that a gentleman who goes forth from the lay life to homelessness in this teaching and training should anticipate.”*";
P_HTM[3277]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3278]="*2. Ūmibhayasuttaṃ**Difference (1st)*";
P_HTM[3279]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3280]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3281]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Firstly, a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[3282]="*So tadassādeti, taṃ nikāmeti, tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati.**They enjoy it and like it and find it satisfying.*";
P_HTM[3283]="*Tattha ṭhito tadadhimutto tabbahulavihārī aparihīno kālaṃ kurumāno brahmakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**If they abide in that, are committed to it, and meditate on it often without losing it, when they die they’re reborn in the company of the gods of Brahmā’s Host.*";
P_HTM[3284]="*Brahmakāyikānaṃ, bhikkhave, devānaṃ kappo āyuppamāṇaṃ.**The lifespan of the gods of Brahma’s Host is one eon.*";
P_HTM[3285]="*Tattha puthujjano yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā nirayampi gacchati tiracchānayonimpi gacchati pettivisayampi gacchati.**An ordinary person stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they go to hell or the animal realm or the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[3286]="*Bhagavato pana sāvako tattha yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā tasmiṃyeva bhave parinibbāyati.**But a disciple of the Buddha stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they’re extinguished in that very life.*";
P_HTM[3287]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, viseso ayaṃ adhippayāso idaṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanena, yadidaṃ gatiyā upapattiyā sati.**This is the difference between an educated noble disciple and an uneducated ordinary person, that is, when there is a place of rebirth.*";
P_HTM[3288]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[3289]="*So tadassādeti, taṃ nikāmeti, tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati.**They enjoy it and like it and find it satisfying.*";
P_HTM[3290]="*Tattha ṭhito tadadhimutto tabbahulavihārī aparihīno kālaṃ kurumāno ābhassarānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**If they abide in that, are committed to it, and meditate on it often without losing it, when they die they’re reborn in the company of the gods of streaming radiance.*";
P_HTM[3291]="*Ābhassarānaṃ, bhikkhave, devānaṃ dve kappā āyuppamāṇaṃ.**The lifespan of the gods of streaming radiance is two eons.*";
P_HTM[3292]="*Tattha puthujjano yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā nirayampi gacchati tiracchānayonimpi gacchati pettivisayampi gacchati.**An ordinary person stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they go to hell or the animal realm or the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[3293]="*Bhagavato pana sāvako tattha yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā tasmiṃyeva bhave parinibbāyati.**But a disciple of the Buddha stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they’re extinguished in that very life.*";
P_HTM[3294]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, viseso ayaṃ adhippayāso idaṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanena, yadidaṃ gatiyā upapattiyā sati.**This is the difference between an educated noble disciple and an uneducated ordinary person, that is, when there is a place of rebirth.*";
P_HTM[3295]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[3296]="*So tadassādeti, taṃ nikāmeti, tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati.**They enjoy it and like it and find it satisfying.*";
P_HTM[3297]="*Tattha ṭhito tadadhimutto tabbahulavihārī aparihīno, kālaṃ kurumāno subhakiṇhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**If they abide in that, are committed to it, and meditate on it often without losing it, when they die they’re reborn in the company of the gods replete with glory.*";
P_HTM[3298]="*Subhakiṇhānaṃ, bhikkhave, devānaṃ cattāro kappā āyuppamāṇaṃ.**The lifespan of the gods replete with glory is four eons.*";
P_HTM[3299]="*Tattha puthujjano yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā nirayampi gacchati tiracchānayonimpi gacchati pettivisayampi gacchati.**An ordinary person stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they go to hell or the animal realm or the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[3300]="*Bhagavato pana sāvako tattha yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā tasmiṃyeva bhave parinibbāyati.**But a disciple of the Buddha stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they’re extinguished in that very life.*";
P_HTM[3301]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, viseso ayaṃ adhippayāso idaṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanena, yadidaṃ gatiyā upapattiyā sati.**This is the difference between an educated noble disciple and an uneducated ordinary person, that is, when there is a place of rebirth.*";
P_HTM[3302]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[3303]="*So tadassādeti, taṃ nikāmeti, tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati.**They enjoy it and like it and find it satisfying.*";
P_HTM[3304]="*Tattha ṭhito tadadhimutto tabbahulavihārī aparihīno kālaṃ kurumāno vehapphalānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**If they abide in that, are committed to it, and meditate on it often without losing it, when they die they’re reborn in the company of the gods of abundant fruit.*";
P_HTM[3305]="*Vehapphalānaṃ, bhikkhave, devānaṃ pañca kappasatāni āyuppamāṇaṃ.**The lifespan of the gods of abundant fruit is five hundred eons.*";
P_HTM[3306]="*Tattha puthujjano yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā nirayampi gacchati tiracchānayonimpi gacchati pettivisayampi gacchati.**An ordinary person stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they go to hell or the animal realm or the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[3307]="*Bhagavato pana sāvako tattha yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā tasmiṃyeva bhave parinibbāyati.**But a disciple of the Buddha stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they’re extinguished in that very life.*";
P_HTM[3308]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, viseso ayaṃ adhippayāso idaṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanena, yadidaṃ gatiyā upapattiyā sati.**This is the difference between an educated noble disciple and an uneducated ordinary person, that is, when there is a place of rebirth.*";
P_HTM[3309]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3310]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3311]="*3. Paṭhamanānākaraṇasuttaṃ**Difference (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3312]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3313]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3314]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Firstly, a person, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption …*";
P_HTM[3315]="*So yadeva tattha hoti rūpagataṃ vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ, te dhamme aniccato dukkhato rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato samanupassati.**They contemplate the phenomena there—included in form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness—as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, as empty, as not-self.*";
P_HTM[3316]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā suddhāvāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the gods of the pure abodes.*";
P_HTM[3317]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, upapatti asādhāraṇā puthujjanehi.**This rebirth is not shared with ordinary people.*";
P_HTM[3318]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption …*";
P_HTM[3319]="*So yadeva tattha hoti rūpagataṃ vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ, te dhamme aniccato dukkhato rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato samanupassati.**They contemplate the phenomena there—included in form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness—as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, as empty, as not-self.*";
P_HTM[3320]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā suddhāvāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the gods of the pure abodes.*";
P_HTM[3321]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, upapatti asādhāraṇā puthujjanehi.**This rebirth is not shared with ordinary people.*";
P_HTM[3322]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3323]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3324]="*4. Dutiyanānākaraṇasuttaṃ**Love (1st)*";
P_HTM[3325]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3326]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3327]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati.**Firstly, a person meditates spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[3328]="*So tadassādeti, taṃ nikāmeti, tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati.**They enjoy this and like it and find it satisfying.*";
P_HTM[3329]="*Tattha ṭhito tadadhimutto tabbahulavihārī aparihīno kālaṃ kurumāno brahmakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**If they abide in that, are committed to it, and meditate on it often without losing it, when they die they’re reborn in the company of the gods of Brahmā’s Host.*";
P_HTM[3330]="*Brahmakāyikānaṃ, bhikkhave, devānaṃ kappo āyuppamāṇaṃ.**The lifespan of the gods of Brahma’s Host is one eon.*";
P_HTM[3331]="*Tattha puthujjano yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā nirayampi gacchati tiracchānayonimpi gacchati pettivisayampi gacchati.**An ordinary person stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they go to hell or the animal realm or the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[3332]="*Bhagavato pana sāvako tattha yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā tasmiṃyeva bhave parinibbāyati.**But a disciple of the Buddha stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they’re extinguished in that very life.*";
P_HTM[3333]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, viseso ayaṃ adhippayāso idaṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanena, yadidaṃ gatiyā upapattiyā sati.**This is the difference between an educated noble disciple and an uneducated ordinary person, that is, when there is a place of rebirth.*";
P_HTM[3334]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**Furthermore, a person meditates spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[3335]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[3336]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati.**equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[3337]="*So tadassādeti, taṃ nikāmeti, tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati.**They enjoy this and like it and find it satisfying.*";
P_HTM[3338]="*Tattha ṭhito tadadhimutto tabbahulavihārī aparihīno kālaṃ kurumāno ābhassarānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**If they abide in that, are committed to it, and meditate on it often without losing it, when they die they’re reborn in the company of the gods of streaming radiance. The lifespan of the gods of streaming radiance is two eons.*";
P_HTM[3339]="*Ābhassarānaṃ, bhikkhave, devānaṃ dve kappā āyuppamāṇaṃ … pe … subhakiṇhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**… they’re reborn in the company of the gods replete with glory. The lifespan of the gods replete with glory is four eons.*";
P_HTM[3340]="*Subhakiṇhānaṃ, bhikkhave, devānaṃ cattāro kappā āyuppamāṇaṃ … pe … vehapphalānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**… they’re reborn in the company of the gods of abundant fruit.*";
P_HTM[3341]="*Vehapphalānaṃ, bhikkhave, devānaṃ pañca kappasatāni āyuppamāṇaṃ.**The lifespan of the gods of abundant fruit is five hundred eons.*";
P_HTM[3342]="*Tattha puthujjano yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā nirayampi gacchati tiracchānayonimpi gacchati pettivisayampi gacchati.**An ordinary person stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they go to hell or the animal realm or the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[3343]="*Bhagavato pana sāvako tattha yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā tasmiṃyeva bhave parinibbāyati.**But a disciple of the Buddha stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they’re extinguished in that very life.*";
P_HTM[3344]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, viseso ayaṃ adhippayāso idaṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanena, yadidaṃ gatiyā upapattiyā sati.**This is the difference between an educated noble disciple and an uneducated ordinary person, that is, when there is a place of rebirth.*";
P_HTM[3345]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3346]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3347]="*5. Paṭhamamettāsuttaṃ**Love (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3348]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3349]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3350]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati.**Firstly, a person meditates spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[3351]="*So yadeva tattha hoti rūpagataṃ vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ te dhamme aniccato dukkhato rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato samanupassati.**They contemplate the phenomena there—included in form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness—as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, as empty, as not-self.*";
P_HTM[3352]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā suddhāvāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the gods of the pure abodes.*";
P_HTM[3353]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, upapatti asādhāraṇā puthujjanehi.**This rebirth is not shared with ordinary people.*";
P_HTM[3354]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo karuṇā … pe …**Furthermore, a person meditates spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[3355]="*muditā … pe …**rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[3356]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati.**equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[3357]="*So yadeva tattha hoti rūpagataṃ vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ te dhamme aniccato dukkhato rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato samanupassati.**They contemplate the phenomena there—included in form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness—as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, as empty, as not-self.*";
P_HTM[3358]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā suddhāvāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the gods of the pure abodes.*";
P_HTM[3359]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, upapatti asādhāraṇā puthujjanehi.**This rebirth is not shared with ordinary people.*";
P_HTM[3360]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasminti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3361]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3362]="*6. Dutiyamettāsuttaṃ**Incredible Things About the Realized One (1st)*";
P_HTM[3363]="*“Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvā cattāro acchariyā abbhutā dhammā pātubhavanti.**“Mendicants, with the appearance of a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, four incredible and amazing things appear.*";
P_HTM[3364]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3365]="*Yadā, bhikkhave, bodhisatto tusitā kāyā cavitvā sato sampajāno mātukucchiṃ okkamati, atha sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ.**When the being intent on awakening passes away from the host of Joyful Gods, he’s conceived in his mother’s womb, mindful and aware. And then—in this world with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—an immeasurable, magnificent light appears, surpassing the glory of the gods.*";
P_HTM[3366]="*Yāpi tā lokantarikā aghā asaṃvutā andhakārā andhakāratimisā yatthapimesaṃ candimasūriyānaṃ evaṃmahiddhikānaṃ evaṃmahānubhāvānaṃ ābhā nānubhonti, tatthapi appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ.**Even in the boundless desolation of interstellar space—so utterly dark that even the light of the moon and the sun, so mighty and powerful, makes no impression—an immeasurable, magnificent light appears, surpassing the glory of the gods.*";
P_HTM[3367]="*Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi tenobhāsena aññamaññaṃ sañjānanti:**And the sentient beings reborn there recognize each other by that light:*";
P_HTM[3368]="*‘aññepi kira, bho, santi sattā idhūpapannā’ti.**‘So, it seems other sentient beings have been reborn here!’*";
P_HTM[3369]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvā ayaṃ paṭhamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo pātubhavati.**This is the first incredible and amazing thing that appears with the appearance of a Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3370]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto sato sampajāno mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, atha sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ.**Furthermore, the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’s womb, mindful and aware. And then … an immeasurable, magnificent light appears …*";
P_HTM[3371]="*Yāpi tā lokantarikā aghā asaṃvutā andhakārā andhakāratimisā yatthapimesaṃ candimasūriyānaṃ evaṃmahiddhikānaṃ evaṃmahānubhāvānaṃ ābhā nānubhonti, tatthapi appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ.**even in the boundless desolation of interstellar space …*";
P_HTM[3372]="*Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi tenobhāsena aññamaññaṃ sañjānanti:* **";
P_HTM[3373]="*‘aññepi kira, bho, santi sattā idhūpapannā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3374]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvā ayaṃ dutiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo pātubhavati.**This is the second incredible and amazing thing that appears with the appearance of a Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3375]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, yadā tathāgato anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambujjhati, atha sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ.**Furthermore, the Realized One understands the supreme perfect awakening. And then … an immeasurable, magnificent light appears …*";
P_HTM[3376]="*Yāpi tā lokantarikā aghā asaṃvutā andhakārā andhakāratimisā yatthapimesaṃ candimasūriyānaṃ evaṃmahiddhikānaṃ evaṃmahānubhāvānaṃ ābhā nānubhonti, tatthapi appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ.**even in the boundless desolation of interstellar space …*";
P_HTM[3377]="*Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi tenobhāsena aññamaññaṃ sañjānanti:* **";
P_HTM[3378]="*‘aññepi kira, bho, santi sattā idhūpapannā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3379]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvā ayaṃ tatiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo pātubhavati.**This is the third incredible and amazing thing that appears with the appearance of a Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3380]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, yadā tathāgato anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavatteti, atha sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ.**Furthermore, the Realized One rolls forth the supreme Wheel of Dhamma. And then … an immeasurable, magnificent light appears …*";
P_HTM[3381]="*Yāpi tā lokantarikā aghā asaṃvutā andhakārā andhakāratimisā yatthapimesaṃ candimasūriyānaṃ evaṃmahiddhikānaṃ evaṃmahānubhāvānaṃ ābhā nānubhonti, tatthapi appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ.**even in the boundless desolation of interstellar space …*";
P_HTM[3382]="*Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi tenobhāsena aññamaññaṃ sañjānanti:* **";
P_HTM[3383]="*‘aññepi kira, bho, santi sattā idhūpapannā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3384]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvā ayaṃ catuttho acchariyo abbhuto dhammo pātubhavati.**This is the fourth incredible and amazing thing that appears with the appearance of a Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3385]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvā ime cattāro acchariyā abbhutā dhammā pātubhavantī”ti.**With the appearance of a Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, these four incredible and amazing things appear.”*";
P_HTM[3386]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3387]="*7. Paṭhamatathāgataacchariyasuttaṃ**Incredible Things About the Realized One (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3388]="*“Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvā cattāro acchariyā abbhutā dhammā pātubhavanti.**“Mendicants, with the appearance of a Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, four incredible and amazing things appear.*";
P_HTM[3389]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3390]="*Ālayārāmā, bhikkhave, pajā ālayaratā ālayasammuditā;**People like attachment, they love it and enjoy it.*";
P_HTM[3391]="*sā tathāgatena anālaye dhamme desiyamāne sussūsati sotaṃ odahati aññā cittaṃ upaṭṭhapeti.**Yet when a Realized One is teaching the Dhamma of non-adherence, they want to listen, they lend an ear, and they apply their minds to understand it.*";
P_HTM[3392]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvā ayaṃ paṭhamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo pātubhavati.**This is the first incredible and amazing thing that appears with the appearance of a Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3393]="*Mānārāmā, bhikkhave, pajā mānaratā mānasammuditā.**People like conceit, they love it and enjoy it.*";
P_HTM[3394]="*Sā tathāgatena mānavinaye dhamme desiyamāne sussūsati sotaṃ odahati aññā cittaṃ upaṭṭhapeti.**Yet when a Realized One is teaching the Dhamma of removing conceit, they want to listen, they lend an ear, and they apply their minds to understand it.*";
P_HTM[3395]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvā ayaṃ dutiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo pātubhavati.**This is the second incredible and amazing thing that appears with the appearance of a Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3396]="*Anupasamārāmā, bhikkhave, pajā anupasamaratā anupasamasammuditā.**People like excitement, they love it and enjoy it.*";
P_HTM[3397]="*Sā tathāgatena opasamike dhamme desiyamāne sussūsati sotaṃ odahati aññā cittaṃ upaṭṭhapeti.**Yet when a Realized One is teaching the Dhamma of peace, they want to listen, they lend an ear, and they apply their minds to understand it.*";
P_HTM[3398]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvā ayaṃ tatiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo pātubhavati.**This is the third incredible and amazing thing that appears with the appearance of a Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3399]="*Avijjāgatā, bhikkhave, pajā aṇḍabhūtā pariyonaddhā.**This population is lost in ignorance, trapped in their shells.*";
P_HTM[3400]="*Sā tathāgatena avijjāvinaye dhamme desiyamāne sussūsati sotaṃ odahati aññā cittaṃ upaṭṭhapeti.**Yet when a Realized One is teaching the Dhamma of removing ignorance, they want to listen, they lend an ear, and they apply their minds to understand it.*";
P_HTM[3401]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvā ayaṃ catuttho acchariyo abbhuto dhammo pātubhavati.**This is the fourth incredible and amazing thing that appears with the appearance of a Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3402]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvā ime cattāro acchariyā abbhutā dhammā pātubhavantī”ti.**With the appearance of a Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, four incredible and amazing things appear.”*";
P_HTM[3403]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3404]="*8. Dutiyatathāgataacchariyasuttaṃ**Incredible Things About Ānanda*";
P_HTM[3405]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, acchariyā abbhutā dhammā ānande.**“Mendicants, there are these four incredible and amazing things about Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[3406]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3407]="*Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhuparisā ānandaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamati, dassanenapi sā attamanā hoti.**If an assembly of monks goes to see Ānanda, they’re uplifted by seeing him*";
P_HTM[3408]="*Tatra ce ānando dhammaṃ bhāsati, bhāsitenapi sā attamanā hoti.**and uplifted by hearing him speak.*";
P_HTM[3409]="*Atittāva, bhikkhave, bhikkhuparisā hoti, atha ānando tuṇhī bhavati.**And when he falls silent, they’ve never had enough.*";
P_HTM[3410]="*Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniparisā ānandaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamati, dassanenapi sā attamanā hoti.**If an assembly of nuns …*";
P_HTM[3411]="*Tattha ce ānando dhammaṃ bhāsati, bhāsitenapi sā attamanā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[3412]="*Atittāva, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniparisā hoti, atha ānando tuṇhī bhavati.* **";
P_HTM[3413]="*Sace, bhikkhave, upāsakaparisā ānandaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamati, dassanenapi sā attamanā hoti.**laymen …*";
P_HTM[3414]="*Tatra ce ānando dhammaṃ bhāsati, bhāsitenapi sā attamanā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[3415]="*Atittāva, bhikkhave, upāsakaparisā hoti, atha ānando tuṇhī bhavati.* **";
P_HTM[3416]="*Sace, bhikkhave, upāsikāparisā ānandaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamati, dassanenapi sā attamanā hoti.**or laywomen goes to see Ānanda, they’re uplifted by seeing him*";
P_HTM[3417]="*Tatra ce ānando dhammaṃ bhāsati, bhāsitenapi sā attamanā hoti.**and uplifted by hearing him speak.*";
P_HTM[3418]="*Atittāva, bhikkhave, upāsikāparisā hoti, atha ānando tuṇhī bhavati.**And when he falls silent, they’ve never had enough.*";
P_HTM[3419]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro acchariyā abbhutā dhammā ānande”ti.**These are the four incredible and amazing things about Ānanda.”*";
P_HTM[3420]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3421]="*9. Ānandaacchariyasuttaṃ**Incredible Things About the Wheel*";
P_HTM[3422]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, acchariyā abbhutā dhammā raññe cakkavattimhi.**“Mendicants, there are these four incredible and amazing things about a wheel-turning monarch.*";
P_HTM[3423]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3424]="*Sace, bhikkhave, khattiyaparisā rājānaṃ cakkavattiṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamati, dassanenapi sā attamanā hoti.**If an assembly of aristocrats goes to see a wheel-turning monarch, they’re uplifted by seeing him*";
P_HTM[3425]="*Tatra ce rājā cakkavattī bhāsati, bhāsitenapi sā attamanā hoti.**and uplifted by hearing him speak.*";
P_HTM[3426]="*Atittāva, bhikkhave, khattiyaparisā hoti, atha rājā cakkavattī tuṇhī bhavati.**And when he falls silent, they’ve never had enough.*";
P_HTM[3427]="*Sace, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇaparisā rājānaṃ cakkavattiṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamati, dassanenapi sā attamanā hoti.**If an assembly of brahmins …*";
P_HTM[3428]="*Tatra ce rājā cakkavattī bhāsati, bhāsitenapi sā attamanā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[3429]="*Atittāva, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇaparisā hoti, atha rājā cakkavattī tuṇhī bhavati.* **";
P_HTM[3430]="*Sace, bhikkhave, gahapatiparisā rājānaṃ cakkavattiṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamati, dassanenapi sā attamanā hoti.**householders …*";
P_HTM[3431]="*Tatra ce rājā cakkavattī bhāsati, bhāsitenapi sā attamanā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[3432]="*Atittāva, bhikkhave, gahapatiparisā hoti, atha rājā cakkavattī tuṇhī bhavati.* **";
P_HTM[3433]="*Sace, bhikkhave, samaṇaparisā rājānaṃ cakkavattiṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamati, dassanenapi sā attamanā hoti.**or ascetics goes to see a wheel-turning monarch, they’re uplifted by seeing him*";
P_HTM[3434]="*Tatra ce rājā cakkavattī bhāsati, bhāsitenapi sā attamanā hoti.**and uplifted by hearing him speak.*";
P_HTM[3435]="*Atittāva, bhikkhave, samaṇaparisā hoti, atha rājā cakkavattī tuṇhī bhavati.**And when he falls silent, they’ve never had enough.*";
P_HTM[3436]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro acchariyā abbhutā dhammā raññe cakkavattimhi.**These are the four incredible and amazing things about a wheel-turning monarch.*";
P_HTM[3437]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro acchariyā abbhutā dhammā ānande.**In the same way, there are these four incredible and amazing things about Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[3438]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3439]="*Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhuparisā ānandaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamati, dassanenapi sā attamanā hoti.**If an assembly of monks goes to see Ānanda, they’re uplifted by seeing him*";
P_HTM[3440]="*Tatra ce ānando dhammaṃ bhāsati, bhāsitenapi sā attamanā hoti.**and uplifted by hearing him speak.*";
P_HTM[3441]="*Atittāva, bhikkhave, bhikkhuparisā hoti, atha ānando tuṇhī bhavati.**And when he falls silent, they’ve never had enough.*";
P_HTM[3442]="*Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniparisā … pe … sace, bhikkhave, upāsakaparisā … pe … sace, bhikkhave, upāsikāparisā ānandaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamati, dassanenapi sā attamanā hoti.**If an assembly of nuns … laymen … or laywomen goes to see Ānanda, they’re uplifted by seeing him*";
P_HTM[3443]="*Tatra ce ānando dhammaṃ bhāsati, bhāsitenapi sā attamanā hoti.**and uplifted by hearing him speak.*";
P_HTM[3444]="*Atittāva, bhikkhave, upāsikāparisā hoti, atha ānando tuṇhī bhavati.**And when he falls silent, they’ve never had enough.*";
P_HTM[3445]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro acchariyā abbhutā dhammā ānande”ti.**These are the four incredible and amazing things about Ānanda.”*";
P_HTM[3446]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3447]="*Bhayavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[3448]="*Attānuvādaūmi ca,* **";
P_HTM[3449]="*dve ca nānā dve ca honti;* **";
P_HTM[3450]="*Mettā dve ca acchariyā,* **";
P_HTM[3451]="*aparā ca tathā duveti.* **";
P_HTM[3452]="*10. Cakkavattiacchariyasuttaṃ**Fetters*";
P_HTM[3453]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3454]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3455]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni honti, upapattipaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni honti, bhavapaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni honti.**One person hasn’t given up the lower fetters, the fetters for getting reborn, or the fetters for getting a continued existence.*";
P_HTM[3456]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni honti, upapattipaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni honti, bhavapaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni honti.**One person has given up the lower fetters, but not the fetters for getting reborn, or the fetters for getting a continued existence.*";
P_HTM[3457]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni honti, upapattipaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni honti, bhavapaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni honti.**One person has given up the lower fetters and the fetters for getting reborn, but not the fetters for getting a continued existence.*";
P_HTM[3458]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni honti, upapattipaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni honti, bhavapaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni honti.**One person has given up the lower fetters, the fetters for getting reborn, and the fetters for getting a continued existence.*";
P_HTM[3459]="*Katamassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni, upapattipaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni, bhavapaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni?**What person hasn’t given up the lower fetters, the fetters for getting reborn, or the fetters for getting a continued existence?*";
P_HTM[3460]="*Sakadāgāmissa.**A once-returner.*";
P_HTM[3461]="*Imassa kho, bhikkhave, puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni, upapattipaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni, bhavapaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni.**This is the person who hasn’t given up the lower fetters, the fetters for getting reborn, or the fetters for getting a continued existence.*";
P_HTM[3462]="*Katamassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, upapattipaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni, bhavapaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni?**What person has given up the lower fetters, but not the fetters for getting reborn, or the fetters for getting a continued existence?*";
P_HTM[3463]="*Uddhaṃsotassa akaniṭṭhagāmino.**One heading upstream, going to the Akaniṭṭha realm.*";
P_HTM[3464]="*Imassa kho, bhikkhave, puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, upapattipaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni, bhavapaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni.* **";
P_HTM[3465]="*Katamassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, upapattipaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, bhavapaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni?**What person has given up the lower fetters and the fetters for getting reborn, but not the fetters for getting a continued existence?*";
P_HTM[3466]="*Antarāparinibbāyissa.**One extinguished between one life and the next.*";
P_HTM[3467]="*Imassa kho, bhikkhave, puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, upapattipaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, bhavapaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni.* **";
P_HTM[3468]="*Katamassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, upapattipaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, bhavapaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni?**What person has given up the lower fetters, the fetters for getting reborn, and the fetters for getting a continued existence?*";
P_HTM[3469]="*Arahato.**A perfected one.*";
P_HTM[3470]="*Imassa kho, bhikkhave, puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, upapattipaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, bhavapaṭilābhiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni.* **";
P_HTM[3471]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3472]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3473]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Persons*";
P_HTM[3474]="*1. Saṃyojanasuttaṃ**Eloquence*";
P_HTM[3475]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3476]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3477]="*Yuttappaṭibhāno, no muttappaṭibhāno;**One who speaks on topic, but not fluently.*";
P_HTM[3478]="*muttappaṭibhāno, no yuttappaṭibhāno;**One who speaks fluently, but not on topic.*";
P_HTM[3479]="*yuttappaṭibhāno ca muttappaṭibhāno ca;**One who speaks on topic and fluently.*";
P_HTM[3480]="*neva yuttappaṭibhāno na muttappaṭibhāno—**One who speaks neither on topic nor fluently.*";
P_HTM[3481]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3482]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3483]="*2. Paṭibhānasuttaṃ**One Who Understands Immediately*";
P_HTM[3484]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3485]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3486]="*Ugghaṭitaññū, vipañcitaññū, neyyo, padaparamo—**One who understands immediately, one who understands after detailed explanation, one who needs personal training, and one who merely learns by rote.*";
P_HTM[3487]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3488]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3489]="*3. Ugghaṭitaññūsuttaṃ**The Fruits of Initiative*";
P_HTM[3490]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“These four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3491]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3492]="*Uṭṭhānaphalūpajīvī na kammaphalūpajīvī, kammaphalūpajīvī na uṭṭhānaphalūpajīvī, uṭṭhānaphalūpajīvī ceva kammaphalūpajīvī ca, neva uṭṭhānaphalūpajīvī na kammaphalūpajīvī—**~One who lives off the fruit of initiative, but not deeds; ~one who lives off the fruit of deeds, but not initiative; ~one who lives off the fruit of both initiative and deeds; and ~one who lives off the fruit of neither initiative nor deeds.*";
P_HTM[3493]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3494]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3495]="*4. Uṭṭhānaphalasuttaṃ**Blameworthy*";
P_HTM[3496]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3497]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3498]="*Sāvajjo, vajjabahulo, appavajjo, anavajjo.**The blameworthy, the mostly blameworthy, the slightly blameworthy, and the blameless.*";
P_HTM[3499]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo sāvajjo hoti?**And how is a person blameworthy?*";
P_HTM[3500]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sāvajjena kāyakammena samannāgato hoti, sāvajjena vacīkammena samannāgato hoti, sāvajjena manokammena samannāgato hoti.**It’s when a person does things by way of body, speech, and mind that are blameworthy.*";
P_HTM[3501]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo sāvajjo hoti.**That’s how a person is blameworthy.*";
P_HTM[3502]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo vajjabahulo hoti?**And how is a person mostly blameworthy?*";
P_HTM[3503]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sāvajjena bahulaṃ kāyakammena samannāgato hoti, appaṃ anavajjena;**It’s when a person does things by way of body, speech, and mind that are mostly blameworthy, but occasionally blameless.*";
P_HTM[3504]="*sāvajjena bahulaṃ vacīkammena samannāgato hoti, appaṃ anavajjena;* **";
P_HTM[3505]="*sāvajjena bahulaṃ manokammena samannāgato hoti, appaṃ anavajjena.* **";
P_HTM[3506]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo vajjabahulo hoti.**That’s how a person is mostly blameworthy.*";
P_HTM[3507]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo appavajjo hoti?**And how is a person slightly blameworthy?*";
P_HTM[3508]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo anavajjena bahulaṃ kāyakammena samannāgato hoti, appaṃ sāvajjena;**It’s when a person does things by way of body, speech, and mind that are mostly blameless, but occasionally blameworthy.*";
P_HTM[3509]="*anavajjena bahulaṃ vacīkammena samannāgato hoti, appaṃ sāvajjena;* **";
P_HTM[3510]="*anavajjena bahulaṃ manokammena samannāgato hoti, appaṃ sāvajjena.* **";
P_HTM[3511]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo appavajjo hoti.**That’s how a person is slightly blameworthy.*";
P_HTM[3512]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo anavajjo hoti?**And how is a person blameless?*";
P_HTM[3513]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo anavajjena kāyakammena samannāgato hoti, anavajjena vacīkammena samannāgato hoti, anavajjena manokammena samannāgato hoti.**It’s when a person does things by way of body, speech, and mind that are blameless.*";
P_HTM[3514]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo anavajjo hoti.**That’s how a person is blameless.*";
P_HTM[3515]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3516]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3517]="*5. Sāvajjasuttaṃ**Ethics (1st)*";
P_HTM[3518]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3519]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3520]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sīlesu na paripūrakārī hoti, samādhismiṃ na paripūrakārī, paññāya na paripūrakārī.**One person has not fulfilled ethics, immersion, or wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3521]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti, samādhismiṃ na paripūrakārī, paññāya na paripūrakārī.**One person has fulfilled ethics, but not immersion or wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3522]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti, samādhismiṃ paripūrakārī, paññāya na paripūrakārī.**One person has fulfilled ethics and immersion, but not wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3523]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti, samādhismiṃ paripūrakārī, paññāya paripūrakārī.**One person has fulfilled ethics, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3524]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3525]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3526]="*6. Paṭhamasīlasuttaṃ**Ethics (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3527]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3528]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3529]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na sīlagaru hoti na sīlādhipateyyo, na samādhigaru hoti na samādhādhipateyyo, na paññāgaru hoti na paññādhipateyyo.**One person doesn’t value or submit to ethics, immersion, or wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3530]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sīlagaru hoti sīlādhipateyyo, na samādhigaru hoti na samādhādhipateyyo, na paññāgaru hoti na paññādhipateyyo.**One person values and submits to ethics, but not to immersion or wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3531]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sīlagaru hoti sīlādhipateyyo, samādhigaru hoti samādhādhipateyyo, na paññāgaru hoti na paññādhipateyyo.**One person values and submits to ethics and immersion, but not wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3532]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sīlagaru hoti sīlādhipateyyo, samādhigaru hoti samādhādhipateyyo, paññāgaru hoti paññādhipateyyo.**One person values and submits to ethics, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3533]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3534]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3535]="*7. Dutiyasīlasuttaṃ**Retreat*";
P_HTM[3536]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3537]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3538]="*Nikaṭṭhakāyo anikaṭṭhacitto, anikaṭṭhakāyo nikaṭṭhacitto, anikaṭṭhakāyo ca anikaṭṭhacitto ca, nikaṭṭhakāyo ca nikaṭṭhacitto ca.**~One is on retreat in body, but not mind; ~one is on retreat in mind, but not body; ~one is on retreat in neither body nor mind; and ~one is on retreat in both body and mind.*";
P_HTM[3539]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo nikaṭṭhakāyo hoti anikaṭṭhacitto?**And how is a person on retreat in body, but not mind?*";
P_HTM[3540]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevati.**It’s when a person frequents remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[3541]="*So tattha kāmavitakkampi vitakketi byāpādavitakkampi vitakketi vihiṃsāvitakkampi vitakketi.**But they think sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts.*";
P_HTM[3542]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo nikaṭṭhakāyo hoti anikaṭṭhacitto.**That’s how a person is on retreat in body, but not mind.*";
P_HTM[3543]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo anikaṭṭhakāyo hoti nikaṭṭhacitto?**And how is a person on retreat in mind, but not body?*";
P_HTM[3544]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo naheva kho araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevati.**It’s when a person doesn’t frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[3545]="*So tattha nekkhammavitakkampi vitakketi abyāpādavitakkampi vitakketi avihiṃsāvitakkampi vitakketi.**But they think thoughts of renunciation, good will, and harmlessness.*";
P_HTM[3546]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo anikaṭṭhakāyo hoti nikaṭṭhacitto.**That’s how a person is on retreat in mind, but not body.*";
P_HTM[3547]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo anikaṭṭhakāyo ca hoti anikaṭṭhacitto ca?**And how is a person on retreat in neither body nor mind?*";
P_HTM[3548]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo naheva kho araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevati.**It’s when a person doesn’t frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[3549]="*So tattha kāmavitakkampi vitakketi byāpādavitakkampi vitakketi vihiṃsāvitakkampi vitakketi.**And they think sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts.*";
P_HTM[3550]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo anikaṭṭhakāyo ca hoti anikaṭṭhacitto ca.**That’s how a person is on retreat in neither body nor mind.*";
P_HTM[3551]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo nikaṭṭhakāyo ca hoti nikaṭṭhacitto ca?**And how is a person on retreat in both body and mind?*";
P_HTM[3552]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevati.**It’s when a person frequents remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[3553]="*So tattha nekkhammavitakkampi vitakketi abyāpādavitakkampi vitakketi avihiṃsāvitakkampi vitakketi.**And they think thoughts of renunciation, good will, and harmlessness.*";
P_HTM[3554]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo nikaṭṭhakāyo ca hoti nikaṭṭhacitto ca.**That’s how a person is on retreat in both body and mind.*";
P_HTM[3555]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3556]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3557]="*8. Nikaṭṭhasuttaṃ**Dhamma Speakers*";
P_HTM[3558]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, dhammakathikā.**“Mendicants, there are these four Dhamma speakers.*";
P_HTM[3559]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3560]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco dhammakathiko appañca bhāsati asahitañca;**One Dhamma speaker speaks little and off topic.*";
P_HTM[3561]="*parisā cassa na kusalā hoti sahitāsahitassa.**And their assembly can’t tell what’s on topic and what’s off topic.*";
P_HTM[3562]="*Evarūpo, bhikkhave, dhammakathiko evarūpāya parisāya dhammakathikotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**Such an assembly regards such a Dhamma speaker simply as a Dhamma speaker.*";
P_HTM[3563]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco dhammakathiko appañca bhāsati sahitañca;**One Dhamma speaker speaks little but stays on topic.*";
P_HTM[3564]="*parisā cassa kusalā hoti sahitāsahitassa.**And their assembly can tell what’s on topic and what’s off topic.*";
P_HTM[3565]="*Evarūpo, bhikkhave, dhammakathiko evarūpāya parisāya dhammakathikotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**Such an assembly regards such a Dhamma speaker simply as a Dhamma speaker.*";
P_HTM[3566]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco dhammakathiko bahuñca bhāsati asahitañca;**One Dhamma speaker speaks much but off topic.*";
P_HTM[3567]="*parisā cassa na kusalā hoti sahitāsahitassa.**And their assembly can’t tell what’s on topic and what’s off topic.*";
P_HTM[3568]="*Evarūpo, bhikkhave, dhammakathiko evarūpāya parisāya dhammakathikotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**Such an assembly regards such a Dhamma speaker simply as a Dhamma speaker.*";
P_HTM[3569]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco dhammakathiko bahuñca bhāsati sahitañca;**One Dhamma speaker speaks much and stays on topic.*";
P_HTM[3570]="*parisā cassa kusalā hoti sahitāsahitassa.**And their assembly can tell what’s on topic and what’s off topic.*";
P_HTM[3571]="*Evarūpo, bhikkhave, dhammakathiko evarūpāya parisāya dhammakathikotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**Such an assembly regards such a Dhamma speaker simply as a Dhamma speaker.*";
P_HTM[3572]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro dhammakathikā”ti.**These are the four Dhamma speakers.”*";
P_HTM[3573]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3574]="*9. Dhammakathikasuttaṃ**Speaker*";
P_HTM[3575]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, vādī.**“Mendicants, there are these four speakers.*";
P_HTM[3576]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3577]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, vādī atthato pariyādānaṃ gacchati, no byañjanato;**There’s a speaker who runs out of meaningful things to say, but not of ways of phrasing things.*";
P_HTM[3578]="*atthi, bhikkhave, vādī byañjanato pariyādānaṃ gacchati, no atthato;**There’s a speaker who runs out of ways of phrasing things, but not of meaningful things to say.*";
P_HTM[3579]="*atthi, bhikkhave, vādī atthato ca byañjanato ca pariyādānaṃ gacchati;**There’s a speaker who runs out of both meaningful things to say, and ways of phrasing things.*";
P_HTM[3580]="*atthi, bhikkhave, vādī nevatthato no byañjanato pariyādānaṃ gacchati.**There’s a speaker who never runs out of meaningful things to say, or ways of phrasing things.*";
P_HTM[3581]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro vādī.**These are the four speakers.*";
P_HTM[3582]="*Aṭṭhānametaṃ, bhikkhave, anavakāso yaṃ catūhi paṭisambhidāhi samannāgato atthato vā byañjanato vā pariyādānaṃ gaccheyyā”ti.**It is impossible, it cannot happen that someone accomplished in the four kinds of textual analysis will ever run out of meaningful things to say, or ways of phrasing things.”*";
P_HTM[3583]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3584]="*Puggalavaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[3585]="*Saṃyojanaṃ paṭibhāno,* **";
P_HTM[3586]="*ugghaṭitaññu uṭṭhānaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3587]="*Sāvajjo dve ca sīlāni,* **";
P_HTM[3588]="*nikaṭṭha dhamma vādī cāti.* **";
P_HTM[3589]="*10. Vādīsuttaṃ**Brightness*";
P_HTM[3590]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, ābhā.**“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of brightness.*";
P_HTM[3591]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3592]="*Candābhā, sūriyābhā, aggābhā, paññābhā—**The brightness of the moon, sun, fire, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3593]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso ābhā.**These are the four kinds of brightness.*";
P_HTM[3594]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ catunnaṃ ābhānaṃ yadidaṃ paññābhā”ti.**The best of these four kinds of brightness is the brightness of wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[3595]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3596]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Brightness*";
P_HTM[3597]="*1. Ābhāsuttaṃ**Radiance*";
P_HTM[3598]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, pabhā.**“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of radiance.*";
P_HTM[3599]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3600]="*Candappabhā, sūriyappabhā, aggippabhā, paññāpabhā—**The radiance of the moon, sun, fire, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3601]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso pabhā.**These are the four kinds of radiance.*";
P_HTM[3602]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ catunnaṃ pabhānaṃ yadidaṃ paññāpabhā”ti.**The best of these four kinds of radiance is the radiance of wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[3603]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3604]="*2. Pabhāsuttaṃ**Light*";
P_HTM[3605]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, ālokā.**“Mendicants, there are these four lights.*";
P_HTM[3606]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3607]="*Candāloko, sūriyāloko, aggāloko, paññāloko—**The lights of the moon, sun, fire, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3608]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro ālokā.**These are the four lights.*";
P_HTM[3609]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ catunnaṃ ālokānaṃ yadidaṃ paññāloko”ti.**The best of these four lights is the light of wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[3610]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3611]="*3. Ālokasuttaṃ**Shining*";
P_HTM[3612]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, obhāsā.**“Mendicants, there are four kinds of shining.*";
P_HTM[3613]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3614]="*Candobhāso, sūriyobhāso, aggobhāso, paññobhāso—**The shining of the moon, sun, fire, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3615]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro obhāsā.**These are the four kinds of shining.*";
P_HTM[3616]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ catunnaṃ obhāsānaṃ yadidaṃ paññobhāso”ti.**The best of these four kinds of shining is the shining of wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[3617]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3618]="*4. Obhāsasuttaṃ**Lamps*";
P_HTM[3619]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, pajjotā.**“Mendicants, there are these four lamps.*";
P_HTM[3620]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3621]="*Candapajjoto, sūriyapajjoto, aggipajjoto, paññāpajjoto—**The lamps of the moon, sun, fire, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3622]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro pajjotā.**These are the four lamps.*";
P_HTM[3623]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ catunnaṃ pajjotānaṃ yadidaṃ paññāpajjoto”ti.**The best of these four lamps is the lamp of wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[3624]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3625]="*5. Pajjotasuttaṃ**Times (1st)*";
P_HTM[3626]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, kālā.**“Mendicants, there are these four times.*";
P_HTM[3627]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3628]="*Kālena dhammassavanaṃ, kālena dhammasākacchā, kālena sammasanā, kālena vipassanā—**A time for listening to the teaching, a time for discussing the teaching, a time for serenity, and a time for discernment.*";
P_HTM[3629]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro kālā”ti.**These are the four times.”*";
P_HTM[3630]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3631]="*6. Paṭhamakālasuttaṃ**Times (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3632]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, kālā sammā bhāviyamānā sammā anuparivattiyamānā anupubbena āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpenti.**“Mendicants, when these four times are rightly developed and progressed, they gradually lead to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[3633]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3634]="*Kālena dhammassavanaṃ, kālena dhammasākacchā, kālena sammasanā, kālena vipassanā—**A time for listening to the teaching, a time for discussing the teaching, a time for serenity, and a time for discernment.*";
P_HTM[3635]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro kālā sammā bhāviyamānā sammā anuparivattiyamānā anupubbena āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpenti.* **";
P_HTM[3636]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, uparipabbate thullaphusitake deve vassante taṃ udakaṃ yathāninnaṃ pavattamānaṃ pabbatakandarapadarasākhā paripūreti; pabbatakandarapadarasākhā paripūrā kusobbhe paripūrenti; kusobbhā paripūrā mahāsobbhe paripūrenti; mahāsobbhā paripūrā kunnadiyo paripūrenti; kunnadiyo paripūrā mahānadiyo paripūrenti; mahānadiyo paripūrā samuddaṃ paripūrenti.**It’s like when it rains heavily on a mountain top, and the water flows downhill to fill the hollows, crevices, and creeks. As they become full, they fill up the pools. The pools fill up the lakes, the lakes fill up the streams, and the streams fill up the rivers. And as the rivers become full, they fill up the ocean.*";
P_HTM[3637]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ime cattāro kālā sammā bhāviyamānā sammā anuparivattiyamānā anupubbena āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpentī”ti.**In the same way, when these four times are rightly developed and progressed, they gradually lead to the ending of defilements.”*";
P_HTM[3638]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3639]="*7. Dutiyakālasuttaṃ**Bad Conduct*";
P_HTM[3640]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, vacīduccaritāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of bad conduct by way of speech.*";
P_HTM[3641]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3642]="*Musāvādo, pisuṇā vācā, pharusā vācā, samphappalāpo—**Speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical.*";
P_HTM[3643]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri vacīduccaritānī”ti.**These are the four kinds of bad conduct by way of speech.”*";
P_HTM[3644]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3645]="*8. Duccaritasuttaṃ**Good Conduct*";
P_HTM[3646]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, vacīsucaritāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of good conduct by way of speech.*";
P_HTM[3647]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3648]="*Saccavācā, apisuṇā vācā, saṇhā vācā, mantabhāsā—**Speech that’s true, harmonious, gentle, and thoughtful.*";
P_HTM[3649]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri vacīsucaritānī”ti.**These are the four kinds of good conduct by way of speech.”*";
P_HTM[3650]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3651]="*9. Sucaritasuttaṃ**Essentials*";
P_HTM[3652]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, sārā.**“Mendicants, there are these four essentials.*";
P_HTM[3653]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3654]="*Sīlasāro, samādhisāro, paññāsāro, vimuttisāro—**Ethics, immersion, wisdom, and freedom are essentials.*";
P_HTM[3655]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro sārā”ti.**These are the four essentials.”*";
P_HTM[3656]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3657]="*Ābhāvaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[3658]="*Ābhā pabhā ca ālokā,* **";
P_HTM[3659]="*obhāsā ceva pajjotā;* **";
P_HTM[3660]="*Dve kālā caritā dve ca,* **";
P_HTM[3661]="*honti sārena te dasāti.* **";
P_HTM[3662]="*Tatiyo paṇṇāsako samatto.* **";
P_HTM[3663]="*10. Sārasuttaṃ**Faculties*";
P_HTM[3664]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, indriyāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four faculties.*";
P_HTM[3665]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3666]="*Saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ—**The faculties of faith, energy, mindfulness, and immersion.*";
P_HTM[3667]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri indriyānī”ti.**These are the four faculties.”*";
P_HTM[3668]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3669]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Faculties*";
P_HTM[3670]="*1. Indriyasuttaṃ**The Power of Faith*";
P_HTM[3671]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, balāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four powers.*";
P_HTM[3672]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3673]="*Saddhābalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, satibalaṃ, samādhibalaṃ—**The powers of faith, energy, mindfulness, and immersion.*";
P_HTM[3674]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri balānī”ti.**These are the four powers.”*";
P_HTM[3675]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3676]="*2. Saddhābalasuttaṃ**The Power of Wisdom*";
P_HTM[3677]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, balāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four powers.*";
P_HTM[3678]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3679]="*Paññābalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, anavajjabalaṃ, saṅgahabalaṃ—**The powers of wisdom, energy, blamelessness, and inclusiveness.*";
P_HTM[3680]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri balānī”ti.**These are the four powers.”*";
P_HTM[3681]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3682]="*3. Paññābalasuttaṃ**The Power of Mindfulness*";
P_HTM[3683]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, balāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four powers.*";
P_HTM[3684]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3685]="*Satibalaṃ, samādhibalaṃ, anavajjabalaṃ, saṅgahabalaṃ—**The powers of mindfulness, immersion, blamelessness, and inclusiveness.*";
P_HTM[3686]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri balānī”ti.**These are the four powers.”*";
P_HTM[3687]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3688]="*4. Satibalasuttaṃ**The Power of Reflection*";
P_HTM[3689]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, balāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four powers.*";
P_HTM[3690]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3691]="*Paṭisaṅkhānabalaṃ, bhāvanābalaṃ, anavajjabalaṃ, saṅgahabalaṃ—**The powers of reflection, development, blamelessness, and inclusiveness.*";
P_HTM[3692]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri balānī”ti.**These are the four powers.”*";
P_HTM[3693]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3694]="*5. Paṭisaṅkhānabalasuttaṃ**Eons*";
P_HTM[3695]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, kappassa asaṅkhyeyyāni.**“Mendicants, an eon contains four uncountable periods.*";
P_HTM[3696]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3697]="*Yadā, bhikkhave, kappo saṃvaṭṭati, taṃ na sukaraṃ saṅkhātuṃ—**When an eon contracts, it’s not easy to calculate*";
P_HTM[3698]="*ettakāni vassānīti vā, ettakāni vassasatānīti vā, ettakāni vassasahassānīti vā, ettakāni vassasatasahassānīti vā.**how many years, how many hundreds or thousands or hundreds of thousands of years it takes.*";
P_HTM[3699]="*Yadā, bhikkhave, kappo saṃvaṭṭo tiṭṭhati, taṃ na sukaraṃ saṅkhātuṃ—**When an eon remains fully contracted, it’s not easy to calculate*";
P_HTM[3700]="*ettakāni vassānīti vā, ettakāni vassasatānīti vā, ettakāni vassasahassānīti vā, ettakāni vassasatasahassānīti vā.**how many years, how many hundreds or thousands or hundreds of thousands of years it takes.*";
P_HTM[3701]="*Yadā, bhikkhave, kappo vivaṭṭati, taṃ na sukaraṃ saṅkhātuṃ—**When an eon expands, it’s not easy to calculate*";
P_HTM[3702]="*ettakāni vassānīti vā, ettakāni vassasatānīti vā, ettakāni vassasahassānīti vā, ettakāni vassasatasahassānīti vā.**how many years, how many hundreds or thousands or hundreds of thousands of years it takes.*";
P_HTM[3703]="*Yadā, bhikkhave, kappo vivaṭṭo tiṭṭhati, taṃ na sukaraṃ saṅkhātuṃ—**When an eon remains fully expanded, it’s not easy to calculate*";
P_HTM[3704]="*ettakāni vassānīti vā, ettakāni vassasatānīti vā, ettakāni vassasahassānīti vā, ettakāni vassasatasahassānīti vā.**how many years, how many hundreds or thousands or hundreds of thousands of years it takes.*";
P_HTM[3705]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri kappassa asaṅkhyeyyānī”ti.**These are the four uncountable periods of an eon.”*";
P_HTM[3706]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3707]="*6. Kappasuttaṃ**Illness*";
P_HTM[3708]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, rogā.**“Mendicants, there are two kinds of illness.*";
P_HTM[3709]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[3710]="*Kāyiko ca rogo cetasiko ca rogo.**Mental and physical.*";
P_HTM[3711]="*Dissanti, bhikkhave, sattā kāyikena rogena ekampi vassaṃ ārogyaṃ paṭijānamānā, dvepi vassāni ārogyaṃ paṭijānamānā, tīṇipi vassāni ārogyaṃ paṭijānamānā, cattāripi vassāni ārogyaṃ paṭijānamānā, pañcapi vassāni ārogyaṃ paṭijānamānā, dasapi vassāni ārogyaṃ paṭijānamānā, vīsatipi vassāni ārogyaṃ paṭijānamānā, tiṃsampi vassāni ārogyaṃ paṭijānamānā, cattārīsampi vassāni ārogyaṃ paṭijānamānā, paññāsampi vassāni ārogyaṃ paṭijānamānā, vassasatampi, bhiyyopi ārogyaṃ paṭijānamānā.**Some sentient beings are seen who can claim to be free of physical illness for a year, or two, or three years … even up to a hundred years or more.*";
P_HTM[3712]="*Te, bhikkhave, sattā sudullabhā lokasmiṃ ye cetasikena rogena muhuttampi ārogyaṃ paṭijānanti, aññatra khīṇāsavehi.**But it’s very hard to find any sentient beings in the world who can claim to be free of mental illness even for a moment, apart from those who have ended the defilements.*";
P_HTM[3713]="*Cattārome, bhikkhave, pabbajitassa rogā.**There are four kinds of illness for those gone forth.*";
P_HTM[3714]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3715]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mahiccho hoti vighātavā asantuṭṭho itarītaracīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena.**To start with, a mendicant has many wishes, is frustrated, and is not content with any kind of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[3716]="*So mahiccho samāno vighātavā asantuṭṭho itarītaracīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena pāpikaṃ icchaṃ paṇidahati anavaññappaṭilābhāya lābhasakkārasilokappaṭilābhāya.**Because of this, they focus their corrupt wishes on being looked up to, and on getting material possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[3717]="*So uṭṭhahati ghaṭati vāyamati anavaññappaṭilābhāya lābhasakkārasilokappaṭilābhāya.**They try hard, strive, and make an effort to get these things.*";
P_HTM[3718]="*So saṅkhāya kulāni upasaṅkamati, saṅkhāya nisīdati, saṅkhāya dhammaṃ bhāsati, saṅkhāya uccārapassāvaṃ sandhāreti.**They have an ulterior motive when they visit families. They have an ulterior motive when they sit down, when they speak on Dhamma, and even when they hold it in when they need to go to the toilet.*";
P_HTM[3719]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro pabbajitassa rogā.**These are the four kinds of illness for those gone forth.*";
P_HTM[3720]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[3721]="*‘na mahicchā bhavissāma vighātavanto asantuṭṭhā itarītaracīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena, na pāpikaṃ icchaṃ paṇidahissāma anavaññappaṭilābhāya lābhasakkārasilokappaṭilābhāya, na uṭṭhahissāma na ghaṭessāma na vāyamissāma anavaññappaṭilābhāya lābhasakkārasilokappaṭilābhāya, khamā bhavissāma sītassa uṇhassa jighacchāya pipāsāya ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ duruttānaṃ durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ, uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ adhivāsakajātikā bhavissāmā’ti.**‘We will not have many wishes or be frustrated. We will be content with any kind of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. We won’t focus our corrupt wishes on being looked up to, and on getting material possessions, honor, and popularity. We won’t try hard, strive, and make an effort to get these things. We will endure cold, heat, hunger, and thirst. We will endure the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles. We will endure rude and unwelcome criticism. We will put up with physical pain—sharp, severe, acute, unpleasant, disagreeable, and life-threatening.’*";
P_HTM[3722]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[3723]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3724]="*7. Rogasuttaṃ**Decline*";
P_HTM[3725]="*Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3726]="*“āvuso bhikkhave”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[3727]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3728]="*Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:**Sāriputta said this:*";
P_HTM[3729]="*“Yo hi koci, āvuso, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā cattāro dhamme attani samanupassati, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**“Reverends, any monk or nun who sees four things inside themselves should conclude:*";
P_HTM[3730]="*‘parihāyāmi kusalehi dhammehi’.**‘My skillful qualities are declining.*";
P_HTM[3731]="*Parihānametaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā.**For this is what the Buddha calls decline.’*";
P_HTM[3732]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3733]="*Rāgavepullattaṃ, dosavepullattaṃ, mohavepullattaṃ, gambhīresu kho panassa ṭhānāṭhānesu paññācakkhu na kamati.**They have much greed, much hate, and much delusion; and their wisdom eye doesn’t go into the many deep matters.*";
P_HTM[3734]="*Yo hi koci, āvuso, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā ime cattāro dhamme attani samanupassati, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**Any monk or nun who sees these four things inside themselves should conclude:*";
P_HTM[3735]="*‘parihāyāmi kusalehi dhammehi’.**‘My skillful qualities are declining.*";
P_HTM[3736]="*Parihānametaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā.**For this is what the Buddha calls decline.’*";
P_HTM[3737]="*Yo hi koci, āvuso, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā cattāro dhamme attani samanupassati, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**Any monk or nun who sees four things inside themselves should conclude:*";
P_HTM[3738]="*‘na parihāyāmi kusalehi dhammehi’.**‘My skillful qualities are not declining.*";
P_HTM[3739]="*Aparihānametaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā.**For this is what the Buddha calls non-decline.’*";
P_HTM[3740]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3741]="*Rāgatanuttaṃ, dosatanuttaṃ, mohatanuttaṃ, gambhīresu kho panassa ṭhānāṭhānesu paññācakkhu kamati.**Their greed, hate, and delusion grow less; and their wisdom eye goes into the many deep matters.*";
P_HTM[3742]="*Yo hi koci, āvuso, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā ime cattāro dhamme attani samanupassati, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**Any monk or nun who sees these four things inside themselves should conclude:*";
P_HTM[3743]="*‘na parihāyāmi kusalehi dhammehi’.**‘My skillful qualities are not declining.*";
P_HTM[3744]="*Aparihānametaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā”ti.**For this is what the Buddha calls non-decline.’”*";
P_HTM[3745]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3746]="*8. Parihānisuttaṃ**Nun*";
P_HTM[3747]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3748]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[3749]="*Atha kho aññatarā bhikkhunī aññataraṃ purisaṃ āmantesi:**And then a certain nun addressed a man,*";
P_HTM[3750]="*“ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, yenayyo ānando tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena ayyassa ānandassa pāde sirasā vanda:**“Please, mister, go to Venerable Ānanda, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Say to him:*";
P_HTM[3751]="*‘itthannāmā, bhante, bhikkhunī ābādhikinī dukkhitā bāḷhagilānā.**‘Sir, the nun named so-and-so is sick, suffering, and gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[3752]="*Sā ayyassa ānandassa pāde sirasā vandatī’ti. Evañca vadehi:**She bows with her head to your feet.’ And then say:*";
P_HTM[3753]="*‘sādhu kira, bhante, ayyo ānando yena bhikkhunupassayo yena sā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti.**‘Sir, please go to the nuns’ quarters to visit that nun out of compassion.’”*";
P_HTM[3754]="*“Evaṃ, ayye”ti kho so puriso tassā bhikkhuniyā paṭissutvā yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so puriso āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, ma’am,” that man replied. He did as the nun asked.*";
P_HTM[3755]="*“Itthannāmā, bhante, bhikkhunī ābādhikinī dukkhitā bāḷhagilānā.* **";
P_HTM[3756]="*Sā āyasmato ānandassa pāde sirasā vandati, evañca vadeti:* **";
P_HTM[3757]="*‘sādhu kira, bhante, āyasmā ānando yena bhikkhunupassayo yena sā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3758]="*Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā ānando tuṇhībhāvena.**Ānanda consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[3759]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena bhikkhunupassayo yena sā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami.**Then Ānanda robed up and went to the nuns’ quarters to visit that nun, taking his bowl and robe.*";
P_HTM[3760]="*Addasā kho sā bhikkhunī āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**That nun saw Ānanda coming off in the distance.*";
P_HTM[3761]="*Disvā sasīsaṃ pārupitvā mañcake nipajji.**She wrapped herself up from head to foot and laid down on her cot.*";
P_HTM[3762]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena sā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho āyasmā ānando taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to her, and sat down on the seat spread out. Then Ānanda said to the nun:*";
P_HTM[3763]="*“Āhārasambhūto ayaṃ, bhagini, kāyo āhāraṃ nissāya.**“Sister, this body is produced by food. Relying on food,*";
P_HTM[3764]="*Āhāro pahātabbo.**you should give up food.*";
P_HTM[3765]="*Taṇhāsambhūto ayaṃ, bhagini, kāyo taṇhaṃ nissāya.**This body is produced by craving. Relying on craving,*";
P_HTM[3766]="*Taṇhā pahātabbā.**you should give up craving.*";
P_HTM[3767]="*Mānasambhūto ayaṃ, bhagini, kāyo mānaṃ nissāya.**This body is produced by conceit. Relying on conceit,*";
P_HTM[3768]="*Māno pahātabbo.**you should give up conceit.*";
P_HTM[3769]="*Methunasambhūto ayaṃ, bhagini, kāyo.**This body is produced by sex.*";
P_HTM[3770]="*Methune ca setughāto vutto bhagavatā.**The Buddha spoke of breaking off everything to do with sex.*";
P_HTM[3771]="*‘Āhārasambhūto ayaṃ, bhagini, kāyo āhāraṃ nissāya.**‘This body is produced by food. Relying on food,*";
P_HTM[3772]="*Āhāro pahātabbo’ti, iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ.**you should give up food.’ This is what I said,*";
P_HTM[3773]="*Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[3774]="*Idha, bhagini, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso āhāraṃ āhāreti:**Take a mendicant who reflects properly on the food that they eat:*";
P_HTM[3775]="*‘neva davāya na madāya na maṇḍanāya na vibhūsanāya, yāvadeva imassa kāyassa ṭhitiyā yāpanāya vihiṃsūparatiyā brahmacariyānuggahāya. Iti purāṇañca vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāmi, navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi. Yātrā ca me bhavissati anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro cā’ti.**‘Not for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration, but only to sustain this body, to avoid harm, and to support spiritual practice. In this way, I shall put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and I will live blamelessly and at ease.’*";
P_HTM[3776]="*So aparena samayena āhāraṃ nissāya āhāraṃ pajahati.**After some time, relying on food, they give up food.*";
P_HTM[3777]="*‘Āhārasambhūto ayaṃ, bhagini, kāyo āhāraṃ nissāya āhāro pahātabbo’t* **";
P_HTM[3778]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s why I said what I said.*";
P_HTM[3779]="*‘Taṇhāsambhūto ayaṃ, bhagini, kāyo taṇhaṃ nissāya.**‘This body is produced by craving. Relying on craving,*";
P_HTM[3780]="*Taṇhā pahātabbā’ti, iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ.**you should give up craving.’ This is what I said,*";
P_HTM[3781]="*Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[3782]="*Idha, bhagini, bhikkhu suṇāti:**Take a mendicant who hears this:*";
P_HTM[3783]="*‘itthannāmo kira bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī’ti.**‘They say that the mendicant named so-and-so has realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.’*";
P_HTM[3784]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[3785]="*‘kudāssu nāma ahampi āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissāmī’ti.**‘Oh, when will I too realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. …’*";
P_HTM[3786]="*So aparena samayena taṇhaṃ nissāya taṇhaṃ pajahati.**After some time, relying on craving, they give up craving.*";
P_HTM[3787]="*‘Taṇhāsambhūto ayaṃ, bhagini, kāyo taṇhaṃ nissāya taṇhā pahātabbā’ti,* **";
P_HTM[3788]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That's why I said what I said.*";
P_HTM[3789]="*‘Mānasambhūto ayaṃ, bhagini, kāyo mānaṃ nissāya.**‘This body is produced by conceit. Relying on conceit,*";
P_HTM[3790]="*Māno pahātabbo’ti, iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ.**you should give up conceit.’ This is what I said,*";
P_HTM[3791]="*Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[3792]="*Idha, bhagini, bhikkhu suṇāti:**Take a mendicant who hears this:*";
P_HTM[3793]="*‘itthannāmo kira bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī’ti.**‘They say that the mendicant named so-and-so has realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.’*";
P_HTM[3794]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[3795]="*‘so hi nāma āyasmā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissati;**‘Well, that venerable can realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. …*";
P_HTM[3796]="*kimaṅgaṃ panāhan’ti.**Why can’t I?’*";
P_HTM[3797]="*So aparena samayena mānaṃ nissāya mānaṃ pajahati.**After some time, relying on conceit, they give up conceit.*";
P_HTM[3798]="*‘Mānasambhūto ayaṃ, bhagini, kāyo, mānaṃ nissāya māno pahātabbo’ti,* **";
P_HTM[3799]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s why I said what I said.*";
P_HTM[3800]="*Methunasambhūto ayaṃ, bhagini, kāyo.**‘This body is produced by sex.*";
P_HTM[3801]="*Methune ca setughāto vutto bhagavatā”ti.**The Buddha spoke of breaking off everything to do with sex.’”*";
P_HTM[3802]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī mañcakā vuṭṭhahitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā āyasmato ānandassa pādesu sirasā nipatitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**Then that nun rose from her cot, placed her robe over one shoulder, bowed with her head at Ānanda’s feet, and said,*";
P_HTM[3803]="*“accayo maṃ, bhante, accagamā, yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yāhaṃ evamakāsiṃ.**“I have made a mistake, sir. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of me to act in that way.*";
P_HTM[3804]="*Tassā me, bhante, ayyo ānando accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu, āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti.**Please, sir, accept my mistake for what it is, so I can restrain myself in future.”*";
P_HTM[3805]="*“Taggha taṃ, bhagini, accayo accagamā, yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yā tvaṃ evamakāsi.**“Indeed, sister, you made a mistake. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of you to act in that way.*";
P_HTM[3806]="*Yato ca kho tvaṃ, bhagini, accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikarosi, taṃ te mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma.**But since you have recognized your mistake for what it is, and have dealt with it properly, I accept it.*";
P_HTM[3807]="*Vuddhi hesā, bhagini, ariyassa vinaye yo accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikaroti āyatiṃ saṃvaraṃ āpajjatī”ti.**For it is growth in the training of the noble one to recognize a mistake for what it is, deal with it properly, and commit to restraint in the future.”*";
P_HTM[3808]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3809]="*9. Bhikkhunīsuttaṃ**The Training of a Holy One*";
P_HTM[3810]="*“Sugato vā, bhikkhave, loke tiṭṭhamāno sugatavinayo vā tadassa bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ.**“Mendicants, a Holy One or a Holy One’s training remain in the world for the welfare and happiness of the people, out of compassion for the world, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[3811]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sugato?**And who is a Holy One?*";
P_HTM[3812]="*Idha, bhikkhave, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā.**It’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.*";
P_HTM[3813]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, sugato.**This is a Holy One.*";
P_HTM[3814]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sugatavinayo?**And what is the training of a Holy One?*";
P_HTM[3815]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[3816]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, sugatavinayo.**This is the training of a Holy One.*";
P_HTM[3817]="*Evaṃ sugato vā, bhikkhave, loke tiṭṭhamāno sugatavinayo vā tadassa bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānanti.**This is how a Holy One or a Holy One’s training remain in the world for the welfare and happiness of the people, out of compassion for the world, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[3818]="*Cattārome, bhikkhave, dhammā saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**These four things lead to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3819]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3820]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhū duggahitaṃ suttantaṃ pariyāpuṇanti dunnikkhittehi padabyañjanehi.**Firstly, the mendicants memorize discourses that they learned incorrectly, with misplaced words and phrases.*";
P_HTM[3821]="*Dunnikkhittassa, bhikkhave, padabyañjanassa atthopi dunnayo hoti.**When the words and phrases are misplaced, the meaning is misinterpreted.*";
P_HTM[3822]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the first thing that leads to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3823]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū dubbacā honti dovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgatā akkhamā appadakkhiṇaggāhino anusāsaniṃ.**Furthermore, the mendicants are hard to admonish, having qualities that make them hard to admonish. They’re impatient, and don’t take instruction respectfully.*";
P_HTM[3824]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the second thing that leads to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3825]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā, te na sakkaccaṃ suttantaṃ paraṃ vācenti.**Furthermore, the mendicants who are very learned—knowledgeable in the scriptures, who have memorized the teachings, the monastic law, and the outlines—don’t carefully make others recite the discourses.*";
P_HTM[3826]="*Tesaṃ accayena chinnamūlako suttanto hoti appaṭisaraṇo.**When they pass away, the discourses are cut off at the root, with no-one to preserve them.*";
P_HTM[3827]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the third thing that leads to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3828]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, therā bhikkhū bāhulikā honti sāthalikā, okkamane pubbaṅgamā, paviveke nikkhittadhurā, na vīriyaṃ ārabhanti appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**Furthermore, the senior mendicants are indulgent and slack, leaders in backsliding, neglecting seclusion, not rousing energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.*";
P_HTM[3829]="*Tesaṃ pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjati.**Those who come after them follow their example.*";
P_HTM[3830]="*Sāpi hoti bāhulikā sāthalikā, okkamane pubbaṅgamā, paviveke nikkhittadhurā, na vīriyaṃ ārabhati appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**They too become indulgent and slack, leaders in backsliding, neglecting seclusion, not rousing energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.*";
P_HTM[3831]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fourth thing that leads to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3832]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro dhammā saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattantīti.**These are four things that lead to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3833]="*Cattārome, bhikkhave, dhammā saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**These four things lead to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3834]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3835]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhū suggahitaṃ suttantaṃ pariyāpuṇanti sunikkhittehi padabyañjanehi.**Firstly, the mendicants memorize discourses that have been learned correctly, with well placed words and phrases.*";
P_HTM[3836]="*Sunikkhittassa, bhikkhave, padabyañjanassa atthopi sunayo hoti.**When the words and phrases are well placed, the meaning is interpreted correctly.*";
P_HTM[3837]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the first thing that leads to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3838]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū suvacā honti sovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgatā khamā padakkhiṇaggāhino anusāsaniṃ.**Furthermore, the mendicants are easy to admonish, having qualities that make them easy to admonish. They’re patient, and take instruction respectfully.*";
P_HTM[3839]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the second thing that leads to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3840]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā, te sakkaccaṃ suttantaṃ paraṃ vācenti.**Furthermore, the mendicants who are very learned—knowledgeable in the scriptures, who have memorized the teachings, the monastic law, and the outlines—carefully make others recite the discourses.*";
P_HTM[3841]="*Tesaṃ accayena nacchinnamūlako suttanto hoti sappaṭisaraṇo.**When they pass away, the discourses aren’t cut off at the root, and they have someone to preserve them.*";
P_HTM[3842]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the third thing that leads to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3843]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, therā bhikkhū na bāhulikā honti na sāthalikā, okkamane nikkhittadhurā, paviveke pubbaṅgamā, vīriyaṃ ārabhanti appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**Furthermore, the senior mendicants are not indulgent or slack, nor are they backsliders; instead, they take the lead in seclusion, rousing energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.*";
P_HTM[3844]="*Tesaṃ pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjati.**Those who come after them follow their example.*";
P_HTM[3845]="*Sāpi hoti na bāhulikā na sāthalikā, okkamane nikkhittadhurā, paviveke pubbaṅgamā, vīriyaṃ ārabhati appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**They too aren’t indulgent or slack …*";
P_HTM[3846]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fourth thing that leads to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3847]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro dhammā saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattantī”ti.**These are four things that lead to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3848]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3849]="*Indriyavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[3850]="*Indriyāni saddhā paññā,* **";
P_HTM[3851]="*sati saṅkhānapañcamaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3852]="*Kappo rogo parihāni,* **";
P_HTM[3853]="*bhikkhunī sugatena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[3854]="*10. Sugatavinayasuttaṃ**In Brief*";
P_HTM[3855]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, paṭipadā.**“Mendicants, there are four ways of practice.*";
P_HTM[3856]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3857]="*Dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā—**~Painful practice with slow insight, ~painful practice with swift insight, ~pleasant practice with slow insight, and ~pleasant practice with swift insight.*";
P_HTM[3858]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso paṭipadā”ti.**These are the four ways of practice.”*";
P_HTM[3859]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3860]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Practice*";
P_HTM[3861]="*1. Saṃkhittasuttaṃ**In Detail*";
P_HTM[3862]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, paṭipadā.**“Mendicants, there are four ways of practice.*";
P_HTM[3863]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3864]="*Dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā.**~Painful practice with slow insight, ~painful practice with swift insight, ~pleasant practice with slow insight, and ~pleasant practice with swift insight.*";
P_HTM[3865]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā?**And what’s the painful practice with slow insight?*";
P_HTM[3866]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pakatiyāpi tibbarāgajātiko hoti, abhikkhaṇaṃ rāgajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**It’s when someone is ordinarily full of acute greed, hate, and delusion. They often feel the pain and sadness that greed, hate, and delusion bring.*";
P_HTM[3867]="*Pakatiyāpi tibbadosajātiko hoti, abhikkhaṇaṃ dosajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[3868]="*Pakatiyāpi tibbamohajātiko hoti, abhikkhaṇaṃ mohajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[3869]="*Tassimāni pañcindriyāni mudūni pātubhavanti—**They have these five faculties weakly:*";
P_HTM[3870]="*saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ.**faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3871]="*So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ muduttā dandhaṃ ānantariyaṃ pāpuṇāti āsavānaṃ khayāya.**Because of this, they only slowly attain the conditions for ending the defilements in the present life.*";
P_HTM[3872]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā.**This is called the painful practice with slow insight.*";
P_HTM[3873]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā?**And what’s the painful practice with swift insight?*";
P_HTM[3874]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pakatiyāpi tibbarāgajātiko hoti, abhikkhaṇaṃ rāgajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**It’s when someone is ordinarily full of acute greed, hate, and delusion. They often feel the pain and sadness that greed, hate, and delusion bring.*";
P_HTM[3875]="*Pakatiyāpi tibbadosajātiko hoti, abhikkhaṇaṃ dosajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[3876]="*Pakatiyāpi tibbamohajātiko hoti, abhikkhaṇaṃ mohajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[3877]="*Tassimāni pañcindriyāni adhimattāni pātubhavanti—**And they have these five faculties strongly:*";
P_HTM[3878]="*saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ.**faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3879]="*So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ adhimattattā khippaṃ ānantariyaṃ pāpuṇāti āsavānaṃ khayāya.**Because of this, they swiftly attain the conditions for ending the defilements in the present life.*";
P_HTM[3880]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā.**This is called the painful practice with swift insight.*";
P_HTM[3881]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā?**And what’s pleasant practice with slow insight?*";
P_HTM[3882]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pakatiyāpi na tibbarāgajātiko hoti, nābhikkhaṇaṃ rāgajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**It’s when someone is not ordinarily full of acute greed, hate, and delusion. They rarely feel the pain and sadness that greed, hate, and delusion bring.*";
P_HTM[3883]="*Pakatiyāpi na tibbadosajātiko hoti, nābhikkhaṇaṃ dosajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[3884]="*Pakatiyāpi na tibbamohajātiko hoti, nābhikkhaṇaṃ mohajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[3885]="*Tassimāni pañcindriyāni mudūni pātubhavanti—**They have these five faculties weakly:*";
P_HTM[3886]="*saddhindriyaṃ … pe … paññindriyaṃ.**faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3887]="*So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ muduttā dandhaṃ ānantariyaṃ pāpuṇāti āsavānaṃ khayāya.**Because of this, they only slowly attain the conditions for ending the defilements in the present life.*";
P_HTM[3888]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā.**This is called the pleasant practice with slow insight.*";
P_HTM[3889]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā?**And what’s the pleasant practice with swift insight?*";
P_HTM[3890]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pakatiyāpi na tibbarāgajātiko hoti, nābhikkhaṇaṃ rāgajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**It’s when someone is not ordinarily full of acute greed, hate, and delusion. They rarely feel the pain and sadness that greed, hate, and delusion bring.*";
P_HTM[3891]="*Pakatiyāpi na tibbadosajātiko hoti, nābhikkhaṇaṃ dosajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[3892]="*Pakatiyāpi na tibbamohajātiko hoti, nābhikkhaṇaṃ mohajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[3893]="*Tassimāni pañcindriyāni adhimattāni pātubhavanti—**They have these five faculties strongly:*";
P_HTM[3894]="*saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ.**faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3895]="*So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ adhimattattā khippaṃ ānantariyaṃ pāpuṇāti āsavānaṃ khayāya.**Because of this, they swiftly attain the conditions for ending the defilements in the present life.*";
P_HTM[3896]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā.**This is called the pleasant practice with swift insight.*";
P_HTM[3897]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso paṭipadā”ti.**These are the four ways of practice.”*";
P_HTM[3898]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3899]="*2. Vitthārasuttaṃ**Ugly*";
P_HTM[3900]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, paṭipadā.**“Mendicants, there are four ways of practice.*";
P_HTM[3901]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3902]="*Dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā.**~Painful practice with slow insight, ~painful practice with swift insight, ~pleasant practice with slow insight, and ~pleasant practice with swift insight.*";
P_HTM[3903]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā?**And what’s the painful practice with slow insight?*";
P_HTM[3904]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asubhānupassī kāye viharati, āhāre paṭikūlasaññī, sabbaloke anabhiratisaññī, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī;**It’s when a mendicant meditates observing the ugliness of the body, perceives the repulsiveness of food, perceives dissatisfaction with the whole world, observes the impermanence of all conditions,*";
P_HTM[3905]="*maraṇasaññā kho panassa ajjhattaṃ sūpaṭṭhitā hoti.**and has well established the perception of their own death.*";
P_HTM[3906]="*So imāni pañca sekhabalāni upanissāya viharati—**They rely on these five powers of a trainee:*";
P_HTM[3907]="*saddhābalaṃ, hiribalaṃ, ottappabalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, paññābalaṃ.**faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3908]="*Tassimāni pañcindriyāni mudūni pātubhavanti—**But they have these five faculties weakly:*";
P_HTM[3909]="*saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ.**faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3910]="*So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ muduttā dandhaṃ ānantariyaṃ pāpuṇāti āsavānaṃ khayāya.**Because of this, they only slowly attain the conditions for ending the defilements in the present life.*";
P_HTM[3911]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā.**This is called the painful practice with slow insight.*";
P_HTM[3912]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā?**And what’s the painful practice with swift insight?*";
P_HTM[3913]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asubhānupassī kāye viharati, āhāre paṭikūlasaññī, sabbaloke anabhiratisaññī, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī;**It’s when a mendicant meditates observing the ugliness of the body, perceives the repulsiveness of food, perceives dissatisfaction with the whole world, observes the impermanence of all conditions,*";
P_HTM[3914]="*maraṇasaññā kho panassa ajjhattaṃ sūpaṭṭhitā hoti.**and has well established the perception of their own death.*";
P_HTM[3915]="*So imāni pañca sekhabalāni upanissāya viharati—**They rely on these five powers of a trainee:*";
P_HTM[3916]="*saddhābalaṃ … pe … paññābalaṃ.**faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3917]="*Tassimāni pañcindriyāni adhimattāni pātubhavanti—**And they have these five faculties strongly:*";
P_HTM[3918]="*saddhindriyaṃ … pe … paññindriyaṃ.**faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3919]="*So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ adhimattattā khippaṃ ānantariyaṃ pāpuṇāti āsavānaṃ khayāya.**Because of this, they swiftly attain the conditions for ending the defilements in the present life.*";
P_HTM[3920]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā.**This is called the painful practice with swift insight.*";
P_HTM[3921]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā?**And what’s the pleasant practice with slow insight?*";
P_HTM[3922]="*Idha bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[3923]="*vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[3924]="*pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[3925]="*sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[3926]="*So imāni pañca sekhabalāni upanissāya viharati—**They rely on these five powers of a trainee:*";
P_HTM[3927]="*saddhābalaṃ … pe … paññābalaṃ.**faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3928]="*Tassimāni pañcindriyāni mudūni pātubhavanti—**But they have these five faculties weakly:*";
P_HTM[3929]="*saddhindriyaṃ … pe … paññindriyaṃ.**faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3930]="*So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ muduttā dandhaṃ ānantariyaṃ pāpuṇāti āsavānaṃ khayāya.**Because of this, they only slowly attain the conditions for ending the defilements in the present life.*";
P_HTM[3931]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā.**This is called the pleasant practice with slow insight.*";
P_HTM[3932]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā?**And what’s the pleasant practice with swift insight?*";
P_HTM[3933]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant … enters and remains in the first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption …*";
P_HTM[3934]="*So imāni pañca sekhabalāni upanissāya viharati—**They rely on these five powers of a trainee:*";
P_HTM[3935]="*saddhābalaṃ, hiribalaṃ, ottappabalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, paññābalaṃ.**faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3936]="*Tassimāni pañcindriyāni adhimattāni pātubhavanti—**And they have these five faculties strongly:*";
P_HTM[3937]="*saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ.**faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3938]="*So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ adhimattattā khippaṃ ānantariyaṃ pāpuṇāti āsavānaṃ khayāya.**Because of this, they swiftly attain the conditions for ending the defilements in the present life.*";
P_HTM[3939]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā.**This is called the pleasant practice with swift insight.*";
P_HTM[3940]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso paṭipadā”ti.**These are the four ways of practice.”*";
P_HTM[3941]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3942]="*3. Asubhasuttaṃ**Patient (1st)*";
P_HTM[3943]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, paṭipadā.**“Mendicants, there are four ways of practice.*";
P_HTM[3944]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3945]="*Akkhamā paṭipadā, khamā paṭipadā, damā paṭipadā, samā paṭipadā.**Impatient practice, patient practice, taming practice, and calming practice.*";
P_HTM[3946]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, akkhamā paṭipadā?**And what’s the impatient practice?*";
P_HTM[3947]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco akkosantaṃ paccakkosati, rosantaṃ paṭirosati, bhaṇḍantaṃ paṭibhaṇḍati.**It’s when someone abuses, annoys, or argues with you, and you abuse, annoy, or argue right back at them.*";
P_HTM[3948]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, akkhamā paṭipadā.**This is called the impatient practice.*";
P_HTM[3949]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, khamā paṭipadā?**And what’s the patient practice?*";
P_HTM[3950]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco akkosantaṃ na paccakkosati, rosantaṃ na paṭirosati, bhaṇḍantaṃ na paṭibhaṇḍati.**It’s when someone abuses, annoys, or argues with you, and you don’t abuse, annoy, or argue back at them.*";
P_HTM[3951]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, khamā paṭipadā.**This is called the patient practice.*";
P_HTM[3952]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, damā paṭipadā?**And what’s the taming practice?*";
P_HTM[3953]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī;**When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[3954]="*yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ; cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving restraint over it.*";
P_HTM[3955]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[3956]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[3957]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[3958]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[3959]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī;**When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[3960]="*yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati manindriyaṃ; manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving restraint over it.*";
P_HTM[3961]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, damā paṭipadā.**This is called the taming practice.*";
P_HTM[3962]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, samā paṭipadā?**And what’s the calming practice?*";
P_HTM[3963]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ nādhivāseti pajahati vinodeti sameti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti; uppannaṃ byāpādavitakkaṃ … pe … uppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ … uppannuppanne pāpake akusale dhamme nādhivāseti pajahati vinodeti sameti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti.**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t tolerate a sensual, malicious, or cruel thought. They don’t tolerate any bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen, but give them up, get rid of them, calm them, eliminate them, and obliterate them.*";
P_HTM[3964]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, samā paṭipadā.**This is called the calming practice.*";
P_HTM[3965]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso paṭipadā”ti.**These are the four ways of practice.”*";
P_HTM[3966]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3967]="*4. Paṭhamakhamasuttaṃ**Patience (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3968]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, paṭipadā.**“Mendicants, there are four ways of practice.*";
P_HTM[3969]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3970]="*Akkhamā paṭipadā, khamā paṭipadā, damā paṭipadā, samā paṭipadā.**Impatient practice, patient practice, taming practice, and calming practice.*";
P_HTM[3971]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, akkhamā paṭipadā?**And what’s the impatient practice?*";
P_HTM[3972]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco akkhamo hoti sītassa uṇhassa jighacchāya pipāsāya, ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ duruttānaṃ durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ anadhivāsakajātiko hoti.**It’s when a mendicant cannot endure cold, heat, hunger, and thirst. They cannot endure the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles. They cannot endure rude and unwelcome criticism. And they cannot put up with physical pain—sharp, severe, acute, unpleasant, disagreeable, and life-threatening.*";
P_HTM[3973]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, akkhamā paṭipadā.**This is called the impatient practice.*";
P_HTM[3974]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, khamā paṭipadā?**And what’s the patient practice?*";
P_HTM[3975]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco khamo hoti sītassa uṇhassa jighacchāya pipāsāya, ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ duruttānaṃ durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ adhivāsakajātiko hoti.**It’s when a mendicant endures cold, heat, hunger, and thirst. They endure the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles. They endure rude and unwelcome criticism. And they put up with physical pain—sharp, severe, acute, unpleasant, disagreeable, and life-threatening.*";
P_HTM[3976]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, khamā paṭipadā.**This is called the patient practice.*";
P_HTM[3977]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, damā paṭipadā?**And what’s the taming practice?*";
P_HTM[3978]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti … pe …**When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details. …*";
P_HTM[3979]="*sotena saddaṃ sutvā …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[3980]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[3981]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[3982]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[3983]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī;**When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[3984]="*yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati manindriyaṃ; manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving restraint over it.*";
P_HTM[3985]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, damā paṭipadā.**This is called the taming practice.*";
P_HTM[3986]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, samā paṭipadā?**And what’s the calming practice?*";
P_HTM[3987]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ nādhivāseti pajahati vinodeti sameti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti, uppannaṃ byāpādavitakkaṃ … pe … uppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ … uppannuppanne pāpake akusale dhamme nādhivāseti pajahati vinodeti sameti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti.**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t tolerate a sensual, malicious, or cruel thought. They don’t tolerate any bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen, but give them up, get rid of them, calm them, eliminate them, and obliterate them.*";
P_HTM[3988]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, samā paṭipadā.**This is called the calming practice.*";
P_HTM[3989]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso paṭipadā”ti.**These are the four ways of practice.”*";
P_HTM[3990]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3991]="*5. Dutiyakhamasuttaṃ**Both*";
P_HTM[3992]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, paṭipadā.**“Mendicants, there are four ways of practice.*";
P_HTM[3993]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3994]="*Dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā.**~Painful practice with slow insight, ~painful practice with swift insight, ~pleasant practice with slow insight, and ~pleasant practice with swift insight.*";
P_HTM[3995]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ paṭipadā dukkhā dandhābhiññā, ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭipadā ubhayeneva hīnā akkhāyati. Yampāyaṃ paṭipadā dukkhā, imināpāyaṃ hīnā akkhāyati; yampāyaṃ paṭipadā dandhā, imināpāyaṃ hīnā akkhāyati.**Of these, the painful practice with slow insight is said to be inferior in both ways: because it’s painful and because it’s slow.*";
P_HTM[3996]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭipadā ubhayeneva hīnā akkhāyati.**This practice is said to be inferior in both ways.*";
P_HTM[3997]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ paṭipadā dukkhā khippābhiññā, ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭipadā dukkhattā hīnā akkhāyati.**The painful practice with swift insight is said to be inferior because it’s painful.*";
P_HTM[3998]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ paṭipadā sukhā dandhābhiññā, ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭipadā dandhattā hīnā akkhāyati.**The pleasant practice with slow insight is said to be inferior because it’s slow.*";
P_HTM[3999]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ paṭipadā sukhā khippābhiññā, ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭipadā ubhayeneva paṇītā akkhāyati. Yampāyaṃ paṭipadā sukhā, imināpāyaṃ paṇītā akkhāyati; yampāyaṃ paṭipadā khippā, imināpāyaṃ paṇītā akkhāyati.**The pleasant practice with swift insight is said to be superior in both ways: because it’s pleasant, and because it’s swift.*";
P_HTM[4000]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭipadā ubhayeneva paṇītā akkhāyati.**This practice is said to be superior in both ways.*";
P_HTM[4001]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso paṭipadā”ti.**These are the four ways of practice.”*";
P_HTM[4002]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4003]="*6. Ubhayasuttaṃ**Moggallāna’s Practice*";
P_HTM[4004]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yenāyasmā mahāmoggallāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā mahāmoggallānena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Venerable Sāriputta went up to Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4005]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Sāriputta sat down to one side and said to Mahāmoggallāna:*";
P_HTM[4006]="*“Catasso imā, āvuso moggallāna, paṭipadā.**“Reverend Moggallāna, there are four ways of practice.*";
P_HTM[4007]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4008]="*Dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā.**~Painful practice with slow insight, ~painful practice with swift insight, ~pleasant practice with slow insight, and ~pleasant practice with swift insight.*";
P_HTM[4009]="*Imā kho, āvuso, catasso paṭipadā.**These are the four ways of practice.*";
P_HTM[4010]="*Imāsaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ paṭipadānaṃ katamaṃ te paṭipadaṃ āgamma anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimuttan”ti?**Which one of these four ways of practice did you rely on to free your mind from defilements by not grasping?”*";
P_HTM[4011]="*“Catasso imā, āvuso sāriputta, paṭipadā.**“Reverend Sāriputta …*";
P_HTM[4012]="*Katamā catasso?* **";
P_HTM[4013]="*Dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā.* **";
P_HTM[4014]="*Imā kho, āvuso, catasso paṭipadā.* **";
P_HTM[4015]="*Imāsaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ paṭipadānaṃ yāyaṃ paṭipadā dukkhā khippābhiññā, imaṃ me paṭipadaṃ āgamma anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimuttan”ti.**I relied on the painful practice with swift insight to free my mind from defilements by not grasping.”*";
P_HTM[4016]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4017]="*7. Mahāmoggallānasuttaṃ**Sāriputta’s Practice*";
P_HTM[4018]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Venerable Mahāmoggallāna went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4019]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Mahāmoggallāna sat down to one side, and said to Sāriputta:*";
P_HTM[4020]="*“Catasso imā, āvuso sāriputta, paṭipadā.**“Reverend Sāriputta, there are four ways of practice.*";
P_HTM[4021]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4022]="*Dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā.**~Painful practice with slow insight, ~painful practice with swift insight, ~pleasant practice with slow insight, and ~pleasant practice with swift insight.*";
P_HTM[4023]="*Imā kho, āvuso, catasso paṭipadā.**These are the four ways of practice.*";
P_HTM[4024]="*Imāsaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ paṭipadānaṃ katamaṃ te paṭipadaṃ āgamma anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimuttan”ti?**Which one of these four ways of practice did you rely on to free your mind from defilements by not grasping?”*";
P_HTM[4025]="*“Catasso imā, āvuso moggallāna, paṭipadā.**“Reverend Moggallāna …*";
P_HTM[4026]="*Katamā catasso?* **";
P_HTM[4027]="*Dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, dukkhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññā.* **";
P_HTM[4028]="*Imā kho, āvuso, catasso paṭipadā.* **";
P_HTM[4029]="*Imāsaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ paṭipadānaṃ yāyaṃ paṭipadā sukhā khippābhiññā, imaṃ me paṭipadaṃ āgamma anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimuttan”ti.**I relied on the pleasant practice with swift insight to free my mind from defilements by not grasping.”*";
P_HTM[4030]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4031]="*8. Sāriputtasuttaṃ**Extra Effort*";
P_HTM[4032]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[4033]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4034]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo diṭṭheva dhamme sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti.**One person becomes fully extinguished in the present life by making extra effort.*";
P_HTM[4035]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo kāyassa bhedā sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti.**One person becomes fully extinguished when the body breaks up by making extra effort.*";
P_HTM[4036]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo diṭṭheva dhamme asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti.**One person becomes fully extinguished in the present life without making extra effort.*";
P_HTM[4037]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo kāyassa bhedā asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti.**One person becomes fully extinguished when the body breaks up without making extra effort.*";
P_HTM[4038]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo diṭṭheva dhamme sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti?**And how does a person become fully extinguished in the present life by making extra effort?*";
P_HTM[4039]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asubhānupassī kāye viharati, āhāre paṭikūlasaññī, sabbaloke anabhiratisaññī, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī.**It’s when a mendicant meditates observing the ugliness of the body, perceives the repulsiveness of food, perceives dissatisfaction with the whole world, observes the impermanence of all conditions,*";
P_HTM[4040]="*Maraṇasaññā kho panassa ajjhattaṃ sūpaṭṭhitā hoti.**and has well established the perception of their own death.*";
P_HTM[4041]="*So imāni pañca sekhabalāni upanissāya viharati—**They rely on these five powers of a trainee:*";
P_HTM[4042]="*saddhābalaṃ, hiribalaṃ, ottappabalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, paññābalaṃ.**faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4043]="*Tassimāni pañcindriyāni adhimattāni pātubhavanti—**And they have these five faculties strongly:*";
P_HTM[4044]="*saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ.**faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4045]="*So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ adhimattattā diṭṭheva dhamme sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti.**Because of the strength of the five faculties, they become fully extinguished in the present life by making extra effort.*";
P_HTM[4046]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo diṭṭheva dhamme sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti.**That’s how a person becomes fully extinguished in the present life by making extra effort.*";
P_HTM[4047]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo kāyassa bhedā sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti?**How does a person become fully extinguished when the body breaks up by making extra effort?*";
P_HTM[4048]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asubhānupassī kāye viharati, āhāre paṭikūlasaññī, sabbaloke anabhiratisaññī, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī.**It’s when a mendicant meditates observing the ugliness of the body, perceives the repulsiveness of food, perceives dissatisfaction with the whole world, observes the impermanence of all conditions,*";
P_HTM[4049]="*Maraṇasaññā kho panassa ajjhattaṃ sūpaṭṭhitā hoti.**and has well established the perception of their own death.*";
P_HTM[4050]="*So imāni pañca sekhabalāni upanissāya viharati—**They rely on these five powers of a trainee:*";
P_HTM[4051]="*saddhābalaṃ, hiribalaṃ, ottappabalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, paññābalaṃ.**faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4052]="*Tassimāni pañcindriyāni mudūni pātubhavanti—**But they have these five faculties weakly:*";
P_HTM[4053]="*saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ.**faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4054]="*So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ muduttā kāyassa bhedā sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti.**Because of the weakness of the five faculties, they become fully extinguished when the body breaks up by making extra effort.*";
P_HTM[4055]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo kāyassa bhedā sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti.**That’s how a person becomes fully extinguished when the body breaks up by making extra effort.*";
P_HTM[4056]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo diṭṭheva dhamme asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti?**And how does a person become fully extinguished in the present life without making extra effort?*";
P_HTM[4057]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant … enters and remains in the first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption …*";
P_HTM[4058]="*So imāni pañca sekhabalāni upanissāya viharati—**They rely on these five powers of a trainee:*";
P_HTM[4059]="*saddhābalaṃ … pe … paññābalaṃ.**faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4060]="*Tassimāni pañcindriyāni adhimattāni pātubhavanti—**And they have these five faculties strongly:*";
P_HTM[4061]="*saddhindriyaṃ … pe … paññindriyaṃ.**faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4062]="*So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ adhimattattā diṭṭheva dhamme asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti.**Because of the strength of the five faculties, they become fully extinguished in the present life without making extra effort.*";
P_HTM[4063]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo diṭṭheva dhamme asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti.**That’s how a person becomes fully extinguished in the present life without making extra effort.*";
P_HTM[4064]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo kāyassa bhedā asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti?**And how does a person become fully extinguished when the body breaks up without making extra effort?*";
P_HTM[4065]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant … enters and remains in the first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption …*";
P_HTM[4066]="*So imāni pañca sekhabalāni upanissāya viharati—**They rely on these five powers of a trainee:*";
P_HTM[4067]="*saddhābalaṃ, hiribalaṃ, ottappabalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, paññābalaṃ.**faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4068]="*Tassimāni pañcindriyāni … pe … paññindriyaṃ.**But they have these five faculties weakly: faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4069]="*So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ muduttā kāyassa bhedā asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti.**Because of the weakness of the five faculties, they become fully extinguished when the body breaks up without making extra effort.*";
P_HTM[4070]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo kāyassa bhedā asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti.**That’s how a person becomes fully extinguished when the body breaks up without making extra effort.*";
P_HTM[4071]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[4072]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4073]="*9. Sasaṅkhārasuttaṃ**In Conjunction*";
P_HTM[4074]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4075]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[4076]="*Tatra kho āyasmā ānando bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Ānanda addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[4077]="*“āvuso bhikkhave”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[4078]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4079]="*Āyasmā ānando etadavoca:**Ānanda said this:*";
P_HTM[4080]="*“Yo hi koci, āvuso, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā mama santike arahattappattiṃ byākaroti, sabbo so catūhi maggehi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena.**“Reverends, all of the monks and nuns who declare in my presence that they have attained perfection, did so by one or other of four paths.*";
P_HTM[4081]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4082]="*Idha, āvuso, bhikkhu samathapubbaṅgamaṃ vipassanaṃ bhāveti.**Take a mendicant who develops serenity before discernment.*";
P_HTM[4083]="*Tassa samathapubbaṅgamaṃ vipassanaṃ bhāvayato maggo sañjāyati.**As they do so, the path is born in them.*";
P_HTM[4084]="*So taṃ maggaṃ āsevati bhāveti bahulīkaroti.**They cultivate, develop, and make much of it.*";
P_HTM[4085]="*Tassa taṃ maggaṃ āsevato bhāvayato bahulīkaroto saṃyojanāni pahīyanti, anusayā byantīhonti.**By doing so, they give up the fetters and eliminate the underlying tendencies.*";
P_HTM[4086]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu vipassanāpubbaṅgamaṃ samathaṃ bhāveti.**Another mendicant develops discernment before serenity.*";
P_HTM[4087]="*Tassa vipassanāpubbaṅgamaṃ samathaṃ bhāvayato maggo sañjāyati.**As they do so, the path is born in them.*";
P_HTM[4088]="*So taṃ maggaṃ āsevati bhāveti bahulīkaroti.**They cultivate, develop, and make much of it.*";
P_HTM[4089]="*Tassa taṃ maggaṃ āsevato bhāvayato bahulīkaroto saṃyojanāni pahīyanti, anusayā byantīhonti.**By doing so, they give up the fetters and eliminate the underlying tendencies.*";
P_HTM[4090]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu samathavipassanaṃ yuganaddhaṃ bhāveti.**Another mendicant develops serenity and discernment in conjunction.*";
P_HTM[4091]="*Tassa samathavipassanaṃ yuganaddhaṃ bhāvayato maggo sañjāyati.**As they do so, the path is born in them.*";
P_HTM[4092]="*So taṃ maggaṃ āsevati bhāveti bahulīkaroti.**They cultivate, develop, and make much of it.*";
P_HTM[4093]="*Tassa taṃ maggaṃ āsevato bhāvayato bahulīkaroto saṃyojanāni pahīyanti, anusayā byantīhonti.**By doing so, they give up the fetters and eliminate the underlying tendencies.*";
P_HTM[4094]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno dhammuddhaccaviggahitaṃ mānasaṃ hoti.**Another mendicant’s mind is seized by restlessness to realize the teaching.*";
P_HTM[4095]="*Hoti so, āvuso, samayo yaṃ taṃ cittaṃ ajjhattameva santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati.**But there comes a time when their mind is stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[4096]="*Tassa maggo sañjāyati.**The path is born in them.*";
P_HTM[4097]="*So taṃ maggaṃ āsevati bhāveti bahulīkaroti.**They cultivate, develop, and make much of it.*";
P_HTM[4098]="*Tassa taṃ maggaṃ āsevato bhāvayato bahulīkaroto saṃyojanāni pahīyanti, anusayā byantīhonti.**By doing so, they give up the fetters and eliminate the underlying tendencies.*";
P_HTM[4099]="*Yo hi koci, āvuso, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā mama santike arahattappattiṃ byākaroti, sabbo so imehi catūhi maggehi, etesaṃ vā aññatarenā”ti.**All of the monks and nuns who declare in my presence that they have attained perfection, did so by one or other of these four paths.”*";
P_HTM[4100]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4101]="*Paṭipadāvaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[4102]="*Saṅkhittaṃ vitthārāsubhaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[4103]="*Dve khamā ubhayena ca;* **";
P_HTM[4104]="*Moggallāno sāriputto,* **";
P_HTM[4105]="*Sasaṅkhāraṃ yuganaddhena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[4106]="*10. Yuganaddhasuttaṃ**Intention*";
P_HTM[4107]="*“Kāye vā, bhikkhave, sati kāyasañcetanāhetu uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ.**“Mendicants, as long as there’s a body, the intention that gives rise to bodily action causes pleasure and pain to arise in oneself.*";
P_HTM[4108]="*Vācāya vā, bhikkhave, sati vacīsañcetanāhetu uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ.**As long as there’s a voice, the intention that gives rise to verbal action causes pleasure and pain to arise in oneself.*";
P_HTM[4109]="*Mane vā, bhikkhave, sati manosañcetanāhetu uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ avijjāpaccayāva.**As long as there’s a mind, the intention that gives rise to mental action causes pleasure and pain to arise in oneself. But these only apply when conditioned by ignorance.*";
P_HTM[4110]="*Sāmaṃ vā taṃ, bhikkhave, kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ.**By oneself one makes the choice that gives rise to bodily, verbal, and mental action, conditioned by which that pleasure and pain arise in oneself.*";
P_HTM[4111]="*Pare vāssa taṃ, bhikkhave, kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharonti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ.**Or else others make the choice …*";
P_HTM[4112]="*Sampajāno vā taṃ, bhikkhave, kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ.**One consciously makes the choice …*";
P_HTM[4113]="*Asampajāno vā taṃ, bhikkhave, kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ.**Or else one unconsciously makes the choice …*";
P_HTM[4114]="*Sāmaṃ vā taṃ, bhikkhave, vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4115]="*pare vāssa taṃ, bhikkhave, vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharonti;* **";
P_HTM[4116]="*yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4117]="*sampajāno vā taṃ, bhikkhave, vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4118]="*asampajāno vā taṃ, bhikkhave, vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4119]="*Sāmaṃ vā taṃ, bhikkhave, manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4120]="*pare vāssa taṃ, bhikkhave, manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharonti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4121]="*sampajāno vā taṃ, bhikkhave, manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4122]="*asampajāno vā taṃ, bhikkhave, manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4123]="*Imesu, bhikkhave, dhammesu avijjā anupatitā,**Ignorance is included in all these things.*";
P_HTM[4124]="*avijjāya tveva asesavirāganirodhā so kāyo na hoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ, sā vācā na hoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ, so mano na hoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ,**But when ignorance fades away and ceases with nothing left over, there is no body and no voice and no mind, conditioned by which that pleasure and pain arise in oneself.*";
P_HTM[4125]="*khettaṃ taṃ na hoti … pe … vatthu taṃ na hoti … pe … āyatanaṃ taṃ na hoti … pe … adhikaraṇaṃ taṃ na hoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhanti.**There is no field, no ground, no scope, and no basis, conditioned by which that pleasure and pain arise in oneself.*";
P_HTM[4126]="*Cattārome, bhikkhave, attabhāvapaṭilābhā.**Mendicants, there are four kinds of reincarnation.*";
P_HTM[4127]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4128]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, attabhāvapaṭilābho, yasmiṃ attabhāvapaṭilābhe attasañcetanā kamati, no parasañcetanā.**There is a reincarnation where one’s own intention is effective, not that of others.*";
P_HTM[4129]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, attabhāvapaṭilābho, yasmiṃ attabhāvapaṭilābhe parasañcetanā kamati, no attasañcetanā.**There is a reincarnation where the intention of others is effective, not one’s own.*";
P_HTM[4130]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, attabhāvapaṭilābho, yasmiṃ attabhāvapaṭilābhe attasañcetanā ca kamati parasañcetanā ca.**There is a reincarnation where both one’s own and others’ intentions are effective.*";
P_HTM[4131]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, attabhāvapaṭilābho, yasmiṃ attabhāvapaṭilābhe nevattasañcetanā kamati, no parasañcetanā.**There is a reincarnation where neither one’s own nor others’ intentions are effective.*";
P_HTM[4132]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro attabhāvapaṭilābhā”ti.**These are the four kinds of reincarnation.”*";
P_HTM[4133]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Sāriputta said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4134]="*“imassa kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi:**“Sir, this is how I understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief statement.*";
P_HTM[4135]="*‘tatra, bhante, yāyaṃ attabhāvapaṭilābho yasmiṃ attabhāvapaṭilābhe attasañcetanā kamati no parasañcetanā, attasañcetanāhetu tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhā kāyā cuti hoti.**Take the case of the reincarnation where one’s own intention is effective, not that of others. Those sentient beings pass away from that realm due to their own intention.*";
P_HTM[4136]="*Tatra, bhante, yāyaṃ attabhāvapaṭilābho yasmiṃ attabhāvapaṭilābhe parasañcetanā kamati no attasañcetanā, parasañcetanāhetu tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhā kāyā cuti hoti.**Take the case of the reincarnation where the intention of others is effective, not one’s own. Those sentient beings pass away from that realm due to the intention of others.*";
P_HTM[4137]="*Tatra, bhante, yāyaṃ attabhāvapaṭilābho yasmiṃ attabhāvapaṭilābhe attasañcetanā ca kamati parasañcetanā ca, attasañcetanā ca parasañcetanā ca hetu tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhā kāyā cuti hoti.**Take the case of the reincarnation where both one’s own and others’ intentions are effective. Those sentient beings pass away from that realm due to both their own and others’ intentions.*";
P_HTM[4138]="*Tatra, bhante, yāyaṃ attabhāvapaṭilābho yasmiṃ attabhāvapaṭilābhe neva attasañcetanā kamati no parasañcetanā, katame tena devā daṭṭhabbā’”ti?**But sir, in the case of the reincarnation where neither one’s own nor others’ intentions are effective, what kind of gods does this refer to?”*";
P_HTM[4139]="*“Nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpagā, sāriputta, devā tena daṭṭhabbā”ti.**“Sāriputta, it refers to the gods reborn in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.”*";
P_HTM[4140]="*“Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce sattā tamhā kāyā cutā āgāmino honti āgantāro itthattaṃ?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings pass away from that realm as returners who come back to this state of existence,*";
P_HTM[4141]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce sattā tamhā kāyā cutā anāgāmino honti anāgantāro itthattan”ti?**while others are non-returners who don’t come back?”*";
P_HTM[4142]="*“Idha, sāriputta, ekaccassa puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni appahīnāni honti, so diṭṭheva dhamme nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**“Sāriputta, take a person who hasn’t given up the lower fetters. In the present life they enter and abide in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[4143]="*So tadassādeti, taṃ nikāmeti, tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati;**They enjoy it and like it and find it satisfying.*";
P_HTM[4144]="*tattha ṭhito tadadhimutto tabbahulavihārī aparihīno kālaṃ kurumāno nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**If they abide in that, are committed to it, and meditate on it often without losing it, when they die they’re reborn in the company of the gods of the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[4145]="*So tato cuto āgāmī hoti āgantā itthattaṃ.**When they pass away from there, they’re a returner, who comes back to this state of existence.*";
P_HTM[4146]="*Idha pana, sāriputta, ekaccassa puggalassa orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni honti, so diṭṭheva dhamme nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Sāriputta, take a person who has given up the lower fetters. In the present life they enter and abide in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[4147]="*So tadassādeti, taṃ nikāmeti, tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati;**They enjoy it and like it and find it satisfying.*";
P_HTM[4148]="*tattha ṭhito tadadhimutto tabbahulavihārī aparihīno kālaṃ kurumāno nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**If they abide in that, are committed to it, and meditate on it often without losing it, when they die they’re reborn in the company of the gods of the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[4149]="*So tato cuto anāgāmī hoti anāgantā itthattaṃ.**When they pass away from there, they’re a non-returner, not coming back to this state of existence.*";
P_HTM[4150]="*Ayaṃ kho, sāriputta, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena m’idhekacce sattā tamhā kāyā cutā āgāmino honti āgantāro itthattaṃ.**This is the cause, this is the reason why some sentient beings pass away from that realm as returners who come back to this state of existence,*";
P_HTM[4151]="*Ayaṃ pana, sāriputta, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena m’idhekacce sattā tamhā kāyā cutā anāgāmino honti anāgantāro itthattan”ti.**while others are non-returners who don’t come back.”*";
P_HTM[4152]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4153]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Intention*";
P_HTM[4154]="*1. Cetanāsuttaṃ**Sāriputta’s Attainment of Textual Analysis*";
P_HTM[4155]="*Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[4156]="*“āvuso bhikkhave”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[4157]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4158]="*Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:**Sāriputta said this:*";
P_HTM[4159]="*“Addhamāsūpasampannena me, āvuso, atthapaṭisambhidā sacchikatā odhiso byañjanaso.**“Reverends, I realized the textual analysis of the meaning—piece by piece and expression by expression—a fortnight after I ordained.*";
P_HTM[4160]="*Tamahaṃ anekapariyāyena ācikkhāmi desemi paññāpemi paṭṭhapemi vivarāmi vibhajāmi uttānīkaromi.**In many ways I explain, teach, assert, establish, clarify, analyze, and reveal it.*";
P_HTM[4161]="*Yassa kho panassa kaṅkhā vā vimati vā, so maṃ pañhena.**Whoever has any doubt or uncertainty, let them ask me,*";
P_HTM[4162]="*Ahaṃ veyyākaraṇena sammukhībhūto no satthā yo no dhammānaṃ sukusalo.**I will answer. Our teacher is present, he who is so very skilled in our teachings.*";
P_HTM[4163]="*Addhamāsūpasampannena me, āvuso, dhammapaṭisambhidā sacchikatā odhiso byañjanaso.**I realized the textual analysis of the text—piece by piece and expression by expression—a fortnight after I ordained. …*";
P_HTM[4164]="*Tamahaṃ anekapariyāyena ācikkhāmi desemi paññāpemi paṭṭhapemi vivarāmi vibhajāmi uttānīkaromi.* **";
P_HTM[4165]="*Yassa kho panassa kaṅkhā vā vimati vā, so maṃ pañhena.* **";
P_HTM[4166]="*Ahaṃ veyyākaraṇena sammukhībhūto no satthā yo no dhammānaṃ sukusalo.* **";
P_HTM[4167]="*Addhamāsūpasampannena me, āvuso, niruttipaṭisambhidā sacchikatā odhiso byañjanaso.**I realized the textual analysis of terminology—piece by piece and expression by expression—a fortnight after I ordained. …*";
P_HTM[4168]="*Tamahaṃ anekapariyāyena ācikkhāmi desemi paññāpemi paṭṭhapemi vivarāmi vibhajāmi uttānīkaromi.* **";
P_HTM[4169]="*Yassa kho panassa kaṅkhā vā vimati vā, so maṃ pañhena.* **";
P_HTM[4170]="*Ahaṃ veyyākaraṇena sammukhībhūto no satthā yo no dhammānaṃ sukusalo.* **";
P_HTM[4171]="*Addhamāsūpasampannena me, āvuso, paṭibhānapaṭisambhidā sacchikatā odhiso byañjanaso.**I realized the textual analysis of eloquence—piece by piece and expression by expression—a fortnight after I ordained.*";
P_HTM[4172]="*Tamahaṃ anekapariyāyena ācikkhāmi desemi paññāpemi paṭṭhapemi vivarāmi vibhajāmi uttānīkaromi.**In many ways I explain, teach, assert, establish, clarify, analyze, and reveal it.*";
P_HTM[4173]="*Yassa kho panassa kaṅkhā vā vimati vā, so maṃ pañhena.**If anyone has any doubt or uncertainty, let them ask me,*";
P_HTM[4174]="*Ahaṃ veyyākaraṇena sammukhībhūto no satthā yo no dhammānaṃ sukusalo”ti.**I will answer. Our teacher is present, he who is so very skilled in our teachings.”*";
P_HTM[4175]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4176]="*2. Vibhattisuttaṃ**With Mahākoṭṭhita*";
P_HTM[4177]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4178]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Mahākoṭṭhita sat down to one side, and said to Sāriputta:*";
P_HTM[4179]="*“Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthaññaṃ kiñcī”ti?**“Reverend, when the six fields of contact have faded away and ceased with nothing left over, does something else exist?”*";
P_HTM[4180]="*“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso”.**“Don’t put it like that, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4181]="*“Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā natthaññaṃ kiñcī”ti?**“Does nothing else exist?”*";
P_HTM[4182]="*“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso”.**“Don’t put it like that, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4183]="*“Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthi ca natthi ca aññaṃ kiñcī”ti?**“Do both something else and nothing else exist?”*";
P_HTM[4184]="*“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso”.**“Don’t put it like that, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4185]="*“Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā nevatthi no natthaññaṃ kiñcī”ti?**“Do neither something else nor nothing else exist?”*";
P_HTM[4186]="*“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso”.**“Don’t put it like that, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4187]="*“‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno ‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.**“Reverend, when asked whether—when the six fields of contact have faded away and ceased with nothing left over—something else exists, you say ‘don’t put it like that’.*";
P_HTM[4188]="*‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā natthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:**When asked whether nothing else exists,*";
P_HTM[4189]="*‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.**you say ‘don’t put it like that’.*";
P_HTM[4190]="*‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthi ca natthi ca aññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:**When asked whether both something else and nothing else exist,*";
P_HTM[4191]="*‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.**you say ‘don’t put it like that’.*";
P_HTM[4192]="*‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā nevatthi no natthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:**When asked whether neither something else nor nothing else exist,*";
P_HTM[4193]="*‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.**you say ‘don’t put it like that’.*";
P_HTM[4194]="*Yathā kathaṃ pana, āvuso, imassa bhāsitassa attho daṭṭhabbo”ti?**How then should we see the meaning of this statement?”*";
P_HTM[4195]="*“‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti vadaṃ appapañcaṃ papañceti.**“If you say that, ‘When the six fields of contact have faded away and ceased with nothing left over, something else exists’, you’re proliferating the unproliferated.*";
P_HTM[4196]="*‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā natthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti vadaṃ appapañcaṃ papañceti.**If you say that ‘nothing else exists’, you’re proliferating the unproliferated.*";
P_HTM[4197]="*‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthi ca natthi ca aññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti vadaṃ appapañcaṃ papañceti.**If you say that ‘both something else and nothing else exist’, you’re proliferating the unproliferated.*";
P_HTM[4198]="*‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā nevatthi no natthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti vadaṃ appapañcaṃ papañceti.**If you say that ‘neither something else nor nothing else exists’, you’re proliferating the unproliferated.*";
P_HTM[4199]="*Yāvatā, āvuso, channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ gati tāvatā papañcassa gati;**The scope of the six fields of contact extends as far as the scope of proliferation.*";
P_HTM[4200]="*yāvatā papañcassa gati tāvatā channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ gati.**The scope of proliferation extends as far as the scope of the six fields of contact.*";
P_HTM[4201]="*Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā papañcanirodho papañcavūpasamo”ti.**When the six fields of contact fade away and cease with nothing left over, proliferation stops and is stilled.”*";
P_HTM[4202]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4203]="*3. Mahākoṭṭhikasuttaṃ**With Ānanda*";
P_HTM[4204]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yenāyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā mahākoṭṭhikena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4205]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ mahākoṭṭhikaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Ānanda sat down to one side, and said to Mahākoṭṭhita:*";
P_HTM[4206]="*“Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthaññaṃ kiñcī”ti?**“Reverend, when these six fields of contact have faded away and ceased with nothing left over, does anything else exist?”*";
P_HTM[4207]="*“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso”.**“Don’t put it like that, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4208]="*“Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā natthaññaṃ kiñcī”ti?**“Does nothing else exist?”*";
P_HTM[4209]="*“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso”.**“Don’t put it like that, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4210]="*“Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthi ca natthi ca aññaṃ kiñcī”ti?**“Do both something else and nothing else exist?”*";
P_HTM[4211]="*“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso”.**“Don’t put it like that, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4212]="*“Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā nevatthi no natthaññaṃ kiñcī”ti?**“Do neither something else nor nothing else exist?”*";
P_HTM[4213]="*“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso”.**“Don’t put it like that, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4214]="*“‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:**“Reverend, when asked these questions,*";
P_HTM[4215]="*‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.**you say ‘don’t put it like that’.*";
P_HTM[4216]="*‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā natthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:* **";
P_HTM[4217]="*‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[4218]="*‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthi ca natthi ca aññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:* **";
P_HTM[4219]="*‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[4220]="*‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā nevatthi no natthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:* **";
P_HTM[4221]="*‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[4222]="*Yathā kathaṃ panāvuso, imassa bhāsitassa attho daṭṭhabbo”ti?**… How then should we see the meaning of this statement?”*";
P_HTM[4223]="*“‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti vadaṃ appapañcaṃ papañceti.**“If you say that ‘when the six fields of contact have faded away and ceased with nothing left over, something else exists’, you’re proliferating the unproliferated.*";
P_HTM[4224]="*‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā natthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti vadaṃ appapañcaṃ papañceti.**If you say that ‘nothing else exists’, you’re proliferating the unproliferated.*";
P_HTM[4225]="*‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthi ca natthi ca aññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti vadaṃ appapañcaṃ papañceti.**If you say that ‘both something else and nothing else exist’, you’re proliferating the unproliferated.*";
P_HTM[4226]="*‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā nevatthi no natthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti vadaṃ appapañcaṃ papañceti.**If you say that ‘neither something else nor nothing else exist’, you’re proliferating the unproliferated.*";
P_HTM[4227]="*Yāvatā, āvuso, channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ gati tāvatā papañcassa gati.**The scope of the six fields of contact extends as far as the scope of proliferation.*";
P_HTM[4228]="*Yāvatā papañcassa gati tāvatā channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ gati.**The scope of proliferation extends as far as the scope of the six fields of contact.*";
P_HTM[4229]="*Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā papañcanirodho papañcavūpasamo”ti.**When the six fields of contact fade away and cease with nothing left over, proliferation stops and is stilled.”*";
P_HTM[4230]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4231]="*4. Ānandasuttaṃ**With Upavāṇa*";
P_HTM[4232]="*Atha kho āyasmā upavāṇo yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Venerable Upavāṇa went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4233]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā upavāṇo āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Upavāṇa sat down to one side, and said to Sāriputta:*";
P_HTM[4234]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, vijjāyantakaro hotī”ti?**“Reverend Sāriputta, do you become a terminator because of knowledge?”*";
P_HTM[4235]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“That’s not it, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4236]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso sāriputta, caraṇenantakaro hotī”ti?**“Do you become a terminator because of conduct?”*";
P_HTM[4237]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“That’s not it, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4238]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso sāriputta, vijjācaraṇenantakaro hotī”ti?**“Do you become a terminator because of both knowledge and conduct?”*";
P_HTM[4239]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“That’s not it, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4240]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso sāriputta, aññatra vijjācaraṇenantakaro hotī”ti?**“Do you become a terminator for some reason other than knowledge and conduct?”*";
P_HTM[4241]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“That’s not it, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4242]="*“‘Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, vijjāyantakaro hotī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:**“Reverend Sāriputta, when asked whether you become a terminator because of knowledge or conduct or knowledge and conduct, or for some other reason,*";
P_HTM[4243]="*‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.**you say ‘that’s not it’.*";
P_HTM[4244]="*‘Kiṃ panāvuso sāriputta, caraṇenantakaro hotī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:* **";
P_HTM[4245]="*‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[4246]="*‘Kiṃ panāvuso sāriputta, vijjācaraṇenantakaro hotī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:* **";
P_HTM[4247]="*‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[4248]="*‘Kiṃ panāvuso sāriputta, aññatra vijjācaraṇenantakaro hotī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:* **";
P_HTM[4249]="*‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[4250]="*Yathā kathaṃ panāvuso, antakaro hotī”ti?**How then do you become a terminator?”*";
P_HTM[4251]="*“Vijjāya ce, āvuso, antakaro abhavissa, saupādānova samāno antakaro abhavissa.**“Reverend, if you became a terminator because of knowledge, then even someone who still has grasping could be a terminator.*";
P_HTM[4252]="*Caraṇena ce, āvuso, antakaro abhavissa, saupādānova samāno antakaro abhavissa.**If you became a terminator because of conduct, then even someone who still has grasping could be a terminator.*";
P_HTM[4253]="*Vijjācaraṇena ce, āvuso, antakaro abhavissa, saupādānova samāno antakaro abhavissa.**If you became a terminator because of both knowledge and conduct, then even someone who still has grasping could be a terminator.*";
P_HTM[4254]="*Aññatra vijjācaraṇena ce, āvuso, antakaro abhavissa, puthujjano antakaro abhavissa.**If you became a terminator for some reason other than knowledge and conduct, then even an ordinary person could be a terminator.*";
P_HTM[4255]="*Puthujjano hi, āvuso, aññatra vijjācaraṇena.**For an ordinary person lacks knowledge and conduct.*";
P_HTM[4256]="*Caraṇavipanno kho, āvuso, yathābhūtaṃ na jānāti na passati.**Reverend, someone lacking good conduct does not know and see things as they are.*";
P_HTM[4257]="*Caraṇasampanno yathābhūtaṃ jānāti passati.**Someone accomplished in good conduct knows and sees things as they are.*";
P_HTM[4258]="*Yathābhūtaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ antakaro hotī”ti.**Knowing and seeing things as they are, one is a terminator.”*";
P_HTM[4259]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4260]="*5. Upavāṇasuttaṃ**Aspiration*";
P_HTM[4261]="*“Saddho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ sammā āyācamāno āyāceyya:**“Mendicants, a faithful monk would rightly aspire:*";
P_HTM[4262]="*‘tādiso homi yādisā sāriputtamoggallānā’ti.**‘May I be like Sāriputta and Moggallāna!’*";
P_HTM[4263]="*Esā, bhikkhave, tulā etaṃ pamāṇaṃ mama sāvakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, yadidaṃ sāriputtamoggallānā.**These are a standard and a measure for my monk disciples, that is, Sāriputta and Moggallāna.*";
P_HTM[4264]="*Saddhā, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī evaṃ sammā āyācamānā āyāceyya:**A faithful nun would rightly aspire:*";
P_HTM[4265]="*‘tādisā homi yādisā khemā ca bhikkhunī uppalavaṇṇā cā’ti.**‘May I be like the nuns Khemā and Uppalavaṇṇā!’*";
P_HTM[4266]="*Esā, bhikkhave, tulā etaṃ pamāṇaṃ mama sāvikānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ, yadidaṃ khemā ca bhikkhunī uppalavaṇṇā ca.**These are a standard and a measure for my nun disciples, that is, the nuns Khemā and Uppalavaṇṇā.*";
P_HTM[4267]="*Saddho, bhikkhave, upāsako evaṃ sammā āyācamāno āyāceyya:**A faithful layman would rightly aspire:*";
P_HTM[4268]="*‘tādiso homi yādiso citto ca gahapati hatthako ca āḷavako’ti.**‘May I be like the householder Citta and Hatthaka of Aḷavī!’*";
P_HTM[4269]="*Esā, bhikkhave, tulā etaṃ pamāṇaṃ mama sāvakānaṃ upāsakānaṃ, yadidaṃ citto ca gahapati hatthako ca āḷavako.**These are a standard and a measure for my male lay disciples, that is, the householder Citta and Hatthaka of Aḷavī.*";
P_HTM[4270]="*Saddhā, bhikkhave, upāsikā evaṃ sammā āyācamānā āyāceyya:**A faithful laywoman would rightly aspire:*";
P_HTM[4271]="*‘tādisā homi yādisā khujjuttarā ca upāsikā veḷukaṇḍakiyā ca nandamātā’ti.**‘May I be like the laywomen Khujjuttarā and Veḷukaṇṭakī, Nanda’s mother!’*";
P_HTM[4272]="*Esā, bhikkhave, tulā etaṃ pamāṇaṃ mama sāvikānaṃ upāsikānaṃ, yadidaṃ khujjuttarā ca upāsikā veḷukaṇḍakiyā ca nandamātā”ti.**These are a standard and a measure for my female lay disciples, that is, the laywomen Khujjuttarā and Veḷukaṇṭakī, Nanda’s mother.”*";
P_HTM[4273]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4274]="*6. Āyācanasuttaṃ**With Rāhula*";
P_HTM[4275]="*Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Venerable Rāhula went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[4276]="*“Yā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā pathavīdhātu yā ca bāhirā pathavīdhātu, pathavīdhāturevesā.**“Rāhula, the interior earth element and the exterior earth element are just the earth element.*";
P_HTM[4277]="*‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti, evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[4278]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā pathavīdhātuyā nibbindati, pathavīdhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the earth element, detaching the mind from the earth element.*";
P_HTM[4279]="*Yā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā āpodhātu yā ca bāhirā āpodhātu, āpodhāturevesā.**The interior water element and the exterior water element are just the water element.*";
P_HTM[4280]="*‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti, evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[4281]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā āpodhātuyā nibbindati, āpodhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the water element, detaching the mind from the water element.*";
P_HTM[4282]="*Yā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā tejodhātu yā ca bāhirā tejodhātu, tejodhāturevesā.**The interior fire element and the exterior fire element are just the fire element.*";
P_HTM[4283]="*‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti, evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[4284]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā tejodhātuyā nibbindati, tejodhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the fire element, detaching the mind from the fire element.*";
P_HTM[4285]="*Yā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā vāyodhātu yā ca bāhirā vāyodhātu, vāyodhāturevesā.**The interior air element and the exterior air element are just the air element.*";
P_HTM[4286]="*‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti, evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[4287]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā vāyodhātuyā nibbindati, vāyodhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the air element, detaching the mind from the air element.*";
P_HTM[4288]="*Yato kho, rāhula, bhikkhu imāsu catūsu dhātūsu nevattānaṃ na attaniyaṃ samanupassati, ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, bhikkhu acchecchi taṇhaṃ, vivattayi saṃyojanaṃ, sammā mānābhisamayā antamakāsi dukkhassā”ti.**When a mendicant sees these four elements as neither self nor belonging to self, they’re called a mendicant who has cut off craving, untied the fetters, and by rightly comprehending conceit has made an end of suffering.”*";
P_HTM[4289]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4290]="*7. Rāhulasuttaṃ**Billabong*";
P_HTM[4291]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[4292]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4293]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ santaṃ cetovimuttiṃ upasampajja viharati.**Take a mendicant who enters and remains in a peaceful release of the heart.*";
P_HTM[4294]="*So sakkāyanirodhaṃ manasi karoti.**They focus on the cessation of identification,*";
P_HTM[4295]="*Tassa sakkāyanirodhaṃ manasi karoto sakkāyanirodhe cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati nādhimuccati.**but their mind isn’t eager, confident, settled, and decided about it.*";
P_HTM[4296]="*Tassa kho evaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno na sakkāyanirodho pāṭikaṅkho.**You wouldn’t expect that mendicant to stop identifying.*";
P_HTM[4297]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso lepagatena hatthena sākhaṃ gaṇheyya, tassa so hattho sajjeyyapi gaṇheyyapi bajjheyyapi;**Suppose a person were to grab a branch with a glue-smeared hand. Their hand would stick, hold, and bind to it.*";
P_HTM[4298]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ santaṃ cetovimuttiṃ upasampajja viharati.**In the same way, take a mendicant who enters and remains in a peaceful release of the heart.*";
P_HTM[4299]="*So sakkāyanirodhaṃ manasi karoti.**They focus on the cessation of identification,*";
P_HTM[4300]="*Tassa sakkāyanirodhaṃ manasi karoto sakkāyanirodhe cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati nādhimuccati.**but their mind isn’t eager, confident, settled, and decided about it.*";
P_HTM[4301]="*Tassa kho evaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno na sakkāyanirodho pāṭikaṅkho.**You wouldn’t expect that mendicant to stop identifying.*";
P_HTM[4302]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ santaṃ cetovimuttiṃ upasampajja viharati.**Next, take a mendicant who enters and remains in a peaceful release of the heart.*";
P_HTM[4303]="*So sakkāyanirodhaṃ manasi karoti.**They focus on the cessation of identification,*";
P_HTM[4304]="*Tassa sakkāyanirodhaṃ manasi karoto sakkāyanirodhe cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati adhimuccati.**and their mind is eager, confident, settled, and decided about it.*";
P_HTM[4305]="*Tassa kho evaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno sakkāyanirodho pāṭikaṅkho.**You’d expect that mendicant to stop identifying.*";
P_HTM[4306]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso suddhena hatthena sākhaṃ gaṇheyya, tassa so hattho neva sajjeyya na gaṇheyya na bajjheyya;**Suppose a person were to grab a branch with a clean hand. Their hand wouldn’t stick, hold, or bind to it.*";
P_HTM[4307]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ santaṃ cetovimuttiṃ upasampajja viharati.**In the same way, take a mendicant who enters and remains in a peaceful release of the heart.*";
P_HTM[4308]="*So sakkāyanirodhaṃ manasi karoti.**They focus on the cessation of identification,*";
P_HTM[4309]="*Tassa sakkāyanirodhaṃ manasi karoto sakkāyanirodhe cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati adhimuccati.**and their mind is eager, confident, settled, and decided about it.*";
P_HTM[4310]="*Tassa kho evaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno sakkāyanirodho pāṭikaṅkho.**You’d expect that mendicant to stop identifying.*";
P_HTM[4311]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ santaṃ cetovimuttiṃ upasampajja viharati.**Next, take a mendicant who enters and remains in a peaceful release of the heart.*";
P_HTM[4312]="*So avijjāppabhedaṃ manasi karoti.**They focus on smashing ignorance,*";
P_HTM[4313]="*Tassa avijjāppabhedaṃ manasi karoto avijjāppabhede cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati nādhimuccati.**but their mind isn’t eager, confident, settled, and decided about it.*";
P_HTM[4314]="*Tassa kho evaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno na avijjāppabhedo pāṭikaṅkho.**You wouldn’t expect that mendicant to smash ignorance.*";
P_HTM[4315]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, jambālī anekavassagaṇikā.**Suppose there was a billabong that had been stagnant for many years.*";
P_HTM[4316]="*Tassā puriso yāni ceva āyamukhāni tāni pidaheyya, yāni ca apāyamukhāni tāni vivareyya, devo ca na sammā dhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya.**And someone was to close off the inlets and open up the drains, and the heavens didn’t provide enough rain.*";
P_HTM[4317]="*Evañhi tassā, bhikkhave, jambāliyā na āḷippabhedo pāṭikaṅkho.**You wouldn’t expect that billabong to break its banks.*";
P_HTM[4318]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ santaṃ cetovimuttiṃ upasampajja viharati.**In the same way, take a mendicant who enters and remains in a certain peaceful release of the heart.*";
P_HTM[4319]="*So avijjāppabhedaṃ manasi karoti.**They focus on smashing ignorance,*";
P_HTM[4320]="*Tassa avijjāppabhedaṃ manasi karoto avijjāppabhede cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati nādhimuccati.**but their mind isn’t eager, confident, settled, and decided about it.*";
P_HTM[4321]="*Tassa kho evaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno na avijjāppabhedo pāṭikaṅkho.**You wouldn’t expect that mendicant to smash ignorance.*";
P_HTM[4322]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ santaṃ cetovimuttiṃ upasampajja viharati.**Next, take a mendicant who enters and remains in a peaceful release of the heart.*";
P_HTM[4323]="*So avijjāppabhedaṃ manasi karoti.**They focus on smashing ignorance,*";
P_HTM[4324]="*Tassa avijjāppabhedaṃ manasi karoto avijjāppabhede cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati adhimuccati.**and their mind is eager, confident, settled, and decided about it.*";
P_HTM[4325]="*Tassa kho evaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno avijjāppabhedo pāṭikaṅkho.**You’d expect that mendicant to smash ignorance.*";
P_HTM[4326]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, jambālī anekavassagaṇikā.**Suppose there was a billabong that had been stagnant for many years.*";
P_HTM[4327]="*Tassā puriso yāni ceva āyamukhāni tāni vivareyya, yāni ca apāyamukhāni tāni pidaheyya, devo ca sammā dhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya.**And someone was to open up the inlets and close off the drains, and the heavens provided plenty of rain.*";
P_HTM[4328]="*Evañhi tassā, bhikkhave, jambāliyā āḷippabhedo pāṭikaṅkho.**You’d expect that billabong to break its banks.*";
P_HTM[4329]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ santaṃ cetovimuttiṃ upasampajja viharati.**In the same way, take a mendicant who enters and remains in a certain peaceful release of the heart.*";
P_HTM[4330]="*So avijjāppabhedaṃ manasi karoti.**They focus on smashing ignorance,*";
P_HTM[4331]="*Tassa avijjāppabhedaṃ manasi karoto avijjāppabhede cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati adhimuccati.**and their mind is eager, confident, settled, and decided about it.*";
P_HTM[4332]="*Tassa kho evaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno avijjāppabhedo pāṭikaṅkho.**You’d expect that mendicant to smash ignorance.*";
P_HTM[4333]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[4334]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4335]="*8. Jambālīsuttaṃ**Extinguishment*";
P_HTM[4336]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4337]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Ānanda sat down to one side, and said to Sāriputta:*";
P_HTM[4338]="*“ko nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, hetu ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme na parinibbāyantī”ti?**“What is the cause, Reverend Sāriputta, what is the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully extinguished in the present life?”*";
P_HTM[4339]="*“Idhāvuso ānanda, sattā imā hānabhāgiyā saññāti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti, imā ṭhitibhāgiyā saññāti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti, imā visesabhāgiyā saññāti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti, imā nibbedhabhāgiyā saññāti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti.**“Reverend Ānanda, it’s because some sentient beings don’t really understand which perceptions make things worse, which keep things steady, which lead to distinction, and which lead to penetration.*";
P_HTM[4340]="*Ayaṃ kho, āvuso ānanda, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme na parinibbāyantī”ti.**That’s the cause, that’s the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully extinguished in the present life.”*";
P_HTM[4341]="*“Ko panāvuso sāriputta, hetu ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti?**“What is the cause, Reverend Sāriputta, what is the reason why some sentient beings are fully extinguished in the present life?”*";
P_HTM[4342]="*“Idhāvuso ānanda, sattā imā hānabhāgiyā saññāti yathābhūtaṃ pajānanti, imā ṭhitibhāgiyā saññāti yathābhūtaṃ pajānanti, imā visesabhāgiyā saññāti yathābhūtaṃ pajānanti, imā nibbedhabhāgiyā saññāti yathābhūtaṃ pajānanti.**“Reverend Ānanda, it’s because some sentient beings truly understand which perceptions make things worse, which keep things steady, which lead to distinction, and which lead to penetration.*";
P_HTM[4343]="*Ayaṃ kho, āvuso ānanda, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti.**That’s the cause, that’s the reason why some sentient beings are fully extinguished in the present life.”*";
P_HTM[4344]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4345]="*9. Nibbānasuttaṃ**The Four Great References*";
P_HTM[4346]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bhoganagare viharati ānandacetiye.**At one time the Buddha was staying near the city of Bhoga, at the Ānanda Tree-shrine.*";
P_HTM[4347]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[4348]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[4349]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4350]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4351]="*“cattārome, bhikkhave, mahāpadese desessāmi,**“Mendicants, I will teach you the four great references.*";
P_HTM[4352]="*taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4353]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4354]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4355]="*“Katame, bhikkhave, cattāro mahāpadesā?**“Mendicants, what are the four great references?*";
P_HTM[4356]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:**Take a mendicant who says:*";
P_HTM[4357]="*‘sammukhā metaṃ, āvuso, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ—**‘Reverend, I have heard and learned this in the presence of the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4358]="*ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanan’ti.**this is the teaching, this is the training, this is the Teacher’s instruction.’*";
P_HTM[4359]="*Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhāsitaṃ neva abhinanditabbaṃ nappaṭikkositabbaṃ.**You should neither approve nor dismiss that mendicant’s statement.*";
P_HTM[4360]="*Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā tāni padabyañjanāni sādhukaṃ uggahetvā sutte otāretabbāni, vinaye sandassetabbāni.**Instead, you should carefully memorize those words and phrases, then check if they’re included in the discourses and found in the texts on monastic training.*";
P_HTM[4361]="*Tāni ce sutte otāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni na ceva sutte otaranti na vinaye sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**If they’re not included in the discourses and found in the texts on monastic training, you should draw the conclusion:*";
P_HTM[4362]="*‘addhā idaṃ na ceva tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa;**‘Clearly this is not the word of the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4363]="*imassa ca bhikkhuno duggahitan’ti.**It has been incorrectly memorized by that mendicant.’*";
P_HTM[4364]="*Iti hetaṃ, bhikkhave, chaḍḍeyyātha.**And so you should reject it.*";
P_HTM[4365]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:**Take another mendicant who says:*";
P_HTM[4366]="*‘sammukhā metaṃ, āvuso, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ—**‘Reverend, I have heard and learned this in the presence of the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4367]="*ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanan’ti.**this is the teaching, this is the training, this is the Teacher’s instruction.’*";
P_HTM[4368]="*Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhāsitaṃ neva abhinanditabbaṃ nappaṭikkositabbaṃ.**You should neither approve nor dismiss that mendicant’s statement.*";
P_HTM[4369]="*Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā tāni padabyañjanāni sādhukaṃ uggahetvā sutte otāretabbāni, vinaye sandassetabbāni.**Instead, you should carefully memorize those words and phrases, then check if they’re included in the discourses and found in the texts on monastic training.*";
P_HTM[4370]="*Tāni ce sutte otāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni sutte ceva otaranti vinaye ca sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**If they are included in the discourses and found in the texts on monastic training, you should draw the conclusion:*";
P_HTM[4371]="*‘addhā idaṃ tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa;**‘Clearly this is the word of the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4372]="*imassa ca bhikkhuno suggahitan’ti.**It has been correctly memorized by that mendicant.’*";
P_HTM[4373]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ mahāpadesaṃ dhāreyyātha.**You should remember it. This is the first great reference.*";
P_HTM[4374]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:**Take another mendicant who says:*";
P_HTM[4375]="*‘asukasmiṃ nāma āvāse saṅgho viharati sathero sapāmokkho.**‘In such-and-such monastery lives a Saṅgha with seniors and leaders.*";
P_HTM[4376]="*Tassa me saṅghassa sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ—**I’ve heard and learned this in the presence of that Saṅgha:*";
P_HTM[4377]="*ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanan’ti.**this is the teaching, this is the training, this is the Teacher’s instruction.’*";
P_HTM[4378]="*Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhāsitaṃ neva abhinanditabbaṃ nappaṭikkositabbaṃ.**You should neither approve nor dismiss that mendicant’s statement.*";
P_HTM[4379]="*Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā tāni padabyañjanāni sādhukaṃ uggahetvā sutte otāretabbāni, vinaye sandassetabbāni.**Instead, you should carefully memorize those words and phrases, then check if they’re included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic training.*";
P_HTM[4380]="*Tāni ce sutte otāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni na ceva sutte otaranti na vinaye sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**If they’re not included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic training, you should draw the conclusion:*";
P_HTM[4381]="*‘addhā idaṃ na ceva tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa;**‘Clearly this is not the word of the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4382]="*tassa ca saṅghassa duggahitan’ti.**It has been incorrectly memorized by that Saṅgha.’*";
P_HTM[4383]="*Iti hetaṃ, bhikkhave, chaḍḍeyyātha.**And so you should reject it.*";
P_HTM[4384]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:**Take another mendicant who says:*";
P_HTM[4385]="*‘asukasmiṃ nāma āvāse saṅgho viharati sathero sapāmokkho.**‘In such-and-such monastery lives a Saṅgha with seniors and leaders.*";
P_HTM[4386]="*Tassa me saṅghassa sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ—**I’ve heard and learned this in the presence of that Saṅgha:*";
P_HTM[4387]="*ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanan’ti.**this is the teaching, this is the training, this is the Teacher’s instruction.’*";
P_HTM[4388]="*Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhāsitaṃ neva abhinanditabbaṃ nappaṭikkositabbaṃ.**You should neither approve nor dismiss that mendicant’s statement.*";
P_HTM[4389]="*Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā tāni padabyañjanāni sādhukaṃ uggahetvā sutte otāretabbāni, vinaye sandassetabbāni.**Instead, you should carefully memorize those words and phrases, then check if they’re included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic training.*";
P_HTM[4390]="*Tāni ce sutte otāriyamānāni, vinaye sandassiyamānāni sutte ceva otaranti vinaye ca sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**If they are included in the discourses and found in the texts on monastic training, you should draw the conclusion:*";
P_HTM[4391]="*‘addhā idaṃ tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa;**‘Clearly this is the word of the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4392]="*tassa ca saṅghassa suggahitan’ti.**It has been correctly memorized by that Saṅgha.’*";
P_HTM[4393]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyaṃ mahāpadesaṃ dhāreyyātha.**You should remember it. This is the second great reference.*";
P_HTM[4394]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:**Take another mendicant who says:*";
P_HTM[4395]="*‘asukasmiṃ nāma āvāse sambahulā therā bhikkhū viharanti bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā.**‘In such-and-such monastery there are several senior mendicants who are very learned, knowledgeable in the scriptures, who remember the teachings, the texts on monastic training, and the outlines.*";
P_HTM[4396]="*Tesaṃ me therānaṃ sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ—**I’ve heard and learned this in the presence of those senior mendicants:*";
P_HTM[4397]="*ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanan’ti.**this is the teaching, this is the training, this is the Teacher’s instruction.’*";
P_HTM[4398]="*Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhāsitaṃ neva abhinanditabbaṃ nappaṭikkositabbaṃ.**You should neither approve nor dismiss that mendicant’s statement.*";
P_HTM[4399]="*Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā tāni padabyañjanāni sādhukaṃ uggahetvā sutte otāretabbāni, vinaye sandassetabbāni.**Instead, you should carefully memorize those words and phrases, then check if they’re included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic training.*";
P_HTM[4400]="*Tāni ce sutte otāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni na ceva sutte otaranti na vinaye sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**If they’re not included in the discourses or found in the monastic law, you should draw the conclusion:*";
P_HTM[4401]="*‘addhā idaṃ na ceva tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa;**‘Clearly this is not the word of the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4402]="*tesañca therānaṃ duggahitan’ti.**It has been incorrectly memorized by those senior mendicants.’*";
P_HTM[4403]="*Iti hetaṃ, bhikkhave, chaḍḍeyyātha.**And so you should reject it.*";
P_HTM[4404]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:**Take another mendicant who says:*";
P_HTM[4405]="*‘asukasmiṃ nāma āvāse sambahulā therā bhikkhū viharanti bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā.**‘In such-and-such monastery there are several senior mendicants who are very learned, knowledgeable in the scriptures, who remember the teachings, the texts on monastic training, and the outlines.*";
P_HTM[4406]="*Tesaṃ me therānaṃ sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ—**I’ve heard and learned this in the presence of those senior mendicants:*";
P_HTM[4407]="*ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanan’ti.**this is the teaching, this is the training, this is the Teacher’s instruction.’*";
P_HTM[4408]="*Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhāsitaṃ neva abhinanditabbaṃ nappaṭikkositabbaṃ.**You should neither approve nor dismiss that mendicant’s statement.*";
P_HTM[4409]="*Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā tāni padabyañjanāni sādhukaṃ uggahetvā sutte otāretabbāni, vinaye sandassetabbāni.**Instead, you should carefully memorize those words and phrases, then check if they’re included in the discourses and found in the texts on monastic training.*";
P_HTM[4410]="*Tāni ce sutte otāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni sutte ceva otaranti vinaye ca sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**If they are included in the discourses and found in the texts on monastic training, you should draw the conclusion:*";
P_HTM[4411]="*‘addhā idaṃ tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa;**‘Clearly this is the word of the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4412]="*tesañca therānaṃ suggahitan’ti.**It has been correctly memorized by those senior mendicants.’*";
P_HTM[4413]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyaṃ mahāpadesaṃ dhāreyyātha.**You should remember it. This is the third great reference.*";
P_HTM[4414]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:**Take another mendicant who says:*";
P_HTM[4415]="*‘asukasmiṃ nāma āvāse eko thero bhikkhu viharati bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo.**‘In such-and-such monastery there is a single senior mendicant who is very learned and knowledgeable in the scriptures, who has memorized the teachings, the texts on monastic discipline, and the outlines.*";
P_HTM[4416]="*Tassa me therassa sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ—**I’ve heard and learned this in the presence of that senior mendicant:*";
P_HTM[4417]="*ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanan’ti.**this is the teaching, this is the training, this is the Teacher’s instruction.’*";
P_HTM[4418]="*Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhāsitaṃ neva abhinanditabbaṃ nappaṭikkositabbaṃ.**You should neither approve nor dismiss that mendicant’s statement.*";
P_HTM[4419]="*Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā tāni padabyañjanāni sādhukaṃ uggahetvā sutte otāretabbāni, vinaye sandassetabbāni.**Instead, you should carefully memorize those words and phrases, then check if they’re included in the discourses and found in the texts on monastic discipline.*";
P_HTM[4420]="*Tāni ce sutte otāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni na ceva sutte otaranti na vinaye sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**If they’re not included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic discipline, you should draw the conclusion:*";
P_HTM[4421]="*‘addhā idaṃ na ceva tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa;**‘Clearly this is not the word of the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4422]="*tassa ca therassa duggahitan’ti.**It has been incorrectly memorized by that senior mendicant.’*";
P_HTM[4423]="*Iti hetaṃ, bhikkhave, chaḍḍeyyātha.**And so you should reject it.*";
P_HTM[4424]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:**Take another mendicant who says:*";
P_HTM[4425]="*‘asukasmiṃ nāma āvāse eko thero bhikkhu viharati bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo.**‘In such-and-such monastery there is a single senior mendicant who is very learned and knowledgeable in the scriptures, who has memorized the teachings, the texts on monastic discipline, and the outlines.*";
P_HTM[4426]="*Tassa me therassa sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ—**I’ve heard and learned this in the presence of that senior mendicant:*";
P_HTM[4427]="*ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanan’ti.**this is the teaching, this is the training, this is the Teacher’s instruction.’*";
P_HTM[4428]="*Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhāsitaṃ neva abhinanditabbaṃ nappaṭikkositabbaṃ.**You should neither approve nor dismiss that mendicant’s statement.*";
P_HTM[4429]="*Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā tāni padabyañjanāni sādhukaṃ uggahetvā sutte otāretabbāni, vinaye sandassetabbāni.**Instead, you should carefully memorize those words and phrases, then check if they’re included in the discourses and found in the texts on monastic discipline.*";
P_HTM[4430]="*Tāni ce sutte otāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni sutte ceva otaranti vinaye ca sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**If they are included in the discourses and found in the monastic law, you should draw the conclusion:*";
P_HTM[4431]="*‘addhā idaṃ tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa;**‘Clearly this is the word of the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4432]="*tassa ca therassa suggahitan’ti.**It has been correctly memorized by that senior mendicant.’*";
P_HTM[4433]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, catutthaṃ mahāpadesaṃ dhāreyyātha.**You should remember it. This is the fourth great reference.*";
P_HTM[4434]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro mahāpadesā”ti.**These are the four great references.”*";
P_HTM[4435]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4436]="*Sañcetaniyavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[4437]="*Cetanā vibhatti koṭṭhiko,* **";
P_HTM[4438]="*Ānando upavāṇapañcamaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4439]="*Āyācana rāhula jambālī,* **";
P_HTM[4440]="*Nibbānaṃ mahāpadesenāti.* **";
P_HTM[4441]="*10. Mahāpadesasuttaṃ**A Warrior*";
P_HTM[4442]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato yodhājīvo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**“Mendicants, a warrior with four factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[4443]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4444]="*Idha, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo ṭhānakusalo ca hoti, dūrepātī ca, akkhaṇavedhī ca, mahato ca kāyassa padāletā.**He’s skilled in the basics, a long-distance shooter, a marksman, one who shatters large objects.*";
P_HTM[4445]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi aṅgehi samannāgato yodhājīvo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**A warrior with these four factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[4446]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**In the same way, a mendicant with four factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[4447]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4448]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ṭhānakusalo ca hoti, dūrepātī ca, akkhaṇavedhī ca, mahato ca kāyassa padāletā.**He’s skilled in the basics, a long-distance shooter, a marksman, one who shatters large objects.*";
P_HTM[4449]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ṭhānakusalo hoti?**And how is a mendicant skilled in the basics?*";
P_HTM[4450]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu.**It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[4451]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ṭhānakusalo hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is skilled in the basics.*";
P_HTM[4452]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dūrepātī hoti?**And how is a mendicant a long-distance shooter?*";
P_HTM[4453]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati.**It’s when a mendicant truly sees any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[4454]="*Yā kāci vedanā …**They truly see any kind of feeling …*";
P_HTM[4455]="*yā kāci saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[4456]="*ye keci saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[4457]="*yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati.**consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near, all consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[4458]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dūrepātī hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is a long-distance shooter.*";
P_HTM[4459]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhaṇavedhī hoti?**And how is a mendicant a marksman?*";
P_HTM[4460]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**It’s when they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[4461]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhaṇavedhī hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is a marksman.*";
P_HTM[4462]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mahato kāyassa padāletā hoti?**And how does a mendicant shatter large objects?*";
P_HTM[4463]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mahantaṃ avijjākkhandhaṃ padāletā.**It’s when a mendicant shatters the great mass of ignorance.*";
P_HTM[4464]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mahato kāyassa padāletā hoti.**That’s how a mendicant shatters large objects.*";
P_HTM[4465]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti.**A mendicant with these four factors … is the supreme field of merit for the world.”*";
P_HTM[4466]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4467]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Brahmins*";
P_HTM[4468]="*1. Yodhājīvasuttaṃ**Guarantee*";
P_HTM[4469]="*“Catunnaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ natthi koci pāṭibhogo—**“There are four things that no-one can guarantee—*";
P_HTM[4470]="*samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā devo vā māro vā brahmā vā koci vā lokasmiṃ.**not an ascetic, a brahmin, a god, a Māra, a Brahmā, or anyone in the world.*";
P_HTM[4471]="*Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4472]="*‘Jarādhammaṃ mā jīrī’ti natthi koci pāṭibhogo—**No-one can guarantee that someone liable to grow old will not grow old.*";
P_HTM[4473]="*samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā devo vā māro vā brahmā vā koci vā lokasmiṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4474]="*‘byādhidhammaṃ mā byādhiyī’ti natthi koci pāṭibhogo—**No-one can guarantee that someone liable to sickness will not get sick.*";
P_HTM[4475]="*samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā devo vā māro vā brahmā vā koci vā lokasmiṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4476]="*‘maraṇadhammaṃ mā mīyī’ti natthi koci pāṭibhogo—**No-one can guarantee that someone liable to death will not die.*";
P_HTM[4477]="*samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā devo vā māro vā brahmā vā koci vā lokasmiṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4478]="*‘yāni kho pana tāni pubbe attanā katāni pāpakāni kammāni saṅkilesikāni ponobhavikāni sadarāni dukkhavipākāni āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇikāni, tesaṃ vipāko mā nibbattī’ti natthi koci pāṭibhogo—**No-one can guarantee that the bad deeds done in past lives—corrupted, leading to future lives, hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and death—will not produce their result.*";
P_HTM[4479]="*samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā devo vā māro vā brahmā vā koci vā lokasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4480]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ natthi koci pāṭibhogo—**These are the four things that no-one can guarantee—*";
P_HTM[4481]="*samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā devo vā māro vā brahmā vā koci vā lokasmin”ti.**not an ascetic, a brahmin, a god, a Māra, a Brahmā, or anyone in the world.”*";
P_HTM[4482]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4483]="*2. Pāṭibhogasuttaṃ**Vassakāra on What is Heard*";
P_HTM[4484]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[4485]="*Atha kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Vassakāra the brahmin, a chief minister of Magadha, went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4486]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4487]="*“Ahañhi, bho gotama, evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“Master Gotama, this is my doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[4488]="*‘yo koci diṭṭhaṃ bhāsati—**There’s nothing wrong with talking about what you’ve seen, saying:*";
P_HTM[4489]="*evaṃ me diṭṭhanti, natthi tato doso;**‘So I have seen.’*";
P_HTM[4490]="*yo koci sutaṃ bhāsati—**There’s nothing wrong with talking about what you’ve heard, saying:*";
P_HTM[4491]="*evaṃ me sutanti, natthi tato doso;**‘So I have heard.’*";
P_HTM[4492]="*yo koci mutaṃ bhāsati—**There’s nothing wrong with talking about what you’ve thought, saying:*";
P_HTM[4493]="*evaṃ me mutanti, natthi tato doso;**‘So I have thought.’*";
P_HTM[4494]="*yo koci viññātaṃ bhāsati—**There’s nothing wrong with talking about what you’ve known, saying:*";
P_HTM[4495]="*evaṃ me viññātanti, natthi tato doso’”ti.**‘So I have known.’”*";
P_HTM[4496]="*“Nāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ diṭṭhaṃ bhāsitabbanti vadāmi;**“Brahmin, I don’t say you should talk about everything you see, hear, think, and know.*";
P_HTM[4497]="*na panāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ diṭṭhaṃ na bhāsitabbanti vadāmi;**But I also don’t say you should talk about nothing you see, hear, think, and know.*";
P_HTM[4498]="*nāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ sutaṃ bhāsitabbanti vadāmi;* **";
P_HTM[4499]="*na panāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ sutaṃ na bhāsitabbanti vadāmi;* **";
P_HTM[4500]="*nāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ mutaṃ bhāsitabbanti vadāmi;* **";
P_HTM[4501]="*na panāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ mutaṃ na bhāsitabbanti vadāmi;* **";
P_HTM[4502]="*nāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ viññātaṃ bhāsitabbanti vadāmi;* **";
P_HTM[4503]="*na panāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ viññātaṃ na bhāsitabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4504]="*Yañhi, brāhmaṇa, diṭṭhaṃ bhāsato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, evarūpaṃ diṭṭhaṃ na bhāsitabbanti vadāmi.**When talking about certain things you’ve seen, heard, thought, or known, unskillful qualities grow while skillful qualities decline. I say that you shouldn’t talk about those things.*";
P_HTM[4505]="*Yañca khvassa, brāhmaṇa, diṭṭhaṃ abhāsato kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, evarūpaṃ diṭṭhaṃ bhāsitabbanti vadāmi.**When talking about other things you’ve seen, heard, thought, or known, unskillful qualities decline while skillful qualities grow. I say that you should talk about those things.”*";
P_HTM[4506]="*Yañhi, brāhmaṇa, sutaṃ bhāsato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, evarūpaṃ sutaṃ na bhāsitabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4507]="*Yañca khvassa, brāhmaṇa, sutaṃ abhāsato kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, evarūpaṃ sutaṃ bhāsitabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4508]="*Yañhi, brāhmaṇa, mutaṃ bhāsato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, evarūpaṃ mutaṃ na bhāsitabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4509]="*Yañca khvassa, brāhmaṇa, mutaṃ abhāsato kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, evarūpaṃ mutaṃ bhāsitabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4510]="*Yañhi, brāhmaṇa, viññātaṃ bhāsato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, evarūpaṃ viññātaṃ na bhāsitabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4511]="*Yañca khvassa, brāhmaṇa, viññātaṃ abhāsato kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, evarūpaṃ viññātaṃ bhāsitabbanti vadāmī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4512]="*Atha kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmīti.**Then Vassakāra the brahmin, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[4513]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4514]="*3. Sutasuttaṃ**Fearless*";
P_HTM[4515]="*Atha kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4516]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4517]="*“Ahañhi, bho gotama, evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“Master Gotama, this is my doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[4518]="*‘natthi yo maraṇadhammo samāno na bhāyati, na santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassā’”ti.**‘All those liable to death are frightened and terrified of death.’”*";
P_HTM[4519]="*“Atthi, brāhmaṇa, maraṇadhammo samāno bhāyati, santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassa;**“Brahmin, some of those liable to death are frightened and terrified of death.*";
P_HTM[4520]="*atthi pana, brāhmaṇa, maraṇadhammo samāno na bhāyati, na santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassa.**But some of those liable to death are not frightened and terrified of death.*";
P_HTM[4521]="*Katamo ca, brāhmaṇa, maraṇadhammo samāno bhāyati, santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassa?**Who are those frightened of death?*";
P_HTM[4522]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco kāmesu avītarāgo hoti avigatacchando avigatapemo avigatapipāso avigatapariḷāho avigatataṇho.**It’s someone who isn’t free of greed, desire, fondness, thirst, passion, and craving for sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[4523]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro gāḷho rogātaṅko phusati.**When they fall seriously ill,*";
P_HTM[4524]="*Tassa aññatarena gāḷhena rogātaṅkena phuṭṭhassa evaṃ hoti:**they think:*";
P_HTM[4525]="*‘piyā vata maṃ kāmā jahissanti, piye cāhaṃ kāme jahissāmī’ti.**‘The sensual pleasures that I love so much will leave me, and I’ll leave them.’*";
P_HTM[4526]="*So socati kilamati paridevati, urattāḷiṃ kandati, sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They sorrow and wail and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[4527]="*Ayaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, maraṇadhammo samāno bhāyati, santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassa.**This is someone who is frightened of death.*";
P_HTM[4528]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, idhekacco kāye avītarāgo hoti avigatacchando avigatapemo avigatapipāso avigatapariḷāho avigatataṇho.**Furthermore, it’s someone who isn’t free of greed, desire, fondness, thirst, passion, and craving for the body.*";
P_HTM[4529]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro gāḷho rogātaṅko phusati.**When they fall seriously ill,*";
P_HTM[4530]="*Tassa aññatarena gāḷhena rogātaṅkena phuṭṭhassa evaṃ hoti:**they think:*";
P_HTM[4531]="*‘piyo vata maṃ kāyo jahissati, piyañcāhaṃ kāyaṃ jahissāmī’ti.**‘This body that I love so much will leave me, and I’ll leave it.’*";
P_HTM[4532]="*So socati kilamati paridevati, urattāḷiṃ kandati, sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They sorrow and wail and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[4533]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, maraṇadhammo samāno bhāyati, santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassa.**This, too, is someone who is frightened of death.*";
P_HTM[4534]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, idhekacco akatakalyāṇo hoti akatakusalo akatabhīruttāṇo katapāpo kataluddo katakibbiso.**Furthermore, it’s someone who hasn’t done good and skillful things that keep them safe, but has done bad, violent, and corrupt things.*";
P_HTM[4535]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro gāḷho rogātaṅko phusati.**When they fall seriously ill,*";
P_HTM[4536]="*Tassa aññatarena gāḷhena rogātaṅkena phuṭṭhassa evaṃ hoti:**they think:*";
P_HTM[4537]="*‘akataṃ vata me kalyāṇaṃ, akataṃ kusalaṃ, akataṃ bhīruttāṇaṃ;**‘Well, I haven’t done good and skillful things that keep me safe.*";
P_HTM[4538]="*kataṃ pāpaṃ, kataṃ luddaṃ, kataṃ kibbisaṃ.**And I have done bad, violent, and corrupt things.*";
P_HTM[4539]="*Yāvatā, bho, akatakalyāṇānaṃ akatakusalānaṃ akatabhīruttāṇānaṃ katapāpānaṃ kataluddānaṃ katakibbisānaṃ gati taṃ gatiṃ pecca gacchāmī’ti.**When I depart, I’ll go to the place where people who’ve done such things go.’*";
P_HTM[4540]="*So socati kilamati paridevati, urattāḷiṃ kandati, sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They sorrow and wail and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[4541]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, maraṇadhammo samāno bhāyati, santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassa.**This, too, is someone who is frightened of death.*";
P_HTM[4542]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, idhekacco kaṅkhī hoti vicikicchī aniṭṭhaṅgato saddhamme.**Furthermore, it’s someone who’s doubtful, uncertain, and undecided about the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[4543]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro gāḷho rogātaṅko phusati.**When they fall seriously ill,*";
P_HTM[4544]="*Tassa aññatarena gāḷhena rogātaṅkena phuṭṭhassa evaṃ hoti:**they think:*";
P_HTM[4545]="*‘kaṅkhī vatamhi vicikicchī aniṭṭhaṅgato saddhamme’ti.**‘I’m doubtful, uncertain, and undecided about the true teaching.’*";
P_HTM[4546]="*So socati kilamati paridevati, urattāḷiṃ kandati, sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They sorrow and wail and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[4547]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, maraṇadhammo samāno bhāyati, santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassa.**This, too, is someone who is frightened of death.*";
P_HTM[4548]="*Ime kho, brāhmaṇa, cattāro maraṇadhammā samānā bhāyanti, santāsaṃ āpajjanti maraṇassa.**These are the four people liable to death who are frightened and terrified of death.*";
P_HTM[4549]="*Katamo ca, brāhmaṇa, maraṇadhammo samāno na bhāyati, na santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassa?**Who are those not frightened of death?*";
P_HTM[4550]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco kāmesu vītarāgo hoti vigatacchando vigatapemo vigatapipāso vigatapariḷāho vigatataṇho.**It’s someone who is rid of greed, desire, fondness, thirst, passion, and craving for sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[4551]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro gāḷho rogātaṅko phusati.**When they fall seriously ill,*";
P_HTM[4552]="*Tassa aññatarena gāḷhena rogātaṅkena phuṭṭhassa na evaṃ hoti:**they don’t think:*";
P_HTM[4553]="*‘piyā vata maṃ kāmā jahissanti, piye cāhaṃ kāme jahissāmī’ti.**‘The sensual pleasures that I love so much will leave me, and I’ll leave them.’*";
P_HTM[4554]="*So na socati na kilamati na paridevati, na urattāḷiṃ kandati, na sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They don’t sorrow and wail and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[4555]="*Ayaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, maraṇadhammo samāno na bhāyati, na santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassa.**This is someone who’s not frightened of death.*";
P_HTM[4556]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, idhekacco kāye vītarāgo hoti vigatacchando vigatapemo vigatapipāso vigatapariḷāho vigatataṇho.**Furthermore, it’s someone who is rid of greed, desire, fondness, thirst, passion, and craving for the body.*";
P_HTM[4557]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro gāḷho rogātaṅko phusati.**When they fall seriously ill,*";
P_HTM[4558]="*Tassa aññatarena gāḷhena rogātaṅkena phuṭṭhassa na evaṃ hoti:**they don’t think:*";
P_HTM[4559]="*‘piyo vata maṃ kāyo jahissati, piyañcāhaṃ kāyaṃ jahissāmī’ti.**‘This body that I love so much will leave me, and I’ll leave it.’*";
P_HTM[4560]="*So na socati na kilamati na paridevati, na urattāḷiṃ kandati, na sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They don’t sorrow and wail and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[4561]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, maraṇadhammo samāno na bhāyati, na santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassa.**This, too, is someone who’s not frightened of death.*";
P_HTM[4562]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, idhekacco akatapāpo hoti akataluddo akatakibbiso katakalyāṇo katakusalo katabhīruttāṇo.**Furthermore, it’s someone who hasn’t done bad, violent, and corrupt deeds, but has done good and skillful deeds that keep them safe.*";
P_HTM[4563]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro gāḷho rogātaṅko phusati.**When they fall seriously ill,*";
P_HTM[4564]="*Tassa aññatarena gāḷhena rogātaṅkena phuṭṭhassa evaṃ hoti:**they think:*";
P_HTM[4565]="*‘akataṃ vata me pāpaṃ, akataṃ luddaṃ, akataṃ kibbisaṃ;**‘Well, I haven’t done bad, violent, and corrupt things.*";
P_HTM[4566]="*kataṃ kalyāṇaṃ, kataṃ kusalaṃ, kataṃ bhīruttāṇaṃ.**And I have done good and skillful deeds that keep me safe.*";
P_HTM[4567]="*Yāvatā, bho, akatapāpānaṃ akataluddānaṃ akatakibbisānaṃ katakalyāṇānaṃ katakusalānaṃ katabhīruttāṇānaṃ gati taṃ gatiṃ pecca gacchāmī’ti.**When I depart, I’ll go to the place where people who’ve done such things go.’*";
P_HTM[4568]="*So na socati na kilamati na paridevati, na urattāḷiṃ kandati, na sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They don’t sorrow and wail and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[4569]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, maraṇadhammo samāno na bhāyati, na santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassa.**This, too, is someone who’s not frightened of death.*";
P_HTM[4570]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, idhekacco akaṅkhī hoti avicikicchī niṭṭhaṅgato saddhamme.**Furthermore, it’s someone who’s not doubtful, uncertain, or undecided about the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[4571]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro gāḷho rogātaṅko phusati.**When they fall seriously ill,*";
P_HTM[4572]="*Tassa aññatarena gāḷhena rogātaṅkena phuṭṭhassa evaṃ hoti:**they think:*";
P_HTM[4573]="*‘akaṅkhī vatamhi avicikicchī niṭṭhaṅgato saddhamme’ti.**‘I’m not doubtful, uncertain, or undecided about the true teaching.’*";
P_HTM[4574]="*So na socati na kilamati na paridevati, na urattāḷiṃ kandati, na sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They don’t sorrow and wail and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[4575]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, maraṇadhammo samāno na bhāyati, na santāsaṃ āpajjati maraṇassa.**This, too, is someone who’s not frightened of death.*";
P_HTM[4576]="*Ime kho, brāhmaṇa, cattāro maraṇadhammā samānā na bhāyanti, na santāsaṃ āpajjanti maraṇassā”ti.**These are the four people liable to death who are not frightened and terrified of death.”*";
P_HTM[4577]="*“Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**“Excellent, Master Gotama! … From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[4578]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4579]="*4. Abhayasuttaṃ**Truths of the Brahmins*";
P_HTM[4580]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate.**Once the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain.*";
P_HTM[4581]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā paribbājakā sippinikātīre paribbājakārāme paṭivasanti, seyyathidaṃ annabhāro varadharo sakuludāyī ca paribbājako aññe ca abhiññātā abhiññātā paribbājakā.**Now at that time several very well-known wanderers were residing in the monastery of the wanderers on the bank of the Sappinī river. They included Annabhāra, Varadhara, Sakuludāyī, and other very well-known wanderers.*";
P_HTM[4582]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena sippinikātīre paribbājakārāmo tenupasaṅkami.**Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the wanderer’s monastery on the bank of the Sappinī river.*";
P_HTM[4583]="*Tena kho pana samayena tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarā kathā udapādi:**Now at that time this discussion came up while those wanderers who follow other paths were sitting together,*";
P_HTM[4584]="*“itipi brāhmaṇasaccāni, itipi brāhmaṇasaccānī”ti.**“The truths of the brahmins are like this; the truths of the brahmins are like that.”*";
P_HTM[4585]="*Atha kho bhagavā yena te paribbājakā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho bhagavā te paribbājake etadavoca:**Then the Buddha went up to those wanderers, sat down on the seat spread out, and said to them,*";
P_HTM[4586]="*“Kāya nuttha, paribbājakā, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā, kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti?**“Wanderers, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation was unfinished?”*";
P_HTM[4587]="*“Idha, bho gotama, amhākaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi:**“Well, Master Gotama, this discussion came up among us while we were sitting together:*";
P_HTM[4588]="*‘itipi brāhmaṇasaccāni, itipi brāhmaṇasaccānī’”ti.**‘The truths of the brahmins are like this; the truths of the brahmins are like that.’”*";
P_HTM[4589]="*“Cattārimāni, paribbājakā, brāhmaṇasaccāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni.**“Wanderers, I declare these four truths of the brahmins, having realized them with my own insight.*";
P_HTM[4590]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4591]="*Idha, paribbājakā, brāhmaṇo evamāha:**Take a brahmin who says:*";
P_HTM[4592]="*‘sabbe pāṇā avajjhā’ti.**‘No sentient beings should be killed.’*";
P_HTM[4593]="*Iti vadaṃ brāhmaṇo saccaṃ āha, no musā.**Saying this, a brahmin speaks the truth, not lies.*";
P_HTM[4594]="*So tena na samaṇoti maññati, na brāhmaṇoti maññati, na seyyohamasmīti maññati, na sadisohamasmīti maññati, na hīnohamasmīti maññati.**But they don’t think of themselves as an ‘ascetic’ or ‘brahmin’ because of that. Nor do they think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’.*";
P_HTM[4595]="*Api ca yadeva tattha saccaṃ tadabhiññāya pāṇānaṃyeva anuddayāya anukampāya paṭipanno hoti.**Rather, they simply practice out of kindness and compassion for living creatures, having had insight into the truth of that.*";
P_HTM[4596]="*Puna caparaṃ, paribbājakā, brāhmaṇo evamāha:**Take another brahmin who says:*";
P_HTM[4597]="*‘sabbe kāmā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā’ti.**‘All sensual pleasures are impermanent, suffering, and perishable.’*";
P_HTM[4598]="*Iti vadaṃ brāhmaṇo saccamāha, no musā.**Saying this, a brahmin speaks the truth, not lies.*";
P_HTM[4599]="*So tena na samaṇoti maññati, na brāhmaṇoti maññati, na seyyohamasmīti maññati, na sadisohamasmīti maññati, na hīnohamasmīti maññati.**But they don’t think of themselves as an ‘ascetic’ or ‘brahmin’ because of that. Nor do they think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’.*";
P_HTM[4600]="*Api ca yadeva tattha saccaṃ tadabhiññāya kāmānaṃyeva nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti.**Rather, they simply practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding sensual pleasures, having had insight into the truth of that.*";
P_HTM[4601]="*Puna caparaṃ, paribbājakā, brāhmaṇo evamāha:**Take another brahmin who says:*";
P_HTM[4602]="*‘sabbe bhavā aniccā … pe … tadabhiññāya bhavānaṃyeva nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti.**‘All states of existence are impermanent, suffering, and perishable.’ … They simply practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding future lives, having had insight into the truth of that.*";
P_HTM[4603]="*Puna caparaṃ, paribbājakā, brāhmaṇo evamāha:**Take another brahmin who says:*";
P_HTM[4604]="*‘nāhaṃ kvacani kassaci kiñcanatasmiṃ na ca mama kvacani katthaci kiñcanatatthī’ti.**‘I don’t belong to anyone anywhere. And nothing belongs to me anywhere.’*";
P_HTM[4605]="*Iti vadaṃ brāhmaṇo saccaṃ āha, no musā.**Saying this, a brahmin speaks the truth, not lies.*";
P_HTM[4606]="*So tena na samaṇoti maññati, na brāhmaṇoti maññati, na seyyohamasmīti maññati, na sadisohamasmīti maññati, na hīnohamasmīti maññati.**But they don’t think of themselves as an ‘ascetic’ or ‘brahmin’ because of that. Nor do they think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’.*";
P_HTM[4607]="*Api ca yadeva tattha saccaṃ tadabhiññāya ākiñcaññaṃyeva paṭipadaṃ paṭipanno hoti.**Rather, they simply practice the path of nothingness, having had insight into the truth of that.*";
P_HTM[4608]="*Imāni kho, paribbājakā, cattāri brāhmaṇasaccāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditānī”ti.**These are the four truths of the brahmins that I declare, having realized them with my own insight.”*";
P_HTM[4609]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4610]="*5. Brāhmaṇasaccasuttaṃ**Approach*";
P_HTM[4611]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then one of the mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[4612]="*“kena nu kho, bhante, loko nīyati, kena loko parikassati, kassa ca uppannassa vasaṃ gacchatī”ti?**“Sir, what leads the world on? What drags it around? What arises and takes control?”*";
P_HTM[4613]="*“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhu.**“Good, good, mendicant!*";
P_HTM[4614]="*Bhaddako kho te, bhikkhu, ummaggo, bhaddakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ, kalyāṇī paripucchā.**Your approach and articulation are excellent, and it’s a good question.*";
P_HTM[4615]="*Evañhi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, pucchasi:**For you asked:*";
P_HTM[4616]="*‘kena nu kho, bhante, loko nīyati, kena loko parikassati, kassa ca uppannassa vasaṃ gacchatī’”ti?**‘What leads the world on? What drags it around? What arises and takes control?’”*";
P_HTM[4617]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4618]="*“Cittena kho, bhikkhu, loko nīyati, cittena parikassati, cittassa uppannassa vasaṃ gacchatī”ti.**“Mendicant, the mind leads the world on. The mind drags it around. When the mind arises, it takes control.”*";
P_HTM[4619]="*“Sādhu, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā bhagavantaṃ uttari pañhaṃ apucchi:**Saying “Good, sir”, that mendicant approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. Then he asked another question:*";
P_HTM[4620]="*“‘bahussuto dhammadharo, bahussuto dhammadharo’ti, bhante, vuccati.**“Sir, they speak of ‘a learned memorizer of the teaching’.*";
P_HTM[4621]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, bahussuto dhammadharo hotī”ti?**How is a learned memorizer of the teaching defined?”*";
P_HTM[4622]="*“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhu.**“Good, good, mendicant!*";
P_HTM[4623]="*Bhaddako kho te, bhikkhu ummaggo, bhaddakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ, kalyāṇī paripucchā.**Your approach and articulation are excellent, and it’s a good question. …*";
P_HTM[4624]="*Evañhi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, pucchasi:* **";
P_HTM[4625]="*‘bahussuto dhammadharo, bahussuto dhammadharoti, bhante, vuccati.* **";
P_HTM[4626]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, bahussuto dhammadharo hotī’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4627]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[4628]="*“Bahū kho, bhikkhu, mayā dhammā desitā—**I have taught many teachings:*";
P_HTM[4629]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthā, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.**statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications.*";
P_HTM[4630]="*Catuppadāya cepi, bhikkhu, gāthāya atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammappaṭipanno hoti bahussuto dhammadharoti alaṃvacanāyā”ti.**But if anyone understands the meaning and the text of even a four-line verse, and if they practice in line with that teaching, they’re qualified to be called a ‘learned memorizer of the teaching’.”*";
P_HTM[4631]="*“Sādhu, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā bhagavantaṃ uttari pañhaṃ apucchi:**Saying “Good, sir”, that mendicant approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. Then he asked another question:*";
P_HTM[4632]="*“‘sutavā nibbedhikapañño, sutavā nibbedhikapañño’ti, bhante, vuccati.**“Sir, they speak of ‘a learned person with penetrating wisdom’.*";
P_HTM[4633]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, sutavā nibbedhikapañño hotī”ti?**How is a learned person with penetrating wisdom defined?”*";
P_HTM[4634]="*“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhu.**“Good, good, mendicant!*";
P_HTM[4635]="*Bhaddako kho te, bhikkhu, ummaggo, bhaddakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ, kalyāṇī paripucchā.**Your approach and articulation are excellent, and it’s a good question. …*";
P_HTM[4636]="*Evañhi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, pucchasi:* **";
P_HTM[4637]="*‘sutavā nibbedhikapañño, sutavā nibbedhikapaññoti, bhante, vuccati.* **";
P_HTM[4638]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, sutavā nibbedhikapañño hotī’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4639]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[4640]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, bhikkhuno ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti sutaṃ hoti, paññāya cassa atthaṃ ativijjha passati;**Take a mendicant who has heard: ‘This is suffering.’ They see what it means with penetrating wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4641]="*‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti sutaṃ hoti, paññāya cassa atthaṃ ativijjha passati;**They’ve heard: ‘This is the origin of suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[4642]="*‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti sutaṃ hoti, paññāya cassa atthaṃ ativijjha passati;**‘This is the cessation of suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[4643]="*‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti sutaṃ hoti, paññāya cassa atthaṃ ativijjha passati.**‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.’ They see what it means with penetrating wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4644]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, sutavā nibbedhikapañño hotī”ti.**That’s how a person is learned, with penetrating wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[4645]="*“Sādhu, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā bhagavantaṃ uttari pañhaṃ apucchi:**Saying “Good, sir”, that mendicant approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. Then he asked another question:*";
P_HTM[4646]="*“‘paṇḍito mahāpañño, paṇḍito mahāpañño’ti, bhante, vuccati.**“Sir, they speak of ‘an astute person with great wisdom’.*";
P_HTM[4647]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, paṇḍito mahāpañño hotī”ti?**How is an astute person with great wisdom defined?”*";
P_HTM[4648]="*“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhu.**“Good, good, mendicant!*";
P_HTM[4649]="*Bhaddako kho te, bhikkhu, ummaggo, bhaddakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ, kalyāṇī paripucchā.**Your approach and articulation are excellent, and it’s a good question. …*";
P_HTM[4650]="*Evañhi tvaṃ bhikkhu pucchasi:* **";
P_HTM[4651]="*‘paṇḍito mahāpañño, paṇḍito mahāpaññoti, bhante, vuccati.* **";
P_HTM[4652]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, paṇḍito mahāpañño hotī’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4653]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[4654]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, paṇḍito mahāpañño nevattabyābādhāya ceteti na parabyābādhāya ceteti na ubhayabyābādhāya ceteti attahitaparahitaubhayahitasabbalokahitameva cintayamāno cinteti.**An astute person with great wisdom is one who has no intention to hurt themselves, or to hurt others, or to hurt both. When they think, they only think of the benefit for themselves, for others, for both, and for the whole world.*";
P_HTM[4655]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, paṇḍito mahāpañño hotī”ti.**That’s how a person is astute, with great wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[4656]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4657]="*6. Ummaggasuttaṃ**With Vassakāra*";
P_HTM[4658]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[4659]="*Atha kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Vassakāra the brahmin, a chief minister of Magadha, went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4660]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4661]="*“Jāneyya nu kho, bho gotama, asappuriso asappurisaṃ:**“Master Gotama, could a bad person know of a bad person:*";
P_HTM[4662]="*‘asappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti?**‘This fellow is a bad person’?”*";
P_HTM[4663]="*“Aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, anavakāso yaṃ asappuriso asappurisaṃ jāneyya:**“That’s impossible, brahmin, it can’t happen.”*";
P_HTM[4664]="*‘asappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4665]="*“Jāneyya pana, bho gotama, asappuriso sappurisaṃ:**“Could a bad person know of a good person:*";
P_HTM[4666]="*‘sappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti?**‘This fellow is a good person’?”*";
P_HTM[4667]="*“Etampi kho, brāhmaṇa, aṭṭhānaṃ anavakāso yaṃ asappuriso sappurisaṃ jāneyya:**“That too is impossible, it can’t happen.”*";
P_HTM[4668]="*‘sappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4669]="*“Jāneyya nu kho, bho gotama, sappuriso sappurisaṃ:**“Master Gotama, could a good person know of a good person:*";
P_HTM[4670]="*‘sappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti?**‘This fellow is a good person’?”*";
P_HTM[4671]="*“Ṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, vijjati yaṃ sappuriso sappurisaṃ jāneyya:**“That, brahmin, is possible.”*";
P_HTM[4672]="*‘sappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4673]="*“Jāneyya pana, bho gotama, sappuriso asappurisaṃ:**“Could a good person know of a bad person:*";
P_HTM[4674]="*‘asappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti?**‘This fellow is a bad person’?”*";
P_HTM[4675]="*“Etampi kho, brāhmaṇa, ṭhānaṃ vijjati yaṃ sappuriso asappurisaṃ jāneyya:**“That too is possible.”*";
P_HTM[4676]="*‘asappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4677]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bho gotama, abbhutaṃ, bho gotama.**“It’s incredible, Master Gotama, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[4678]="*Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ bhotā gotamena:**how well said this was by Master Gotama:*";
P_HTM[4679]="*‘aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, anavakāso yaṃ asappuriso asappurisaṃ jāneyya—**‘It’s impossible, it can’t happen, that a bad person could know …*";
P_HTM[4680]="*asappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.* **";
P_HTM[4681]="*Etampi kho, brāhmaṇa, aṭṭhānaṃ anavakāso yaṃ asappuriso sappurisaṃ jāneyya—* **";
P_HTM[4682]="*sappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.* **";
P_HTM[4683]="*Ṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, vijjati yaṃ sappuriso sappurisaṃ jāneyya—**But it is possible that a good person could know …’*";
P_HTM[4684]="*sappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.* **";
P_HTM[4685]="*Etampi kho, brāhmaṇa, ṭhānaṃ vijjati yaṃ sappuriso asappurisaṃ jāneyya—* **";
P_HTM[4686]="*asappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4687]="*Ekamidaṃ, bho gotama, samayaṃ todeyyassa brāhmaṇassa parisati parūpārambhaṃ vattenti:**Once, members of the brahmin Todeyya’s assembly were going on complaining about others:*";
P_HTM[4688]="*‘bālo ayaṃ rājā eḷeyyo samaṇe rāmaputte abhippasanno, samaṇe ca pana rāmaputte evarūpaṃ paramanipaccakāraṃ karoti, yadidaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikammanti.**‘This King Eḷeyya is a fool to be so devoted to Rāmaputta. He even shows him the utmost deference by bowing down to him, rising up for him, greeting him with joined palms, and observing proper etiquette for him.*";
P_HTM[4689]="*Imepi rañño eḷeyyassa parihārakā bālā—**And these king’s men are fools too—*";
P_HTM[4690]="*yamako moggallo uggo nāvindakī gandhabbo aggivesso, ye samaṇe rāmaputte abhippasannā, samaṇe ca pana rāmaputte evarūpaṃ paramanipaccakāraṃ karonti, yadidaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikamman’ti.**Yamaka, Moggalla, Ugga, Nāvindakī, Gandhabba, and Aggivessa—for they show the same kind of deference to Rāmaputta.’*";
P_HTM[4691]="*Tyāssudaṃ todeyyo brāhmaṇo iminā nayena neti.**Then the brahmin Todeyya reasoned with them like this:*";
P_HTM[4692]="*‘Taṃ kiṃ maññanti, bhonto,**‘What do you think, sirs?*";
P_HTM[4693]="*paṇḍito rājā eḷeyyo karaṇīyādhikaraṇīyesu vacanīyādhivacanīyesu alamatthadasatarehi alamatthadasataro’ti?**When it comes to the various duties and speeches, isn’t King Eḷeyya astute, even better than the experts?’*";
P_HTM[4694]="*‘Evaṃ, bho, paṇḍito rājā eḷeyyo karaṇīyādhikaraṇīyesu vacanīyādhivacanīyesu alamatthadasatarehi alamatthadasataroti.**‘That’s true, sir.’*";
P_HTM[4695]="*Yasmā ca kho, bho, samaṇo rāmaputto raññā eḷeyyena paṇḍitena paṇḍitataro karaṇīyādhikaraṇīyesu vacanīyādhivacanīyesu alamatthadasatarena alamatthadasataro, tasmā rājā eḷeyyo samaṇe rāmaputte abhippasanno, samaṇe ca pana rāmaputte evarūpaṃ paramanipaccakāraṃ karoti, yadidaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikammaṃ’.**‘It’s because Rāmaputta is even more astute and expert than King Eḷeyya that the king is so devoted to him. That’s why he even shows Rāmaputta the utmost deference by bowing down to him, rising up for him, greeting him with joined palms, and observing proper etiquette for him.*";
P_HTM[4696]="*‘Taṃ kiṃ maññanti, bhonto,**What do you think, sirs?*";
P_HTM[4697]="*paṇḍitā rañño eḷeyyassa parihārakā—* **";
P_HTM[4698]="*yamako moggallo uggo nāvindakī gandhabbo aggivesso, karaṇīyādhikaraṇīyesu vacanīyādhivacanīyesu alamatthadasatarehi alamatthadasatarā’ti?**When it comes to the various duties and speeches, aren’t the king’s men—Yamaka, Moggalla, Ugga, Nāvindakī, Gandhabba, and Aggivessa—astute, even better than the experts?’*";
P_HTM[4699]="*‘Evaṃ, bho, paṇḍitā rañño eḷeyyassa parihārakā—**‘That’s true, sir.’*";
P_HTM[4700]="*yamako moggallo uggo nāvindakī gandhabbo aggivesso, karaṇīyādhikaraṇīyesu vacanīyādhivacanīyesu alamatthadasatarehi alamatthadasatarāti.* **";
P_HTM[4701]="*Yasmā ca kho, bho, samaṇo rāmaputto rañño eḷeyyassa parihārakehi paṇḍitehi paṇḍitataro karaṇīyādhikaraṇīyesu vacanīyādhivacanīyesu alamatthadasatarehi alamatthadasataro, tasmā rañño eḷeyyassa parihārakā samaṇe rāmaputte abhippasannā;**‘It’s because Rāmaputta is even more astute and expert than the king’s men that they have such devotion to him. …*";
P_HTM[4702]="*samaṇe ca pana rāmaputte evarūpaṃ paramanipaccakāraṃ karonti, yadidaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikamman’ti.**It’s because Rāmaputta is even more astute and expert than King Eḷeyya that the king is so devoted to him. That’s why he even shows Rāmaputta the utmost deference by bowing down to him, rising up for him, greeting him with joined palms, and observing proper etiquette for him.’*";
P_HTM[4703]="*Acchariyaṃ, bho gotama, abbhutaṃ, bho gotama.**It’s incredible, Master Gotama, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[4704]="*Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ bhotā gotamena:**how well said this was by Master Gotama:*";
P_HTM[4705]="*‘aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, anavakāso yaṃ asappuriso asappurisaṃ jāneyya—**‘It’s impossible, it can’t happen, that a bad person could know …*";
P_HTM[4706]="*asappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.* **";
P_HTM[4707]="*Etampi kho, brāhmaṇa, aṭṭhānaṃ anavakāso yaṃ asappuriso sappurisaṃ jāneyya—* **";
P_HTM[4708]="*sappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.* **";
P_HTM[4709]="*Ṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, vijjati yaṃ sappuriso sappurisaṃ jāneyya—**But it is possible that a good person could know …*";
P_HTM[4710]="*sappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti.* **";
P_HTM[4711]="*Etampi kho, brāhmaṇa, ṭhānaṃ vijjati yaṃ sappuriso asappurisaṃ jāneyya—* **";
P_HTM[4712]="*asappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4713]="*Handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bho gotama, gacchāma.**Well, now, Master Gotama, I must go.*";
P_HTM[4714]="*Bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti.**I have many duties, and much to do.”*";
P_HTM[4715]="*“Yassadāni tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**“Please, brahmin, go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[4716]="*Atha kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmīti.**Then Vassakāra the brahmin, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[4717]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4718]="*7. Vassakārasuttaṃ**With Upaka*";
P_HTM[4719]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate.**Once the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain.*";
P_HTM[4720]="*Atha kho upako maṇḍikāputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho upako maṇḍikāputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Upaka the son of Maṇḍikā went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[4721]="*“Ahañhi, bhante, evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“Sir, this is my doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[4722]="*‘yo koci parūpārambhaṃ vatteti, parūpārambhaṃ vattento sabbo so na upapādeti.**‘Whoever goes on complaining about others without giving any reasons*";
P_HTM[4723]="*Anupapādento gārayho hoti upavajjo’”ti.**is reprehensible and at fault.’”*";
P_HTM[4724]="*“Parūpārambhañce, upaka, vatteti parūpārambhaṃ vattento na upapādeti, anupapādento gārayho hoti upavajjo.**“Upaka, if someone goes on complaining about others without giving a reason, they’re reprehensible and at fault.*";
P_HTM[4725]="*Tvaṃ kho, upaka, parūpārambhaṃ vattesi, parūpārambhaṃ vattento na upapādesi, anupapādento gārayho hosi upavajjo”ti.**But that’s what you do, so you’re reprehensible and at fault!”*";
P_HTM[4726]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhante, ummujjamānakaṃyeva mahatā pāsena bandheyya;**“Sir, like a fish caught in a big trap just as it rises,*";
P_HTM[4727]="*evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, ummujjamānakoyeva bhagavatā mahatā vādapāsena baddho”ti.**so the Buddha caught me in a big trap of words just as I rose up.”*";
P_HTM[4728]="*“Idaṃ akusalanti kho, upaka, mayā paññattaṃ.**“Upaka, I’ve declared: ‘This is unskillful.’*";
P_HTM[4729]="*Tattha aparimāṇā padā aparimāṇā byañjanā aparimāṇā tathāgatassa dhammadesanā—**And there are limitless words, phrases, and teachings of the Realized One about that:*";
P_HTM[4730]="*itipidaṃ akusalanti.**‘This is another way of saying that this is unskillful.’*";
P_HTM[4731]="*Taṃ kho panidaṃ akusalaṃ pahātabbanti kho, upaka, mayā paññattaṃ.**I’ve declared: ‘The unskillful should be given up.’*";
P_HTM[4732]="*Tattha aparimāṇā padā aparimāṇā byañjanā aparimāṇā tathāgatassa dhammadesanā—**And there are limitless words, phrases, and teachings of the Realized One about that:*";
P_HTM[4733]="*itipidaṃ akusalaṃ pahātabbanti.**‘This is another way of saying that the unskillful should be given up.’*";
P_HTM[4734]="*Idaṃ kusalanti kho, upaka, mayā paññattaṃ.**I’ve declared that: ‘This is skillful.’*";
P_HTM[4735]="*Tattha aparimāṇā padā aparimāṇā byañjanā aparimāṇā tathāgatassa dhammadesanā—**And there are limitless words, phrases, and teachings of the Realized One about that:*";
P_HTM[4736]="*itipidaṃ kusalanti.**‘This is another way of saying that this is skillful.’*";
P_HTM[4737]="*Taṃ kho panidaṃ kusalaṃ bhāvetabbanti kho, upaka, mayā paññattaṃ.**I’ve declared: ‘The skillful should be developed.’*";
P_HTM[4738]="*Tattha aparimāṇā padā aparimāṇā byañjanā aparimāṇā tathāgatassa dhammadesanā—**And there are limitless words, phrases, and teachings of the Realized One about that:*";
P_HTM[4739]="*itipidaṃ kusalaṃ bhāvetabban”ti.**‘This is another way of saying that the skillful should be developed.’”*";
P_HTM[4740]="*Atha kho upako maṇḍikāputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā yāvatako ahosi bhagavatā saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ rañño māgadhassa ajātasattussa vedehiputtassa ārocesi.**And then Upaka the son of Maṇḍikā approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right. Then he went up to King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha. He told the King of all they had discussed.*";
P_HTM[4741]="*Evaṃ vutte, rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto kupito anattamano upakaṃ maṇḍikāputtaṃ etadavoca:**But Ajātasattu became angry and upset, and said to Upaka,*";
P_HTM[4742]="*“yāva dhaṃsī vatāyaṃ loṇakāradārako yāva mukharo yāva pagabbo yatra hi nāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ āsādetabbaṃ maññissati;**“How rude of this salt-maker’s boy! How impolite and impudent of him to imagine he could attack the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[4743]="*apehi tvaṃ, upaka, vinassa, mā taṃ addasan”ti.**Get out, Upaka, go away! Don’t let me see you again.”*";
P_HTM[4744]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4745]="*8. Upakasuttaṃ**Things to be Realized*";
P_HTM[4746]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, sacchikaraṇīyā dhammā.**“Mendicants, these four things should be realized.*";
P_HTM[4747]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4748]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, dhammā kāyena sacchikaraṇīyā;**There are things to be realized directly.*";
P_HTM[4749]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dhammā satiyā sacchikaraṇīyā;**There are things to be realized with mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[4750]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dhammā cakkhunā sacchikaraṇīyā;**There are things to be realized with vision.*";
P_HTM[4751]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dhammā paññāya sacchikaraṇīyā.**There are things to be realized with wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4752]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā kāyena sacchikaraṇīyā?**What things are to be realized directly?*";
P_HTM[4753]="*Aṭṭha vimokkhā, bhikkhave, kāyena sacchikaraṇīyā.**The eight liberations.*";
P_HTM[4754]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā satiyā sacchikaraṇīyā?**What things are to be realized with mindfulness?*";
P_HTM[4755]="*Pubbenivāso, bhikkhave, satiyā sacchikaraṇīyo.**Past lives.*";
P_HTM[4756]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā cakkhunā sacchikaraṇīyā?**What things are to be realized with vision?*";
P_HTM[4757]="*Sattānaṃ cutūpapāto, bhikkhave, cakkhunā sacchikaraṇīyo.**The passing away and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[4758]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā paññāya sacchikaraṇīyā?**What things are to be realized with wisdom?*";
P_HTM[4759]="*Āsavānaṃ khayo, bhikkhave, paññāya sacchikaraṇīyo.**The ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4760]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro sacchikaraṇīyā dhammā”ti.**These are the four things to be realized.”*";
P_HTM[4761]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4762]="*9. Sacchikaraṇīyasuttaṃ**Sabbath*";
P_HTM[4763]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother.*";
P_HTM[4764]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā tadahuposathe bhikkhusaṃghaparivuto nisinno hoti.**Now, at that time it was the sabbath, and the Buddha was sitting surrounded by the Saṅgha of monks.*";
P_HTM[4765]="*Atha kho bhagavā tuṇhībhūtaṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ anuviloketvā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha looked around the Saṅgha of monks, who were so very silent. He addressed them:*";
P_HTM[4766]="*“Apalāpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā nippalāpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā suddhā sāre patiṭṭhitā.**“This assembly has no nonsense, mendicants, it’s free of nonsense. It consists purely of the essential core.*";
P_HTM[4767]="*Tathārūpo ayaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhusaṃgho, tathārūpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā.**Such is this Saṅgha of monks, such is this assembly!*";
P_HTM[4768]="*Yathārūpā parisā dullabhā dassanāyapi lokasmiṃ, tathārūpo ayaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhusaṃgho, tathārūpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā.**An assembly such as this is rarely seen in the world.*";
P_HTM[4769]="*Yathārūpā parisā āhuneyyā pāhuneyyā dakkhiṇeyyā añjalikaraṇīyā anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa, tathārūpo ayaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhusaṃgho, tathārūpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā.**An assembly such as this is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[4770]="*Yathārūpāya parisāya appaṃ dinnaṃ bahu hoti bahu dinnaṃ bahutaraṃ, tathārūpo ayaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhusaṃgho, tathārūpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā.**Even a small gift to an assembly such as this is plentiful, while giving more is even more plentiful.*";
P_HTM[4771]="*Yathārūpaṃ parisaṃ alaṃ yojanagaṇanānipi dassanāya gantuṃ api puṭosenāpi, tathārūpo ayaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhusaṃgho, tathārūpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā.**An assembly such as this is worth traveling many leagues to see, even if you have to carry your own provisions in a shoulder bag.*";
P_HTM[4772]="*Santi, bhikkhave, bhikkhū imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṅghe devappattā viharanti;**There are monks staying in this Saṅgha who have attained to the gods.*";
P_HTM[4773]="*santi, bhikkhave, bhikkhū imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṅghe brahmappattā viharanti;**There are monks staying in this Saṅgha who have attained to Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[4774]="*santi, bhikkhave, bhikkhū imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṅghe āneñjappattā viharanti;**There are monks staying in this Saṅgha who have attained to the imperturbable.*";
P_HTM[4775]="*santi, bhikkhave, bhikkhū imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṅghe ariyappattā viharanti.**There are monks staying in this Saṅgha who have attained to nobility.*";
P_HTM[4776]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu devappatto hoti?**And how has a monk attained to the gods?*";
P_HTM[4777]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**It’s when a monk, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption …*";
P_HTM[4778]="*vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption …*";
P_HTM[4779]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu devappatto hoti.**That’s how a monk has attained to the gods.*";
P_HTM[4780]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu brahmappatto hoti?**And how has a monk attained to Brahmā?*";
P_HTM[4781]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati.**Firstly, a monk meditates spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[4782]="*Karuṇā …**Furthermore, a monk meditates spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[4783]="*muditā …**rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[4784]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati.**equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[4785]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu brahmappatto hoti.**That’s how a monk has attained to Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[4786]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āneñjappatto hoti?**And how has a monk attained to the imperturbable?*";
P_HTM[4787]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a monk—going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity—aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space.*";
P_HTM[4788]="*Sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, he enters and remains in the dimension of infinite consciousness.*";
P_HTM[4789]="*Sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, he enters and remains in the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[4790]="*Sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, he enters and remains in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[4791]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āneñjappatto hoti.**That’s how a monk has attained to the imperturbable.*";
P_HTM[4792]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyappatto hoti?**And how has a monk attained to nobility?*";
P_HTM[4793]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**It’s when they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[4794]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyappatto hotī”ti.**That’s how a monk has attained to nobility.”*";
P_HTM[4795]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4796]="*Brāhmaṇavaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[4797]="*Yodhā pāṭibhogasutaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[4798]="*Abhayaṃ brāhmaṇasaccena pañcamaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4799]="*Ummaggavassakāro,* **";
P_HTM[4800]="*Upako sacchikiriyā ca uposathoti.* **";
P_HTM[4801]="*10. Uposathasuttaṃ**Followed by Ear*";
P_HTM[4802]="*“Sotānugatānaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ, vacasā paricitānaṃ, manasānupekkhitānaṃ, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhānaṃ cattāro ānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā.**“Mendicants, you can expect four benefits when the teachings have been followed by ear, reinforced by recitation, examined by the mind, and well comprehended theoretically.*";
P_HTM[4803]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4804]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—**Take a mendicant who memorizes the teaching—*";
P_HTM[4805]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.**statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications.*";
P_HTM[4806]="*Tassa te dhammā sotānugatā honti, vacasā paricitā, manasānupekkhitā, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.**They’ve followed those teachings by ear, reinforced them by recitation, examined them by the mind, and well comprehended them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[4807]="*So muṭṭhassati kālaṃ kurumāno aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ upapajjati.**But they die unmindful and are reborn in one of the orders of gods.*";
P_HTM[4808]="*Tassa tattha sukhino dhammapadā plavanti.**Being happy there, passages of the teaching come back to them.*";
P_HTM[4809]="*Dandho, bhikkhave, satuppādo;**Memory comes up slowly,*";
P_HTM[4810]="*atha so satto khippaṃyeva visesagāmī hoti.**but then that being quickly reaches distinction.*";
P_HTM[4811]="*Sotānugatānaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ, vacasā paricitānaṃ, manasānupekkhitānaṃ, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhānaṃ ayaṃ paṭhamo ānisaṃso pāṭikaṅkho.**This is the first benefit you can expect when the teachings have been followed by ear, reinforced by recitation, examined by the mind, and well comprehended theoretically.*";
P_HTM[4812]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—**Take another mendicant who memorizes the teaching—*";
P_HTM[4813]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.**statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications.*";
P_HTM[4814]="*Tassa te dhammā sotānugatā honti, vacasā paricitā, manasānupekkhitā, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.**They’ve followed those teachings by ear, reinforced them by recitation, examined them by the mind, and well comprehended them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[4815]="*So muṭṭhassati kālaṃ kurumāno aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ upapajjati.**But they die unmindful and are reborn in one of the orders of gods.*";
P_HTM[4816]="*Tassa tattha na heva kho sukhino dhammapadā plavanti;**Though they’re happy there, passages of the teaching don’t come back to them.*";
P_HTM[4817]="*api ca kho bhikkhu iddhimā cetovasippatto devaparisāyaṃ dhammaṃ deseti.**However, a mendicant with psychic powers, who has achieved mastery of the mind, teaches Dhamma to the assembly of gods.*";
P_HTM[4818]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[4819]="*‘ayaṃ vā so dhammavinayo, yatthāhaṃ pubbe brahmacariyaṃ acarin’ti.**‘I used to live the spiritual life in this same teaching and training.’*";
P_HTM[4820]="*Dandho, bhikkhave, satuppādo;**Memory comes up slowly,*";
P_HTM[4821]="*atha so satto khippameva visesagāmī hoti.**but then that being quickly reaches distinction.*";
P_HTM[4822]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso kusalo bherisaddassa.**Suppose a person was skilled in the sound of drums.*";
P_HTM[4823]="*So addhānamaggappaṭipanno bherisaddaṃ suṇeyya.**While traveling along a road they hear the sound of drums.*";
P_HTM[4824]="*Tassa na heva kho assa kaṅkhā vā vimati vā:**They wouldn’t have any doubts or uncertainties about whether*";
P_HTM[4825]="*‘bherisaddo nu kho, na nu kho bherisaddo’ti.**that was the sound of drums or not.*";
P_HTM[4826]="*Atha kho bherisaddotveva niṭṭhaṃ gaccheyya.**They’d just conclude, ‘That’s the sound of drums.’*";
P_HTM[4827]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—**In the same way, take another mendicant who memorizes the teaching …*";
P_HTM[4828]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4829]="*Tassa te dhammā sotānugatā honti, vacasā paricitā, manasānupekkhitā, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.* **";
P_HTM[4830]="*So muṭṭhassati kālaṃ kurumāno aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ upapajjati.**But they die unmindful and are reborn in one of the orders of gods. …*";
P_HTM[4831]="*Tassa tattha na heva kho sukhino dhammapadā plavanti;* **";
P_HTM[4832]="*api ca kho bhikkhu iddhimā cetovasippatto devaparisāyaṃ dhammaṃ deseti.* **";
P_HTM[4833]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:* **";
P_HTM[4834]="*‘ayaṃ vā so dhammavinayo, yatthāhaṃ pubbe brahmacariyaṃ acarin’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4835]="*Dandho, bhikkhave, satuppādo;**Memory comes up slowly,*";
P_HTM[4836]="*atha so satto khippaṃyeva visesagāmī hoti.**but then that being quickly reaches distinction.*";
P_HTM[4837]="*Sotānugatānaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ, vacasā paricitānaṃ, manasānupekkhitānaṃ, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhānaṃ ayaṃ dutiyo ānisaṃso pāṭikaṅkho.**This is the second benefit you can expect when the teachings have been followed by ear, reinforced by recitation, examined by the mind, and well comprehended theoretically.*";
P_HTM[4838]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—**Take another mendicant who memorizes the teaching—*";
P_HTM[4839]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.**statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications.*";
P_HTM[4840]="*Tassa te dhammā sotānugatā honti, vacasā paricitā, manasānupekkhitā, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.**They’ve followed those teachings by ear, reinforced them by recitation, examined them by the mind, and well comprehended them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[4841]="*So muṭṭhassati kālaṃ kurumāno aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ upapajjati.**But they die unmindful and are reborn in one of the orders of gods.*";
P_HTM[4842]="*Tassa tattha na heva kho sukhino dhammapadā plavanti, napi bhikkhu iddhimā cetovasippatto devaparisāyaṃ dhammaṃ deseti;**But passages of the teaching don’t come back to them when they’re happy, nor does a mendicant with psychic powers … teach Dhamma to the assembly of gods.*";
P_HTM[4843]="*api ca kho devaputto devaparisāyaṃ dhammaṃ deseti.**However, a god teaches Dhamma to the assembly of gods.*";
P_HTM[4844]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[4845]="*‘ayaṃ vā so dhammavinayo, yatthāhaṃ pubbe brahmacariyaṃ acarin’ti.**‘I used to live the spiritual life in this same teaching and training.’*";
P_HTM[4846]="*Dandho, bhikkhave, satuppādo;**Memory comes up slowly,*";
P_HTM[4847]="*atha so satto khippaṃyeva visesagāmī hoti.**but then that being quickly reaches distinction.*";
P_HTM[4848]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso kusalo saṅkhasaddassa.**Suppose a person was skilled in the sound of horns.*";
P_HTM[4849]="*So addhānamaggappaṭipanno saṅkhasaddaṃ suṇeyya.**While traveling along a road they hear the sound of horns.*";
P_HTM[4850]="*Tassa na heva kho assa kaṅkhā vā vimati vā:**They wouldn’t have any doubt about whether*";
P_HTM[4851]="*‘saṅkhasaddo nu kho, na nu kho saṅkhasaddo’ti.**that was the sound of horns or not.*";
P_HTM[4852]="*Atha kho saṅkhasaddotveva niṭṭhaṃ gaccheyya.**They’d just conclude, ‘That’s the sound of horns.’*";
P_HTM[4853]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—**In the same way, take another mendicant who memorizes the teaching …*";
P_HTM[4854]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4855]="*Tassa te dhammā sotānugatā honti, vacasā paricitā, manasānupekkhitā, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.* **";
P_HTM[4856]="*So muṭṭhassati kālaṃ kurumāno aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ upapajjati.**But they die unmindful and are reborn in one of the orders of gods. …*";
P_HTM[4857]="*Tassa tattha na heva kho sukhino dhammapadā plavanti, napi bhikkhu iddhimā cetovasippatto devaparisāyaṃ dhammaṃ deseti;* **";
P_HTM[4858]="*api ca kho devaputto devaparisāyaṃ dhammaṃ deseti.* **";
P_HTM[4859]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:* **";
P_HTM[4860]="*‘ayaṃ vā so dhammavinayo, yatthāhaṃ pubbe brahmacariyaṃ acarin’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4861]="*Dandho, bhikkhave, satuppādo;**Memory comes up slowly,*";
P_HTM[4862]="*atha so satto khippaṃyeva visesagāmī hoti.**but then that being quickly reaches distinction.*";
P_HTM[4863]="*Sotānugatānaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ, vacasā paricitānaṃ, manasānupekkhitānaṃ, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhānaṃ ayaṃ tatiyo ānisaṃso pāṭikaṅkho.**This is the third benefit you can expect when the teachings have been followed by ear, reinforced by recitation, examined by the mind, and well comprehended theoretically.*";
P_HTM[4864]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—**Take another mendicant who memorizes the teaching—*";
P_HTM[4865]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.**statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications.*";
P_HTM[4866]="*Tassa te dhammā sotānugatā honti, vacasā paricitā, manasānupekkhitā, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.**They’ve followed those teachings by ear, reinforced them by recitation, examined them by the mind, and well comprehended them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[4867]="*So muṭṭhassati kālaṃ kurumāno aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ upapajjati.**But they die unmindful and are reborn in one of the orders of gods.*";
P_HTM[4868]="*Tassa tattha na heva kho sukhino dhammapadā plavanti, napi bhikkhu iddhimā cetovasippatto devaparisāyaṃ dhammaṃ deseti, napi devaputto devaparisāyaṃ dhammaṃ deseti;**But passages of the teaching don’t come back to them when they’re happy, and neither a mendicant with psychic powers … nor a god teaches Dhamma to the assembly of gods.*";
P_HTM[4869]="*api ca kho opapātiko opapātikaṃ sāreti:**But a being who has been reborn spontaneously reminds another such being:*";
P_HTM[4870]="*‘sarasi tvaṃ, mārisa, sarasi tvaṃ, mārisa, yattha mayaṃ pubbe brahmacariyaṃ acarimhā’ti.**‘Do you remember, good sir? Do you remember where we used to live the spiritual life?’*";
P_HTM[4871]="*So evamāha:**He says:*";
P_HTM[4872]="*‘sarāmi, mārisa, sarāmi, mārisā’ti.**‘I remember, good sir, I remember!’*";
P_HTM[4873]="*Dandho, bhikkhave, satuppādo;**Memory comes up slowly,*";
P_HTM[4874]="*atha so satto khippaṃyeva visesagāmī hoti.**but then that being quickly reaches distinction.*";
P_HTM[4875]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dve sahāyakā sahapaṃsukīḷikā.**Suppose there were two friends who had played together in the sand.*";
P_HTM[4876]="*Te kadāci karahaci aññamaññaṃ samāgaccheyyuṃ.**Some time or other they’d meet.*";
P_HTM[4877]="*Añño pana sahāyako sahāyakaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:**And one friend would say to the other:*";
P_HTM[4878]="*‘idampi, samma, sarasi, idampi, samma, sarasī’ti.**‘Do you remember this, friend? Do you remember that, friend?’*";
P_HTM[4879]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**They’d say:*";
P_HTM[4880]="*‘sarāmi, samma, sarāmi, sammā’ti.**‘I remember, friend, I remember!’*";
P_HTM[4881]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—**In the same way, take another mendicant who memorizes the teaching …*";
P_HTM[4882]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4883]="*Tassa te dhammā sotānugatā honti, vacasā paricitā, manasānupekkhitā, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.* **";
P_HTM[4884]="*So muṭṭhassati kālaṃ kurumāno aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ upapajjati.**But they die unmindful and are reborn in one of the orders of gods. …*";
P_HTM[4885]="*Tassa tattha na heva kho sukhino dhammapadā plavanti, napi bhikkhu iddhimā cetovasippatto devaparisāyaṃ dhammaṃ deseti, napi devaputto devaparisāyaṃ dhammaṃ deseti;* **";
P_HTM[4886]="*api ca kho opapātiko opapātikaṃ sāreti:* **";
P_HTM[4887]="*‘sarasi tvaṃ, mārisa, sarasi tvaṃ, mārisa, yattha mayaṃ pubbe brahmacariyaṃ acarimhā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4888]="*So evamāha:* **";
P_HTM[4889]="*‘sarāmi, mārisa, sarāmi, mārisā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4890]="*Dandho, bhikkhave, satuppādo;**Memory comes up slowly,*";
P_HTM[4891]="*atha kho so satto khippaṃyeva visesagāmī hoti.**but then that being quickly reaches distinction.*";
P_HTM[4892]="*Sotānugatānaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ, vacasā paricitānaṃ, manasānupekkhitānaṃ, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhānaṃ ayaṃ catuttho ānisaṃso pāṭikaṅkho.**This is the fourth benefit you can expect when the teachings have been followed by ear, reinforced by recitation, examined by the mind, and well comprehended theoretically.*";
P_HTM[4893]="*Sotānugatānaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ, vacasā paricitānaṃ, manasānupekkhitānaṃ diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhānaṃ ime cattāro ānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā”ti.**You can expect these four benefits when the teachings have been followed by ear, reinforced by recitation, examined by the mind, and well comprehended theoretically.”*";
P_HTM[4894]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4895]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**The Great Chapter*";
P_HTM[4896]="*1. Sotānugatasuttaṃ**Facts*";
P_HTM[4897]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, ṭhānāni catūhi ṭhānehi veditabbāni.**“Mendicants, these four things can be known in four situations.*";
P_HTM[4898]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4899]="*Saṃvāsena, bhikkhave, sīlaṃ veditabbaṃ, tañca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; paññavatā, no duppaññena.**You can get to know a person’s ethics by living with them. But only after a long time, not casually; only when paying attention, not when inattentive; and only by the wise, not the witless.*";
P_HTM[4900]="*Saṃvohārena, bhikkhave, soceyyaṃ veditabbaṃ, tañca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; paññavatā, no duppaññena.**You can get to know a person’s purity by dealing with them. …*";
P_HTM[4901]="*Āpadāsu, bhikkhave, thāmo veditabbo, so ca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; paññavatā, no duppaññena.**You can get to know a person’s resilience in times of trouble. …*";
P_HTM[4902]="*Sākacchāya, bhikkhave, paññā veditabbā, sā ca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; paññavatā, no duppaññenāti.**You can get to know a person’s wisdom by discussion. But only after a long time, not casually; only when paying attention, not when inattentive; and only by the wise, not the witless.*";
P_HTM[4903]="*‘Saṃvāsena, bhikkhave, sīlaṃ veditabbaṃ, tañca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; paññavatā, no duppaññenā’ti,**‘You can get to know a person’s ethics by living with them. But only after a long time, not casually; only when paying attention, not when inattentive; and only by the wise, not the witless.’*";
P_HTM[4904]="*iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**That’s what I said, but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[4905]="*Idha, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalena saddhiṃ saṃvasamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Take a person who’s living with someone else. They come to know:*";
P_HTM[4906]="*‘dīgharattaṃ kho ayamāyasmā khaṇḍakārī chiddakārī sabalakārī kammāsakārī, na santatakārī na santatavutti;**‘For a long time this venerable’s deeds have been broken, tainted, spotty, and marred. Their deeds and behavior are inconsistent.*";
P_HTM[4907]="*sīlesu dussīlo ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā sīlavā’ti.**This venerable is unethical, not ethical.’*";
P_HTM[4908]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalena saddhiṃ saṃvasamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Take another person who’s living with someone else. They come to know:*";
P_HTM[4909]="*‘dīgharattaṃ kho ayamāyasmā akhaṇḍakārī acchiddakārī asabalakārī akammāsakārī santatakārī santatavutti;**‘For a long time this venerable’s deeds have been unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred. Their deeds and behavior are consistent.*";
P_HTM[4910]="*sīlesu sīlavā ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā dussīlo’ti.**This venerable is ethical, not unethical.’*";
P_HTM[4911]="*‘Saṃvāsena, bhikkhave, sīlaṃ veditabbaṃ, tañca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; paññavatā, no duppaññenā’ti, iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (1)**That’s why I said that you can get to know a person’s ethics by living with them. But only after a long time, not a short time; only when paying attention, not when inattentive; and only by the wise, not the witless.*";
P_HTM[4912]="*‘Saṃvohārena, bhikkhave, soceyyaṃ veditabbaṃ, tañca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; paññavatā, no duppaññenā’ti,**‘You can get to know a person’s purity by dealing with them. …’*";
P_HTM[4913]="*iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**That’s what I said, but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[4914]="*Idha, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalena saddhiṃ saṃvoharamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Take a person who has dealings with someone else. They come to know:*";
P_HTM[4915]="*‘aññathā kho ayamāyasmā ekena eko voharati, aññathā dvīhi, aññathā tīhi, aññathā sambahulehi;**‘This venerable deals with one person in one way. Then they deal with two, three, or many people each in different ways.*";
P_HTM[4916]="*vokkamati ayamāyasmā purimavohārā pacchimavohāraṃ;**They’re not consistent from one deal to the next.*";
P_HTM[4917]="*aparisuddhavohāro ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā parisuddhavohāro’ti.**This venerable’s dealings are impure, not pure.’*";
P_HTM[4918]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalena saddhiṃ saṃvoharamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Take another person who has dealings with someone else. They come to know:*";
P_HTM[4919]="*‘yatheva kho ayamāyasmā ekena eko voharati, tathā dvīhi, tathā tīhi, tathā sambahulehi.**‘This venerable deals with one person in one way. Then they deal with two, three, or many people each in the same way.*";
P_HTM[4920]="*Nāyamāyasmā vokkamati purimavohārā pacchimavohāraṃ;**They’re consistent from one deal to the next.*";
P_HTM[4921]="*parisuddhavohāro ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā aparisuddhavohāro’ti.**This venerable’s dealings are pure, not impure.’*";
P_HTM[4922]="*‘Saṃvohārena, bhikkhave, soceyyaṃ veditabbaṃ, tañca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; paññavatā, no duppaññenā’ti, iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (2)**That’s why I said that you can get to know a person’s purity by dealing with them. …*";
P_HTM[4923]="*‘Āpadāsu, bhikkhave, thāmo veditabbo, so ca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; paññavatā, no duppaññenā’ti,**‘You can get to know a person’s resilience in times of trouble. …’*";
P_HTM[4924]="*iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**That’s what I said, but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[4925]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco ñātibyasanena vā phuṭṭho samāno, bhogabyasanena vā phuṭṭho samāno, rogabyasanena vā phuṭṭho samāno na iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Take a person who experiences loss of family, wealth, or health. But they don’t reflect:*";
P_HTM[4926]="*‘tathābhūto kho ayaṃ lokasannivāso tathābhūto ayaṃ attabhāvapaṭilābho yathābhūte lokasannivāse yathābhūte attabhāvapaṭilābhe aṭṭha lokadhammā lokaṃ anuparivattanti loko ca aṭṭha lokadhamme anuparivattati—**‘The world’s like that. Reincarnation’s like that. That’s why the eight worldly conditions revolve around the world, and the world revolves around the eight worldly conditions:*";
P_HTM[4927]="*lābho ca, alābho ca, yaso ca, ayaso ca, nindā ca, pasaṃsā ca, sukhañca, dukkhañcā’ti.**gain and loss, fame and disgrace, praise and blame, pleasure and pain.’*";
P_HTM[4928]="*So ñātibyasanena vā phuṭṭho samāno bhogabyasanena vā phuṭṭho samāno rogabyasanena vā phuṭṭho samāno socati kilamati paridevati, urattāḷiṃ kandati, sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[4929]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco ñātibyasanena vā phuṭṭho samāno bhogabyasanena vā phuṭṭho samāno rogabyasanena vā phuṭṭho samāno iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Take another person who experiences loss of family, wealth, or health. But they reflect:*";
P_HTM[4930]="*‘tathābhūto kho ayaṃ lokasannivāso tathābhūto ayaṃ attabhāvapaṭilābho yathābhūte lokasannivāse yathābhūte attabhāvapaṭilābhe aṭṭha lokadhammā lokaṃ anuparivattanti loko ca aṭṭha lokadhamme anuparivattati—**‘The world’s like that. Reincarnation’s like that. That’s why the eight worldly conditions revolve around the world, and the world revolves around the eight worldly conditions:*";
P_HTM[4931]="*lābho ca, alābho ca, yaso ca, ayaso ca, nindā ca, pasaṃsā ca, sukhañca, dukkhañcā’ti.**gain and loss, fame and disgrace, praise and blame, pleasure and pain.’*";
P_HTM[4932]="*So ñātibyasanena vā phuṭṭho samāno bhogabyasanena vā phuṭṭho samāno rogabyasanena vā phuṭṭho samāno na socati na kilamati na paridevati, na urattāḷiṃ kandati, na sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They don’t sorrow or pine or lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[4933]="*‘Āpadāsu, bhikkhave, thāmo veditabbo, so ca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; paññavatā, no duppaññenā’ti,**That’s why I said that you can get to know a person’s resilience in times of trouble. …*";
P_HTM[4934]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (3)* **";
P_HTM[4935]="*‘Sākacchāya, bhikkhave, paññā veditabbā, sā ca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; paññavatā, no duppaññenā’ti,**‘You can get to know a person’s wisdom by discussion. But only after a long time, not casually; only when paying attention, not when inattentive; and only by the wise, not the witless.’*";
P_HTM[4936]="*iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**That’s what I said, but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[4937]="*Idha, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalena saddhiṃ sākacchāyamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Take a person who is discussing with someone else. They come to know:*";
P_HTM[4938]="*‘yathā kho imassa āyasmato ummaggo yathā ca abhinīhāro yathā ca pañhāsamudāhāro, duppañño ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā paññavā.**‘Judging by this venerable’s approach, by what they’re getting at, and by how they discuss a question, they’re witless, not wise.*";
P_HTM[4939]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4940]="*Tathā hi ayamāyasmā na ceva gambhīraṃ atthapadaṃ udāharati santaṃ paṇītaṃ atakkāvacaraṃ nipuṇaṃ paṇḍitavedanīyaṃ.**This venerable does not interpret a deep and meaningful saying that is peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute.*";
P_HTM[4941]="*Yañca ayamāyasmā dhammaṃ bhāsati tassa ca nappaṭibalo saṅkhittena vā vitthārena vā atthaṃ ācikkhituṃ desetuṃ paññāpetuṃ paṭṭhapetuṃ vivarituṃ vibhajituṃ uttānīkātuṃ.**When this venerable speaks on Dhamma they’re not able to explain the meaning, either briefly or in detail. They can’t teach it, assert it, establish it, open it, analyze it, or make it clear.*";
P_HTM[4942]="*Duppañño ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā paññavā’ti.**This venerable is witless, not wise.’*";
P_HTM[4943]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, cakkhumā puriso udakarahadassa tīre ṭhito passeyya parittaṃ macchaṃ ummujjamānaṃ.**Suppose a person with good eyesight was standing on the bank of a lake. They’d see a little fish rising,*";
P_HTM[4944]="*Tassa evamassa:**and think:*";
P_HTM[4945]="*‘yathā kho imassa macchassa ummaggo yathā ca ūmighāto yathā ca vegāyitattaṃ, paritto ayaṃ maccho, nāyaṃ maccho mahanto’ti.**‘Judging by this fish’s approach, by the ripples it makes, and by its force, it’s a little fish, not a big one.’*";
P_HTM[4946]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalena saddhiṃ sākacchāyamāno evaṃ jānāti:**In the same way, a person who is discussing with someone else would come to know:*";
P_HTM[4947]="*‘yathā kho imassa āyasmato ummaggo yathā ca abhinīhāro yathā ca pañhāsamudāhāro, duppañño ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā paññavā.**‘Judging by this venerable’s approach, by what they’re getting at, and by how they discuss a question, they’re witless, not wise. …’*";
P_HTM[4948]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[4949]="*Tathā hi ayamāyasmā na ceva gambhīraṃ atthapadaṃ udāharati santaṃ paṇītaṃ atakkāvacaraṃ nipuṇaṃ paṇḍitavedanīyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4950]="*Yañca ayamāyasmā dhammaṃ bhāsati, tassa ca na paṭibalo saṅkhittena vā vitthārena vā atthaṃ ācikkhituṃ desetuṃ paññāpetuṃ paṭṭhapetuṃ vivarituṃ vibhajituṃ uttānīkātuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4951]="*Duppañño ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā paññavā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4952]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalena saddhiṃ sākacchāyamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Take another person who is discussing with someone else. They come to know:*";
P_HTM[4953]="*‘yathā kho imassa āyasmato ummaggo yathā ca abhinīhāro yathā ca pañhāsamudāhāro, paññavā ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā duppañño.**‘Judging by this venerable’s approach, by what they’re getting at, and by how they discuss a question, they’re wise, not witless.*";
P_HTM[4954]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4955]="*Tathā hi ayamāyasmā gambhīrañceva atthapadaṃ udāharati santaṃ paṇītaṃ atakkāvacaraṃ nipuṇaṃ paṇḍitavedanīyaṃ.**This venerable interprets a deep and meaningful saying that is peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute.*";
P_HTM[4956]="*Yañca ayamāyasmā dhammaṃ bhāsati, tassa ca paṭibalo saṅkhittena vā vitthārena vā atthaṃ ācikkhituṃ desetuṃ paññāpetuṃ paṭṭhapetuṃ vivarituṃ vibhajituṃ uttānīkātuṃ.**When this venerable speaks on Dhamma they’re able to explain the meaning, either briefly or in detail. They teach it, assert it, establish it, open it, analyze it, and make it clear.*";
P_HTM[4957]="*Paññavā ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā duppañño’ti.**This venerable is wise, not witless.’*";
P_HTM[4958]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, cakkhumā puriso udakarahadassa tīre ṭhito passeyya mahantaṃ macchaṃ ummujjamānaṃ.**Suppose a man with good eyesight was standing on the bank of a lake. He’d see a big fish rising,*";
P_HTM[4959]="*Tassa evamassa:**and think:*";
P_HTM[4960]="*‘yathā kho imassa macchassa ummaggo yathā ca ūmighāto yathā ca vegāyitattaṃ, mahanto ayaṃ maccho, nāyaṃ maccho paritto’ti.**‘Judging by this fish’s approach, by the ripples it makes, and by its force, it’s a big fish, not a little one.’*";
P_HTM[4961]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalena saddhiṃ sākacchāyamāno evaṃ jānāti:**In the same way, a person who is discussing with someone else would come to know:*";
P_HTM[4962]="*‘yathā kho imassa āyasmato ummaggo yathā ca abhinīhāro yathā ca pañhāsamudāhāro, paññavā ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā duppañño.**‘Judging by this venerable’s approach, by what they’re getting at, and by how they articulate a question, they’re wise, not witless. …’*";
P_HTM[4963]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[4964]="*Tathā hi ayamāyasmā gambhīrañceva atthapadaṃ udāharati santaṃ paṇītaṃ atakkāvacaraṃ nipuṇaṃ paṇḍitavedanīyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4965]="*Yañca ayamāyasmā dhammaṃ bhāsati, tassa ca paṭibalo saṅkhittena vā vitthārena vā atthaṃ ācikkhituṃ desetuṃ paññāpetuṃ paṭṭhapetuṃ vivarituṃ vibhajituṃ uttānīkātuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4966]="*Paññavā ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā duppañño’ti. (4)* **";
P_HTM[4967]="*‘Sākacchāya, bhikkhave, paññā veditabbā, sā ca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; paññavatā, no duppaññenā’ti, iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s why I said that you can get to know a person’s wisdom by discussion. But only after a long time, not casually; only when paying attention, not when inattentive; and only by the wise, not the witless.*";
P_HTM[4968]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri ṭhānāni imehi catūhi ṭhānehi veditabbānī”ti.**These are the four things that can be known in four situations.”*";
P_HTM[4969]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4970]="*2. Ṭhānasuttaṃ**With Bhaddiya*";
P_HTM[4971]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[4972]="*Atha kho bhaddiyo licchavi yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho bhaddiyo licchavi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Bhaddiya the Licchavi went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[4973]="*“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:**“Sir, I have heard this:*";
P_HTM[4974]="*‘māyāvī samaṇo gotamo āvaṭṭaniṃ māyaṃ jānāti yāya aññatitthiyānaṃ sāvake āvaṭṭetī’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama is a magician. He knows a conversion magic, and uses it to convert the disciples of those who follow other paths.’*";
P_HTM[4975]="*Ye te, bhante, evamāhaṃsu:* **";
P_HTM[4976]="*‘māyāvī samaṇo gotamo āvaṭṭaniṃ māyaṃ jānāti yāya aññatitthiyānaṃ sāvake āvaṭṭetī’ti, kacci te, bhante, bhagavato vuttavādino, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhanti, dhammassa ca anudhammaṃ byākaronti, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānupāto gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchati, anabbhakkhātukāmā hi mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantan”ti?**I trust that those who say this repeat what the Buddha has said, and do not misrepresent him with an untruth? Is their explanation in line with the teaching? Are there any legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism?”*";
P_HTM[4977]="*“Etha tumhe, bhaddiya, mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā ‘samaṇo no garū’ti.**“Please, Bhaddiya, don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t go by testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t rely on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the acceptance of a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of competence, and don’t think ‘The ascetic is our respected teacher.’*";
P_HTM[4978]="*Yadā tumhe, bhaddiya, attanāva jāneyyātha:**But when you know for yourselves:*";
P_HTM[4979]="*‘ime dhammā akusalā, ime dhammā sāvajjā, ime dhammā viññugarahitā, ime dhammā samattā samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattantī’ti, atha tumhe, bhaddiya, pajaheyyātha.**‘These things are unskillful, blameworthy, criticized by sensible people, and when you undertake them, they lead to harm and suffering’, then you should give them up.*";
P_HTM[4980]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhaddiya,**What do you think, Bhaddiya?*";
P_HTM[4981]="*lobho purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati hitāya vā ahitāya vā”ti?**Does greed come up in a person for their welfare or harm?”*";
P_HTM[4982]="*“Ahitāya, bhante”.**“Harm, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4983]="*“Luddho panāyaṃ, bhaddiya, purisapuggalo lobhena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto pāṇampi hanati, adinnampi ādiyati, paradārampi gacchati, musāpi bhaṇati, parampi tathattāya samādapeti yaṃsa hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti.**“A greedy individual—overcome by greed—kills living creatures, steals, commits adultery, lies, and encourages others to do the same. Is that for their lasting harm and suffering?”*";
P_HTM[4984]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4985]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhaddiya,**“What do you think, Bhaddiya?*";
P_HTM[4986]="*doso purisassa … pe … moho purisassa … pe … sārambho purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati hitāya vā ahitāya vā”ti?**Does hate … or delusion … or aggression come up in a person for their welfare or harm?”*";
P_HTM[4987]="*“Ahitāya, bhante”.**“Harm, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4988]="*“Sāraddho panāyaṃ, bhaddiya, purisapuggalo sārambhena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto pāṇampi hanati, adinnampi ādiyati, paradārampi gacchati, musāpi bhaṇati, parampi tathattāya samādapeti yaṃsa hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti.**“An aggressive individual kills living creatures, steals, commits adultery, lies, and encourages others to do the same. Is that for their lasting harm and suffering?”*";
P_HTM[4989]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4990]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhaddiya, ime dhammā kusalā vā akusalā vā”ti?**“What do you think, Bhaddiya, are these things skillful or unskillful?”*";
P_HTM[4991]="*“Akusalā, bhante”.**“Unskillful, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4992]="*“Sāvajjā vā anavajjā vā”ti?**“Blameworthy or blameless?”*";
P_HTM[4993]="*“Sāvajjā, bhante”.**“Blameworthy, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4994]="*“Viññugarahitā vā viññuppasatthā vā”ti?**“Criticized or praised by sensible people?”*";
P_HTM[4995]="*“Viññugarahitā, bhante”.**“Criticized by sensible people, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4996]="*“Samattā samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattanti, no vā?**“When you undertake them, do they lead to harm and suffering, or not?*";
P_HTM[4997]="*Kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?**Or how do you see this?”*";
P_HTM[4998]="*“Samattā, bhante, samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattanti.**“When you undertake them, they lead to harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[4999]="*Evaṃ no ettha hotī”ti.**That’s how we see it.”*";
P_HTM[5000]="*“Iti kho, bhaddiya, yaṃ taṃ te avocumhā—**“So, Bhaddiya, when we said:*";
P_HTM[5001]="*etha tumhe, bhaddiya, mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā ‘samaṇo no garū’ti.**‘Please, Bhaddiya, don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t go by testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t rely on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the acceptance of a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of competence, and don’t think “The ascetic is our respected teacher.”*";
P_HTM[5002]="*Yadā tumhe, bhaddiya, attanāva jāneyyātha:**But when you know for yourselves:*";
P_HTM[5003]="*‘ime dhammā akusalā, ime dhammā sāvajjā, ime dhammā viññugarahitā, ime dhammā samattā samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattantīti, atha tumhe, bhaddiya, pajaheyyāthā’ti,**“These things are unskillful, blameworthy, criticized by sensible people, and when you undertake them, they lead to harm and suffering”, then you should give them up.’*";
P_HTM[5004]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.*";
P_HTM[5005]="*Etha tumhe, bhaddiya, mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā ‘samaṇo no garū’ti.**Please, Bhaddiya, don’t rely on oral transmission …*";
P_HTM[5006]="*Yadā tumhe, bhaddiya, attanāva jāneyyātha:**But when you know for yourselves:*";
P_HTM[5007]="*‘ime dhammā kusalā, ime dhammā anavajjā, ime dhammā viññuppasatthā, ime dhammā samattā samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattantī’ti, atha tumhe, bhaddiya, upasampajja vihareyyāthāti.**‘These things are skillful, blameless, praised by sensible people, and when you undertake them, they lead to welfare and happiness’, then you should acquire them and keep them.*";
P_HTM[5008]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhaddiya,**What do you think, Bhaddiya?*";
P_HTM[5009]="*alobho purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati hitāya vā ahitāya vā”ti?**Does contentment … love … understanding … benevolence come up in a person for their welfare or harm?”*";
P_HTM[5010]="*“Hitāya, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[5011]="*“Aluddho panāyaṃ, bhaddiya, purisapuggalo lobhena anabhibhūto apariyādinnacitto neva pāṇaṃ hanati, na adinnaṃ ādiyati, na paradāraṃ gacchati, na musā bhaṇati, parampi tathattāya na samādapeti yaṃsa hoti dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5012]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[5013]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhaddiya, adoso purisassa … pe … amoho purisassa … pe … asārambho purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati hitāya vā ahitāya vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5014]="*“Hitāya, bhante”.**“Welfare, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5015]="*“Asāraddho panāyaṃ, bhaddiya, purisapuggalo sārambhena anabhibhūto apariyādinnacitto neva pāṇaṃ hanati, na adinnaṃ ādiyati, na paradāraṃ gacchati, na musā bhaṇati, parampi tathattāya na samādapeti yaṃsa hoti dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.**“An individual who is benevolent—not overcome by aggression—doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit adultery, lie, or encourage others to do the same. Is that for their lasting welfare and happiness?”*";
P_HTM[5016]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5017]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhaddiya, ime dhammā kusalā vā akusalā vā”ti?**“What do you think, Bhaddiya, are these things skillful or unskillful?”*";
P_HTM[5018]="*“Kusalā, bhante”.**“Skillful, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5019]="*“Sāvajjā vā anavajjā vā”ti?**“Blameworthy or blameless?”*";
P_HTM[5020]="*“Anavajjā, bhante”.**“Blameless, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5021]="*“Viññugarahitā vā viññuppasatthā vā”ti?**“Criticized or praised by sensible people?”*";
P_HTM[5022]="*“Viññuppasatthā, bhante”.**“Praised by sensible people, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5023]="*“Samattā samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattanti no vā?**“When you undertake them, do they lead to welfare and happiness, or not?*";
P_HTM[5024]="*Kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?**Or how do you see this?”*";
P_HTM[5025]="*“Samattā, bhante, samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattanti.**“When you undertake them, they lead to welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[5026]="*Evaṃ no ettha hotī”ti.**That’s how we see it.”*";
P_HTM[5027]="*“Iti kho, bhaddiya, yaṃ taṃ te avocumhā—**“So, Bhaddiya, when we said:*";
P_HTM[5028]="*etha tumhe, bhaddiya, mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā ‘samaṇo no garū’ti.**‘Please, Bhaddiya, don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t go by testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t rely on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the acceptance of a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of competence, and don’t think “The ascetic is our respected teacher.”*";
P_HTM[5029]="*Yadā tumhe, bhaddiya, attanāva jāneyyātha:**But when you know for yourselves:*";
P_HTM[5030]="*‘ime dhammā kusalā, ime dhammā anavajjā, ime dhammā viññuppasatthā, ime dhammā samattā samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattantīti, atha tumhe, bhaddiya, upasampajja vihareyyāthā’ti,**“These things are skillful, blameless, praised by sensible people, and when you undertake them, they lead to welfare and happiness”, then you should acquire them and keep them.’*";
P_HTM[5031]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.*";
P_HTM[5032]="*Ye kho te, bhaddiya, loke santo sappurisā te sāvakaṃ evaṃ samādapenti:**The good people in the world encourage their disciples:*";
P_HTM[5033]="*‘ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, lobhaṃ vineyya viharāhi.**‘Please, mister, live rid of greed.*";
P_HTM[5034]="*Lobhaṃ vineyya viharanto na lobhajaṃ kammaṃ karissasi kāyena vācāya manasā.**Then you won’t act out of greed by way of body, speech, or mind.*";
P_HTM[5035]="*Dosaṃ vineyya viharāhi.**Live rid of hate … delusion … aggression.*";
P_HTM[5036]="*Dosaṃ vineyya viharanto na dosajaṃ kammaṃ karissasi kāyena vācāya manasā.**Then you won’t act out of hate … delusion … aggression by way of body, speech, or mind.”*";
P_HTM[5037]="*Mohaṃ vineyya viharāhi.* **";
P_HTM[5038]="*Mohaṃ vineyya viharanto na mohajaṃ kammaṃ karissasi kāyena vācāya manasā.* **";
P_HTM[5039]="*Sārambhaṃ vineyya viharāhi.* **";
P_HTM[5040]="*Sārambhaṃ vineyya viharanto na sārambhajaṃ kammaṃ karissasi kāyena vācāya manasā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5041]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhaddiyo licchavi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Bhaddiya the Licchavi said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[5042]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe … upāsakaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**“Excellent, sir! … From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[5043]="*“Api nu tāhaṃ, bhaddiya, evaṃ avacaṃ:**“Well, Bhaddiya, did I say to you:*";
P_HTM[5044]="*‘ehi me tvaṃ, bhaddiya, sāvako hohi;**‘Please, Bhaddiya, be my disciple,*";
P_HTM[5045]="*ahaṃ satthā bhavissāmī’”ti?**and I will be your teacher’?”*";
P_HTM[5046]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5047]="*“Evaṃvādiṃ kho maṃ, bhaddiya, evamakkhāyiṃ eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā asatā tucchā musā abhūtena abbhācikkhanti:**“Though I speak and explain like this, certain ascetics and brahmins misrepresent me with the false, hollow, lying, untruthful claim:*";
P_HTM[5048]="*‘māyāvī samaṇo gotamo āvaṭṭaniṃ māyaṃ jānāti yāya aññatitthiyānaṃ sāvake āvaṭṭetī’”ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama is a magician. He knows a conversion magic, and uses it to convert the disciples of those who follow other paths.’”*";
P_HTM[5049]="*“Bhaddikā, bhante, āvaṭṭanī māyā.**“Sir, this conversion magic is excellent.*";
P_HTM[5050]="*Kalyāṇī, bhante, āvaṭṭanī māyā.**This conversion magic is lovely!*";
P_HTM[5051]="*Piyā me, bhante, ñātisālohitā imāya āvaṭṭaniyā āvaṭṭeyyuṃ, piyānampi me assa ñātisālohitānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**If my loved ones—relatives and kin—were to be converted by this, it would be for their lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[5052]="*Sabbe cepi, bhante, khattiyā imāya āvaṭṭaniyā āvaṭṭeyyuṃ, sabbesampissa khattiyānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**If all the aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers were to be converted by this, it would be for their lasting welfare and happiness.”*";
P_HTM[5053]="*Sabbe cepi, bhante, brāhmaṇā … vessā … suddā imāya āvaṭṭaniyā āvaṭṭeyyuṃ, sabbesampissa suddānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5054]="*“Evametaṃ, bhaddiya, evametaṃ, bhaddiya.**“That’s so true, Bhaddiya! That’s so true, Bhaddiya!*";
P_HTM[5055]="*Sabbe cepi, bhaddiya, khattiyā imāya āvaṭṭaniyā āvaṭṭeyyuṃ akusaladhammappahānāya kusaladhammūpasampadāya, sabbesampissa khattiyānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**If all the aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers were to be converted by this, it would be for their lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[5056]="*Sabbe cepi, bhaddiya, brāhmaṇā … vessā … suddā āvaṭṭeyyuṃ akusaladhammappahānāya kusaladhammūpasampadāya, sabbesampissa suddānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.* **";
P_HTM[5057]="*Sadevako cepi, bhaddiya, loko samārako sabrahmako sassamaṇabrāhmaṇī pajā sadevamanussā imāya āvaṭṭaniyā āvaṭṭeyyuṃ akusaladhammappahānāya kusaladhammūpasampadāya, sadevakassapissa lokassa samārakassa sabrahmakassa sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**If the whole world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—were to be converted by this, for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities, it would be for their lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[5058]="*Ime cepi, bhaddiya, mahāsālā imāya āvaṭṭaniyā āvaṭṭeyyuṃ akusaladhammappahānāya kusaladhammūpasampadāya, imesampissa mahāsālānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya ().**If these great sal trees were to be converted by this, for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities, it would be for their lasting welfare and happiness—if they were sentient.*";
P_HTM[5059]="*Ko pana vādo manussabhūtassā”ti.**How much more then a human being!”*";
P_HTM[5060]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5061]="*3. Bhaddiyasuttaṃ**At Sāpūga*";
P_HTM[5062]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando koliyesu viharati sāmugaṃ nāma koliyānaṃ nigamo.**At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying in the land of the Koliyans, where they have a town named Sāpūga.*";
P_HTM[5063]="*Atha kho sambahulā sāmugiyā koliyaputtā yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te sāmugiye koliyaputte āyasmā ānando etadavoca:**Then several Koliyans from Sāpūga went up to Ānanda, bowed, and sat down to one side. Then Venerable Ānanda said to them:*";
P_HTM[5064]="*“Cattārimāni, byagghapajjā, pārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgāni tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sammadakkhātāni sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāya.**“Byagghapajjas, these four factors of trying to be pure have been rightly explained by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to end the cycle of suffering, and to realize extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[5065]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5066]="*Sīlapārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ, cittapārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ, diṭṭhipārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ, vimuttipārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ.**The factors of trying to be pure in ethics, mind, view, and freedom.*";
P_HTM[5067]="*Katamañca, byagghapajjā, sīlapārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ?**And what is the factor of trying to be pure in ethics?*";
P_HTM[5068]="*Idha, byagghapajjā, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu.**It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[5069]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, byagghapajjā, sīlapārisuddhi.**This is called purity of ethics.*";
P_HTM[5070]="*Iti evarūpiṃ sīlapārisuddhiṃ aparipūraṃ vā paripūressāmi paripūraṃ vā tattha tattha paññāya anuggahessāmīti, yo tattha chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca, idaṃ vuccati, byagghapajjā, sīlapārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ.**They think: ‘I will fulfill such purity of ethics, or, if it’s already fulfilled, I’ll support it in every situation by wisdom.’ Their enthusiasm for that—their effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, mindfulness, and situational awareness—is called the factor of trying to be pure in ethics.*";
P_HTM[5071]="*Katamañca, byagghapajjā, cittapārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ?**And what is the factor of trying to be pure in mind?*";
P_HTM[5072]="*Idha, byagghapajjā, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[5073]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, byagghapajjā, cittapārisuddhi.**This is called purity of mind.*";
P_HTM[5074]="*Iti evarūpiṃ cittapārisuddhiṃ aparipūraṃ vā paripūressāmi paripūraṃ vā tattha tattha paññāya anuggahessāmīti, yo tattha chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca, idaṃ vuccati, byagghapajjā, cittapārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ.**They think: ‘I will fulfill such purity of mind, or, if it’s already fulfilled, I’ll support it in every situation by wisdom.’ Their enthusiasm for that—their effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, mindfulness, and situational awareness—is called the factor of trying to be pure in mind.*";
P_HTM[5075]="*Katamañca, byagghapajjā, diṭṭhipārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ?**And what is the factor of trying to be pure in view?*";
P_HTM[5076]="*Idha, byagghapajjā, bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**Take a mendicant who truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[5077]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, byagghapajjā, diṭṭhipārisuddhi.**This is called purity of view.*";
P_HTM[5078]="*Iti evarūpiṃ diṭṭhipārisuddhiṃ aparipūraṃ vā … pe … tattha tattha paññāya anuggahessāmīti, yo tattha chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca, idaṃ vuccati, byagghapajjā, diṭṭhipārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ.**They think: ‘I will fulfill such purity of view, or, if it’s already fulfilled, I’ll support it in every situation by wisdom.’ Their enthusiasm for that—their effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, mindfulness, and situational awareness—is called the factor of trying to be pure in view.*";
P_HTM[5079]="*Katamañca, byagghapajjā, vimuttipārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ?**And what is the factor of trying to be pure in freedom?*";
P_HTM[5080]="*Sa kho so, byagghapajjā, ariyasāvako iminā ca sīlapārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgena samannāgato iminā ca cittapārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgena samannāgato iminā ca diṭṭhipārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgena samannāgato rajanīyesu dhammesu cittaṃ virājeti, vimocanīyesu dhammesu cittaṃ vimoceti.**That noble disciple—who has these factors of trying to be pure in ethics, mind, and view—detaches their mind from things that arouse greed, and frees their mind from things that it should be freed from.*";
P_HTM[5081]="*So rajanīyesu dhammesu cittaṃ virājetvā, vimocanīyesu dhammesu cittaṃ vimocetvā sammāvimuttiṃ phusati.**Doing so, they experience perfect freedom.*";
P_HTM[5082]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, byagghapajjā, vimuttipārisuddhi.**This is called purity of freedom.*";
P_HTM[5083]="*Iti evarūpiṃ vimuttipārisuddhiṃ aparipūraṃ vā paripūressāmi paripūraṃ vā tattha tattha paññāya anuggahessāmīti, yo tattha chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca, idaṃ vuccati, byagghapajjā, vimuttipārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ.**They think: ‘I will fulfill such purity of freedom, or, if it’s already fulfilled, I’ll support it in every situation by wisdom.’ Their enthusiasm for that—their effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, mindfulness, and situational awareness—is called the factor of trying to be pure in freedom.*";
P_HTM[5084]="*Imāni kho, byagghapajjā, cattāri pārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgāni tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sammadakkhātāni sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti.**These four factors of trying to be pure have been rightly explained by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to end the cycle of suffering, and to realize extinguishment.”*";
P_HTM[5085]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5086]="*4. Sāmugiyasuttaṃ**With Vappa*";
P_HTM[5087]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery.*";
P_HTM[5088]="*Atha kho vappo sakko nigaṇṭhasāvako yenāyasmā mahāmoggallāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho vappaṃ sakkaṃ nigaṇṭhasāvakaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca:**Then Vappa of the Sakyans, a disciple of the Jains, went up to Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, bowed, and sat down to one side. Mahāmoggallāna said to him:*";
P_HTM[5089]="*“Idhassa, vappa, kāyena saṃvuto vācāya saṃvuto manasā saṃvuto avijjāvirāgā vijjuppādā.**“Vappa, take a person who is restrained in body, speech, and mind. When ignorance fades away and knowledge arises,*";
P_HTM[5090]="*Passasi no tvaṃ, vappa, taṃ ṭhānaṃ yatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan”ti?**do you see any reason why defilements giving rise to painful feelings would defile that person in the next life?”*";
P_HTM[5091]="*“Passāmahaṃ, bhante, taṃ ṭhānaṃ.**“Sir, I do see such a case.*";
P_HTM[5092]="*Idhassa, bhante, pubbe pāpakammaṃ kataṃ avipakkavipākaṃ.**Take a person who did bad deeds in a past life. But the result of that has not yet ripened.*";
P_HTM[5093]="*Tatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan”ti.**For this reason defilements giving rise to painful feelings would defile that person in the next life.”*";
P_HTM[5094]="*Ayañceva kho pana āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa vappena sakkena nigaṇṭhasāvakena saddhiṃ antarākathā vippakatā hoti.**But this conversation between Mahāmoggallāna and Vappa was left unfinished.*";
P_HTM[5095]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena upaṭṭhānasālā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ etadavoca:**Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the assembly hall. He sat down on the seat spread out, and said to Mahāmoggallāna,*";
P_HTM[5096]="*“Kāya nuttha, moggallāna, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā;**“Moggallāna, what were you sitting talking about just now?*";
P_HTM[5097]="*kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti?**What conversation was unfinished?”*";
P_HTM[5098]="*“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, vappaṃ sakkaṃ nigaṇṭhasāvakaṃ etadavocaṃ:**Moggallāna repeated the entire conversation to the Buddha, and concluded:*";
P_HTM[5099]="*‘idhassa, vappa, kāyena saṃvuto vācāya saṃvuto manasā saṃvuto avijjāvirāgā vijjuppādā.* **";
P_HTM[5100]="*Passasi no tvaṃ, vappa, taṃ ṭhānaṃ yatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan’ti?* **";
P_HTM[5101]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, vappo sakko nigaṇṭhasāvako maṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[5102]="*‘passāmahaṃ, bhante, taṃ ṭhānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5103]="*Idhassa, bhante, pubbe pāpakammaṃ kataṃ avipakkavipākaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5104]="*Tatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5105]="*Ayaṃ kho no, bhante, vappena sakkena nigaṇṭhasāvakena saddhiṃ antarākathā vippakatā; atha bhagavā anuppatto”ti.**“This was my conversation with Vappa that was unfinished when the Buddha arrived.”*";
P_HTM[5106]="*Atha kho bhagavā vappaṃ sakkaṃ nigaṇṭhasāvakaṃ etadavoca:**Then the Buddha said to Vappa,*";
P_HTM[5107]="*“sace me tvaṃ, vappa, anuññeyyañceva anujāneyyāsi, paṭikkositabbañca paṭikkoseyyāsi, yassa ca me bhāsitassa atthaṃ na jāneyyāsi mamevettha uttari paṭipuccheyyāsi:**“Vappa, we can discuss this. But only if you allow what should be allowed, and reject what should be rejected. And if you ask me the meaning of anything you don’t understand, saying:*";
P_HTM[5108]="*‘idaṃ, bhante, kathaṃ, imassa ko attho’ti, siyā no ettha kathāsallāpo”ti.**‘Sir, why is this? What’s the meaning of that?’”*";
P_HTM[5109]="*“Anuññeyyañcevāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato anujānissāmi, paṭikkositabbañca paṭikkosissāmi, yassa cāhaṃ bhagavato bhāsitassa atthaṃ na jānissāmi bhagavantaṃyevettha uttari paṭipucchissāmi:**“Sir, let us discuss this. I will do as you say.”*";
P_HTM[5110]="*‘idaṃ, bhante, kathaṃ, imassa ko attho’ti?* **";
P_HTM[5111]="*Hotu no ettha kathāsallāpo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5112]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, vappa,**“What do you think, Vappa?*";
P_HTM[5113]="*ye kāyasamārambhapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, kāyasamārambhā paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti.**There are distressing and feverish defilements that arise because of undertaking bodily activity. These don’t occur in someone who avoids such bodily activity.*";
P_HTM[5114]="*So navañca kammaṃ na karoti, purāṇañca kammaṃ phussa phussa byantīkaroti, sandiṭṭhikā nijjarā akālikā ehipassikā opaneyyikā paccattaṃ veditabbā viññūhi.**They don’t perform any new deeds, and old deeds are eliminated by experiencing their results little by little. This wearing away is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.*";
P_HTM[5115]="*Passasi no tvaṃ, vappa, taṃ ṭhānaṃ yatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan”ti?**Do you see any reason why defilements giving rise to painful feelings would defile that person in the next life?”*";
P_HTM[5116]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5117]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, vappa,**“What do you think, Vappa?*";
P_HTM[5118]="*ye vacīsamārambhapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, vacīsamārambhā paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti.**There are distressing and feverish defilements that arise because of undertaking verbal activity. These don’t occur in someone who avoids such verbal activity.*";
P_HTM[5119]="*So navañca kammaṃ na karoti, purāṇañca kammaṃ phussa phussa byantīkaroti.**They don’t perform any new deeds, and old deeds are eliminated by experiencing their results little by little.*";
P_HTM[5120]="*Sandiṭṭhikā nijjarā akālikā ehipassikā opaneyyikā paccattaṃ veditabbā viññūhi.**This wearing away is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.*";
P_HTM[5121]="*Passasi no tvaṃ, vappa, taṃ ṭhānaṃ yatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan”ti?**Do you see any reason why defilements giving rise to painful feelings would defile that person in the next life?”*";
P_HTM[5122]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5123]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, vappa,**“What do you think, Vappa?*";
P_HTM[5124]="*ye manosamārambhapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, manosamārambhā paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti.**There are distressing and feverish defilements that arise because of undertaking mental activity. These don’t occur in someone who avoids such mental activity.*";
P_HTM[5125]="*So navañca kammaṃ na karoti, purāṇañca kammaṃ phussa phussa byantīkaroti.**They don’t perform any new deeds, and old deeds are eliminated by experiencing their results little by little.*";
P_HTM[5126]="*Sandiṭṭhikā nijjarā akālikā ehipassikā opaneyyikā paccattaṃ veditabbā viññūhi.**This wearing away is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.*";
P_HTM[5127]="*Passasi no tvaṃ, vappa, taṃ ṭhānaṃ yatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan”ti?**Do you see any reason why defilements giving rise to painful feelings would defile that person in the next life?”*";
P_HTM[5128]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5129]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, vappa,**“What do you think, Vappa?*";
P_HTM[5130]="*ye avijjāpaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, avijjāvirāgā vijjuppādā evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti.**There are distressing and feverish defilements that arise because of ignorance. These don’t occur when ignorance fades away and knowledge arises.*";
P_HTM[5131]="*So navañca kammaṃ na karoti, purāṇañca kammaṃ phussa phussa byantīkaroti.**They don’t perform any new deeds, and old deeds are eliminated by experiencing their results little by little.*";
P_HTM[5132]="*Sandiṭṭhikā nijjarā akālikā ehipassikā opaneyyikā paccattaṃ veditabbā viññūhi.**This wearing away is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.*";
P_HTM[5133]="*Passasi no tvaṃ, vappa, taṃ ṭhānaṃ yatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan”ti?**Do you see any reason why defilements giving rise to painful feelings would defile that person in the next life?”*";
P_HTM[5134]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5135]="*“Evaṃ sammā vimuttacittassa kho, vappa, bhikkhuno cha satatavihārā adhigatā honti.**“A mendicant whose mind is rightly freed like this has achieved six consistent responses.*";
P_HTM[5136]="*So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā neva sumano hoti na dummano; upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno.**Seeing a sight with the eye, they’re neither happy nor sad, but remain equanimous, mindful and aware.*";
P_HTM[5137]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**Hearing a sound with the ears …*";
P_HTM[5138]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …**Smelling an odor with the nose …*";
P_HTM[5139]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …**Tasting a flavor with the tongue …*";
P_HTM[5140]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …**Feeling a touch with the body …*";
P_HTM[5141]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya neva sumano hoti na dummano; upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno.**Knowing a thought with the mind, they’re neither happy nor sad, but remain equanimous, mindful and aware.*";
P_HTM[5142]="*So kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyamāno ‘kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyāmī’ti pajānāti; jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyamāno ‘jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyāmī’ti pajānāti;**Feeling the end of the body approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of the body approaching.’ Feeling the end of life approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of life approaching.’*";
P_HTM[5143]="*‘kāyassa bhedā uddhaṃ jīvitapariyādānā idheva sabbavedayitāni anabhinanditāni sītī bhavissantī’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘When my body breaks up and my life has come to an end, everything that’s felt, being no longer relished, will become cool right here.’*";
P_HTM[5144]="*Seyyathāpi, vappa, thūṇaṃ paṭicca chāyā paññāyati.**Suppose there was a shadow cast by a sacrificial post.*";
P_HTM[5145]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya kuddālapiṭakaṃ ādāya.**Then along comes a person with a spade and basket.*";
P_HTM[5146]="*So taṃ thūṇaṃ mūle chindeyya;**They cut down the sacrificial post at its base,*";
P_HTM[5147]="*mūle chinditvā palikhaṇeyya;**dig it up,*";
P_HTM[5148]="*palikhaṇitvā mūlāni uddhareyya, antamaso usīranāḷimattānipi.**and pull it out by its roots, right down to the fibers and stems.*";
P_HTM[5149]="*So taṃ thūṇaṃ khaṇḍākhaṇḍikaṃ chindeyya.**Then they split it apart,*";
P_HTM[5150]="*Khaṇḍākhaṇḍikaṃ chetvā phāleyya.**cut up the parts,*";
P_HTM[5151]="*Phāletvā sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ kareyya.**and chop them into splinters.*";
P_HTM[5152]="*Sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ katvā vātātape visoseyya.**Next they dry the splinters in the wind and sun,*";
P_HTM[5153]="*Vātātape visosetvā agginā ḍaheyya.**burn them with fire,*";
P_HTM[5154]="*Agginā ḍahetvā masiṃ kareyya.**and reduce them to ashes.*";
P_HTM[5155]="*Masiṃ karitvā mahāvāte vā ophuṇeyya nadiyā vā sīghasotāya pavāheyya.**Then they sweep away the ashes in a strong wind, or float them away down a swift stream.*";
P_HTM[5156]="*Evaṃ hissa, vappa, yā thūṇaṃ paṭicca chāyā sā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṃkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**And so the shadow cast by the post is cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[5157]="*Evamevaṃ kho, vappa, evaṃ sammā vimuttacittassa bhikkhuno cha satatavihārā adhigatā honti.**In the same way, a mendicant whose mind is rightly freed like this has achieved six consistent responses.*";
P_HTM[5158]="*So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā neva sumano hoti na dummano; upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno.**Seeing a sight with the eye, they’re neither happy nor sad, but remain equanimous, mindful and aware.*";
P_HTM[5159]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**Hearing a sound with the ears …*";
P_HTM[5160]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …**Smelling an odor with the nose …*";
P_HTM[5161]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …**Tasting a flavor with the tongue …*";
P_HTM[5162]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …**Feeling a touch with the body …*";
P_HTM[5163]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya neva sumano hoti na dummano; upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno.**Knowing a thought with the mind, they’re neither happy nor sad, but remain equanimous, mindful and aware.*";
P_HTM[5164]="*So kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyamāno ‘kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyāmī’ti pajānāti; jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyamāno ‘jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyāmī’ti pajānāti;**Feeling the end of the body approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of the body approaching.’ Feeling the end of life approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of life approaching.’*";
P_HTM[5165]="*‘kāyassa bhedā uddhaṃ jīvitapariyādānā idheva sabbavedayitāni anabhinanditāni sītī bhavissantī’ti pajānāti”.**They understand: ‘When my body breaks up and my life has come to an end, everything that’s felt, being no longer relished, will become cool right here.’”*";
P_HTM[5166]="*Evaṃ vutte, vappo sakko nigaṇṭhasāvako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Vappa the Sakyan, the disciple of the Jains, said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[5167]="*“seyyathāpi, bhante, puriso udayatthiko assapaṇiyaṃ poseyya.**“Sir, suppose there was a man who raised commercial horses for profit.*";
P_HTM[5168]="*So udayañceva nādhigaccheyya, uttariñca kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assa.**But he never made any profit, and instead just got weary and frustrated.*";
P_HTM[5169]="*Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, udayatthiko bāle nigaṇṭhe payirupāsiṃ.**In the same way, I paid homage to those Jain fools for profit.*";
P_HTM[5170]="*Svāhaṃ udayañceva nādhigacchiṃ, uttariñca kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī ahosiṃ.**But I never made any profit, and instead just got weary and frustrated.*";
P_HTM[5171]="*Esāhaṃ, bhante, ajjatagge yo me bālesu nigaṇṭhesu pasādo taṃ mahāvāte vā ophuṇāmi nadiyā vā sīghasotāya pavāhemi.**From this day forth, any confidence I had in those Jain fools I sweep away as in a strong wind, or float away as down a swift stream.*";
P_HTM[5172]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe … upāsakaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**Excellent, sir! … From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[5173]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5174]="*5. Vappasuttaṃ**With Sāḷha*";
P_HTM[5175]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[5176]="*Atha kho sāḷho ca licchavi abhayo ca licchavi yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho sāḷho licchavi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Sāḷha and Abhaya the Licchavis went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[5177]="*“Santi, bhante, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā dvayena oghassa nittharaṇaṃ paññapenti—**“There are, sir, some ascetics and brahmins who advocate crossing the flood by means of two things:*";
P_HTM[5178]="*sīlavisuddhihetu ca tapojigucchāhetu ca.**purification of ethics, and mortification in disgust of sin.*";
P_HTM[5179]="*Idha, bhante, bhagavā kimāhā”ti?**What does the Buddha say about this?”*";
P_HTM[5180]="*“Sīlavisuddhiṃ kho ahaṃ, sāḷha, aññataraṃ sāmaññaṅganti vadāmi.**“Sāḷha, purification of ethics is one of the factors of the ascetic life, I say.*";
P_HTM[5181]="*Ye te, sāḷha, samaṇabrāhmaṇā tapojigucchāvādā tapojigucchāsārā tapojigucchāallīnā viharanti, abhabbā te oghassa nittharaṇāya.**But those ascetics and brahmins who teach mortification in disgust of sin—regarding it as essential and clinging to it—are incapable of crossing the flood.*";
P_HTM[5182]="*Yepi te, sāḷha, samaṇabrāhmaṇā aparisuddhakāyasamācārā aparisuddhavacīsamācārā aparisuddhamanosamācārā aparisuddhājīvā, abhabbā te ñāṇadassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.**And those ascetics and brahmins whose behavior by way of body, speech, and mind is not pure are also incapable of knowing and seeing, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[5183]="*Seyyathāpi, sāḷha, puriso nadiṃ taritukāmo tiṇhaṃ kuṭhāriṃ ādāya vanaṃ paviseyya.**Suppose a man who wanted to cross a river took a sharp axe into a wood.*";
P_HTM[5184]="*So tattha passeyya mahatiṃ sālalaṭṭhiṃ ujuṃ navaṃ akukkuccakajātaṃ.**There he’d see a large green sal tree, straight and young and grown free of defects.*";
P_HTM[5185]="*Tamenaṃ mūle chindeyya;**He’d cut it down at the base,*";
P_HTM[5186]="*mūle chetvā agge chindeyya;**cut off the top,*";
P_HTM[5187]="*agge chetvā sākhāpalāsaṃ suvisodhitaṃ visodheyya;**and completely strip off the branches and foliage.*";
P_HTM[5188]="*sākhāpalāsaṃ suvisodhitaṃ visodhetvā kuṭhārīhi taccheyya;**Then he’d trim it with axes and*";
P_HTM[5189]="*kuṭhārīhi tacchetvā vāsīhi taccheyya;**machetes,*";
P_HTM[5190]="*vāsīhi tacchetvā lekhaṇiyā likheyya;**plane it,*";
P_HTM[5191]="*lekhaṇiyā likhitvā pāsāṇaguḷena dhoveyya;**and sand it with a rock.*";
P_HTM[5192]="*pāsāṇaguḷena dhovetvā nadiṃ patāreyya.**Finally, he’d launch out on the river.*";
P_HTM[5193]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, sāḷha,**What do you think, Sāḷha?*";
P_HTM[5194]="*bhabbo nu kho so puriso nadiṃ taritun”ti?**Is that man capable of crossing the river?”*";
P_HTM[5195]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[5196]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why not?*";
P_HTM[5197]="*“Asu hi, bhante, sālalaṭṭhi bahiddhā suparikammakatā anto avisuddhā.**Because that green sal tree is well worked on the outside, but inside it’s still not cleared out.*";
P_HTM[5198]="*Tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—sālalaṭṭhi saṃsīdissati, puriso anayabyasanaṃ āpajjissatī”ti.**I’d expect that green sal tree to sink, and the man to come to ruin.”*";
P_HTM[5199]="*“Evamevaṃ kho, sāḷha, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā tapojigucchāvādā tapojigucchāsārā tapojigucchāallīnā viharanti, abhabbā te oghassa nittharaṇāya.**“In the same way, Sāḷha, those ascetics and brahmins who teach mortification in disgust of sin—regarding it as essential and clinging to it—are incapable of crossing the flood.*";
P_HTM[5200]="*Yepi te, sāḷha, samaṇabrāhmaṇā aparisuddhakāyasamācārā aparisuddhavacīsamācārā aparisuddhamanosamācārā aparisuddhājīvā, abhabbā te ñāṇadassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.**And those ascetics and brahmins whose behavior by way of body, speech, and mind is not pure are also incapable of knowing and seeing, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[5201]="*Ye ca kho te, sāḷha, samaṇabrāhmaṇā na tapojigucchāvādā na tapojigucchāsārā na tapojigucchāallīnā viharanti, bhabbā te oghassa nittharaṇāya.**But those ascetics and brahmins who don’t teach mortification in disgust of sin—not regarding it as essential or clinging to it—are capable of crossing the flood.*";
P_HTM[5202]="*Yepi te, sāḷha, samaṇabrāhmaṇā parisuddhakāyasamācārā parisuddhavacīsamācārā parisuddhamanosamācārā parisuddhājīvā, bhabbā te ñāṇadassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.**And those ascetics and brahmins whose behavior by way of body, speech, and mind is pure are also capable of knowing and seeing, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[5203]="*Seyyathāpi, sāḷha, puriso nadiṃ taritukāmo tiṇhaṃ kuṭhāriṃ ādāya vanaṃ paviseyya.**Suppose a man who wanted to cross a river took a sharp axe into a wood.*";
P_HTM[5204]="*So tattha passeyya mahatiṃ sālalaṭṭhiṃ ujuṃ navaṃ akukkuccakajātaṃ.**There he’d see a large green sal tree, straight and young and grown free of defects.*";
P_HTM[5205]="*Tamenaṃ mūle chindeyya;**He’d cut it down at the base,*";
P_HTM[5206]="*mūle chinditvā agge chindeyya;**cut off the top,*";
P_HTM[5207]="*agge chinditvā sākhāpalāsaṃ suvisodhitaṃ visodheyya;**and completely strip off the branches and foliage.*";
P_HTM[5208]="*sākhāpalāsaṃ suvisodhitaṃ visodhetvā kuṭhārīhi taccheyya;**Then he’d trim it with axes and*";
P_HTM[5209]="*kuṭhārīhi tacchetvā vāsīhi taccheyya;**machetes.*";
P_HTM[5210]="*vāsīhi tacchetvā nikhādanaṃ ādāya anto suvisodhitaṃ visodheyya;**Then he’d take a chisel and completely clear it out inside.*";
P_HTM[5211]="*anto suvisodhitaṃ visodhetvā lekhaṇiyā likheyya;**Then he’d plane it,*";
P_HTM[5212]="*lekhaṇiyā likhitvā pāsāṇaguḷena dhoveyya;**sand it with a rock,*";
P_HTM[5213]="*pāsāṇaguḷena dhovetvā nāvaṃ kareyya;**and make it into a boat.*";
P_HTM[5214]="*nāvaṃ katvā phiyārittaṃ bandheyya;**Finally he’d fix it with oars and rudder,*";
P_HTM[5215]="*phiyārittaṃ bandhitvā nadiṃ patāreyya.**and launch out on the river.*";
P_HTM[5216]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, sāḷha,**What do you think, Sāḷha?*";
P_HTM[5217]="*bhabbo nu kho so puriso nadiṃ taritun”ti?**Is that man capable of crossing the river?”*";
P_HTM[5218]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.*";
P_HTM[5219]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[5220]="*“Asu hi, bhante, sālalaṭṭhi bahiddhā suparikammakatā, anto suvisuddhā nāvākatā phiyārittabaddhā.**Because that green sal tree is well worked on the outside, cleared out on the inside, made into a boat, and fixed with oars and rudder.*";
P_HTM[5221]="*Tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ:**I’d expect*";
P_HTM[5222]="*‘nāvā na saṃsīdissati, puriso sotthinā pāraṃ gamissatī’”ti.**that boat to not sink, and the man to safely make it to the far shore.”*";
P_HTM[5223]="*“Evamevaṃ kho, sāḷha, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā na tapojigucchāvādā na tapojigucchāsārā na tapojigucchāallīnā viharanti, bhabbā te oghassa nittharaṇāya.**“In the same way, Sāḷha, those ascetics and brahmins who don’t teach mortification in disgust of sin—not regarding it as essential or clinging to it—are capable of crossing the flood.*";
P_HTM[5224]="*Yepi te, sāḷha, samaṇabrāhmaṇā parisuddhakāyasamācārā parisuddhavacīsamācārā parisuddhamanosamācārā parisuddhājīvā, bhabbā te ñāṇadassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.**And those ascetics and brahmins whose behavior by way of body, speech, and mind is pure are also capable of knowing and seeing, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[5225]="*Seyyathāpi, sāḷha, yodhājīvo bahūni cepi kaṇḍacitrakāni jānāti;**Suppose there was a warrior who knew lots of fancy archery tricks.*";
P_HTM[5226]="*atha kho so tīhi ṭhānehi rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**It is only with these three factors that he becomes worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[5227]="*Katamehi tīhi?**What three?*";
P_HTM[5228]="*Dūrepātī ca, akkhaṇavedhī ca, mahato ca kāyassa padāletā.**He’s a long-distance shooter, a marksman, and one who shatters large objects.*";
P_HTM[5229]="*Seyyathāpi, sāḷha, yodhājīvo dūrepātī;**Just as a warrior is a long-distance shooter,*";
P_HTM[5230]="*evamevaṃ kho, sāḷha, ariyasāvako sammāsamādhi hoti.**a noble disciple has right immersion.*";
P_HTM[5231]="*Sammāsamādhi, sāḷha, ariyasāvako yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati.**A noble disciple with right immersion truly sees any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[5232]="*Yā kāci vedanā …**They truly see any kind of feeling …*";
P_HTM[5233]="*yā kāci saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[5234]="*ye keci saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[5235]="*yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati.**consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near, all consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[5236]="*Seyyathāpi, sāḷha, yodhājīvo akkhaṇavedhī;**Just as a warrior is a marksman,*";
P_HTM[5237]="*evamevaṃ kho, sāḷha, ariyasāvako sammādiṭṭhi hoti.**a noble disciple has right view.*";
P_HTM[5238]="*Sammādiṭṭhi, sāḷha, ariyasāvako ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**A noble disciple with right view truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[5239]="*Seyyathāpi, sāḷha, yodhājīvo mahato kāyassa padāletā;**Just as a warrior shatters large objects,*";
P_HTM[5240]="*evamevaṃ kho, sāḷha, ariyasāvako sammāvimutti hoti.**a noble disciple has right freedom.*";
P_HTM[5241]="*Sammāvimutti, sāḷha, ariyasāvako mahantaṃ avijjākkhandhaṃ padāletī”ti.**A noble disciple with right freedom shatters the great mass of ignorance.”*";
P_HTM[5242]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5243]="*6. Sāḷhasuttaṃ**Queen Mallikā*";
P_HTM[5244]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[5245]="*Atha kho mallikā devī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho mallikā devī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Queen Mallikā went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[5246]="*“Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena midhekacco mātugāmo dubbaṇṇā ca hoti durūpā supāpikā dassanāya;**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why in this life some females are ugly, unattractive, and bad-looking;*";
P_HTM[5247]="*daliddā ca hoti appassakā appabhogā appesakkhā ca?**and poor, with few assets and possessions; and insignificant?*";
P_HTM[5248]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena midhekacco mātugāmo dubbaṇṇā ca hoti durūpā supāpikā dassanāya;**And why are some females ugly, unattractive, and bad-looking;*";
P_HTM[5249]="*aḍḍhā ca hoti mahaddhanā mahābhogā mahesakkhā ca?**but rich, affluent, wealthy, and illustrious?*";
P_HTM[5250]="*Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena midhekacco mātugāmo abhirūpā ca hoti dassanīyā pāsādikā paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgatā;**And why are some females attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty;*";
P_HTM[5251]="*daliddā ca hoti appassakā appabhogā appesakkhā ca?**but poor, with few assets and possessions; and insignificant?*";
P_HTM[5252]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena midhekacco mātugāmo abhirūpā ca hoti dassanīyā pāsādikā paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgatā, aḍḍhā ca hoti mahaddhanā mahābhogā mahesakkhā cā”ti?**And why are some females attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty; and rich, affluent, wealthy, and illustrious?”*";
P_HTM[5253]="*“Idha, mallike, ekacco mātugāmo kodhanā hoti upāyāsabahulā.**“Take a female who is irritable and bad-tempered.*";
P_HTM[5254]="*Appampi vuttā samānā abhisajjati kuppati byāpajjati patitthīyati, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.**Even when criticized a little bit she loses her temper, becoming annoyed, hostile, and hard-hearted, and displaying annoyance, hate, and bitterness.*";
P_HTM[5255]="*Sā na dātā hoti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ.**She doesn’t give to ascetics or brahmins such things as food, drink, clothing, vehicles; garlands, fragrance, and makeup; and bed, house, and lighting.*";
P_HTM[5256]="*Issāmanikā kho pana hoti;**And she’s jealous,*";
P_HTM[5257]="*paralābhasakkāragarukāramānanavandanapūjanāsu issati upadussati issaṃ bandhati.**envying, resenting, and begrudging the possessions, honor, respect, reverence, homage, and veneration given to others.*";
P_HTM[5258]="*Sā ce tato cutā itthattaṃ āgacchati, sā yattha yattha paccājāyati dubbaṇṇā ca hoti durūpā supāpikā dassanāya;**If she comes back to this state of existence after passing away, wherever she is reborn she’s ugly, unattractive, and bad-looking;*";
P_HTM[5259]="*daliddā ca hoti appassakā appabhogā appesakkhā ca.**and poor, with few assets and possessions; and insignificant.*";
P_HTM[5260]="*Idha pana, mallike, ekacco mātugāmo kodhanā hoti upāyāsabahulā.**Take another female who is irritable and bad-tempered. …*";
P_HTM[5261]="*Appampi vuttā samānā abhisajjati kuppati byāpajjati patitthīyati, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.* **";
P_HTM[5262]="*Sā dātā hoti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ.**But she does give to ascetics or brahmins …*";
P_HTM[5263]="*Anissāmanikā kho pana hoti;**And she’s not jealous …*";
P_HTM[5264]="*paralābhasakkāragarukāramānanavandanapūjanāsu na issati na upadussati na issaṃ bandhati.* **";
P_HTM[5265]="*Sā ce tato cutā itthattaṃ āgacchati, sā yattha yattha paccājāyati dubbaṇṇā ca hoti durūpā supāpikā dassanāya;**If she comes back to this state of existence after passing away, wherever she is reborn she’s ugly, unattractive, and bad-looking;*";
P_HTM[5266]="*aḍḍhā ca hoti mahaddhanā mahābhogā mahesakkhā ca.**but rich, affluent, wealthy, and illustrious.*";
P_HTM[5267]="*Idha pana, mallike, ekacco mātugāmo akkodhanā hoti anupāyāsabahulā.**Take another female who isn’t irritable and bad-tempered. …*";
P_HTM[5268]="*Bahumpi vuttā samānā nābhisajjati na kuppati na byāpajjati na patitthīyati, na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.* **";
P_HTM[5269]="*Sā na dātā hoti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ.**But she doesn’t give to ascetics or brahmins …*";
P_HTM[5270]="*Issāmanikā kho pana hoti;**And she’s jealous …*";
P_HTM[5271]="*paralābhasakkāragarukāramānanavandanapūjanāsu issati upadussati issaṃ bandhati.* **";
P_HTM[5272]="*Sā ce tato cutā itthattaṃ āgacchati, sā yattha yattha paccājāyati abhirūpā ca hoti dassanīyā pāsādikā paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgatā;**If she comes back to this state of existence after passing away, wherever she is reborn she’s attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty;*";
P_HTM[5273]="*daliddā ca hoti appassakā appabhogā appesakkhā ca.**but poor, with few assets and possessions; and insignificant.*";
P_HTM[5274]="*Idha pana, mallike, ekacco mātugāmo akkodhanā hoti anupāyāsabahulā.**Take another female who isn’t irritable and bad-tempered. …*";
P_HTM[5275]="*Bahumpi vuttā samānā nābhisajjati na kuppati na byāpajjati na patitthīyati, na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.* **";
P_HTM[5276]="*Sā dātā hoti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ.**She gives to ascetics and brahmins …*";
P_HTM[5277]="*Anissāmanikā kho pana hoti;**And she’s not jealous …*";
P_HTM[5278]="*paralābhasakkāragarukāramānanavandanapūjanāsu na issati na upadussati na issaṃ bandhati.* **";
P_HTM[5279]="*Sā ce tato cutā itthattaṃ āgacchati, sā yattha yattha paccājāyati abhirūpā ca hoti dassanīyā pāsādikā paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgatā;**If she comes back to this state of existence after passing away, wherever she is reborn she’s attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty;*";
P_HTM[5280]="*aḍḍhā ca hoti mahaddhanā mahābhogā mahesakkhā ca.**and rich, affluent, wealthy, and illustrious.*";
P_HTM[5281]="*Ayaṃ kho, mallike, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco mātugāmo dubbaṇṇā ca hoti durūpā supāpikā dassanāya;**This is why are some females are ugly …*";
P_HTM[5282]="*daliddā ca hoti appassakā appabhogā appesakkhā ca.**and poor … and insignificant.*";
P_HTM[5283]="*Ayaṃ pana, mallike, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco mātugāmo dubbaṇṇā ca hoti durūpā supāpikā dassanāya;**And some females are ugly …*";
P_HTM[5284]="*aḍḍhā ca hoti mahaddhanā mahābhogā mahesakkhā ca.**but rich … and illustrious.*";
P_HTM[5285]="*Ayaṃ kho, mallike, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco mātugāmo abhirūpā ca hoti dassanīyā pāsādikā paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgatā;**And some females are attractive …*";
P_HTM[5286]="*daliddā ca hoti appassakā appabhogā appesakkhā ca.**but poor … and insignificant.*";
P_HTM[5287]="*Ayaṃ pana, mallike, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco mātugāmo abhirūpā ca hoti dassanīyā pāsādikā paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgatā;**And some females are attractive …*";
P_HTM[5288]="*aḍḍhā ca hoti mahaddhanā mahābhogā mahesakkhā cā”ti.**and rich … and illustrious.”*";
P_HTM[5289]="*Evaṃ vutte, mallikā devī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When this was said, Queen Mallikā said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[5290]="*“yā nūnāhaṃ, bhante, aññaṃ jātiṃ kodhanā ahosiṃ upāyāsabahulā,**“Sir, in another life I must have been irritable and bad-tempered.*";
P_HTM[5291]="*appampi vuttā samānā abhisajjiṃ kuppiṃ byāpajjiṃ patitthīyiṃ kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātvākāsiṃ,**Even when lightly criticized I must have lost my temper, becoming annoyed, hostile, and hard-hearted, and displaying annoyance, hate, and bitterness.*";
P_HTM[5292]="*sāhaṃ, bhante, etarahi dubbaṇṇā durūpā supāpikā dassanāya.**For now I am ugly, unattractive, and bad-looking.*";
P_HTM[5293]="*Yā nūnāhaṃ, bhante, aññaṃ jātiṃ dātā ahosiṃ samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ, sāhaṃ, bhante, etarahi aḍḍhā mahaddhanā mahābhogā.**In another life I must have given to ascetics or brahmins such things as food, drink, clothing, vehicles; garlands, fragrance, and makeup; and bed, house, and lighting. For now I am rich, affluent, and wealthy.*";
P_HTM[5294]="*Yā nūnāhaṃ, bhante, aññaṃ jātiṃ anissāmanikā ahosiṃ, paralābhasakkāragarukāramānanavandanapūjanāsu na issiṃ na upadussiṃ na issaṃ bandhiṃ, sāhaṃ, bhante, etarahi mahesakkhā.**In another life, I must not have been jealous, envying, resenting, and begrudging the possessions, honor, respect, reverence, homage, and veneration given to others. For now I am illustrious.*";
P_HTM[5295]="*Santi kho pana, bhante, imasmiṃ rājakule khattiyakaññāpi brāhmaṇakaññāpi gahapatikaññāpi, tāsāhaṃ issarādhipaccaṃ kāremi.**In this royal court I command maidens of the aristocrats, brahmins, and householders.*";
P_HTM[5296]="*Esāhaṃ, bhante, ajjatagge akkodhanā bhavissāmi anupāyāsabahulā,**So, sir, from this day forth I will not be irritable and bad-tempered.*";
P_HTM[5297]="*bahumpi vuttā samānā nābhisajjissāmi na kuppissāmi na byāpajjissāmi na patitthīyissāmi, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca na pātukarissāmi;**Even when heavily criticized I won’t lose my temper, become annoyed, hostile, and hard-hearted, or display annoyance, hate, and bitterness.*";
P_HTM[5298]="*dassāmi samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ.**I will give to ascetics or brahmins such things as food, drink, clothing, vehicles; garlands, fragrance, and makeup; and bed, house, and lighting.*";
P_HTM[5299]="*Anissāmanikā bhavissāmi, paralābhasakkāragarukāramānanavandanapūjanāsu na ississāmi na upadussissāmi na issaṃ bandhissāmi.**I will not be jealous, envying, resenting, and begrudging the possessions, honor, respect, reverence, homage, and veneration given to others.*";
P_HTM[5300]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe … upāsikaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**Excellent, sir! … From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[5301]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5302]="*7. Mallikādevīsuttaṃ**Self*";
P_HTM[5303]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[5304]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5305]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo attantapo hoti attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**One person mortifies themselves, pursuing the practice of mortifying themselves.*";
P_HTM[5306]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo parantapo hoti paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**One person mortifies others, pursuing the practice of mortifying others.*";
P_HTM[5307]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo attantapo ca hoti attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**One person mortifies themselves and others, pursuing the practice of mortifying themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[5308]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo nevattantapo hoti nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**One person neither mortifies themselves nor others, pursuing the practice of not mortifying themselves or others.*";
P_HTM[5309]="*So neva attantapo na parantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati.**They live without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves.*";
P_HTM[5310]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo attantapo hoti attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?**And how does one person mortify themselves, pursuing the practice of mortifying themselves?*";
P_HTM[5311]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco acelako hoti muttācāro hatthāpalekhano naehibhaddantiko natiṭṭhabhaddantiko nābhihaṭaṃ na uddissakataṃ na nimantanaṃ sādiyati.**It’s when someone goes naked, ignoring conventions. They lick their hands, and don’t come or wait when asked. They don’t consent to food brought to them, or food prepared on purpose for them, or an invitation for a meal.*";
P_HTM[5312]="*So na kumbhimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti, na kaḷopimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti, na eḷakamantaraṃ na daṇḍamantaraṃ na musalamantaraṃ na dvinnaṃ bhuñjamānānaṃ na gabbhiniyā na pāyamānāya na purisantaragatāya na saṅkittīsu na yattha sā upaṭṭhito hoti na yattha makkhikā saṇḍasaṇḍacārinī na macchaṃ na maṃsaṃ na suraṃ na merayaṃ na thusodakaṃ pivati.**They don’t receive anything from a pot or bowl; or from someone who keeps sheep, or who has a weapon or a shovel in their home; or where a couple is eating; or where there is a woman who is pregnant, breastfeeding, or who has a man in her home; or where there’s a dog waiting or flies buzzing. They accept no fish or meat or liquor or wine, and drink no beer.*";
P_HTM[5313]="*So ekāgāriko vā hoti ekālopiko dvāgāriko vā hoti dvālopiko … pe … sattāgāriko vā hoti sattālopiko;**They go to just one house for alms, taking just one mouthful, or two houses and two mouthfuls, up to seven houses and seven mouthfuls.*";
P_HTM[5314]="*ekissāpi dattiyā yāpeti dvīhipi dattīhi yāpeti … pe … sattahipi dattīhi yāpeti;**They feed on one saucer a day, two saucers a day, up to seven saucers a day.*";
P_HTM[5315]="*ekāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti dvāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti … pe … sattāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti. Iti evarūpaṃ aḍḍhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharati.**They eat once a day, once every second day, up to once a week, and so on, even up to once a fortnight. They live pursuing the practice of eating food at set intervals.*";
P_HTM[5316]="*So sākabhakkhopi hoti sāmākabhakkhopi hoti nīvārabhakkhopi hoti daddulabhakkhopi hoti haṭabhakkhopi hoti kaṇabhakkhopi hoti ācāmabhakkhopi hoti piññākabhakkhopi hoti tiṇabhakkhopi hoti gomayabhakkhopi hoti; vanamūlaphalāhāropi yāpeti pavattaphalabhojī.**They eat herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. They survive on forest roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit.*";
P_HTM[5317]="*So sāṇānipi dhāreti masāṇānipi dhāreti chavadussānipi dhāreti paṃsukūlānipi dhāreti tirīṭānipi dhāreti ajinampi dhāreti ajinakkhipampi dhāreti kusacīrampi dhāreti vākacīrampi dhāreti phalakacīrampi dhāreti kesakambalampi dhāreti vāḷakambalampi dhāreti ulūkapakkhampi dhāreti;**They wear robes of sunn hemp, mixed hemp, corpse-wrapping cloth, rags, lodh tree bark, antelope hide (whole or in strips), kusa grass, bark, wood-chips, human hair, horse-tail hair, or owls’ wings.*";
P_HTM[5318]="*kesamassulocakopi hoti kesamassulocanānuyogamanuyutto;**They tear out hair and beard, pursuing this practice.*";
P_HTM[5319]="*ubbhaṭṭhakopi hoti āsanappaṭikkhitto;**They constantly stand, refusing seats.*";
P_HTM[5320]="*ukkuṭikopi hoti ukkuṭikappadhānamanuyutto;**They squat, committed to the endeavor of squatting.*";
P_HTM[5321]="*kaṇṭakāpassayikopi hoti kaṇṭakāpassaye seyyaṃ kappeti;**They lie on a mat of thorns, making a mat of thorns their bed.*";
P_HTM[5322]="*sāyatatiyakampi udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharati.**They pursue the practice of immersion in water three times a day, including the evening.*";
P_HTM[5323]="*Iti evarūpaṃ anekavihitaṃ kāyassa ātāpanaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto viharati.**And so they live pursuing these various ways of mortifying and tormenting the body.*";
P_HTM[5324]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo attantapo hoti attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**That’s how one person mortifies themselves, pursuing the practice of mortifying themselves.*";
P_HTM[5325]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo parantapo hoti paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?**And how does one person mortify others, pursuing the practice of mortifying others?*";
P_HTM[5326]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo orabbhiko hoti sūkariko sākuṇiko māgaviko luddo macchaghātako coro coraghātako goghātako bandhanāgāriko, ye vā panaññepi keci kurūrakammantā.**It’s when a person is a slaughterer of sheep, pigs, poultry, or deer, a hunter or fisher, a bandit, an executioner, a butcher of cattle, a jailer, or has some other cruel livelihood.*";
P_HTM[5327]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo parantapo hoti paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**That’s how one person mortifies others, pursuing the practice of mortifying others.*";
P_HTM[5328]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo attantapo ca hoti attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?**And how does one person mortify themselves and others, pursuing the practice of mortifying themselves and others?*";
P_HTM[5329]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo rājā vā hoti khattiyo muddhāvasitto, brāhmaṇo vā hoti mahāsālo.**It’s when a person is an anointed king or a well-to-do brahmin.*";
P_HTM[5330]="*So puratthimena nagarassa navaṃ santhāgāraṃ kārāpetvā kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kharājinaṃ nivāsetvā sappitelena kāyaṃ abbhañjitvā magavisāṇena piṭṭhiṃ kaṇḍuvamāno navaṃ santhāgāraṃ pavisati, saddhiṃ mahesiyā brāhmaṇena ca purohitena.**He has a new temple built to the east of the city. He shaves off his hair and beard, dresses in a rough antelope hide, and smears his body with ghee and oil. Scratching his back with antlers, he enters the temple with his chief queen and the brahmin high priest.*";
P_HTM[5331]="*So tattha anantarahitāya bhūmiyā haritupalittāya seyyaṃ kappeti.**There he lies on the bare ground strewn with grass.*";
P_HTM[5332]="*Ekissāya gāviyā sarūpavacchāya yaṃ ekasmiṃ thane khīraṃ hoti tena rājā yāpeti; yaṃ dutiyasmiṃ thane khīraṃ hoti tena mahesī yāpeti; yaṃ tatiyasmiṃ thane khīraṃ hoti tena brāhmaṇo purohito yāpeti; yaṃ catutthasmiṃ thane khīraṃ hoti tena aggiṃ juhati; avasesena vacchako yāpeti.**The king feeds on the milk from one teat of a cow that has a calf of the same color. The chief queen feeds on the milk from the second teat. The brahmin high priest feeds on the milk from the third teat. The milk from the fourth teat is offered to the flames. The calf feeds on the remainder.*";
P_HTM[5333]="*So evamāha:**He says:*";
P_HTM[5334]="*‘ettakā usabhā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā vacchatarā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā vacchatariyo haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā ajā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā urabbhā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā assā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā rukkhā chijjantu yūpatthāya, ettakā dabbhā lūyantu barihisatthāyā’ti.**‘Slaughter this many bulls, bullocks, heifers, goats, rams, and horses for the sacrifice! Fell this many trees and reap this much grass for the sacrificial equipment!’*";
P_HTM[5335]="*Yepissa te honti dāsāti vā pessāti vā kammakarāti vā tepi daṇḍatajjitā bhayatajjitā assumukhā rudamānā parikammāni karonti.**His bondservants, workers, and staff do their jobs under threat of punishment and danger, weeping, with tearful faces.*";
P_HTM[5336]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo attantapo ca hoti attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**That’s how one person mortifies themselves and others, pursuing the practice of mortifying themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[5337]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo nevattantapo hoti nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?**And how does one person neither mortify themselves nor others, pursuing the practice of not mortifying themselves or others,*";
P_HTM[5338]="*So anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati.**living without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves?*";
P_HTM[5339]="*Idha, bhikkhave, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā.**It’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.*";
P_HTM[5340]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[5341]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[5342]="*Taṃ dhammaṃ suṇāti gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aññatarasmiṃ vā kule paccājāto.**A householder hears that teaching, or a householder’s child, or someone reborn in some good family.*";
P_HTM[5343]="*So taṃ dhammaṃ sutvā tathāgate saddhaṃ paṭilabhati.**They gain faith in the Realized One,*";
P_HTM[5344]="*So tena saddhāpaṭilābhena samannāgato iti paṭisañcikkhati:**and reflect:*";
P_HTM[5345]="*‘sambādho gharāvāso rajāpatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā;**‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is wide open.*";
P_HTM[5346]="*nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ;**It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell.*";
P_HTM[5347]="*yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[5348]="*So aparena samayena appaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya, mahantaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya, appaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya, mahantaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**After some time they give up a large or small fortune, and a large or small family circle. They shave off hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5349]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāsājīvasamāpanno pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati.**Once they’ve gone forth, they take up the training and livelihood of the mendicants. They give up killing living creatures, renouncing the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings.*";
P_HTM[5350]="*Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti dinnādāyī dinnapāṭikaṅkhī, athenena sucibhūtena attanā viharati.**They give up stealing. They take only what’s given, and expect only what’s given. They keep themselves clean by not thieving.*";
P_HTM[5351]="*Abrahmacariyaṃ pahāya brahmacārī hoti ārācārī virato asaddhammā gāmadhammā.**They give up unchastity. They are celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex.*";
P_HTM[5352]="*Musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti saccavādī saccasandho theto paccayiko avisaṃvādako lokassa.**They give up lying. They speak the truth and stick to the truth. They’re honest and trustworthy, and don’t trick the world with their words.*";
P_HTM[5353]="*Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, na ito sutvā amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, na amutra vā sutvā imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya; iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā, sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā, samaggārāmo samaggarato samagganandī samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up divisive speech. They don’t repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, they reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony.*";
P_HTM[5354]="*Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti; yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up harsh speech. They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable, and agreeable to the people.*";
P_HTM[5355]="*Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī; nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti kālena sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ.**They give up talking nonsense. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. They say things at the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[5356]="*So bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato hoti.**They refrain from injuring plants and seeds.*";
P_HTM[5357]="*Ekabhattiko hoti rattūparato virato vikālabhojanā.**They eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night and food at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[5358]="*Naccagītavāditavisūkadassanā paṭivirato hoti.**They refrain from dancing, singing, music, and seeing shows.*";
P_HTM[5359]="*Mālāgandhavilepanadhāraṇamaṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti.**They refrain from beautifying and adorning themselves with garlands, fragrance, and makeup.*";
P_HTM[5360]="*Uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato hoti.**They refrain from high and luxurious beds.*";
P_HTM[5361]="*Jātarūparajatapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**They refrain from receiving gold and money,*";
P_HTM[5362]="*Āmakadhaññapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**raw grains,*";
P_HTM[5363]="*Āmakamaṃsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**raw meat,*";
P_HTM[5364]="*Itthikumārikapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**women and girls,*";
P_HTM[5365]="*Dāsidāsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**male and female bondservants,*";
P_HTM[5366]="*Ajeḷakapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**goats and sheep,*";
P_HTM[5367]="*Kukkuṭasūkarapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**chickens and pigs,*";
P_HTM[5368]="*Hatthigavāssavaḷavapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**elephants, cows, horses, and mares,*";
P_HTM[5369]="*Khettavatthupaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**and fields and land.*";
P_HTM[5370]="*Dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato hoti.**They refrain from running errands and messages;*";
P_HTM[5371]="*Kayavikkayā paṭivirato hoti.**buying and selling;*";
P_HTM[5372]="*Tulākūṭakaṃsakūṭamānakūṭā paṭivirato hoti.**falsifying weights, metals, or measures;*";
P_HTM[5373]="*Ukkoṭanavañcananikatisāciyogā paṭivirato hoti.**bribery, fraud, cheating, and duplicity;*";
P_HTM[5374]="*Chedanavadhabandhanaviparāmosaālopasahasākārā paṭivirato hoti.**mutilation, murder, abduction, banditry, plunder, and violence.*";
P_HTM[5375]="*So santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. So yena yeneva pakkamati samādāyeva pakkamati.**They’re content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things.*";
P_HTM[5376]="*Seyyathāpi nāma pakkhī sakuṇo yena yeneva ḍeti, sapattabhārova ḍeti;**They’re like a bird: wherever it flies, wings are its only burden.*";
P_HTM[5377]="*evamevaṃ bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. So yena yeneva pakkamati, samādāyeva pakkamati.**In the same way, a mendicant is content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things.*";
P_HTM[5378]="*So iminā ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ anavajjasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**When they have this entire spectrum of noble ethics, they experience a blameless happiness inside themselves.*";
P_HTM[5379]="*So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**Seeing a sight with the eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[5380]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ; cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving restraint over it.*";
P_HTM[5381]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …**Hearing a sound with the ears …*";
P_HTM[5382]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**Smelling an odor with the nose …*";
P_HTM[5383]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**Tasting a flavor with the tongue …*";
P_HTM[5384]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**Feeling a touch with the body …*";
P_HTM[5385]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**Knowing a thought with the mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[5386]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati manindriyaṃ; manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving restraint over it.*";
P_HTM[5387]="*So iminā ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ abyāsekasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**When they have this noble sense restraint, they experience an unsullied bliss inside themselves.*";
P_HTM[5388]="*So abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, ālokite vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti.**They act with situational awareness when going out and coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent.*";
P_HTM[5389]="*So iminā ca ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato, imāya ca ariyāya santuṭṭhiyā samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena satisampajaññena samannāgato**When they have this noble spectrum of ethics, this noble sense restraint, and this noble mindfulness and situational awareness,*";
P_HTM[5390]="*vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanappatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ.**they frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw.*";
P_HTM[5391]="*So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**After the meal, they return from alms-round, sit down cross-legged with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[5392]="*So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya vigatābhijjhena cetasā viharati, abhijjhāya cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up desire for the world, they meditate with a heart rid of desire, cleansing the mind of desire.*";
P_HTM[5393]="*Byāpādapadosaṃ pahāya abyāpannacitto viharati sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī, byāpādapadosā cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up ill will and malevolence, they meditate with a mind rid of ill will, full of compassion for all living beings, cleansing the mind of ill will.*";
P_HTM[5394]="*Thinamiddhaṃ pahāya vigatathinamiddho viharati ālokasaññī sato sampajāno, thinamiddhā cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up dullness and drowsiness, they meditate with a mind rid of dullness and drowsiness, perceiving light, mindful and aware, cleansing the mind of dullness and drowsiness.*";
P_HTM[5395]="*Uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahāya anuddhato viharati ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto, uddhaccakukkuccā cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up restlessness and remorse, they meditate without restlessness, their mind peaceful inside, cleansing the mind of restlessness and remorse.*";
P_HTM[5396]="*Vicikicchaṃ pahāya tiṇṇavicikiccho viharati akathaṃkathī kusalesu dhammesu, vicikicchāya cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up doubt, they meditate having gone beyond doubt, not undecided about skillful qualities, cleansing the mind of doubt.*";
P_HTM[5397]="*So ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe**They give up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom.*";
P_HTM[5398]="*vivicceva kāmehi … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[5399]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya … pe …**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward recollection of past lives …*";
P_HTM[5400]="*sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya … pe …**knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings …*";
P_HTM[5401]="*āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[5402]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[5403]="*‘Ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’.*";
P_HTM[5404]="*Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati;**Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[5405]="*vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[5406]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[5407]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo nevattantapo hoti nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**That’s how one person neither mortifies themselves nor others, pursuing the practice of not mortifying themselves or others,*";
P_HTM[5408]="*So na attantapo na parantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati.**living without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves.*";
P_HTM[5409]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the four people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[5410]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5411]="*8. Attantapasuttaṃ**Craving, the Weaver*";
P_HTM[5412]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[5413]="*“taṇhaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi jāliniṃ saritaṃ visaṭaṃ visattikaṃ, yāya ayaṃ loko uddhasto pariyonaddho tantākulakajāto gulāguṇṭhikajāto muñjapabbajabhūto apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ saṃsāraṃ nātivattati.**“Mendicants, I will teach you about craving—the weaver, the migrant, the ubiquitous, the clinging. This world is choked by it, engulfed by it. It makes the world tangled like yarn, knotted like a ball of thread, and matted like rushes and reeds, not escaping the places of loss, the bad places, the underworld, transmigration.*";
P_HTM[5414]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[5415]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[5416]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[5417]="*“Katamā ca sā, bhikkhave, taṇhā jālinī saritā visaṭā visattikā, yāya ayaṃ loko uddhasto pariyonaddho tantākulakajāto gulāguṇṭhikajāto muñjapabbajabhūto apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ saṃsāraṃ nātivattati?**“And what is that craving …?*";
P_HTM[5418]="*Aṭṭhārasa kho panimāni, bhikkhave, taṇhāvicaritāni ajjhattikassa upādāya, aṭṭhārasa taṇhāvicaritāni bāhirassa upādāya.**There are eighteen currents of craving that derive from the interior, and eighteen that derive from the exterior.*";
P_HTM[5419]="*Katamāni aṭṭhārasa taṇhāvicaritāni ajjhattikassa upādāya?**What are the eighteen currents of craving that derive from the interior?*";
P_HTM[5420]="*Asmīti, bhikkhave, sati itthasmīti hoti, evaṃsmīti hoti, aññathāsmīti hoti, asasmīti hoti, satasmīti hoti, santi hoti, itthaṃ santi hoti, evaṃ santi hoti, aññathā santi hoti, apihaṃ santi hoti, apihaṃ itthaṃ santi hoti, apihaṃ evaṃ santi hoti, apihaṃ aññathā santi hoti, bhavissanti hoti, itthaṃ bhavissanti hoti, evaṃ bhavissanti hoti, aññathā bhavissanti hoti.**When there is the concept ‘I am’, there are the concepts ‘I am such’, ‘I am thus’, ‘I am otherwise’; ‘I am fleeting’, ‘I am lasting’; ‘mine’, ‘such is mine’, ‘thus is mine’, ‘otherwise is mine’; ‘also mine’, ‘such is also mine’, ‘thus is also mine’, ‘otherwise is also mine’; ‘I will be’, ‘I will be such’, ‘I will be thus’, ‘I will be otherwise’.*";
P_HTM[5421]="*Imāni aṭṭhārasa taṇhāvicaritāni ajjhattikassa upādāya.**These are the eighteen currents of craving that derive from the interior.*";
P_HTM[5422]="*Katamāni aṭṭhārasa taṇhāvicaritāni bāhirassa upādāya?**What are the eighteen currents of craving that derive from the exterior?*";
P_HTM[5423]="*Imināsmīti, bhikkhave, sati iminā itthasmīti hoti, iminā evaṃsmīti hoti, iminā aññathāsmīti hoti, iminā asasmīti hoti, iminā satasmīti hoti, iminā santi hoti, iminā itthaṃ santi hoti, iminā evaṃ santi hoti, iminā aññathā santi hoti, iminā apihaṃ santi hoti, iminā apihaṃ itthaṃ santi hoti, iminā apihaṃ evaṃ santi hoti, iminā apihaṃ aññathā santi hoti, iminā bhavissanti hoti, iminā itthaṃ bhavissanti hoti, iminā evaṃ bhavissanti hoti, iminā aññathā bhavissanti hoti.**When there is the concept ‘I am because of this’, there are the concepts ‘I am such because of this’, ‘I am thus because of this’, ‘I am otherwise because of this’; ‘I am fleeting because of this’, ‘I am lasting because of this’; ‘mine because of this’, ‘such is mine because of this’, ‘thus is mine because of this’, ‘otherwise is mine because of this’; ‘also mine because of this’, ‘such is also mine because of this’, ‘thus is also mine because of this’, ‘otherwise is also mine because of this’; ‘I will be because of this’, ‘I will be such because of this’, ‘I will be thus because of this’, ‘I will be otherwise because of this’.*";
P_HTM[5424]="*Imāni aṭṭhārasa taṇhāvicaritāni bāhirassa upādāya.**These are the eighteen currents of craving that derive from the exterior.*";
P_HTM[5425]="*Iti aṭṭhārasa taṇhāvicaritāni ajjhattikassa upādāya, aṭṭhārasa taṇhāvicaritāni bāhirassa upādāya.**So there are eighteen currents of craving that derive from the interior, and eighteen that derive from the exterior.*";
P_HTM[5426]="*Imāni vuccanti, bhikkhave, chattiṃsa taṇhāvicaritāni.**These are called the thirty-six currents of craving.*";
P_HTM[5427]="*Iti evarūpāni atītāni chattiṃsa taṇhāvicaritāni, anāgatāni chattiṃsa taṇhāvicaritāni, paccuppannāni chattiṃsa taṇhāvicaritāni.**Each of these pertain to the past, future, and present,*";
P_HTM[5428]="*Evaṃ aṭṭhasataṃ taṇhāvicaritaṃ honti.**making one hundred and eight currents of craving.*";
P_HTM[5429]="*Ayaṃ kho sā, bhikkhave, taṇhā jālinī saritā visaṭā visattikā, yāya ayaṃ loko uddhasto pariyonaddho tantākulakajāto guṇāguṇṭhikajāto muñjapabbajabhūto apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ saṃsāraṃ nātivattatī”ti.**This is that craving—the weaver, the migrant, the ubiquitous, the clinging. This world is choked by it, engulfed by it. It makes the world tangled like yarn, knotted like a ball of thread, and matted like rushes and reeds, not escaping the places of loss, the bad places, the underworld, transmigration.”*";
P_HTM[5430]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5431]="*9. Taṇhāsuttaṃ**Love and Hate*";
P_HTM[5432]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, pemāni jāyanti.**“Mendicants, these four things are born of love and hate.*";
P_HTM[5433]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5434]="*Pemā pemaṃ jāyati, pemā doso jāyati, dosā pemaṃ jāyati, dosā doso jāyati.**~Love is born of love, ~hate is born of love, ~love is born of hate, and ~hate is born of hate.*";
P_HTM[5435]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, pemā pemaṃ jāyati?**And how is love born of love?*";
P_HTM[5436]="*Idha, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalassa iṭṭho hoti kanto manāpo.**It’s when someone likes, loves, and cares for a person.*";
P_HTM[5437]="*Taṃ pare iṭṭhena kantena manāpena samudācaranti.**Others treat that person with liking, love, and care.*";
P_HTM[5438]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[5439]="*‘yo kho myāyaṃ puggalo iṭṭho kanto manāpo, taṃ pare iṭṭhena kantena manāpena samudācarantī’ti.**‘These others like the person I like.’*";
P_HTM[5440]="*So tesu pemaṃ janeti.**And so love for them springs up.*";
P_HTM[5441]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pemā pemaṃ jāyati.**That’s how love is born of love.*";
P_HTM[5442]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, pemā doso jāyati?**And how is hate born of love?*";
P_HTM[5443]="*Idha, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalassa iṭṭho hoti kanto manāpo.**It’s when someone likes, loves, and cares for a person.*";
P_HTM[5444]="*Taṃ pare aniṭṭhena akantena amanāpena samudācaranti.**Others treat that person with disliking, loathing, and detestation.*";
P_HTM[5445]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[5446]="*‘yo kho myāyaṃ puggalo iṭṭho kanto manāpo, taṃ pare aniṭṭhena akantena amanāpena samudācarantī’ti.**‘These others dislike the person I like.’*";
P_HTM[5447]="*So tesu dosaṃ janeti.**And so hate for them springs up.*";
P_HTM[5448]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pemā doso jāyati.**That’s how hate is born of love.*";
P_HTM[5449]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dosā pemaṃ jāyati?**And how is love born of hate?*";
P_HTM[5450]="*Idha, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalassa aniṭṭho hoti akanto amanāpo.**It’s when someone dislikes, loathes, and detests a person.*";
P_HTM[5451]="*Taṃ pare aniṭṭhena akantena amanāpena samudācaranti.**Others treat that person with disliking, loathing, and detestation.*";
P_HTM[5452]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[5453]="*‘yo kho myāyaṃ puggalo aniṭṭho akanto amanāpo, taṃ pare aniṭṭhena akantena amanāpena samudācarantī’ti.**‘These others dislike the person I dislike.’*";
P_HTM[5454]="*So tesu pemaṃ janeti.**And so love for them springs up.*";
P_HTM[5455]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dosā pemaṃ jāyati.**That’s how love is born of hate.*";
P_HTM[5456]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dosā doso jāyati?**And how is hate born of hate?*";
P_HTM[5457]="*Idha, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalassa aniṭṭho hoti akanto amanāpo.**It’s when someone dislikes, loathes, and detests a person.*";
P_HTM[5458]="*Taṃ pare iṭṭhena kantena manāpena samudācaranti.**Others treat that person with liking, love, and care.*";
P_HTM[5459]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[5460]="*‘yo kho myāyaṃ puggalo aniṭṭho akanto amanāpo, taṃ pare iṭṭhena kantena manāpena samudācarantī’ti.**‘These others like the person I dislike.’*";
P_HTM[5461]="*So tesu dosaṃ janeti.**And so hate for them springs up.*";
P_HTM[5462]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dosā doso jāyati.**That’s how hate is born of hate.*";
P_HTM[5463]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri pemāni jāyanti.**These are the four things that are born of love and hate.*";
P_HTM[5464]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati,**A time comes when a mendicant … enters and remains in the first absorption.*";
P_HTM[5465]="*yampissa pemā pemaṃ jāyati tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti, yopissa pemā doso jāyati sopissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti, yampissa dosā pemaṃ jāyati tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti, yopissa dosā doso jāyati sopissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti.**At that time they have no love born of love, hate born of love, love born of hate, or hate born of hate.*";
P_HTM[5466]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati,**A time comes when a mendicant … enters and remains in the second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[5467]="*yampissa pemā pemaṃ jāyati tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti, yopissa pemā doso jāyati sopissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti, yampissa dosā pemaṃ jāyati tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti, yopissa dosā doso jāyati sopissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti.**At that time they have no love born of love, hate born of love, love born of hate, or hate born of hate.*";
P_HTM[5468]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati, yampissa pemā pemaṃ jāyati tampissa pahīnaṃ hoti ucchinnamūlaṃ tālāvatthukataṃ anabhāvaṃkataṃ āyatiṃ anuppādadhammaṃ, yopissa pemā doso jāyati sopissa pahīno hoti ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṃkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo,**A time comes when a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[5469]="*yampissa dosā pemaṃ jāyati tampissa pahīnaṃ hoti ucchinnamūlaṃ tālāvatthukataṃ anabhāvaṃkataṃ āyatiṃ anuppādadhammaṃ, yopissa dosā doso jāyati sopissa pahīno hoti ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṃkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo.**At that time any love born of love, hate born of love, love born of hate, or hate born of hate is given up, cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[5470]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu neva usseneti na paṭiseneti na dhūpāyati na pajjalati na sampajjhāyati.**This is called a mendicant who doesn’t draw close or push back or fume or ignite or burn up.*";
P_HTM[5471]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu usseneti?**And how does a mendicant draw close?*";
P_HTM[5472]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ, attani vā rūpaṃ, rūpasmiṃ vā attānaṃ;**It’s when a mendicant regards form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form.*";
P_HTM[5473]="*vedanaṃ attato samanupassati, vedanāvantaṃ vā attānaṃ, attani vā vedanaṃ, vedanāya vā attānaṃ;**They regard feeling as self, self as having feeling, feeling in self, or self in feeling.*";
P_HTM[5474]="*saññaṃ attato samanupassati, saññāvantaṃ vā attānaṃ, attani vā saññaṃ, saññāya vā attānaṃ;**They regard perception as self, self as having perception, perception in self, or self in perception.*";
P_HTM[5475]="*saṅkhāre attato samanupassati, saṅkhāravantaṃ vā attānaṃ, attani vā saṅkhāre, saṅkhāresu vā attānaṃ;**They regard choices as self, self as having choices, choices in self, or self in choices.*";
P_HTM[5476]="*viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ, attani vā viññāṇaṃ, viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ.**They regard consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, or self in consciousness.*";
P_HTM[5477]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu usseneti.**That’s how a mendicant draws close.*";
P_HTM[5478]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na usseneti?**And how does a mendicant not draw close?*";
P_HTM[5479]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, na rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ, na attani vā rūpaṃ, na rūpasmiṃ vā attānaṃ;**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form.*";
P_HTM[5480]="*na vedanaṃ attato samanupassati, na vedanāvantaṃ vā attānaṃ, na attani vā vedanaṃ, na vedanāya vā attānaṃ;**They don’t regard feeling as self, self as having feeling, feeling in self, or self in feeling.*";
P_HTM[5481]="*na saññaṃ attato samanupassati, na saññāvantaṃ vā attānaṃ, na attani vā saññaṃ, na saññāya vā attānaṃ;**They don’t regard perception as self, self as having perception, perception in self, or self in perception.*";
P_HTM[5482]="*na saṅkhāre attato samanupassati, na saṅkhāravantaṃ vā attānaṃ, na attani vā saṅkhāre, na saṅkhāresu vā attānaṃ;**They don’t regard choices as self, self as having choices, choices in self, or self in choices.*";
P_HTM[5483]="*na viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, na viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ, na attani vā viññāṇaṃ, na viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ.**They don’t regard consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, or self in consciousness.*";
P_HTM[5484]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na usseneti.**That’s how a mendicant doesn’t draw close.*";
P_HTM[5485]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭiseneti?**And how does a mendicant push back?*";
P_HTM[5486]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkosantaṃ paccakkosati, rosantaṃ paṭirosati, bhaṇḍantaṃ paṭibhaṇḍati.**It’s when someone abuses, annoys, or argues with a mendicant, and the mendicant abuses, annoys, or argues back at them.*";
P_HTM[5487]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭiseneti.**That’s how a mendicant pushes back.*";
P_HTM[5488]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na paṭiseneti?**And how does a mendicant not push back?*";
P_HTM[5489]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkosantaṃ na paccakkosati, rosantaṃ na paṭirosati, bhaṇḍantaṃ na paṭibhaṇḍati.**It’s when someone abuses, annoys, or argues with a mendicant, and the mendicant doesn’t abuse, annoy, or argue back at them.*";
P_HTM[5490]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na paṭiseneti.**That’s how a mendicant doesn’t push back.*";
P_HTM[5491]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhūpāyati?**And how does a mendicant fume?*";
P_HTM[5492]="*Asmīti, bhikkhave, sati itthasmīti hoti, evaṃsmīti hoti, aññathāsmīti hoti, asasmīti hoti, satasmīti hoti, santi hoti, itthaṃ santi hoti, evaṃ santi hoti, aññathā santi hoti, apihaṃ santi hoti, apihaṃ itthaṃ santi hoti, apihaṃ evaṃ santi hoti, apihaṃ aññathā santi hoti, bhavissanti hoti, itthaṃ bhavissanti hoti, evaṃ bhavissanti hoti, aññathā bhavissanti hoti.**When there is the concept ‘I am’, there are the concepts ‘I am such’, ‘I am thus’, ‘I am otherwise’; ‘I am fleeting’, ‘I am lasting’; ‘mine’, ‘such is mine’, ‘thus is mine’, ‘otherwise is mine’; ‘also mine’, ‘such is also mine’, ‘thus is also mine’, ‘otherwise is also mine’; ‘I will be’, ‘I will be such’, ‘I will be thus’, ‘I will be otherwise’.*";
P_HTM[5493]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhūpāyati.**That’s how a mendicant fumes.*";
P_HTM[5494]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na dhūpāyati?**And how does a mendicant not fume?*";
P_HTM[5495]="*Asmīti, bhikkhave, asati itthasmīti na hoti, evaṃsmīti na hoti, aññathāsmīti na hoti, asasmīti na hoti, satasmīti na hoti, santi na hoti, itthaṃ santi na hoti, evaṃ santi na hoti, aññathā santi na hoti, apihaṃ santi na hoti, apihaṃ itthaṃ santi na hoti, apihaṃ evaṃ santi na hoti, apihaṃ aññathā santi na hoti, bhavissanti na hoti, itthaṃ bhavissanti na hoti, evaṃ bhavissanti na hoti, aññathā bhavissanti na hoti.**When there is no concept ‘I am’, there are no concepts ‘I am such’, ‘I am thus’, ‘I am otherwise’; ‘I am fleeting’, ‘I am lasting’; ‘mine’, ‘such is mine’, ‘thus is mine’, ‘otherwise is mine’; ‘also mine’, ‘such is also mine’, ‘thus is also mine’, ‘otherwise is also mine’; ‘I will be’, ‘I will be such’, ‘I will be thus’, ‘I will be otherwise’.*";
P_HTM[5496]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na dhūpāyati.**That’s how a mendicant doesn’t fume.*";
P_HTM[5497]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pajjalati?**And how is a mendicant ignited?*";
P_HTM[5498]="*Iminā asmīti, bhikkhave, sati iminā itthasmīti hoti, iminā evaṃsmīti hoti, iminā aññathāsmīti hoti, iminā asasmīti hoti, iminā satasmīti hoti, iminā santi hoti, iminā itthaṃ santi hoti, iminā evaṃ santi hoti, iminā aññathā santi hoti, iminā apihaṃ santi hoti, iminā apihaṃ itthaṃ santi hoti, iminā apihaṃ evaṃ santi hoti, iminā apihaṃ aññathā santi hoti, iminā bhavissanti hoti, iminā itthaṃ bhavissanti hoti, iminā evaṃ bhavissanti hoti, iminā aññathā bhavissanti hoti.**When there is the concept ‘I am because of this’, there are the concepts ‘I am such because of this’, ‘I am thus because of this’, ‘I am otherwise because of this’; ‘I am fleeting because of this’, ‘I am lasting because of this’; ‘mine because of this’, ‘such is mine because of this’, ‘thus is mine because of this’, ‘otherwise is mine because of this’; ‘also mine because of this’, ‘such is also mine because of this’, ‘thus is also mine because of this’, ‘otherwise is also mine because of this’; ‘I will be because of this’, ‘I will be such because of this’, ‘I will be thus because of this’, ‘I will be otherwise because of this’.*";
P_HTM[5499]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pajjalati.**That’s how a mendicant is ignited.*";
P_HTM[5500]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na pajjalati?**And how is a mendicant not ignited?*";
P_HTM[5501]="*Iminā asmīti, bhikkhave, asati iminā itthasmīti na hoti, iminā evaṃsmīti na hoti, iminā aññathāsmīti na hoti, iminā asasmīti na hoti, iminā satasmīti na hoti, iminā santi na hoti, iminā itthaṃ santi na hoti, iminā evaṃ santi na hoti, iminā aññathā santi na hoti, iminā apihaṃ santi na hoti, iminā apihaṃ itthaṃ santi na hoti, iminā apihaṃ evaṃ santi na hoti, iminā apihaṃ aññathā santi na hoti, iminā bhavissanti na hoti, iminā itthaṃ bhavissanti na hoti, iminā evaṃ bhavissanti na hoti, iminā aññathā bhavissanti na hoti.**When there is no concept ‘I am because of this’, there are no concepts ‘I am such because of this’, ‘I am thus because of this’, ‘I am otherwise because of this’; ‘I am fleeting because of this’, ‘I am lasting because of this’; ‘mine because of this’, ‘such is mine because of this’, ‘thus is mine because of this’, ‘otherwise is mine because of this’; ‘also mine because of this’, ‘such is also mine because of this’, ‘thus is also mine because of this’, ‘otherwise is also mine because of this’; ‘I will be because of this’, ‘I will be such because of this’, ‘I will be thus because of this’, ‘I will be otherwise because of this’.*";
P_HTM[5502]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na pajjalati.**That’s how a mendicant is not ignited.*";
P_HTM[5503]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sampajjhāyati?**And how does a mendicant burn up?*";
P_HTM[5504]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno asmimāno pahīno na hoti ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo.**It’s when a mendicant hasn’t given up the conceit ‘I am’, cut it off at the root, made it like a palm stump, obliterated it, so it’s unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[5505]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sampajjhāyati.**That’s how a mendicant is burned up.*";
P_HTM[5506]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na sampajjhāyati?**And how does a mendicant not burn up?*";
P_HTM[5507]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno asmimāno pahīno hoti ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo.**It’s when a mendicant has given up the conceit ‘I am’, cut it off at the root, made it like a palm stump, obliterated it, so it’s unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[5508]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na sampajjhāyatī”ti.**That’s how a mendicant is not burned up.”*";
P_HTM[5509]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5510]="*Mahāvaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[5511]="*Sotānugataṃ ṭhānaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5512]="*Bhaddiya sāmugiya vappa sāḷhā ca;* **";
P_HTM[5513]="*Mallika attantāpo,* **";
P_HTM[5514]="*Taṇhā pemena ca dasā teti.* **";
P_HTM[5515]="*Catuttho mahāpaṇṇāsako samatto.* **";
P_HTM[5516]="*10. Pemasuttaṃ**Training Rules*";
P_HTM[5517]="*“Asappurisañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, asappurisena asappurisatarañca;**“Mendicants, I will teach you a bad person and a worse person,*";
P_HTM[5518]="*sappurisañca, sappurisena sappurisatarañca.**a good person and a better person.*";
P_HTM[5519]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[5520]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[5521]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[5522]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappuriso?**“And what is a bad person?*";
P_HTM[5523]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyī hoti.**It’s someone who kills living creatures, steals, commits sexual misconduct, lies, and uses alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[5524]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappuriso.**This is called a bad person.*";
P_HTM[5525]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro?**And what is a worse person?*";
P_HTM[5526]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā ca pāṇātipātī hoti, parañca pāṇātipāte samādapeti;**It’s someone who kills living creatures, steals, commits sexual misconduct, lies, and uses alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. And they encourage others to do these things.*";
P_HTM[5527]="*attanā ca adinnādāyī hoti, parañca adinnādāne samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5528]="*attanā ca kāmesumicchācārī hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācāre samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5529]="*attanā ca musāvādī hoti, parañca musāvāde samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5530]="*attanā ca surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyī hoti, parañca surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāne samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[5531]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro.**This is called a worse person.*";
P_HTM[5532]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappuriso?**And what is a good person?*";
P_HTM[5533]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti.**It’s someone who doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[5534]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappuriso.**This is called a good person.*";
P_HTM[5535]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappurisena sappurisataro?**And what is a better person?*";
P_HTM[5536]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā ca pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, parañca pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;**It’s someone who doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. And they encourage others to avoid these things.*";
P_HTM[5537]="*attanā ca adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, parañca adinnādānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5538]="*attanā ca kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5539]="*attanā ca musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, parañca musāvādā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5540]="*attanā ca surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti, parañca surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[5541]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappurisena sappurisataro”ti.**This is called a better person.”*";
P_HTM[5542]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5543]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**A Good Person*";
P_HTM[5544]="*1. Sikkhāpadasuttaṃ**Faithless*";
P_HTM[5545]="*“Asappurisañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, asappurisena asappurisatarañca;**“Mendicants, I will teach you a bad person and a worse person,*";
P_HTM[5546]="*sappurisañca, sappurisena sappurisatarañca. Taṃ suṇātha … pe ….**a good person and a better person.*";
P_HTM[5547]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappuriso?**And what is a bad person?*";
P_HTM[5548]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco assaddho hoti, ahiriko hoti, anottappī hoti, appassuto hoti, kusīto hoti, muṭṭhassati hoti, duppañño hoti.**It’s someone who is faithless, shameless, imprudent, with little learning, lazy, unmindful, and witless.*";
P_HTM[5549]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappuriso.**This is called a bad person.*";
P_HTM[5550]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro?**And what is a worse person?*";
P_HTM[5551]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā ca assaddho hoti, parañca assaddhiye samādapeti;**It’s someone who is faithless, shameless, imprudent, with little learning, lazy, confused, and witless. And they encourage others in these same qualities.*";
P_HTM[5552]="*attanā ca ahiriko hoti, parañca ahirikatāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5553]="*attanā ca anottappī hoti, parañca anottappe samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5554]="*attanā ca appassuto hoti, parañca appassute samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5555]="*attanā ca kusīto hoti, parañca kosajje samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5556]="*attanā ca muṭṭhassati hoti, parañca muṭṭhassacce samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5557]="*attanā ca duppañño hoti, parañca duppaññatāya samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[5558]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro.**This is called a worse person.*";
P_HTM[5559]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappuriso?**And what is a good person?*";
P_HTM[5560]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco saddho hoti, hirimā hoti, ottappī hoti, bahussuto hoti, āraddhavīriyo hoti, satimā hoti, paññavā hoti.**It’s someone who is faithful, conscientious, prudent, learned, energetic, mindful, and wise.*";
P_HTM[5561]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappuriso.**This is called a good person.*";
P_HTM[5562]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappurisena sappurisataro?**And what is a better person?*";
P_HTM[5563]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā ca saddhāsampanno hoti, parañca saddhāsampadāya samādapeti;**It’s someone who is personally accomplished in faith, conscience, prudence, learning, energy, mindfulness, and wisdom. And they encourage others in these same qualities.*";
P_HTM[5564]="*attanā ca hirimā hoti, parañca hirimatāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5565]="*attanā ca ottappī hoti, parañca ottappe samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5566]="*attanā ca bahussuto hoti, parañca bāhusacce samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5567]="*attanā ca āraddhavīriyo hoti, parañca vīriyārambhe samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5568]="*attanā ca upaṭṭhitassati hoti, parañca satiupaṭṭhāne samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5569]="*attanā ca paññāsampanno hoti, parañca paññāsampadāya samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[5570]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappurisena sappurisataro”ti.**This is called a better person.”*";
P_HTM[5571]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5572]="*2. Assaddhasuttaṃ**Seven Kinds of Deeds*";
P_HTM[5573]="*“Asappurisañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, asappurisena asappurisatarañca;**“Mendicants, I will teach you a bad person and a worse person,*";
P_HTM[5574]="*sappurisañca, sappurisena sappurisatarañca. Taṃ suṇātha … pe ….**a good person and a better person.*";
P_HTM[5575]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappuriso?**And what is a bad person?*";
P_HTM[5576]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, pisuṇavāco hoti, pharusavāco hoti, samphappalāpī hoti.**It’s someone who kills living creatures, steals, commits sexual misconduct, and uses speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical.*";
P_HTM[5577]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappuriso.**This is called a bad person.*";
P_HTM[5578]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro?**And what is a worse person?*";
P_HTM[5579]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā ca pāṇātipātī hoti, parañca pāṇātipāte samādapeti;**It’s someone who kills living creatures, steals, commits sexual misconduct, and uses speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they encourage others to do these things.*";
P_HTM[5580]="*attanā ca adinnādāyī hoti, parañca adinnādāne samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5581]="*attanā ca kāmesumicchācārī hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācāre samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5582]="*attanā ca musāvādī hoti, parañca musāvāde samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5583]="*attanā ca pisuṇavāco hoti, parañca pisuṇāya vācāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5584]="*attanā ca pharusavāco hoti, parañca pharusāya vācāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5585]="*attanā ca samphappalāpī hoti, parañca samphappalāpe samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[5586]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro.**This is called a worse person.*";
P_HTM[5587]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappuriso?**And what is a good person?*";
P_HTM[5588]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato, hoti, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti.**It’s someone who doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, or use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical.*";
P_HTM[5589]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappuriso.**This is called a good person.*";
P_HTM[5590]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappurisena sappurisataro?**And what is a better person?*";
P_HTM[5591]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā ca pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, parañca pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;**It’s someone who doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, or use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they encourage others to avoid these things.*";
P_HTM[5592]="*attanā ca adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, parañca adinnādānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5593]="*attanā ca kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5594]="*attanā ca musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, parañca musāvādā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5595]="*attanā ca pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, parañca pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5596]="*attanā ca pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, parañca pharusāya vācāya veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5597]="*attanā ca samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, parañca samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[5598]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappurisena sappurisataro”ti.**This is called a better person.”*";
P_HTM[5599]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5600]="*3. Sattakammasuttaṃ**Ten Kinds of Deeds*";
P_HTM[5601]="*“Asappurisañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, asappurisena asappurisatarañca;**“Mendicants, I will teach you a bad person and a worse person,*";
P_HTM[5602]="*sappurisañca, sappurisena sappurisatarañca. Taṃ suṇātha … pe ….**a good person and a better person.*";
P_HTM[5603]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappuriso?**And what is a bad person?*";
P_HTM[5604]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, pisuṇavāco hoti, pharusavāco hoti, samphappalāpī hoti, abhijjhālu hoti, byāpannacitto hoti, micchādiṭṭhiko hoti.**It’s someone who kills living creatures, steals, and commits sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5605]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappuriso.**This is called a bad person.*";
P_HTM[5606]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro?**And what is a worse person?*";
P_HTM[5607]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā ca pāṇātipātī hoti, parañca pāṇātipāte samādapeti … pe … attanā ca abhijjhālu hoti, parañca abhijjhāya samādapeti;**It’s someone who kills living creatures, steals, and commits sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. They’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view. And they encourage others to do these things.*";
P_HTM[5608]="*attanā ca byāpannacitto hoti, parañca byāpāde samādapeti, attanā ca micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca micchādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[5609]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro.**This is called a worse person.*";
P_HTM[5610]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappuriso?**And what is a good person?*";
P_HTM[5611]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … anabhijjhālu hoti, abyāpannacitto hoti, sammādiṭṭhiko hoti.**It’s someone who doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view.*";
P_HTM[5612]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappuriso.**This is called a good person.*";
P_HTM[5613]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappurisena sappurisataro?**And what is a better person?*";
P_HTM[5614]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā ca pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, parañca pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti … pe … attanā ca anabhijjhālu hoti, parañca anabhijjhāya samādapeti;**It’s someone who doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. They’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view. And they encourage others to do these things.*";
P_HTM[5615]="*attanā ca abyāpannacitto hoti, parañca abyāpāde samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5616]="*attanā ca sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca sammādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[5617]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappurisena sappurisataro”ti.**This is called a better person.”*";
P_HTM[5618]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5619]="*4. Dasakammasuttaṃ**Eightfold*";
P_HTM[5620]="*“Asappurisañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, asappurisena asappurisatarañca;**“Mendicants, I will teach you a bad person and a worse person,*";
P_HTM[5621]="*sappurisañca, sappurisena sappurisatarañca. Taṃ suṇātha … pe ….**a good person and a better person.*";
P_HTM[5622]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappuriso?**And what is a bad person?*";
P_HTM[5623]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, micchāsaṅkappo hoti, micchāvāco hoti, micchākammanto hoti, micchāājīvo hoti, micchāvāyāmo hoti, micchāsati hoti, micchāsamādhi hoti.**It’s someone who has wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion.*";
P_HTM[5624]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappuriso.**This is called a bad person.*";
P_HTM[5625]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro?**And what is a worse person?*";
P_HTM[5626]="*Idha bhikkhave, ekacco attanā ca micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca micchādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti;**It’s someone who has wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion. And they encourage others in these same qualities.*";
P_HTM[5627]="*attanā ca micchāsaṅkappo hoti, parañca micchāsaṅkappe samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5628]="*attanā ca micchāvāco hoti, parañca micchāvācāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5629]="*attanā ca micchākammanto hoti, parañca micchākammante samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5630]="*attanā ca micchāājīvo hoti, parañca micchāājīve samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5631]="*attanā ca micchāvāyāmo hoti, parañca micchāvāyāme samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5632]="*attanā ca micchāsati hoti, parañca micchāsatiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5633]="*attanā ca micchāsamādhi hoti, parañca micchāsamādhimhi samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[5634]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro.**This is called a worse person.*";
P_HTM[5635]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappuriso?**And what is a good person?*";
P_HTM[5636]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, sammāsaṅkappo hoti, sammāvāco hoti, sammākammanto hoti, sammāājīvo hoti, sammāvāyāmo hoti, sammāsati hoti, sammāsamādhi hoti.**It’s someone who has right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[5637]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappuriso.**This is called a good person.*";
P_HTM[5638]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappurisena sappurisataro?**And what is a better person?*";
P_HTM[5639]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā ca sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca sammādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti;**It’s someone who has right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. And they encourage others in these same qualities.*";
P_HTM[5640]="*attanā ca sammāsaṅkappo hoti, parañca sammāsaṅkappe samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5641]="*attanā ca sammāvāco hoti, parañca sammāvācāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5642]="*attanā ca sammākammanto hoti, parañca sammākammante samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5643]="*attanā ca sammāājīvo hoti, parañca sammāājīve samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5644]="*attanā ca sammāvāyāmo hoti, parañca sammāvāyāme samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5645]="*attanā ca sammāsati hoti, parañca sammāsatiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[5646]="*attanā ca sammāsamādhi hoti, parañca sammāsamādhimhi samādapeti.* **";
P_HTM[5647]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappurisena sappurisataro”ti.**This is called a better person.”*";
P_HTM[5648]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5649]="*5. Aṭṭhaṅgikasuttaṃ**The Path with Ten Factors*";
P_HTM[5650]="*“Asappurisañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, asappurisena asappurisatarañca;**“Mendicants, I will teach you a bad person and a worse person,*";
P_HTM[5651]="*sappurisañca, sappurisena sappurisatarañca. Taṃ suṇātha … pe ….**a good person and a better person.*";
P_HTM[5652]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappuriso?**And what is a bad person?*";
P_HTM[5653]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco micchādiṭṭhiko hoti … pe … micchāñāṇī hoti, micchāvimutti hoti.**It’s someone who has wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[5654]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappuriso.**This is called a bad person.*";
P_HTM[5655]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro?**And what is a worse person?*";
