P_HTM[5702]="*8. Dutiyapāpadhammasuttaṃ**Bad Character (3rd)*";
P_HTM[5703]="*“Pāpadhammañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, pāpadhammena pāpadhammatarañca;**“Mendicants, I will teach you bad character and worse character,*";
P_HTM[5704]="*kalyāṇadhammañca, kalyāṇadhammena kalyāṇadhammatarañca. Taṃ suṇātha … pe ….**good character and better character.*";
P_HTM[5705]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, pāpadhammo?**And who has bad character?*";
P_HTM[5706]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti … pe … micchādiṭṭhiko hoti.**It’s someone who kills living creatures, steals, and commits sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5707]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, pāpadhammo.**This is called bad character.*";
