P_HTM[5736]="*Sappurisavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[5737]="*Sikkhāpadañca assaddhaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5738]="*Sattakammaṃ atho ca dasakammaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[5739]="*Aṭṭhaṅgikañca dasamaggaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5740]="*Dve pāpadhammā apare dveti.* **";
P_HTM[5741]="*10. Catutthapāpadhammasuttaṃ**Assembly*";
P_HTM[5742]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, parisadūsanā.**“Mendicants, these four corrupt an assembly.*";
P_HTM[5743]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5744]="*Bhikkhu, bhikkhave, dussīlo pāpadhammo parisadūsano;**A monk, nun, layman, or laywoman who is unethical, of bad character.*";
P_HTM[5745]="*bhikkhunī, bhikkhave, dussīlā pāpadhammā parisadūsanā;* **";
P_HTM[5746]="*upāsako, bhikkhave, dussīlo pāpadhammo parisadūsano;* **";
P_HTM[5747]="*upāsikā, bhikkhave, dussīlā pāpadhammā parisadūsanā.* **";
P_HTM[5748]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro parisadūsanā.**These are the four that corrupt an assembly.*";
P_HTM[5749]="*Cattārome, bhikkhave, parisasobhanā.**Mendicants, these four beautify an assembly.*";
P_HTM[5750]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5751]="*Bhikkhu, bhikkhave, sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo parisasobhano;**A monk, nun, layman, or laywoman who is ethical, of good character.*";
P_HTM[5752]="*bhikkhunī, bhikkhave, sīlavatī kalyāṇadhammā parisasobhanā;* **";
P_HTM[5753]="*upāsako, bhikkhave, sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo parisasobhano;* **";
P_HTM[5754]="*upāsikā, bhikkhave, sīlavatī kalyāṇadhammā parisasobhanā.* **";
P_HTM[5755]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro parisasobhanā”ti.**These are the four that beautify an assembly.”*";
P_HTM[5756]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5757]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Assembly*";
P_HTM[5758]="*1. Parisāsuttaṃ**View*";
P_HTM[5759]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5760]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5761]="*Kāyaduccaritena, vacīduccaritena, manoduccaritena, micchādiṭṭhiyā—**Bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5762]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5763]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[5764]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5765]="*Kāyasucaritena, vacīsucaritena, manosucaritena, sammādiṭṭhiyā—**Good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and right view.*";
P_HTM[5766]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these four qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[5767]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5768]="*2. Diṭṭhisuttaṃ**Ungrateful*";
P_HTM[5769]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5770]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5771]="*Kāyaduccaritena, vacīduccaritena, manoduccaritena, akataññutā akataveditā—**Bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and being ungrateful and thankless.*";
P_HTM[5772]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5773]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[5774]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5775]="*Kāyasucaritena, vacīsucaritena, manosucaritena, kataññutā kataveditā—**Good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and being grateful and thankful.*";
P_HTM[5776]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these four qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[5777]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5778]="*3. Akataññutāsuttaṃ**Killing Living Creatures*";
P_HTM[5779]="*… pe … Pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti … pe … pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti.**“Someone with four qualities is cast down to hell. … They kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, and lie. … Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven. … They don’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, or lie. …”*";
P_HTM[5780]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5781]="*4. Pāṇātipātīsuttaṃ**Path (1st)*";
P_HTM[5782]="*… pe … Micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, micchāsaṅkappo hoti, micchāvāco hoti, micchākammanto hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, sammāsaṅkappo hoti, sammāvāco hoti, sammākammanto hoti.**“Someone with four qualities is cast down to hell. … wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action. … Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven. … right view, right thought, right speech, right action. …”*";
P_HTM[5783]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5784]="*5. Paṭhamamaggasuttaṃ**Path (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5785]="*… pe … Micchāājīvo hoti, micchāvāyāmo hoti, micchāsati hoti, micchāsamādhi hoti … pe … sammāājīvo hoti, sammāvāyāmo hoti, sammāsati hoti, sammāsamādhi hoti.**“Someone with four qualities is cast down to hell. … wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion. Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven. … right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. …”*";
P_HTM[5786]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5787]="*6. Dutiyamaggasuttaṃ**Kinds of Expression (1st)*";
P_HTM[5788]="*… pe … Adiṭṭhe diṭṭhavādī hoti, asute sutavādī hoti, amute mutavādī hoti, aviññāte viññātavādī hoti … pe … adiṭṭhe adiṭṭhavādī hoti, asute asutavādī hoti, amute amutavādī hoti, aviññāte aviññātavādī hoti.**“Someone with four qualities is cast down to hell. … They say they’ve seen, heard, thought, or known something, but they haven’t. … Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven. … They say they haven’t seen, heard, thought, or known something, and they haven’t. …”*";
P_HTM[5789]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5790]="*7. Paṭhamavohārapathasuttaṃ**Kinds of Expression (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5791]="*… pe … Diṭṭhe adiṭṭhavādī hoti, sute asutavādī hoti, mute amutavādī hoti, viññāte aviññātavādī hoti … pe … diṭṭhe diṭṭhavādī hoti, sute sutavādī hoti, mute mutavādī hoti, viññāte viññātavādī hoti.**“Someone with four qualities is cast down to hell. … They say they haven’t seen, heard, thought, or known something, but they have. … Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven. … They say they’ve seen, heard, thought, or known something, and they have. …”*";
P_HTM[5792]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5793]="*8. Dutiyavohārapathasuttaṃ**Imprudence*";
P_HTM[5794]="*… pe … Assaddho hoti, dussīlo hoti, ahiriko hoti, anottappī hoti … pe … saddho hoti, sīlavā hoti, hirimā hoti, ottappī hoti.**“Someone with four qualities is cast down to hell. … They’re faithless, unethical, shameless, and imprudent. … Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven. … They’re faithful, ethical, conscientious, and prudent. …”*";
P_HTM[5795]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5796]="*9. Ahirikasuttaṃ**Unethical*";
P_HTM[5797]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5798]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5799]="*Assaddho hoti, dussīlo hoti, kusīto hoti, duppañño hoti—**They’re faithless, unethical, lazy, and witless.*";
P_HTM[5800]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5801]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[5802]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5803]="*Saddho hoti, sīlavā hoti, āraddhavīriyo hoti, paññavā hoti—**They’re faithful, ethical, energetic, and wise.*";
P_HTM[5804]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these four qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[5805]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5806]="*Parisasobhaṇavaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[5807]="*Parisā diṭṭhi akataññutā,* **";
P_HTM[5808]="*Pāṇātipātāpi dve maggā;* **";
P_HTM[5809]="*Dve vohārapathā vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[5810]="*Ahirikaṃ duppaññena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[5811]="*10. Dussīlasuttaṃ**Verbal Conduct*";
P_HTM[5812]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, vacīduccaritāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of bad conduct by way of speech.*";
P_HTM[5813]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5814]="*Musāvādo, pisuṇā vācā, pharusā vācā, samphappalāpo—**Speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical.*";
P_HTM[5815]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri vacīduccaritāni.**These are the four kinds of bad conduct by way of speech.*";
P_HTM[5816]="*Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, vacīsucaritāni.**There are these four kinds of good conduct by way of speech.*";
P_HTM[5817]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5818]="*Saccavācā, apisuṇā vācā, saṇhā vācā, mantavācā—**Speech that’s true, harmonious, gentle, and thoughtful.*";
P_HTM[5819]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri vacīsucaritānī”ti.**These are the four kinds of good conduct by way of speech.”*";
P_HTM[5820]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5821]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Bad Conduct*";
P_HTM[5822]="*1. Duccaritasuttaṃ**View*";
P_HTM[5823]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo viññūnaṃ; bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**“When a foolish, incompetent bad person has four qualities they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[5824]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5825]="*Kāyaduccaritena, vacīduccaritena, manoduccaritena, micchādiṭṭhiyā—**Bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5826]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**When a foolish, incompetent bad person has these four qualities they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[5827]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavati.**When an astute, competent good person has four qualities they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.*";
P_HTM[5828]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5829]="*Kāyasucaritena, vacīsucaritena, manosucaritena, sammādiṭṭhiyā—**Good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and right view.*";
P_HTM[5830]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo viññūnaṃ; bahuñca puññaṃ pasavatī”ti.**When an astute, competent good person has these four qualities they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.”*";
P_HTM[5831]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5832]="*2. Diṭṭhisuttaṃ**Ungrateful*";
P_HTM[5833]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**“When a foolish, incompetent bad person has four qualities they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[5834]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5835]="*Kāyaduccaritena, vacīduccaritena, manoduccaritena, akataññutā akataveditā—**Bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and being ungrateful and thankless.*";
P_HTM[5836]="*imehi … pe … kāyasucaritena, vacīsucaritena, manosucaritena kataññutākataveditā … pe ….**An astute person … makes much merit. … Good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and being grateful and thankful. …”*";
P_HTM[5837]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5838]="*3. Akataññutāsuttaṃ**Killing Living Creatures*";
P_HTM[5839]="*… pe … Pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti … pe … pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti … pe ….**“A foolish person … makes much bad karma. … They kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, and lie. … An astute person … makes much merit. … They don’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, or lie. …”*";
P_HTM[5840]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5841]="*4. Pāṇātipātīsuttaṃ**Path (1st)*";
P_HTM[5842]="*… pe … Micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, micchāsaṅkappo hoti, micchāvāco hoti, micchākammanto hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, sammāsaṅkappo hoti, sammāvāco hoti, sammākammanto hoti … pe ….**“A foolish person … makes much bad karma. … wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action. … An astute person … makes much merit. … right view, right thought, right speech, right action. …”*";
P_HTM[5843]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5844]="*5. Paṭhamamaggasuttaṃ**Path (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5845]="*… pe … Micchāājīvo hoti, micchāvāyāmo hoti, micchāsati hoti, micchāsamādhi hoti … pe … sammāājīvo hoti, sammāvāyāmo hoti, sammāsati hoti, sammāsamādhi hoti … pe ….**“A foolish person … makes much bad karma. … wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion. … An astute person … makes much merit. … right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. …”*";
P_HTM[5846]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5847]="*6. Dutiyamaggasuttaṃ**Kinds of Expression (1st)*";
P_HTM[5848]="*… pe … Adiṭṭhe diṭṭhavādī hoti, asute sutavādī hoti, amute mutavādī hoti, aviññāte viññātavādī hoti … pe … adiṭṭhe adiṭṭhavādī hoti, asute asutavādī hoti, amute amutavādī hoti, aviññāte aviññātavādī hoti … pe ….**“A foolish person … makes much bad karma. … They say they’ve seen, heard, thought, or known something, but they haven’t. … An astute person … makes much merit. … They say they haven’t seen, heard, thought, or known something, and they haven’t. …”*";
P_HTM[5849]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5850]="*7. Paṭhamavohārapathasuttaṃ**Kinds of Expression (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5851]="*… pe … Diṭṭhe adiṭṭhavādī hoti, sute asutavādī hoti, mute amutavādī hoti, viññāte aviññātavādī hoti … pe … diṭṭhe diṭṭhavādī hoti, sute sutavādī hoti, mute mutavādī hoti, viññāte viññātavādī hoti … pe ….**“A foolish person … makes much bad karma. … They say they haven’t seen, heard, thought, or known something, but they have. … An astute person … makes much merit. … They say they’ve seen, heard, thought, or known something, and they have. …”*";
P_HTM[5852]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5853]="*8. Dutiyavohārapathasuttaṃ**Imprudence*";
P_HTM[5854]="*… pe … Assaddho hoti, dussīlo hoti, ahiriko hoti, anottappī hoti … pe … saddho hoti, sīlavā hoti, hirimā hoti, ottappī hoti … pe ….**“A foolish person … makes much bad karma. … They’re faithless, unethical, shameless, and imprudent. … An astute person … makes much merit. … They’re faithful, ethical, conscientious, and prudent. …”*";
P_HTM[5855]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5856]="*9. Ahirikasuttaṃ**Witless*";
P_HTM[5857]="*… pe … Assaddho hoti, dussīlo hoti, kusīto hoti, duppañño hoti … pe … saddho hoti, sīlavā hoti, āraddhavīriyo hoti, paññavā hoti—**“A foolish person … makes much bad karma. … They’re faithless, unethical, lazy, and witless. … An astute person … makes much merit. … They’re faithful, ethical, energetic, and wise.*";
P_HTM[5858]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavatī”ti.**When an astute, competent good person has these four qualities they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.”*";
P_HTM[5859]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5860]="*10. Duppaññasuttaṃ**Poets*";
P_HTM[5861]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, kavī.**“Mendicants, there are these four poets.*";
P_HTM[5862]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5863]="*Cintākavi, sutakavi, atthakavi, paṭibhānakavi—**A poet who thoughtfully composes their own work, a poet who repeats the oral transmission, a poet who educates, and a poet who improvises.*";
P_HTM[5864]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro kavī”ti.**These are the four poets.”*";
P_HTM[5865]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5866]="*Duccaritavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[5867]="*Duccaritaṃ diṭṭhi akataññū ca,* **";
P_HTM[5868]="*Pāṇātipātāpi dve maggā;* **";
P_HTM[5869]="*Dve vohārapathā vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[5870]="*Ahirikaṃ duppaññakavinā cāti.* **";
P_HTM[5871]="*11. Kavisuttaṃ**Deeds In Brief*";
P_HTM[5872]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni.**“Mendicants, I declare these four kinds of deeds, having realized them with my own insight.*";
P_HTM[5873]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5874]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ;**There are dark deeds with dark results.*";
P_HTM[5875]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ;**There are bright deeds with bright results.*";
P_HTM[5876]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ;**There are dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results.*";
P_HTM[5877]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**There are neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[5878]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditānī”ti.**These are the four kinds of deeds that I declare, having realized them with my own insight.”*";
P_HTM[5879]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5880]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Deeds*";
P_HTM[5881]="*1. Saṃkhittasuttaṃ**Deeds in Detail*";
P_HTM[5882]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni.**“Mendicants, I declare these four kinds of deeds, having realized them with my own insight.*";
P_HTM[5883]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5884]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ;**There are dark deeds with dark results;*";
P_HTM[5885]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ;**bright deeds with bright results;*";
P_HTM[5886]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ;**dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results; and*";
P_HTM[5887]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[5888]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ?**And what are dark deeds with dark results?*";
P_HTM[5889]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti.**It’s when someone makes hurtful choices by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[5890]="*So sabyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā sabyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**Having made these choices, they’re reborn in a hurtful world,*";
P_HTM[5891]="*Tamenaṃ sabyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapannaṃ samānaṃ sabyābajjhā phassā phusanti.**where hurtful contacts touch them.*";
P_HTM[5892]="*So sabyābajjhehi phassehi phuṭṭho samāno sabyābajjhaṃ vedanaṃ vediyati ekantadukkhaṃ, seyyathāpi sattā nerayikā.**Touched by hurtful contacts, they experience hurtful feelings that are exclusively painful—like the beings in hell.*";
P_HTM[5893]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ.**These are called dark deeds with dark results.*";
P_HTM[5894]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ?**And what are bright deeds with bright results?*";
P_HTM[5895]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco abyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, abyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, abyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti.**It’s when someone makes pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[5896]="*So abyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, abyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, abyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā abyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**Having made these choices, they’re reborn in a pleasing world,*";
P_HTM[5897]="*Tamenaṃ abyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapannaṃ samānaṃ abyābajjhā phassā phusanti.**where pleasing contacts touch them.*";
P_HTM[5898]="*So abyābajjhehi phassehi phuṭṭho samāno abyābajjhaṃ vedanaṃ vediyati ekantasukhaṃ, seyyathāpi devā subhakiṇhā.**Touched by pleasing contacts, they experience pleasing feelings that are exclusively happy—like the gods replete with glory.*";
P_HTM[5899]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ.**These are called bright deeds with bright results.*";
P_HTM[5900]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ?**And what are dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results?*";
P_HTM[5901]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti.**It’s when someone makes both hurtful and pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[5902]="*So sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi lokaṃ upapajjati.**Having made these choices, they are reborn in a world that is both hurtful and pleasing,*";
P_HTM[5903]="*Tamenaṃ sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi lokaṃ upapannaṃ samānaṃ sabyābajjhāpi abyābajjhāpi phassā phusanti.**where hurtful and pleasing contacts touch them.*";
P_HTM[5904]="*So sabyābajjhehipi abyābajjhehipi phassehi phuṭṭho samāno sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi vedanaṃ vediyati vokiṇṇasukhadukkhaṃ, seyyathāpi manussā ekacce ca devā ekacce ca vinipātikā.**Touched by both hurtful and pleasing contacts, they experience both hurtful and pleasing feelings that are a mixture of pleasure and pain—like humans, some gods, and some beings in the underworld.*";
P_HTM[5905]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ.**These are called dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results.*";
P_HTM[5906]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati?**And what are neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds?*";
P_HTM[5907]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ tassa pahānāya yā cetanā, yamidaṃ kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ tassa pahānāya yā cetanā, yamidaṃ kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ tassa pahānāya yā cetanā—**It’s the intention to give up dark deeds with dark results, bright deeds with bright results, and both dark and bright deeds with both dark and bright results.*";
P_HTM[5908]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**These are called neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[5909]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditānī”ti.**These are the four kinds of deeds that I declare, having realized them with my own insight.”*";
P_HTM[5910]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5911]="*2. Vitthārasuttaṃ**About Soṇakāyana*";
P_HTM[5912]="*Atha kho sikhāmoggallāno brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Sikhāmoggallāna the brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[5913]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho sikhāmoggallāno brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Sikhāmoggallāna sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[5914]="*“Purimāni, bho gotama, divasāni purimatarāni soṇakāyano māṇavo yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ etadavoca:**“Master Gotama, a few days ago the student Soṇakāyana came to me and said:*";
P_HTM[5915]="*‘samaṇo gotamo sabbakammānaṃ akiriyaṃ paññapeti, sabbakammānaṃ kho pana akiriyaṃ paññapento ucchedaṃ āha lokassa’—**‘The ascetic Gotama advocates not doing any deeds. So he teaches the annihilation of the world!’*";
P_HTM[5916]="*kammasaccāyaṃ, bho, loko kammasamārambhaṭṭhāyī”ti.**The world exists through deeds, and it remains because deeds are undertaken.”*";
P_HTM[5917]="*“Dassanampi kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, soṇakāyanassa māṇavassa nābhijānāmi;**“Brahmin, I can’t recall even seeing the student Soṇakāyana,*";
P_HTM[5918]="*kuto panevarūpo kathāsallāpo.**so how could we possibly have had such a discussion?*";
P_HTM[5919]="*Cattārimāni, brāhmaṇa, kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni.**I declare these four kinds of deeds, having realized them with my own insight.*";
P_HTM[5920]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5921]="*Atthi, brāhmaṇa, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ;**There are dark deeds with dark results;*";
P_HTM[5922]="*atthi, brāhmaṇa, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ;**bright deeds with bright results;*";
P_HTM[5923]="*atthi, brāhmaṇa, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ;**dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results; and*";
P_HTM[5924]="*atthi, brāhmaṇa, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[5925]="*Katamañca, brāhmaṇa, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ?**And what are the dark deeds with dark results?*";
P_HTM[5926]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco sabyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti.**It’s when someone makes hurtful choices by way of body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[5927]="*So sabyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā sabyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5928]="*Tamenaṃ sabyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapannaṃ samānaṃ sabyābajjhā phassā phusanti.* **";
P_HTM[5929]="*So sabyābajjhehi phassehi phuṭṭho samāno sabyābajjhaṃ vedanaṃ vediyati ekantadukkhaṃ, seyyathāpi sattā nerayikā.**Touched by hurtful contacts, they experience hurtful feelings that are exclusively painful—like the beings in hell.*";
P_HTM[5930]="*Idaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ.**These are called dark deeds with dark results.*";
P_HTM[5931]="*Katamañca, brāhmaṇa, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ?**And what are bright deeds with bright results?*";
P_HTM[5932]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco abyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, abyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, abyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti.**It’s when someone makes pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[5933]="*So abyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, abyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, abyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā abyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5934]="*Tamenaṃ abyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapannaṃ samānaṃ abyābajjhā phassā phusanti.* **";
P_HTM[5935]="*So abyābajjhehi phassehi phuṭṭho samāno abyābajjhaṃ vedanaṃ vediyati ekantasukhaṃ, seyyathāpi devā subhakiṇhā.**Touched by pleasing contacts, they experience pleasing feelings that are exclusively happy—like the gods replete with glory.*";
P_HTM[5936]="*Idaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ.**These are called bright deeds with bright results.*";
P_HTM[5937]="*Katamañca, brāhmaṇa, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ?**And what are dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results?*";
P_HTM[5938]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti.**It’s when someone makes both hurtful and pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[5939]="*So sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi lokaṃ upapajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5940]="*Tamenaṃ sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi lokaṃ upapannaṃ samānaṃ sabyābajjhāpi abyābajjhāpi phassā phusanti.* **";
P_HTM[5941]="*So sabyābajjhehipi abyābajjhehipi phassehi phuṭṭho samāno sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi vedanaṃ vediyati vokiṇṇasukhadukkhaṃ, seyyathāpi manussā ekacce ca devā ekacce ca vinipātikā.**Touched by both hurtful and pleasing contacts, they experience both hurtful and pleasing feelings that are a mixture of pleasure and pain—like humans, some gods, and some beings in the underworld.*";
P_HTM[5942]="*Idaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ.**These are called dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results.*";
P_HTM[5943]="*Katamañca, brāhmaṇa, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati?**And what are neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds?*";
P_HTM[5944]="*Tatra, brāhmaṇa, yamidaṃ kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ tassa pahānāya yā cetanā, yamidaṃ kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ tassa pahānāya yā cetanā, yamidaṃ kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ tassa pahānāya yā cetanā—**It’s the intention to give up dark deeds with dark results, bright deeds with bright results, and both dark and bright deeds with both dark and bright results.*";
P_HTM[5945]="*idaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**These are called neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[5946]="*Imāni kho, brāhmaṇa, cattāri kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditānī”ti.**These are the four kinds of deeds that I declare, having realized them with my own insight.”*";
P_HTM[5947]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5948]="*3. Soṇakāyanasuttaṃ**Training Rules (1st)*";
P_HTM[5949]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni.**“Mendicants, I declare these four kinds of deeds, having realized them with my own insight.*";
P_HTM[5950]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5951]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ;**There are dark deeds with dark results;*";
P_HTM[5952]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ;**bright deeds with bright results;*";
P_HTM[5953]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ;**dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results; and*";
P_HTM[5954]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[5955]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ?**And what are the dark deeds with dark results?*";
P_HTM[5956]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyī hoti.**It’s when someone kills living creatures, steals, commits sexual misconduct, lies, and uses alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[5957]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ.**These are called dark deeds with dark results.*";
P_HTM[5958]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ?**And what are bright deeds with bright results?*";
P_HTM[5959]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti.**It’s when someone doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[5960]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ.**These are called bright deeds with bright results.*";
P_HTM[5961]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ?**And what are dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results?*";
P_HTM[5962]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti … pe … idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ.**It’s when someone makes both hurtful and pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind. These are called dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results.*";
P_HTM[5963]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati?**And what are neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds?*";
P_HTM[5964]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ … pe … idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**It’s the intention to give up dark deeds with dark results, bright deeds with bright results, and both dark and bright deeds with both dark and bright results. These are called neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[5965]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditānī”ti.**These are the four kinds of deeds that I declare, having realized them with my own insight.”*";
P_HTM[5966]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5967]="*4. Paṭhamasikkhāpadasuttaṃ**Training Rules (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5968]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni.**“Mendicants, I declare these four kinds of deeds, having realized them with my own insight.*";
P_HTM[5969]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5970]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ;**There are dark deeds with dark results;*";
P_HTM[5971]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ;**bright deeds with bright results;*";
P_HTM[5972]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ;**dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results; and*";
P_HTM[5973]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[5974]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ?**And what are dark deeds with dark results?*";
P_HTM[5975]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccena mātā jīvitā voropitā hoti, pitā jīvitā voropito hoti, arahaṃ jīvitā voropito hoti, tathāgatassa duṭṭhena cittena lohitaṃ uppāditaṃ hoti, saṃgho bhinno hoti.**It's when someone murders their mother or father or a perfected one. They maliciously shed the blood of a Realized One. Or they cause a schism in the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[5976]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ.**These are called dark deeds with dark results.*";
P_HTM[5977]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ?**And what are bright deeds with bright results?*";
P_HTM[5978]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, anabhijjhālu hoti, abyāpannacitto hoti, sammādiṭṭhi hoti.**It’s when someone doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re content, kind-hearted, with right view.*";
P_HTM[5979]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ.**These are called bright deeds with bright results.*";
P_HTM[5980]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ?**And what are dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results?*";
P_HTM[5981]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti … pe … idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ.**It’s when someone makes both hurtful and pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind. These are called dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results.*";
P_HTM[5982]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati?**And what are neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds?*";
P_HTM[5983]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ … pe … idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**It’s the intention to give up dark deeds with dark results, bright deeds with bright results, and both dark and bright deeds with both dark and bright results. These are called neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[5984]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditānī”ti.**These are the four kinds of deeds that I declare, having realized them with my own insight.”*";
P_HTM[5985]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5986]="*5. Dutiyasikkhāpadasuttaṃ**The Noble Path*";
P_HTM[5987]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni.**“Mendicants, I declare these four kinds of deeds, having realized them with my own insight.*";
P_HTM[5988]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5989]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ;**There are dark deeds with dark results;*";
P_HTM[5990]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ;**bright deeds with bright results;*";
P_HTM[5991]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ;**dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results; and*";
P_HTM[5992]="*atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[5993]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ?**And what are dark deeds with dark results?*";
P_HTM[5994]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti … pe … idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ.**It’s when someone makes hurtful choices by way of body, speech, and mind. These are called dark deeds with dark results.*";
P_HTM[5995]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ?**And what are bright deeds with bright results?*";
P_HTM[5996]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco abyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti … pe … idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ.**It’s when someone makes pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind. These are called bright deeds with bright results.*";
P_HTM[5997]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ?**And what are dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results?*";
P_HTM[5998]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti … pe … idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ.**It’s when someone makes both hurtful and pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind. These are called dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results.*";
P_HTM[5999]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati?**And what are neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds?*";
P_HTM[6000]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[6001]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**These are called neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[6002]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditānī”ti.**These are the four kinds of deeds that I declare, having realized them with my own insight.”*";
P_HTM[6003]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6004]="*6. Ariyamaggasuttaṃ**Awakening Factors*";
P_HTM[6005]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, kammāni … pe … kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ … pe …**“Mendicants, I declare these four kinds of deeds, having realized them with my own insight....*";
P_HTM[6006]="*idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti … pe … idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ.**And what are dark deeds with dark results? It’s when someone makes hurtful choices by way of body, speech, and mind. These are called dark deeds with dark results.*";
P_HTM[6007]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ?**And what are bright deeds with bright results?*";
P_HTM[6008]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco abyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti … pe … idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ.**It’s when someone makes pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind. These are called bright deeds with bright results.*";
P_HTM[6009]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ?**And what are dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results?*";
P_HTM[6010]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti … pe … idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ.**It’s when someone makes both hurtful and pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind. These are called dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results.*";
P_HTM[6011]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati?**And what are neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds?*";
P_HTM[6012]="*Satisambojjhaṅgo, dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo, vīriyasambojjhaṅgo, pītisambojjhaṅgo, passaddhisambojjhaṅgo, samādhisambojjhaṅgo, upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo—**The awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity.*";
P_HTM[6013]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**These are called neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[6014]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditānī”ti.**These are the four kinds of deeds that I declare, having realized them with my own insight.”*";
P_HTM[6015]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6016]="*7. Bojjhaṅgasuttaṃ**Blameworthy*";
P_HTM[6017]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6018]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6019]="*Sāvajjena kāyakammena, sāvajjena vacīkammena, sāvajjena manokammena, sāvajjāya diṭṭhiyā—**Blameworthy deeds by way of body, speech, and mind, and blameworthy view.*";
P_HTM[6020]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6021]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[6022]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6023]="*Anavajjena kāyakammena, anavajjena vacīkammena, anavajjena manokammena, anavajjāya diṭṭhiyā—**Blameless deeds by way of body, speech, and mind, and blameless view.*";
P_HTM[6024]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these four qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[6025]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6026]="*8. Sāvajjasuttaṃ**Pleasing*";
P_HTM[6027]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6028]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6029]="*Sabyābajjhena kāyakammena, sabyābajjhena vacīkammena, sabyābajjhena manokammena, sabyābajjhāya diṭṭhiyā—**Hurtful deeds by way of body, speech, and mind, and hurtful view.*";
P_HTM[6030]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6031]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[6032]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6033]="*Abyābajjhena kāyakammena, abyābajjhena vacīkammena, abyābajjhena manokammena, abyābajjhāya diṭṭhiyā—**Pleasing deeds by way of body, speech, and mind, and pleasing view.*";
P_HTM[6034]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these four qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[6035]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6036]="*9. Abyābajjhasuttaṃ**Ascetics*";
P_HTM[6037]="*“‘Idheva, bhikkhave, paṭhamo samaṇo, idha dutiyo samaṇo, idha tatiyo samaṇo, idha catuttho samaṇo;**“‘Only here is there a true ascetic, here a second ascetic, here a third ascetic, and here a fourth ascetic.*";
P_HTM[6038]="*suññā parappavādā samaṇehi aññehī’ti—**Other sects are empty of ascetics.’*";
P_HTM[6039]="*evametaṃ, bhikkhave, sammā sīhanādaṃ nadatha.**This, mendicants, is how you should rightly roar your lion’s roar.*";
P_HTM[6040]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, paṭhamo samaṇo?**And who is the first ascetic?*";
P_HTM[6041]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo.**It’s a mendicant who—with the ending of three fetters—is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[6042]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo samaṇo.**This is the first ascetic.*";
P_HTM[6043]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dutiyo samaṇo?**And who is the second ascetic?*";
P_HTM[6044]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmī hoti, sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karoti.**It’s a mendicant who—with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion—is a once-returner. They come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering.*";
P_HTM[6045]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo samaṇo.**This is the second ascetic.*";
P_HTM[6046]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, tatiyo samaṇo?**And who is the third ascetic?*";
P_HTM[6047]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko hoti tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā.**It’s a mendicant who—with the ending of the five lower fetters—is reborn spontaneously. They’re extinguished there, and are not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[6048]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo samaṇo.**This is the third ascetic.*";
P_HTM[6049]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, catuttho samaṇo?**And who is the fourth ascetic?*";
P_HTM[6050]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**It’s a mendicant who realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[6051]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho samaṇo.**This is the fourth ascetic.*";
P_HTM[6052]="*‘Idheva, bhikkhave, paṭhamo samaṇo, idha dutiyo samaṇo, idha tatiyo samaṇo, idha catuttho samaṇo;**‘Only here is there a true ascetic, here a second ascetic, here a third ascetic, and here a fourth ascetic.*";
P_HTM[6053]="*suññā parappavādā samaṇebhi aññehī’ti—**Other sects are empty of ascetics.’*";
P_HTM[6054]="*evametaṃ, bhikkhave, sammā sīhanādaṃ nadathā”ti.**This, mendicants, is how you should rightly roar your lion’s roar.”*";
P_HTM[6055]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6056]="*10. Samaṇasuttaṃ**Benefits of a Good Person*";
P_HTM[6057]="*“Sappurisaṃ, bhikkhave, nissāya cattāro ānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā.**“Mendicants, you can expect four benefits from relying on a good person.*";
P_HTM[6058]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6059]="*Ariyena sīlena vaḍḍhati, ariyena samādhinā vaḍḍhati, ariyāya paññāya vaḍḍhati, ariyāya vimuttiyā vaḍḍhati—**Growth in noble ethics, immersion, wisdom, and freedom.*";
P_HTM[6060]="*sappurisaṃ, bhikkhave, nissāya ime cattāro ānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā”ti.**You can expect these four benefits from relying on a good person.”*";
P_HTM[6061]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6062]="*Kammavaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[6063]="*Saṅkhitta vitthāra soṇakāyana,* **";
P_HTM[6064]="*Sikkhāpadaṃ ariyamaggo bojjhaṅgaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6065]="*Sāvajjañceva abyābajjhaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[6066]="*Samaṇo ca sappurisānisaṃsoti.* **";
P_HTM[6067]="*11. Sappurisānisaṃsasuttaṃ**Schism in the Saṅgha*";
P_HTM[6068]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[6069]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[6070]="*“api nu taṃ, ānanda, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantan”ti?**“Well, Ānanda, has that disciplinary issue been settled yet?”*";
P_HTM[6071]="*“Kuto taṃ, bhante, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamissati.**“How could it be, sir?*";
P_HTM[6072]="*Āyasmato, bhante, anuruddhassa bāhiyo nāma saddhivihāriko kevalakappaṃ saṃghabhedāya ṭhito.**Venerable Anuruddha’s pupil Bāhiya remains entirely committed to creating a schism in the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[6073]="*Tatrāyasmā anuruddho na ekavācikampi bhaṇitabbaṃ maññatī”ti.**But Anuruddha doesn’t think to say a single word about it.”*";
P_HTM[6074]="*“Kadā panānanda, anuruddho saṃghamajjhe adhikaraṇesu voyuñjati.**“But Ānanda, since when has Anuruddha been involved in disciplinary issues in the midst of the Saṅgha?*";
P_HTM[6075]="*Nanu, ānanda, yāni kānici adhikaraṇāni uppajjanti, sabbāni tāni tumhe ceva vūpasametha sāriputtamoggallānā ca.**Shouldn’t you, together with Sāriputta and Moggallāna, settle all disciplinary issues that come up?*";
P_HTM[6076]="*Cattārome, ānanda, atthavase sampassamāno pāpabhikkhu saṅghabhedena nandati.**A bad monk sees four reasons to relish schism in the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[6077]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6078]="*Idhānanda, pāpabhikkhu dussīlo hoti pāpadhammo asuci saṅkassarasamācāro paṭicchannakammanto assamaṇo samaṇapaṭiñño abrahmacārī brahmacāripaṭiñño antopūti avassuto kasambujāto.**Take an unethical monk, of bad qualities, filthy, with suspicious behavior, underhand, no true ascetic or spiritual practitioner—though claiming to be one—rotten inside, corrupt, and depraved.*";
P_HTM[6079]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**He thinks:*";
P_HTM[6080]="*‘sace kho maṃ bhikkhū jānissanti—**‘Suppose the monks know that I’m a bad monk …*";
P_HTM[6081]="*dussīlo pāpadhammo asuci saṅkassarasamācāro paṭicchannakammanto assamaṇo samaṇapaṭiñño abrahmacārī brahmacāripaṭiñño antopūti avassuto kasambujātoti, samaggā maṃ santā nāsessanti;**If they’re in harmony, they’ll expel me,*";
P_HTM[6082]="*vaggā pana maṃ na nāsessantī’ti.**but if they’re divided they won’t.’*";
P_HTM[6083]="*Idaṃ, ānanda, paṭhamaṃ atthavasaṃ sampassamāno pāpabhikkhu saṅghabhedena nandati.**A bad monk sees this as the first reason to relish schism in the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[6084]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, pāpabhikkhu micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, antaggāhikāya diṭṭhiyā samannāgato.**Furthermore, a bad monk has wrong view, he’s attached to an extremist view.*";
P_HTM[6085]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**He thinks:*";
P_HTM[6086]="*‘sace kho maṃ bhikkhū jānissanti—**‘Suppose the monks know that I have wrong view …*";
P_HTM[6087]="*micchādiṭṭhiko antaggāhikāya diṭṭhiyā samannāgatoti, samaggā maṃ santā nāsessanti;**If they’re in harmony they’ll expel me,*";
P_HTM[6088]="*vaggā pana maṃ na nāsessantī’ti.**but if they’re divided they won’t.’*";
P_HTM[6089]="*Idaṃ, ānanda, dutiyaṃ atthavasaṃ sampassamāno pāpabhikkhu saṅghabhedena nandati.**A bad monk sees this as the second reason to relish schism in the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[6090]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, pāpabhikkhu micchāājīvo hoti, micchāājīvena jīvikaṃ kappeti.**Furthermore, a bad monk has wrong livelihood and earns a living by wrong livelihood.*";
P_HTM[6091]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**He thinks:*";
P_HTM[6092]="*‘sace kho maṃ bhikkhū jānissanti—**‘Suppose the monks know that I have wrong livelihood …*";
P_HTM[6093]="*micchāājīvo micchāājīvena jīvikaṃ kappetīti, samaggā maṃ santā nāsessanti;**If they’re in harmony they’ll expel me,*";
P_HTM[6094]="*vaggā pana maṃ na nāsessantī’ti.**but if they’re divided they won’t.’*";
P_HTM[6095]="*Idaṃ, ānanda, tatiyaṃ atthavasaṃ sampassamāno pāpabhikkhu saṃghabhedena nandati.**A bad monk sees this as the third reason to relish schism in the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[6096]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, pāpabhikkhu lābhakāmo hoti sakkārakāmo anavaññattikāmo.**Furthermore, a bad monk desires material possessions, honor, and admiration.*";
P_HTM[6097]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**He thinks:*";
P_HTM[6098]="*‘sace kho maṃ bhikkhū jānissanti—**‘Suppose the monks know that I desire material possessions, honor, and admiration.*";
P_HTM[6099]="*lābhakāmo sakkārakāmo anavaññattikāmoti, samaggā maṃ santā na sakkarissanti na garuṃ karissanti na mānessanti na pūjessanti;**If they’re in harmony they won’t honor, respect, revere, or venerate me,*";
P_HTM[6100]="*vaggā pana maṃ sakkarissanti garuṃ karissanti mānessanti pūjessantī’ti.**but if they’re divided they will.’*";
P_HTM[6101]="*Idaṃ, ānanda, catutthaṃ atthavasaṃ sampassamāno pāpabhikkhu saṅghabhedena nandati.**A bad monk sees this as the fourth reason to relish schism in the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[6102]="*Ime kho, ānanda, cattāro atthavase sampassamāno pāpabhikkhu saṅghabhedena nandatī”ti.**A bad monk sees these four reasons to relish schism in the Saṅgha.”*";
P_HTM[6103]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6104]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Perils of Offenses*";
P_HTM[6105]="*1. Saṅghabhedakasuttaṃ**Perils of Offenses*";
P_HTM[6106]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, āpattibhayāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four perils of offenses.*";
P_HTM[6107]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6108]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, coraṃ āgucāriṃ gahetvā rañño dasseyyuṃ:**Suppose they were to arrest a bandit, a criminal and present him to the king, saying:*";
P_HTM[6109]="*‘ayaṃ te, deva, coro āgucārī.**‘Your Majesty, this is a bandit, a criminal.*";
P_HTM[6110]="*Imassa devo daṇḍaṃ paṇetū’ti.**May Your Majesty punish them!’*";
P_HTM[6111]="*Tamenaṃ rājā evaṃ vadeyya:**The king would say:*";
P_HTM[6112]="*‘gacchatha, bho, imaṃ purisaṃ daḷhāya rajjuyā pacchābāhaṃ gāḷhabandhanaṃ bandhitvā khuramuṇḍaṃ karitvā kharassarena paṇavena rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ parinetvā dakkhiṇena dvārena nikkhāmetvā dakkhiṇato nagarassa sīsaṃ chindathā’ti.**‘Go, my men, and tie this man’s arms tightly behind his back with a strong rope. Shave his head and march him from street to street and square to square to the beating of a harsh drum. Then take him out the south gate and there, to the south of the city, chop off his head.’*";
P_HTM[6113]="*Tamenaṃ rañño purisā daḷhāya rajjuyā pacchābāhaṃ gāḷhabandhanaṃ bandhitvā khuramuṇḍaṃ karitvā kharassarena paṇavena rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ parinetvā dakkhiṇena dvārena nikkhāmetvā dakkhiṇato nagarassa sīsaṃ chindeyyuṃ.**The king’s men would do as they were told.*";
P_HTM[6114]="*Tatraññatarassa thalaṭṭhassa purisassa evamassa:**Then a bystander might think:*";
P_HTM[6115]="*‘pāpakaṃ vata, bho, ayaṃ puriso kammaṃ akāsi gārayhaṃ sīsacchejjaṃ.**‘This man must have done a truly bad and reprehensible deed, a capital offense.*";
P_HTM[6116]="*Yatra hi nāma rañño purisā daḷhāya rajjuyā pacchābāhaṃ gāḷhabandhanaṃ bandhitvā khuramuṇḍaṃ karitvā kharassarena paṇavena rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ parinetvā dakkhiṇena dvārena nikkhāmetvā dakkhiṇato nagarassa sīsaṃ chindissanti.* **";
P_HTM[6117]="*So vatassāhaṃ evarūpaṃ pāpakammaṃ na kareyyaṃ gārayhaṃ sīsacchejjan’ti.**There’s no way I’d ever do such a bad and reprehensible deed, a capital offense.’*";
P_HTM[6118]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yassa kassaci bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā evaṃ tibbā bhayasaññā paccupaṭṭhitā hoti pārājikesu dhammesu.**In the same way, take any monk or nun who has set up such an acute perception of peril regarding expulsion offenses.*";
P_HTM[6119]="*Tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—anāpanno vā pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ na āpajjissati, āpanno vā pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ yathādhammaṃ paṭikarissati.**It can be expected that if they haven’t committed an expulsion offense they won’t, and if they committed one they will deal with it properly.*";
P_HTM[6120]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso kāḷavatthaṃ paridhāya kese pakiritvā musalaṃ khandhe āropetvā mahājanakāyaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya:**Suppose a man was to put on a black cloth, mess up his hair, and put a club on his shoulder. Then he approaches a large crowd and says:*";
P_HTM[6121]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, pāpakammaṃ akāsiṃ gārayhaṃ mosallaṃ, yena me āyasmanto attamanā honti taṃ karomī’ti.**‘Sirs, I’ve done a bad and reprehensible deed, deserving of clubbing. I submit to your pleasure.’*";
P_HTM[6122]="*Tatraññatarassa thalaṭṭhassa purisassa evamassa:**Then a bystander might think:*";
P_HTM[6123]="*‘pāpakaṃ vata, bho, ayaṃ puriso kammaṃ akāsi gārayhaṃ mosallaṃ.**‘This man must have done a truly bad and reprehensible deed, deserving of clubbing. …*";
P_HTM[6124]="*Yatra hi nāma kāḷavatthaṃ paridhāya kese pakiritvā musalaṃ khandhe āropetvā mahājanakāyaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vakkhati:* **";
P_HTM[6125]="*“ahaṃ, bhante, pāpakammaṃ akāsiṃ gārayhaṃ mosallaṃ, yena me āyasmanto attamanā honti taṃ karomī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6126]="*So vatassāhaṃ evarūpaṃ pāpakammaṃ na kareyyaṃ gārayhaṃ mosallan’ti.**There’s no way I’d ever do such a bad and reprehensible deed, deserving of clubbing.’*";
P_HTM[6127]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yassa kassaci bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā evaṃ tibbā bhayasaññā paccupaṭṭhitā hoti saṃghādisesesu dhammesu, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—anāpanno vā saṃghādisesaṃ dhammaṃ na āpajjissati, āpanno vā saṃghādisesaṃ dhammaṃ yathādhammaṃ paṭikarissati.**In the same way, take any monk or nun who has set up such an acute perception of peril regarding suspension offenses. It can be expected that if they haven’t committed a suspension offense they won’t, and if they committed one they will deal with it properly.*";
P_HTM[6128]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso kāḷavatthaṃ paridhāya kese pakiritvā bhasmapuṭaṃ khandhe āropetvā mahājanakāyaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya:**Suppose a man was to put on a black cloth, mess up his hair, and put a sack of ashes on his shoulder. Then he approaches a large crowd and says:*";
P_HTM[6129]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, pāpakammaṃ akāsiṃ gārayhaṃ bhasmapuṭaṃ.**‘Sirs, I’ve done a bad and reprehensible deed, deserving of a sack of ashes.*";
P_HTM[6130]="*Yena me āyasmanto attamanā honti taṃ karomī’ti.**I submit to your pleasure.’*";
P_HTM[6131]="*Tatraññatarassa thalaṭṭhassa purisassa evamassa:**Then a bystander might think:*";
P_HTM[6132]="*‘pāpakaṃ vata, bho, ayaṃ puriso kammaṃ akāsi gārayhaṃ bhasmapuṭaṃ.**‘This man must have done a truly bad and reprehensible deed, deserving of a sack of ashes. …*";
P_HTM[6133]="*Yatra hi nāma kāḷavatthaṃ paridhāya kese pakiritvā bhasmapuṭaṃ khandhe āropetvā mahājanakāyaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vakkhati:* **";
P_HTM[6134]="*“ahaṃ, bhante, pāpakammaṃ akāsiṃ gārayhaṃ bhasmapuṭaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6135]="*yena me āyasmanto attamanā honti taṃ karomī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6136]="*So vatassāhaṃ evarūpaṃ pāpakammaṃ na kareyyaṃ gārayhaṃ bhasmapuṭan’ti.**There’s no way I’d ever do such a bad and reprehensible deed, deserving of a sack of ashes.’*";
P_HTM[6137]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yassa kassaci bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā evaṃ tibbā bhayasaññā paccupaṭṭhitā hoti pācittiyesu dhammesu, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—anāpanno vā pācittiyaṃ dhammaṃ na āpajjissati, āpanno vā pācittiyaṃ dhammaṃ yathādhammaṃ paṭikarissati.**In the same way, take any monk or nun who has set up such an acute perception of peril regarding confessable offenses. It can be expected that if they haven’t committed a confessable offense they won’t, and if they committed one they will deal with it properly.*";
P_HTM[6138]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso kāḷavatthaṃ paridhāya kese pakiritvā mahājanakāyaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya:**Suppose a man was to put on a black cloth and mess up his hair. Then he approaches a large crowd and says:*";
P_HTM[6139]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, pāpakammaṃ akāsiṃ gārayhaṃ upavajjaṃ.**‘Sirs, I’ve done a bad and reprehensible deed, deserving of criticism.*";
P_HTM[6140]="*Yena me āyasmanto attamanā honti taṃ karomī’ti.**I submit to your pleasure.’*";
P_HTM[6141]="*Tatraññatarassa thalaṭṭhassa purisassa evamassa:**Then a bystander might think:*";
P_HTM[6142]="*‘pāpakaṃ vata, bho, ayaṃ puriso kammaṃ akāsi gārayhaṃ upavajjaṃ.**‘This man must have done a truly bad and reprehensible deed, deserving of criticism. …*";
P_HTM[6143]="*Yatra hi nāma kāḷavatthaṃ paridhāya kese pakiritvā mahājanakāyaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vakkhati:* **";
P_HTM[6144]="*“ahaṃ, bhante, pāpakammaṃ akāsiṃ gārayhaṃ upavajjaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6145]="*yena me āyasmanto attamanā honti taṃ karomī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6146]="*So vatassāhaṃ evarūpaṃ pāpakammaṃ na kareyyaṃ gārayhaṃ upavajjan’ti.**There’s no way I’d ever do such a bad and reprehensible deed, deserving of criticism.’*";
P_HTM[6147]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yassa kassaci bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā evaṃ tibbā bhayasaññā paccupaṭṭhitā hoti pāṭidesanīyesu dhammesu, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—anāpanno vā pāṭidesanīyaṃ dhammaṃ na āpajjissati, āpanno vā pāṭidesanīyaṃ dhammaṃ yathādhammaṃ paṭikarissati.**In the same way, take any monk or nun who has set up such an acute perception of peril regarding acknowledgable offenses. It can be expected that if they haven’t committed an acknowledgeable offense they won’t, and if they committed one they will deal with it properly.*";
P_HTM[6148]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri āpattibhayānī”ti.**These are the four perils of offenses.”*";
P_HTM[6149]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6150]="*2. Āpattibhayasuttaṃ**The Benefits of Training*";
P_HTM[6151]="*“Sikkhānisaṃsamidaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmacariyaṃ vussati paññuttaraṃ vimuttisāraṃ satādhipateyyaṃ.**“Mendicants, living this spiritual life is benefited by training and overseen by wisdom; freedom is its heart, and mindfulness is in charge.*";
P_HTM[6152]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, sikkhānisaṃsaṃ hoti?**And how is it benefited by training?*";
P_HTM[6153]="*Idha, bhikkhave, mayā sāvakānaṃ ābhisamācārikā sikkhā paññattā appasannānaṃ pasādāya pasannānaṃ bhiyyobhāvāya.**Firstly, I laid down for my disciples the training that deals with supplementary regulations in order to inspire confidence in those without it and to increase confidence in those who have it.*";
P_HTM[6154]="*Yathā yathā, bhikkhave, mayā sāvakānaṃ ābhisamācārikā sikkhā paññattā appasannānaṃ pasādāya pasannānaṃ bhiyyobhāvāya tathā tathā so tassā sikkhāya akhaṇḍakārī hoti acchiddakārī asabalakārī akammāsakārī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu.**They undertake whatever supplementary regulations I have laid down, keeping them unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred.*";
P_HTM[6155]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, mayā sāvakānaṃ ādibrahmacariyikā sikkhā paññattā sabbaso sammā dukkhakkhayāya.**Furthermore, I laid down for my disciples the training that deals with the fundamentals of the spiritual life in order to rightly end suffering in every way.*";
P_HTM[6156]="*Yathā yathā, bhikkhave, mayā sāvakānaṃ ādibrahmacariyikā sikkhā paññattā sabbaso sammā dukkhakkhayāya tathā tathā so tassā sikkhāya akhaṇḍakārī hoti acchiddakārī asabalakārī akammāsakārī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu.**They undertake whatever training that deals with the fundamentals of the spiritual life I have laid down, keeping it unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred.*";
P_HTM[6157]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sikkhānisaṃsaṃ hoti.**That’s how it’s benefited by training.*";
P_HTM[6158]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, paññuttaraṃ hoti?**And how is it overseen by wisdom?*";
P_HTM[6159]="*Idha, bhikkhave, mayā sāvakānaṃ dhammā desitā sabbaso sammā dukkhakkhayāya.**I taught the Dhamma to my disciples in order to rightly end suffering in every way.*";
P_HTM[6160]="*Yathā yathā, bhikkhave, mayā sāvakānaṃ dhammā desitā sabbaso sammā dukkhakkhayāya tathā tathāssa te dhammā paññāya samavekkhitā honti.**They examine with wisdom any teachings I taught them.*";
P_HTM[6161]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, paññuttaraṃ hoti.**That’s how it’s overseen by wisdom.*";
P_HTM[6162]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, vimuttisāraṃ hoti?**And how does it have freedom at its heart?*";
P_HTM[6163]="*Idha, bhikkhave, mayā sāvakānaṃ dhammā desitā sabbaso sammā dukkhakkhayāya.**I taught the Dhamma to my disciples in order to rightly end suffering in every way.*";
P_HTM[6164]="*Yathā yathā, bhikkhave, mayā sāvakānaṃ dhammā desitā sabbaso sammā dukkhakkhayāya tathā tathāssa te dhammā vimuttiyā phusitā honti.**They experience through freedom any teachings I taught them.*";
P_HTM[6165]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, vimuttisāraṃ hoti.**That’s how it has freedom at its heart.*";
P_HTM[6166]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, satādhipateyyaṃ hoti?**And how is mindfulness in charge?*";
P_HTM[6167]="*‘Iti aparipūraṃ vā ābhisamācārikaṃ sikkhaṃ paripūressāmi, paripūraṃ vā ābhisamācārikaṃ sikkhaṃ tattha tattha paññāya anuggahessāmī’ti—ajjhattaṃyeva sati sūpaṭṭhitā hoti.**Mindfulness is well established in oneself: ‘In this way I’ll fulfill the training dealing with supplementary regulations, or support with wisdom in every situation the training dealing with supplementary regulations I’ve already fulfilled.’*";
P_HTM[6168]="*‘Iti aparipūraṃ vā ādibrahmacariyikaṃ sikkhaṃ paripūressāmi, paripūraṃ vā ādibrahmacariyikaṃ sikkhaṃ tattha tattha paññāya anuggahessāmī’ti—ajjhattaṃyeva sati sūpaṭṭhitā hoti.**Mindfulness is well established in oneself: ‘In this way I’ll fulfill the training dealing with the fundamentals of the spiritual life, or support with wisdom in every situation the training dealing with the fundamentals of the spiritual life I’ve already fulfilled.’*";
P_HTM[6169]="*‘Iti asamavekkhitaṃ vā dhammaṃ paññāya samavekkhissāmi, samavekkhitaṃ vā dhammaṃ tattha tattha paññāya anuggahessāmī’ti—ajjhattaṃyeva sati sūpaṭṭhitā hoti.**Mindfulness is well established in oneself: ‘In this way I’ll examine with wisdom the teaching that I haven’t yet examined, or support with wisdom in every situation the teaching I’ve already examined.’*";
P_HTM[6170]="*‘Iti aphusitaṃ vā dhammaṃ vimuttiyā phusissāmi, phusitaṃ vā dhammaṃ tattha tattha paññāya anuggahessāmī’ti—ajjhattaṃyeva sati sūpaṭṭhitā hoti.**Mindfulness is well established in oneself: ‘In this way I’ll experience through freedom the teaching that I haven’t yet experienced, or support with wisdom in every situation the teaching I’ve already experienced.’*";
P_HTM[6171]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, satādhipateyyaṃ hoti.**That’s how mindfulness is in charge.*";
P_HTM[6172]="*‘Sikkhānisaṃsamidaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmacariyaṃ vussati paññuttaraṃ vimuttisāraṃ satādhipateyyan’ti,**‘Living this spiritual life is benefited by training and overseen by wisdom; freedom is its heart, and mindfulness is in charge.’*";
P_HTM[6173]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.”*";
P_HTM[6174]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6175]="*3. Sikkhānisaṃsasuttaṃ**Lying Postures*";
P_HTM[6176]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, seyyā.**“Mendicants, there are these four ways of lying down.*";
P_HTM[6177]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6178]="*Petaseyyā, kāmabhogiseyyā, sīhaseyyā, tathāgataseyyā.**The ways a corpse, a pleasure seeker, a lion, and a Realized One lie down.*";
P_HTM[6179]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, petaseyyā?**And how does a corpse lie down?*";
P_HTM[6180]="*Yebhuyyena, bhikkhave, petā uttānā senti;**Corpses usually lie flat on their backs.*";
P_HTM[6181]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, petaseyyā.**This is called the way a corpse lies down.*";
P_HTM[6182]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, kāmabhogiseyyā?**And how does a pleasure seeker lie down?*";
P_HTM[6183]="*Yebhuyyena, bhikkhave, kāmabhogī vāmena passena senti;**Pleasure seekers usually lie down on their left side.*";
P_HTM[6184]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kāmabhogiseyyā.**This is called the way a pleasure seeker lies down.*";
P_HTM[6185]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sīhaseyyā?**And how does a lion lie down?*";
P_HTM[6186]="*Sīho, bhikkhave, migarājā dakkhiṇena passena seyyaṃ kappeti, pāde pādaṃ accādhāya, antarasatthimhi naṅguṭṭhaṃ anupakkhipitvā.**The lion, king of beasts, lies down on the right side, placing one foot on top of the other, with his tail tucked between his thighs.*";
P_HTM[6187]="*So paṭibujjhitvā purimaṃ kāyaṃ abbhunnāmetvā pacchimaṃ kāyaṃ anuviloketi.**When he wakes, he lifts his front quarters and checks his hind quarters.*";
P_HTM[6188]="*Sace, bhikkhave, sīho migarājā kiñci passati kāyassa vikkhittaṃ vā visaṭaṃ vā, tena, bhikkhave, sīho migarājā anattamano hoti.**If he sees that any part of his body is disordered or displaced, he is displeased.*";
P_HTM[6189]="*Sace pana, bhikkhave, sīho migarājā na kiñci passati kāyassa vikkhittaṃ vā visaṭaṃ vā, tena, bhikkhave, sīho migarājā attamano hoti.**But if he sees that no part of his body is disordered or displaced, he is pleased.*";
P_HTM[6190]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sīhaseyyā.**This is called the way a lion lies down.*";
P_HTM[6191]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, tathāgataseyyā?**And how does a Realized One lie down?*";
P_HTM[6192]="*Idha, bhikkhave, tathāgato vivicceva kāmehi … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a Realized One, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[6193]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, tathāgataseyyā.**This is called the way a Realized One lies down.*";
P_HTM[6194]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso seyyā”ti.**These are the four ways of lying down.”*";
P_HTM[6195]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6196]="*4. Seyyāsuttaṃ**Worthy of a Monument*";
P_HTM[6197]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, thūpārahā.**“Mendicants, these four are worthy of a monument.*";
P_HTM[6198]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6199]="*Tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho thūpāraho, paccekabuddho thūpāraho, tathāgatasāvako thūpāraho, rājā cakkavattī thūpāraho—**A Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha; a Buddha awakened for themselves; a disciple of a Realized One; and a wheel-turning monarch.*";
P_HTM[6200]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro thūpārahā”ti.**These four are worthy of a monument.”*";
P_HTM[6201]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6202]="*5. Thūpārahasuttaṃ**The Growth of Wisdom*";
P_HTM[6203]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, dhammā paññāvuddhiyā saṃvattanti.**“Mendicants, these four things lead to the growth of wisdom.*";
P_HTM[6204]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6205]="*Sappurisasaṃsevo, saddhammasavanaṃ, yonisomanasikāro, dhammānudhammappaṭipatti—**Associating with good people, listening to the true teaching, proper attention, and practicing in line with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[6206]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro dhammā paññāvuddhiyā saṃvattantī”ti.**These four things lead to the growth of wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[6207]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6208]="*6. Paññāvuddhisuttaṃ**Very Helpful*";
P_HTM[6209]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, dhammā manussabhūtassa bahukārā honti.**“Mendicants, these four things are very helpful to a human being.*";
P_HTM[6210]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6211]="*Sappurisasaṃsevo, saddhammasavanaṃ, yonisomanasikāro, dhammānudhammappaṭipatti—**Associating with good people, listening to the true teaching, proper attention, and practicing in line with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[6212]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro dhammā manussabhūtassa bahukārā hontī”ti.**These four things are very helpful to a human being.”*";
P_HTM[6213]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6214]="*7. Bahukārasuttaṃ**Expressions (1st)*";
P_HTM[6215]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, anariyavohārā.**“Mendicants, there are these four ignoble expressions.*";
P_HTM[6216]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6217]="*Adiṭṭhe diṭṭhavāditā, asute sutavāditā, amute mutavāditā, aviññāte viññātavāditā—**Saying you’ve seen, heard, thought, or known something, but you haven’t.*";
P_HTM[6218]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro anariyavohārā”ti.**These are the four ignoble expressions.”*";
P_HTM[6219]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6220]="*8. Paṭhamavohārasuttaṃ**Expressions (2nd)*";
P_HTM[6221]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, ariyavohārā.**“Mendicants, there are these four noble expressions.*";
P_HTM[6222]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6223]="*Adiṭṭhe adiṭṭhavāditā, asute asutavāditā, amute amutavāditā, aviññāte aviññātavāditā—**Saying you haven’t seen, heard, thought, or known something, and you haven’t.*";
P_HTM[6224]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro ariyavohārā”ti.**These are the four noble expressions.”*";
P_HTM[6225]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6226]="*9. Dutiyavohārasuttaṃ**Expressions (3rd)*";
P_HTM[6227]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, anariyavohārā.**“Mendicants, there are these four ignoble expressions.*";
P_HTM[6228]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6229]="*Diṭṭhe adiṭṭhavāditā, sute asutavāditā, mute amutavāditā, viññāte aviññātavāditā—**Saying you haven’t seen, heard, thought, or known something, and you have.*";
P_HTM[6230]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro anariyavohārā”ti.**These are the four ignoble expressions.”*";
P_HTM[6231]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6232]="*10. Tatiyavohārasuttaṃ**Expressions (4th)*";
P_HTM[6233]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, ariyavohārā.**“Mendicants, there are these four noble expressions.*";
P_HTM[6234]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6235]="*Diṭṭhe diṭṭhavāditā, sute sutavāditā, mute mutavāditā, viññāte viññātavāditā—**Saying you’ve seen, heard, thought, or known something, and you have.*";
P_HTM[6236]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro ariyavohārā”ti.**These are the four noble expressions.”*";
P_HTM[6237]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6238]="*Āpattibhayavaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[6239]="*Bhedaāpatti sikkhā ca,* **";
P_HTM[6240]="*seyyā thūpārahena ca;* **";
P_HTM[6241]="*Paññāvuddhi bahukārā,* **";
P_HTM[6242]="*vohārā caturo ṭhitāti.* **";
P_HTM[6243]="*Pañcamo paṇṇāsako samatto.* **";
P_HTM[6244]="*11. Catutthavohārasuttaṃ**Insight*";
P_HTM[6245]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, dhammā.**Mendicants, there are these four things.*";
P_HTM[6246]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6247]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā pariññeyyā;**There are things that should be completely understood by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[6248]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā pahātabbā;**There are things that should be given up by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[6249]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā bhāvetabbā;**There are things that should be developed by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[6250]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā sacchikātabbā.**There are things that should be realized by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[6251]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā pariññeyyā?**And what are the things that should be completely understood by direct knowledge?*";
P_HTM[6252]="*Pañcupādānakkhandhā—**The five grasping aggregates.*";
P_HTM[6253]="*ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā pariññeyyā.**These are called the things that should be completely understood by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[6254]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā pahātabbā?**And what are the things that should be given up by direct knowledge?*";
P_HTM[6255]="*Avijjā ca bhavataṇhā ca—**Ignorance and craving for continued existence.*";
P_HTM[6256]="*ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā pahātabbā.**These are called the things that should be given up by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[6257]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā bhāvetabbā?**And what are the things that should be developed by direct knowledge?*";
P_HTM[6258]="*Samatho ca vipassanā ca—**Serenity and discernment.*";
P_HTM[6259]="*ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā bhāvetabbā.**These are called the things that should be developed by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[6260]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā sacchikātabbā?**And what are the things that should be realized by direct knowledge?*";
P_HTM[6261]="*Vijjā ca vimutti ca—**Knowledge and freedom.*";
P_HTM[6262]="*ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā sacchikātabbā.**These are called the things that should be realized by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[6263]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro dhammā”ti.**These are the four things.”*";
P_HTM[6264]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6265]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Insight*";
P_HTM[6266]="*1. Abhiññāsuttaṃ**Searches*";
P_HTM[6267]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, anariyapariyesanā.**“Mendicants, there are these four ignoble searches.*";
P_HTM[6268]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6269]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā jarādhammo samāno jarādhammaṃyeva pariyesati;**Someone liable to grow old searches only for what grows old.*";
P_HTM[6270]="*attanā byādhidhammo samāno byādhidhammaṃyeva pariyesati;**Someone liable to sickness searches only for what gets sick.*";
P_HTM[6271]="*attanā maraṇadhammo samāno maraṇadhammaṃyeva pariyesati;**Someone liable to death searches only for what dies.*";
P_HTM[6272]="*attanā saṅkilesadhammo samāno saṅkilesadhammaṃyeva pariyesati.**Someone whose nature is defiled searches only for what is defiled.*";
P_HTM[6273]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso anariyapariyesanā.**These are the four ignoble searches.*";
P_HTM[6274]="*Catasso imā, bhikkhave, ariyapariyesanā.**There are these four noble searches.*";
P_HTM[6275]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6276]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā jarādhammo samāno jarādhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā ajaraṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesati;**Someone who is liable to grow old, knowing the drawback in what grows old, searches for the unaging supreme sanctuary, extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[6277]="*attanā byādhidhammo samāno byādhidhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā abyādhiṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesati;**Someone who is liable to get sick, knowing the drawback in what gets sick, searches for the sickness-free supreme sanctuary, extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[6278]="*attanā maraṇadhammo samāno maraṇadhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā amataṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesati;**Someone who is liable to die, knowing the drawback in what dies, searches for the deathless supreme sanctuary, extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[6279]="*attanā saṅkilesadhammo samāno saṅkilesadhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā asaṅkiliṭṭhaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesati.**Someone whose nature is defiled, knowing the drawback in what is defiled, searches for the undefiled supreme sanctuary, extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[6280]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso ariyapariyesanā”ti.**These are the four noble searches.”*";
P_HTM[6281]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6282]="*2. Pariyesanāsuttaṃ**Ways of Being Inclusive*";
P_HTM[6283]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, saṅgahavatthūni.**“Mendicants, there are these four ways of being inclusive.*";
P_HTM[6284]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6285]="*Dānaṃ, peyyavajjaṃ, atthacariyā, samānattatā—**Giving, kindly words, taking care, and equality.*";
P_HTM[6286]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri saṅgahavatthūnī”ti.**These are the four ways of being inclusive.”*";
P_HTM[6287]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6288]="*3. Saṅgahavatthusuttaṃ**With Māluṅkyaputta*";
P_HTM[6289]="*Atha kho āyasmā mālukyaputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mālukyaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Māluṅkyaputta went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6290]="*“Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti.**“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.”*";
P_HTM[6291]="*“Ettha idāni, mālukyaputta, kiṃ dahare bhikkhū vakkhāma;**“Well now, Māluṅkyaputta, what are we to say to the young monks,*";
P_HTM[6292]="*yatra hi nāma tvaṃ jiṇṇo vuddho mahallako tathāgatassa saṃkhittena ovādaṃ yācasī”ti.**when even an old man like you, elderly and senior, asks the Realized One for brief advice?”*";
P_HTM[6293]="*“Desetu me, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena dhammaṃ; desetu sugato saṃkhittena dhammaṃ. Appeva nāmāhaṃ bhagavato bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājāneyyaṃ; appeva nāmāhaṃ bhagavato bhāsitassa dāyādo assan”ti.**“Sir, may the Buddha teach me the Dhamma in brief! May the Holy One teach me the Dhamma in brief! Hopefully I can understand the meaning of what the Buddha says! Hopefully I can be an heir of the Buddha’s teaching!”*";
P_HTM[6294]="*“Cattārome, mālukyaputta, taṇhuppādā yattha bhikkhuno taṇhā uppajjamānā uppajjati.**“Māluṅkyaputta, there are four things that give rise to craving in a mendicant.*";
P_HTM[6295]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6296]="*Cīvarahetu vā, mālukyaputta, bhikkhuno taṇhā uppajjamānā uppajjati.**For the sake of robes,*";
P_HTM[6297]="*Piṇḍapātahetu vā, mālukyaputta, bhikkhuno taṇhā uppajjamānā uppajjati.**alms-food,*";
P_HTM[6298]="*Senāsanahetu vā, mālukyaputta, bhikkhuno taṇhā uppajjamānā uppajjati.**lodgings,*";
P_HTM[6299]="*Itibhavābhavahetu vā, mālukyaputta, bhikkhuno taṇhā uppajjamānā uppajjati.**or rebirth in this or that state.*";
P_HTM[6300]="*Ime kho, mālukyaputta, cattāro taṇhuppādā yattha bhikkhuno taṇhā uppajjamānā uppajjati.**These are the four things that give rise to craving in a mendicant.*";
P_HTM[6301]="*Yato kho, mālukyaputta, bhikkhuno taṇhā pahīnā hoti ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā, ayaṃ vuccati, mālukyaputta, ‘bhikkhu acchecchi taṇhaṃ, vivattayi saṃyojanaṃ, sammā mānābhisamayā antamakāsi dukkhassā’”ti.**That craving is given up by a mendicant, cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future. Then they’re called a mendicant who has cut off craving, untied the fetters, and by rightly comprehending conceit has made an end of suffering.”*";
P_HTM[6302]="*Atha kho āyasmā mālukyaputto bhagavatā iminā ovādena ovadito uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**When Māluṅkyaputta had been given this advice by the Buddha, he got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[6303]="*Atha kho āyasmā mālukyaputto eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi.**Then Māluṅkyaputta, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[6304]="*“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi.**He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.”*";
P_HTM[6305]="*Aññataro ca panāyasmā mālukyaputto arahataṃ ahosīti.**And Venerable Māluṅkyaputta became one of the perfected.*";
P_HTM[6306]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6307]="*4. Mālukyaputtasuttaṃ**Families*";
P_HTM[6308]="*“Yāni kānici, bhikkhave, kulāni bhogesu mahattaṃ pattāni na ciraṭṭhitikāni bhavanti, sabbāni tāni catūhi ṭhānehi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena.**“Mendicants, when families don’t stay wealthy for long, it’s always for one or more of these four reasons.*";
P_HTM[6309]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6310]="*Naṭṭhaṃ na gavesanti, jiṇṇaṃ na paṭisaṅkharonti, aparimitapānabhojanā honti, dussīlaṃ itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā ādhipacce ṭhapenti.**They don’t look for what’s lost; they don’t fix old things; they eat and drink too much; or they put an unethical woman or man in charge.*";
P_HTM[6311]="*Yāni kānici, bhikkhave, kulāni bhogesu mahattaṃ pattāni na ciraṭṭhitikāni bhavanti, sabbāni tāni imehi catūhi ṭhānehi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena.**When families don’t stay wealthy for long, it’s always for one or more of these four reasons.*";
P_HTM[6312]="*Yāni kānici, bhikkhave, kulāni bhogesu mahattaṃ pattāni ciraṭṭhitikāni bhavanti, sabbāni tāni catūhi ṭhānehi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena.**When families do stay wealthy for long, it’s always for one or more of these four reasons.*";
P_HTM[6313]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6314]="*Naṭṭhaṃ gavesanti, jiṇṇaṃ paṭisaṅkharonti, parimitapānabhojanā honti, sīlavantaṃ itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā ādhipacce ṭhapenti.**They look for what’s lost; they fix old things; they eat and drink in moderation; and they put an ethical woman or man in charge.*";
P_HTM[6315]="*Yāni kānici, bhikkhave, kulāni bhogesu mahattaṃ pattāni ciraṭṭhitikāni bhavanti, sabbāni tāni imehi catūhi ṭhānehi, etesaṃ vā aññatarenā”ti.**When families do stay wealthy for long, it’s always for one or more of these four reasons.”*";
P_HTM[6316]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6317]="*5. Kulasuttaṃ**A Thoroughbred (1st)*";
P_HTM[6318]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**“Mendicants, a fine royal thoroughbred with four factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[6319]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6320]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño bhadro assājānīyo vaṇṇasampanno ca hoti balasampanno ca javasampanno ca ārohapariṇāhasampanno ca.**It’s when a fine royal thoroughbred is beautiful, strong, fast, and well-proportioned.*";
P_HTM[6321]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**A fine royal thoroughbred with these four factors is worthy of a king. …*";
P_HTM[6322]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**In the same way, a mendicant with four factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[6323]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6324]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno ca hoti balasampanno ca javasampanno ca ārohapariṇāhasampanno ca.**It’s when a mendicant is beautiful, strong, fast, and well proportioned.*";
P_HTM[6325]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno hoti?**And how is a mendicant beautiful?*";
P_HTM[6326]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu.**It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[6327]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is beautiful.*";
P_HTM[6328]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu balasampanno hoti?**And how is a mendicant strong?*";
P_HTM[6329]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu.**It’s when a mendicant lives with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities. They are strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[6330]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu balasampanno hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is strong.*";
P_HTM[6331]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu javasampanno hoti?**And how is a mendicant fast?*";
P_HTM[6332]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**It’s when they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[6333]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu javasampanno hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is fast.*";
P_HTM[6334]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ārohapariṇāhasampanno hoti?**And how is a mendicant well proportioned?*";
P_HTM[6335]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu lābhī hoti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ.**It’s when a mendicant receives robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[6336]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ārohapariṇāhasampanno hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is well proportioned.*";
P_HTM[6337]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti.**A mendicant with these four factors … is the supreme field of merit for the world.”*";
P_HTM[6338]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6339]="*6. Paṭhamaājānīyasuttaṃ**A Thoroughbred (2nd)*";
P_HTM[6340]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**“Mendicants, a fine royal thoroughbred with four factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[6341]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6342]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño bhadro assājānīyo vaṇṇasampanno ca hoti, balasampanno ca, javasampanno ca, ārohapariṇāhasampanno ca.**It’s when a fine royal thoroughbred is beautiful, strong, fast, and well-proportioned.*";
P_HTM[6343]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**A fine royal thoroughbred with these four factors is worthy of a king. …*";
P_HTM[6344]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**In the same way, a mendicant with four factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[6345]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6346]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno ca hoti, balasampanno ca, javasampanno ca, ārohapariṇāhasampanno ca.**It’s when a mendicant is beautiful, strong, fast, and well proportioned.*";
P_HTM[6347]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno hoti?**And how is a mendicant beautiful?*";
P_HTM[6348]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu.**It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[6349]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is beautiful.*";
P_HTM[6350]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu balasampanno hoti?**And how is a mendicant strong?*";
P_HTM[6351]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu.**It’s when a mendicant lives with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities. They are strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[6352]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu balasampanno hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is strong.*";
P_HTM[6353]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu javasampanno hoti?**And how is a mendicant fast?*";
P_HTM[6354]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[6355]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu javasampanno hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is fast.*";
P_HTM[6356]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ārohapariṇāhasampanno hoti?**And how is a mendicant well proportioned?*";
P_HTM[6357]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu lābhī hoti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ.**It’s when a mendicant receives robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[6358]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ārohapariṇāhasampanno hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is well proportioned.*";
P_HTM[6359]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti.**A mendicant with these four factors … is the supreme field of merit for the world.”*";
P_HTM[6360]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6361]="*7. Dutiyaājānīyasuttaṃ**Powers*";
P_HTM[6362]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, balāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four powers.*";
P_HTM[6363]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6364]="*Vīriyabalaṃ, satibalaṃ, samādhibalaṃ, paññābalaṃ—**The powers of energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[6365]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri balānī”ti.**These are the four powers.”*";
P_HTM[6366]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6367]="*8. Balasuttaṃ**Wilderness*";
P_HTM[6368]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevituṃ.**“Mendicants, when a mendicant has four qualities they’re not ready to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[6369]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6370]="*Kāmavitakkena, byāpādavitakkena, vihiṃsāvitakkena, duppañño hoti jaḷo elamūgo—**They have sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts; or they’re witless, dull, and stupid.*";
P_HTM[6371]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevituṃ.**When a mendicant has these four qualities they’re not ready to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[6372]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevituṃ.**When a mendicant has four qualities they’re ready to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[6373]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6374]="*Nekkhammavitakkena, abyāpādavitakkena, avihiṃsāvitakkena, paññavā hoti ajaḷo anelamūgo—**They have thoughts of renunciation, good will, and harmlessness; and they’re wise, bright, and clever.*";
P_HTM[6375]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevitun”ti.**When a mendicant has these four qualities they’re ready to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.”*";
P_HTM[6376]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6377]="*9. Araññasuttaṃ**Deeds*";
P_HTM[6378]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**“When a foolish, incompetent bad person has four qualities they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[6379]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6380]="*Sāvajjena kāyakammena, sāvajjena vacīkammena, sāvajjena manokammena, sāvajjāya diṭṭhiyā—**Blameworthy deeds by way of body, speech, and mind, and blameworthy view.*";
P_HTM[6381]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**When a foolish, incompetent bad person has these four qualities they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[6382]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavati.**When an astute, competent good person has four qualities they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.*";
P_HTM[6383]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6384]="*Anavajjena kāyakammena, anavajjena vacīkammena, anavajjena manokammena, anavajjāya diṭṭhiyā—**Blameless deeds by way of body, speech, and mind, and blameless view.*";
P_HTM[6385]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavatī”ti.**When an astute, competent good person has these four qualities they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.”*";
P_HTM[6386]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6387]="*Abhiññāvaggo chaṭṭho.* **";
P_HTM[6388]="*Abhiññā pariyesanā,* **";
P_HTM[6389]="*saṅgahaṃ mālukyaputto;* **";
P_HTM[6390]="*Kulaṃ dve ca ājānīyā,* **";
P_HTM[6391]="*balaṃ araññakammunāti.* **";
P_HTM[6392]="*10. Kammasuttaṃ**Killing Living Creatures*";
P_HTM[6393]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6394]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6395]="*Attanā ca pāṇātipātī hoti, parañca pāṇātipāte samādapeti, pāṇātipāte ca samanuñño hoti, pāṇātipātassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**They themselves kill living creatures; they encourage others to kill living creatures; they approve of killing living creatures; and they praise killing living creatures.*";
P_HTM[6396]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6397]="*Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[6398]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6399]="*Attanā ca pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, parañca pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**They don’t themselves kill living creatures; they encourage others to not kill living creatures; they approve of not killing living creatures; and they praise not killing living creatures.*";
P_HTM[6400]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these four qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[6401]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6402]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Ways of Performing Deeds*";
P_HTM[6403]="*1. Pāṇātipātīsuttaṃ**Stealing*";
P_HTM[6404]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with four qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6405]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6406]="*Attanā ca adinnādāyī hoti, parañca adinnādāne samādapeti, adinnādāne ca samanuñño hoti, adinnādānassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**They themselves steal …*";
P_HTM[6407]="*imehi kho … pe ….**Someone with four qualities is raised up to heaven. …*";
P_HTM[6408]="*Attanā ca adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, parañca adinnādānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, adinnādānā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, adinnādānā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi kho, bhikkhave … pe ….**They don’t themselves steal …*";
P_HTM[6409]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6410]="*2. Adinnādāyīsuttaṃ**Misconduct*";
P_HTM[6411]="*… pe … Attanā ca kāmesumicchācārī hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācāre samādapeti, kāmesumicchācāre ca samanuñño hoti, kāmesumicchācārassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi kho … pe ….**… They themselves commit sexual misconduct …*";
P_HTM[6412]="*Attanā ca kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi kho … pe ….**They themselves don’t commit sexual misconduct …*";
P_HTM[6413]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6414]="*3. Micchācārīsuttaṃ**Lying*";
P_HTM[6415]="*… pe … Attanā ca musāvādī hoti, parañca musāvāde samādapeti, musāvāde ca samanuñño hoti, musāvādassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi kho … pe ….**… They themselves lie …*";
P_HTM[6416]="*Attanā ca musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, parañca musāvādā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, musāvādā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, musāvādā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi … pe ….**… They themselves don’t lie …*";
P_HTM[6417]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6418]="*4. Musāvādīsuttaṃ**Divisive Speech*";
P_HTM[6419]="*… pe … Attanā ca pisuṇavāco hoti, parañca pisuṇāya vācāya samādapeti, pisuṇāya vācāya ca samanuñño hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi … pe ….**… They themselves speak divisively …*";
P_HTM[6420]="*Attanā ca pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, parañca pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi … pe ….**… They themselves don’t speak divisively …*";
P_HTM[6421]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6422]="*5. Pisuṇavācāsuttaṃ**Harsh Speech*";
P_HTM[6423]="*… pe … Attanā ca pharusavāco hoti, parañca pharusāya vācāya samādapeti, pharusāya vācāya ca samanuñño hoti, pharusāya vācāya ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati … pe ….**… They themselves speak harshly …*";
P_HTM[6424]="*Attanā ca pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, parañca pharusāya vācāya veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi kho … pe ….**… They themselves don’t speak harshly …*";
P_HTM[6425]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6426]="*6. Pharusavācāsuttaṃ**Talking Nonsense*";
P_HTM[6427]="*… pe … Attanā ca samphappalāpī hoti, parañca samphappalāpe samādapeti, samphappalāpe ca samanuñño hoti, samphappalāpassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi … pe ….**… They themselves talk nonsense …*";
P_HTM[6428]="*Attanā ca samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, parañca samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi kho, bhikkhave … pe ….**… They themselves don’t talk nonsense …*";
P_HTM[6429]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6430]="*7. Samphappalāpasuttaṃ**Covetousness*";
P_HTM[6431]="*… pe … Attanā ca abhijjhālu hoti, parañca abhijjhāya samādapeti, abhijjhāya ca samanuñño hoti, abhijjhāya ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati … pe ….**… They themselves are covetous …*";
P_HTM[6432]="*Attanā ca anabhijjhālu hoti, parañca anabhijjhāya samādapeti, anabhijjhāya ca samanuñño hoti, anabhijjhāya ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi kho … pe ….**… They themselves are content …*";
P_HTM[6433]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6434]="*8. Abhijjhālusuttaṃ**Ill Will*";
P_HTM[6435]="*… pe … Attanā ca byāpannacitto hoti, parañca byāpāde samādapeti, byāpāde ca samanuñño hoti, byāpādassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi … pe ….**… They themselves have ill will …*";
P_HTM[6436]="*Attanā ca abyāpannacitto hoti, parañca abyāpāde samādapeti, abyāpāde ca samanuñño hoti, abyāpādassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi … pe ….**… They themselves have good will …*";
P_HTM[6437]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6438]="*9. Byāpannacittasuttaṃ**Wrong View*";
P_HTM[6439]="*… pe … Attanā ca micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca micchādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti, micchādiṭṭhiyā ca samanuñño hoti, micchādiṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—imehi … pe ….**… They themselves have wrong view …*";
P_HTM[6440]="*Attanā ca sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca sammādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti, sammādiṭṭhiyā ca samanuñño hoti, sammādiṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**They themselves have right view; they encourage others to have right view; they approve of right view; and they praise right view.*";
P_HTM[6441]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ saggeti.**Someone with these four qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[6442]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6443]="*Kammapathavaggo sattamo.* **";
P_HTM[6444]="*10. Micchādiṭṭhisuttaṃ**Mindfulness Meditation*";
P_HTM[6445]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, four things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[6446]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6447]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**Firstly, a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6448]="*vedanāsu … pe … citte … pe … dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … mind … principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6449]="*Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**For insight into greed, these four things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[6450]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6451]="*3____31-510. Dosaabhiññādisuttāni**Abbreviated Texts Beginning with Greed*";
P_HTM[6452]="*1. Satipaṭṭhānasuttaṃ**Right Efforts*";
P_HTM[6453]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, four things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[6454]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6455]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ anuppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati;**Firstly, a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise.*";
P_HTM[6456]="*uppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya … pe … anuppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ uppādāya … pe … uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati.**…so that unskillful qualities that have arisen are given up … so that skillful qualities arise … so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are fulfilled by development.*";
P_HTM[6457]="*Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**For insight into greed, these four things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[6458]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6459]="*2. Sammappadhānasuttaṃ**Bases of Psychic Power*";
P_HTM[6460]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, four things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[6461]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6462]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti;**It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[6463]="*vīriyasamādhi … pe … cittasamādhi … pe … vīmaṃsāsamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti.**They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to energy … mental development … inquiry, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[6464]="*Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**For insight into greed, these four things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[6465]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6466]="*3. Iddhipādasuttaṃ**277–303. Pariññādisutta*";
P_HTM[6467]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, pariññāya … pe … parikkhayāya … pahānāya … khayāya … vayāya … virāgāya … nirodhāya … cāgāya … paṭinissaggāya cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā … pe ….**“For the complete understanding … finishing … giving up … ending … vanishing … fading away … cessation … giving away … letting go of greed, four things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[6468]="*Tiṃsatimaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6469]="*4-30. Pariññādisuttāni**304–783. Dosaabhiññādisutta*";
P_HTM[6470]="*“Dosassa … pe … mohassa … kodhassa … upanāhassa … makkhassa … paḷāsassa … issāya … macchariyassa … māyāya … sāṭheyyassa … thambhassa … sārambhassa … mānassa … atimānassa … madassa … pamādassa abhiññāya … pariññāya … parikkhayāya … pahānāya … khayāya … vayāya … virāgāya … nirodhāya … cāgāya … paṭinissaggāya ime cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**“Of hate … delusion … anger … hostility … offensiveness … contempt … jealousy … stinginess … deceit … deviousness … obstinacy … aggression … conceit … arrogance … vanity … negligence … for insight … complete understanding … finishing … giving up … ending … vanishing … fading away … cessation … giving away … letting go … four things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[6471]="*Dasuttarapañcasatimaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6472]="*Rāgapeyyālaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6473]="*Pañcamo paṇṇāsako samatto.* **";
P_HTM[6474]="*Catukkanipātapāḷi niṭṭhitā.**The Book of the Fours is finished.*";
